168HSimulate* HBasicBlock::CreateSimulate(BailoutId ast_id,
169 RemovableSimulate removable) {
170 DCHECK(HasEnvironment())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(HasEnvironment())), 0))) { V8_Fatal

); } } while (0);
171 HEnvironment* environment = last_environment();
172 DCHECK(ast_id.IsNone() ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ast_id.IsNone() || ast_id == BailoutId
::StubEntry() || environment->closure()->shared()->VerifyBailoutId
(ast_id))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 174
, "Check failed: %s.", "ast_id.IsNone() || ast_id == BailoutId::StubEntry() || environment->closure()->shared()->VerifyBailoutId(ast_id)"
); } } while (0)
173 ast_id == BailoutId::StubEntry() ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ast_id.IsNone() || ast_id == BailoutId
::StubEntry() || environment->closure()->shared()->VerifyBailoutId
(ast_id))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 174
, "Check failed: %s.", "ast_id.IsNone() || ast_id == BailoutId::StubEntry() || environment->closure()->shared()->VerifyBailoutId(ast_id)"
); } } while (0)
174 environment->closure()->shared()->VerifyBailoutId(ast_id))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ast_id.IsNone() || ast_id == BailoutId
::StubEntry() || environment->closure()->shared()->VerifyBailoutId
(ast_id))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 174
, "Check failed: %s.", "ast_id.IsNone() || ast_id == BailoutId::StubEntry() || environment->closure()->shared()->VerifyBailoutId(ast_id)"
); } } while (0);
175
176 int push_count = environment->push_count();
177 int pop_count = environment->pop_count();
178
179 HSimulate* instr =
180 new(zone()) HSimulate(ast_id, pop_count, zone(), removable);
181#ifdef DEBUG1
182 instr->set_closure(environment->closure());
183#endif
184 // Order of pushed values: newest (top of stack) first. This allows
185 // HSimulate::MergeWith() to easily append additional pushed values
186 // that are older (from further down the stack).
187 for (int i = 0; i < push_count; ++i) {
188 instr->AddPushedValue(environment->ExpressionStackAt(i));
189 }
190 for (GrowableBitVector::Iterator it(environment->assigned_variables(),
191 zone());
192 !it.Done();
193 it.Advance()) {
194 int index = it.Current();
195 instr->AddAssignedValue(index, environment->Lookup(index));
196 }
197 environment->ClearHistory();
198 return instr;
199}

202void HBasicBlock::Finish(HControlInstruction* end, SourcePosition position) {
203 DCHECK(!IsFinished())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!IsFinished())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 203, "Check failed: %s.", "!IsFinished()"
); } } while (0);
204 AddInstruction(end, position);
205 end_ = end;
206 for (HSuccessorIterator it(end); !it.Done(); it.Advance()) {
207 it.Current()->RegisterPredecessor(this);
208 }

212void HBasicBlock::Goto(HBasicBlock* block, SourcePosition position,
213 FunctionState* state, bool add_simulate) {
214 bool drop_extra = state != NULL__null &&
215 state->inlining_kind() == NORMAL_RETURN;
216
217 if (block->IsInlineReturnTarget()) {
218 HEnvironment* env = last_environment();
219 int argument_count = env->arguments_environment()->parameter_count();
220 AddInstruction(new(zone())
221 HLeaveInlined(state->entry(), argument_count),
222 position);
223 UpdateEnvironment(last_environment()->DiscardInlined(drop_extra));
224 }
225
226 if (add_simulate) AddNewSimulate(BailoutId::None(), position);
227 HGoto* instr = new(zone()) HGoto(block);
228 Finish(instr, position);
229}

232void HBasicBlock::AddLeaveInlined(HValue* return_value, FunctionState* state,
233 SourcePosition position) {
234 HBasicBlock* target = state->function_return();
235 bool drop_extra = state->inlining_kind() == NORMAL_RETURN;
236
237 DCHECK(target->IsInlineReturnTarget())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(target->IsInlineReturnTarget
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 237, "Check failed: %s."
, "target->IsInlineReturnTarget()"); } } while (0);
238 DCHECK(return_value != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(return_value != __null)), 0))
) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 238, "Check failed: %s."
, "return_value != __null"); } } while (0);
239 HEnvironment* env = last_environment();
240 int argument_count = env->arguments_environment()->parameter_count();
241 AddInstruction(new(zone()) HLeaveInlined(state->entry(), argument_count),
242 position);
243 UpdateEnvironment(last_environment()->DiscardInlined(drop_extra));
244 last_environment()->Push(return_value);
245 AddNewSimulate(BailoutId::None(), position);
246 HGoto* instr = new(zone()) HGoto(target);
247 Finish(instr, position);
248}

281bool HBasicBlock::Dominates(HBasicBlock* other) const {
282 HBasicBlock* current = other->dominator();
283 while (current != NULL__null) {
284 if (current == this) return true;
285 current = current->dominator();
286 }
287 return false;
288}
289
290
291bool HBasicBlock::EqualToOrDominates(HBasicBlock* other) const {
292 if (this == other) return true;
293 return Dominates(other);
294}

296
297int HBasicBlock::LoopNestingDepth() const {
298 const HBasicBlock* current = this;
299 int result = (current->IsLoopHeader()) ? 1 : 0;
300 while (current->parent_loop_header() != NULL__null) {
301 current = current->parent_loop_header();
302 result++;
303 }
304 return result;
305}

308void HBasicBlock::PostProcessLoopHeader(IterationStatement* stmt) {
309 DCHECK(IsLoopHeader())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsLoopHeader())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 309, "Check failed: %s.", "IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0);
310
311 SetJoinId(stmt->EntryId());
312 if (predecessors()->length() == 1) {
313 // This is a degenerated loop.
314 DetachLoopInformation();
315 return;
316 }
317
318 // Only the first entry into the loop is from outside the loop. All other
319 // entries must be back edges.
320 for (int i = 1; i < predecessors()->length(); ++i) {
321 loop_information()->RegisterBackEdge(predecessors()->at(i));
322 }
323}

327 DCHECK(IsFinished())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsFinished())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 327, "Check failed: %s.", "IsFinished()"
); } } while (0);
328 HBasicBlock* succ_block = end()->SuccessorAt(succ);
329
330 DCHECK(succ_block->predecessors()->length() == 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(succ_block->predecessors()
->length() == 1)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 330, "Check failed: %s.", "succ_block->predecessors()->length() == 1"
); } } while (0);
331 succ_block->MarkUnreachable();
332}

335void HBasicBlock::RegisterPredecessor(HBasicBlock* pred) {
336 if (HasPredecessor()) {
337 // Only loop header blocks can have a predecessor added after
338 // instructions have been added to the block (they have phis for all
339 // values in the environment, these phis may be eliminated later).
340 DCHECK(IsLoopHeader() || first_ == NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsLoopHeader() || first_ == __null
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 340, "Check failed: %s."
, "IsLoopHeader() || first_ == __null"); } } while (0);
341 HEnvironment* incoming_env = pred->last_environment();
342 if (IsLoopHeader()) {
343 DCHECK_EQ(phis()->length(), incoming_env->length())do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (phis()
->length()), (incoming_env->length()), "phis()->length()"
" " "==" " " "incoming_env->length()")) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 343, "Check failed: %s.", _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; }
} while (0);
344 for (int i = 0; i < phis_.length(); ++i) {
345 phis_[i]->AddInput(incoming_env->values()->at(i));
346 }
347 } else {
348 last_environment()->AddIncomingEdge(this, pred->last_environment());
349 }
350 } else if (!HasEnvironment() && !IsFinished()) {
351 DCHECK(!IsLoopHeader())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!IsLoopHeader())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 351, "Check failed: %s.", "!IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0);
352 SetInitialEnvironment(pred->last_environment()->Copy());
353 }
354
355 predecessors_.Add(pred, zone());
356}

359void HBasicBlock::AddDominatedBlock(HBasicBlock* block) {
360 DCHECK(!dominated_blocks_.Contains(block))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!dominated_blocks_.Contains(block
))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 360, "Check failed: %s."
, "!dominated_blocks_.Contains(block)"); } } while (0);
361 // Keep the list of dominated blocks sorted such that if there is two
362 // succeeding block in this list, the predecessor is before the successor.
363 int index = 0;
364 while (index < dominated_blocks_.length() &&
365 dominated_blocks_[index]->block_id() < block->block_id()) {
366 ++index;
367 }
368 dominated_blocks_.InsertAt(index, block, zone());
369}

372void HBasicBlock::AssignCommonDominator(HBasicBlock* other) {
373 if (dominator_ == NULL__null) {
374 dominator_ = other;
375 other->AddDominatedBlock(this);
376 } else if (other->dominator() != NULL__null) {
377 HBasicBlock* first = dominator_;
378 HBasicBlock* second = other;
379
380 while (first != second) {
381 if (first->block_id() > second->block_id()) {
382 first = first->dominator();
383 } else {
384 second = second->dominator();
385 }
386 DCHECK(first != NULL && second != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(first != __null && second
!= __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 386, "Check failed: %s.", "first != __null && second != __null"
); } } while (0);
387 }
388
389 if (dominator_ != first) {
390 DCHECK(dominator_->dominated_blocks_.Contains(this))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(dominator_->dominated_blocks_
.Contains(this))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 390, "Check failed: %s.", "dominator_->dominated_blocks_.Contains(this)"
); } } while (0);
391 dominator_->dominated_blocks_.RemoveElement(this);
392 dominator_ = first;
393 first->AddDominatedBlock(this);
394 }
395 }
396}

398
399void HBasicBlock::AssignLoopSuccessorDominators() {
400 // Mark blocks that dominate all subsequent reachable blocks inside their
401 // loop. Exploit the fact that blocks are sorted in reverse post order. When
402 // the loop is visited in increasing block id order, if the number of
403 // non-loop-exiting successor edges at the dominator_candidate block doesn't
404 // exceed the number of previously encountered predecessor edges, there is no
405 // path from the loop header to any block with higher id that doesn't go
406 // through the dominator_candidate block. In this case, the
407 // dominator_candidate block is guaranteed to dominate all blocks reachable
408 // from it with higher ids.
409 HBasicBlock* last = loop_information()->GetLastBackEdge();
410 int outstanding_successors = 1; // one edge from the pre-header
411 // Header always dominates everything.
412 MarkAsLoopSuccessorDominator();
413 for (int j = block_id(); j <= last->block_id(); ++j) {
414 HBasicBlock* dominator_candidate = graph_->blocks()->at(j);
415 for (HPredecessorIterator it(dominator_candidate); !it.Done();
416 it.Advance()) {
417 HBasicBlock* predecessor = it.Current();
418 // Don't count back edges.
419 if (predecessor->block_id() < dominator_candidate->block_id()) {
420 outstanding_successors--;
421 }
422 }
423
424 // If more successors than predecessors have been seen in the loop up to
425 // now, it's not possible to guarantee that the current block dominates
426 // all of the blocks with higher IDs. In this case, assume conservatively
427 // that those paths through loop that don't go through the current block
428 // contain all of the loop's dependencies. Also be careful to record
429 // dominator information about the current loop that's being processed,
430 // and not nested loops, which will be processed when
431 // AssignLoopSuccessorDominators gets called on their header.
432 DCHECK(outstanding_successors >= 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(outstanding_successors >= 0
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 432, "Check failed: %s."
, "outstanding_successors >= 0"); } } while (0);
433 HBasicBlock* parent_loop_header = dominator_candidate->parent_loop_header();
434 if (outstanding_successors == 0 &&
435 (parent_loop_header == this && !dominator_candidate->IsLoopHeader())) {
436 dominator_candidate->MarkAsLoopSuccessorDominator();
437 }
438 HControlInstruction* end = dominator_candidate->end();
439 for (HSuccessorIterator it(end); !it.Done(); it.Advance()) {
440 HBasicBlock* successor = it.Current();
441 // Only count successors that remain inside the loop and don't loop back
442 // to a loop header.
443 if (successor->block_id() > dominator_candidate->block_id() &&
444 successor->block_id() <= last->block_id()) {
445 // Backwards edges must land on loop headers.
446 DCHECK(successor->block_id() > dominator_candidate->block_id() ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(successor->block_id() >
dominator_candidate->block_id() || successor->IsLoopHeader
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 447, "Check failed: %s."
, "successor->block_id() > dominator_candidate->block_id() || successor->IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0)
447 successor->IsLoopHeader())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(successor->block_id() >
dominator_candidate->block_id() || successor->IsLoopHeader
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 447, "Check failed: %s."
, "successor->block_id() > dominator_candidate->block_id() || successor->IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0);
448 outstanding_successors++;
449 }
450 }
451 }
452}
453
454
455int HBasicBlock::PredecessorIndexOf(HBasicBlock* predecessor) const {
456 for (int i = 0; i < predecessors_.length(); ++i) {
457 if (predecessors_[i] == predecessor) return i;
458 }
459 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 459, "unreachable code"
);
460 return -1;
461}
462
463
464#ifdef DEBUG1
465void HBasicBlock::Verify() {
466 // Check that every block is finished.
467 DCHECK(IsFinished())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsFinished())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 467, "Check failed: %s.", "IsFinished()"
); } } while (0);
468 DCHECK(block_id() >= 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block_id() >= 0)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 468, "Check failed: %s.", "block_id() >= 0"
); } } while (0);
469
470 // Check that the incoming edges are in edge split form.
471 if (predecessors_.length() > 1) {
472 for (int i = 0; i < predecessors_.length(); ++i) {
473 DCHECK(predecessors_[i]->end()->SecondSuccessor() == NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(predecessors_[i]->end()->
SecondSuccessor() == __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 473, "Check failed: %s.", "predecessors_[i]->end()->SecondSuccessor() == __null"
); } } while (0);
474 }
475 }
476}
477#endif

479
480void HLoopInformation::RegisterBackEdge(HBasicBlock* block) {
481 this->back_edges_.Add(block, block->zone());
482 AddBlock(block);
483}
484
485
486HBasicBlock* HLoopInformation::GetLastBackEdge() const {
487 int max_id = -1;
488 HBasicBlock* result = NULL__null;
489 for (int i = 0; i < back_edges_.length(); ++i) {
490 HBasicBlock* cur = back_edges_[i];
491 if (cur->block_id() > max_id) {
492 max_id = cur->block_id();
493 result = cur;
494 }
495 }
496 return result;
497}
498
499
500void HLoopInformation::AddBlock(HBasicBlock* block) {
501 if (block == loop_header()) return;
502 if (block->parent_loop_header() == loop_header()) return;
503 if (block->parent_loop_header() != NULL__null) {
504 AddBlock(block->parent_loop_header());
505 } else {
506 block->set_parent_loop_header(loop_header());
507 blocks_.Add(block, block->zone());
508 for (int i = 0; i < block->predecessors()->length(); ++i) {
509 AddBlock(block->predecessors()->at(i));
510 }
511 }
512}
513
514
515#ifdef DEBUG1
516
517// Checks reachability of the blocks in this graph and stores a bit in
518// the BitVector "reachable()" for every block that can be reached
519// from the start block of the graph. If "dont_visit" is non-null, the given
520// block is treated as if it would not be part of the graph. "visited_count()"
521// returns the number of reachable blocks.
522class ReachabilityAnalyzer BASE_EMBEDDED: public Embedded {
523 public:
524 ReachabilityAnalyzer(HBasicBlock* entry_block,
525 int block_count,
526 HBasicBlock* dont_visit)
527 : visited_count_(0),
528 stack_(16, entry_block->zone()),
529 reachable_(block_count, entry_block->zone()),
530 dont_visit_(dont_visit) {
531 PushBlock(entry_block);
532 Analyze();
533 }
534
535 int visited_count() const { return visited_count_; }
536 const BitVector* reachable() const { return &reachable_; }
537
538 private:
539 void PushBlock(HBasicBlock* block) {
540 if (block != NULL__null && block != dont_visit_ &&
541 !reachable_.Contains(block->block_id())) {
542 reachable_.Add(block->block_id());
543 stack_.Add(block, block->zone());
544 visited_count_++;
545 }
546 }
547
548 void Analyze() {
549 while (!stack_.is_empty()) {
550 HControlInstruction* end = stack_.RemoveLast()->end();
551 for (HSuccessorIterator it(end); !it.Done(); it.Advance()) {
552 PushBlock(it.Current());
553 }
554 }
555 }
556
557 int visited_count_;
558 ZoneList<HBasicBlock*> stack_;
559 BitVector reachable_;
560 HBasicBlock* dont_visit_;
561};
562
563
564void HGraph::Verify(bool do_full_verify) const {
565 Heap::RelocationLock relocation_lock(isolate()->heap());
566 AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
567 AllowDeferredHandleDereference allow_deferred_deref;
568 for (int i = 0; i < blocks_.length(); i++) {
569 HBasicBlock* block = blocks_.at(i);
570
571 block->Verify();
572
573 // Check that every block contains at least one node and that only the last
574 // node is a control instruction.
575 HInstruction* current = block->first();
576 DCHECK(current != NULL && current->IsBlockEntry())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current != __null && current
->IsBlockEntry())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 576, "Check failed: %s.", "current != __null && current->IsBlockEntry()"
); } } while (0);
577 while (current != NULL__null) {
578 DCHECK((current->next() == NULL) == current->IsControlInstruction())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((current->next() == __null
) == current->IsControlInstruction())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 578, "Check failed: %s.", "(current->next() == __null) == current->IsControlInstruction()"
); } } while (0);
579 DCHECK(current->block() == block)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current->block() == block)
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 579, "Check failed: %s."
, "current->block() == block"); } } while (0);
580 current->Verify();
581 current = current->next();
582 }
583
584 // Check that successors are correctly set.
585 HBasicBlock* first = block->end()->FirstSuccessor();
586 HBasicBlock* second = block->end()->SecondSuccessor();
587 DCHECK(second == NULL || first != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(second == __null || first != __null
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 587, "Check failed: %s."
, "second == __null || first != __null"); } } while (0);
588
589 // Check that the predecessor array is correct.
590 if (first != NULL__null) {
591 DCHECK(first->predecessors()->Contains(block))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(first->predecessors()->
Contains(block))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 591, "Check failed: %s.", "first->predecessors()->Contains(block)"
); } } while (0);
592 if (second != NULL__null) {
593 DCHECK(second->predecessors()->Contains(block))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(second->predecessors()->
Contains(block))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 593, "Check failed: %s.", "second->predecessors()->Contains(block)"
); } } while (0);
594 }
595 }
596
597 // Check that phis have correct arguments.
598 for (int j = 0; j < block->phis()->length(); j++) {
599 HPhi* phi = block->phis()->at(j);
600 phi->Verify();
601 }
602
603 // Check that all join blocks have predecessors that end with an
604 // unconditional goto and agree on their environment node id.
605 if (block->predecessors()->length() >= 2) {
606 BailoutId id =
607 block->predecessors()->first()->last_environment()->ast_id();
608 for (int k = 0; k < block->predecessors()->length(); k++) {
609 HBasicBlock* predecessor = block->predecessors()->at(k);
610 DCHECK(predecessor->end()->IsGoto() ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(predecessor->end()->IsGoto
() || predecessor->end()->IsDeoptimize())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 611, "Check failed: %s.", "predecessor->end()->IsGoto() || predecessor->end()->IsDeoptimize()"
); } } while (0)
611 predecessor->end()->IsDeoptimize())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(predecessor->end()->IsGoto
() || predecessor->end()->IsDeoptimize())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 611, "Check failed: %s.", "predecessor->end()->IsGoto() || predecessor->end()->IsDeoptimize()"
); } } while (0);
612 DCHECK(predecessor->last_environment()->ast_id() == id)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(predecessor->last_environment
()->ast_id() == id)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 612, "Check failed: %s.", "predecessor->last_environment()->ast_id() == id"
); } } while (0);
613 }
614 }
615 }
616
617 // Check special property of first block to have no predecessors.
618 DCHECK(blocks_.at(0)->predecessors()->is_empty())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(blocks_.at(0)->predecessors
()->is_empty())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 618, "Check failed: %s.", "blocks_.at(0)->predecessors()->is_empty()"
); } } while (0);
619
620 if (do_full_verify) {
621 // Check that the graph is fully connected.
622 ReachabilityAnalyzer analyzer(entry_block_, blocks_.length(), NULL__null);
623 DCHECK(analyzer.visited_count() == blocks_.length())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(analyzer.visited_count() == blocks_
.length())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc",
623, "Check failed: %s.", "analyzer.visited_count() == blocks_.length()"
); } } while (0);
624
625 // Check that entry block dominator is NULL.
626 DCHECK(entry_block_->dominator() == NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(entry_block_->dominator() ==
__null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 626
, "Check failed: %s.", "entry_block_->dominator() == __null"
); } } while (0);
627
628 // Check dominators.
629 for (int i = 0; i < blocks_.length(); ++i) {
630 HBasicBlock* block = blocks_.at(i);
631 if (block->dominator() == NULL__null) {
632 // Only start block may have no dominator assigned to.
633 DCHECK(i == 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(i == 0)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 633, "Check failed: %s.", "i == 0"); } } while (0);
634 } else {
635 // Assert that block is unreachable if dominator must not be visited.
636 ReachabilityAnalyzer dominator_analyzer(entry_block_,
637 blocks_.length(),
638 block->dominator());
639 DCHECK(!dominator_analyzer.reachable()->Contains(block->block_id()))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!dominator_analyzer.reachable
()->Contains(block->block_id()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 639, "Check failed: %s.", "!dominator_analyzer.reachable()->Contains(block->block_id())"
); } } while (0);
640 }
641 }
642 }
643}

645#endif

648HConstant* HGraph::GetConstant(SetOncePointer<HConstant>* pointer,
649 int32_t value) {
650 if (!pointer->is_set()) {
651 // Can't pass GetInvalidContext() to HConstant::New, because that will
652 // recursively call GetConstant
653 HConstant* constant = HConstant::New(isolate(), zone(), NULL__null, value);
654 constant->InsertAfter(entry_block()->first());
655 pointer->set(constant);
656 return constant;
657 }
658 return ReinsertConstantIfNecessary(pointer->get());
659}
660
661
662HConstant* HGraph::ReinsertConstantIfNecessary(HConstant* constant) {
663 if (!constant->IsLinked()) {
664 // The constant was removed from the graph. Reinsert.
665 constant->ClearFlag(HValue::kIsDead);
666 constant->InsertAfter(entry_block()->first());
667 }
668 return constant;
669}

672HConstant* HGraph::GetConstant0() {

674}

677HConstant* HGraph::GetConstant1() {
678 return GetConstant(&constant_1_, 1);
679}

682HConstant* HGraph::GetConstantMinus1() {
683 return GetConstant(&constant_minus1_, -1);
684}

686
687HConstant* HGraph::GetConstantBool(bool value) {
688 return value ? GetConstantTrue() : GetConstantFalse();
689}
690
691#define DEFINE_GET_CONSTANT(Name, name, type, htype, boolean_value, \
692 undetectable) \
693 HConstant* HGraph::GetConstant##Name() { \
694 if (!constant_##name##_.is_set()) { \
695 HConstant* constant = new (zone()) HConstant( \
696 Unique<Object>::CreateImmovable( \
697 isolate()->factory()->name##_value()), \
698 Unique<Map>::CreateImmovable(isolate()->factory()->type##_map()), \
699 false, Representation::Tagged(), htype, true, boolean_value, \
700 undetectable, ODDBALL_TYPE); \
701 constant->InsertAfter(entry_block()->first()); \
702 constant_##name##_.set(constant); \
703 } \
704 return ReinsertConstantIfNecessary(constant_##name##_.get()); \
705 }
706
707DEFINE_GET_CONSTANT(Undefined, undefined, undefined, HType::Undefined(), false,
708 true)
709DEFINE_GET_CONSTANT(True, true, boolean, HType::Boolean(), true, false)
710DEFINE_GET_CONSTANT(False, false, boolean, HType::Boolean(), false, false)
711DEFINE_GET_CONSTANT(Hole, the_hole, the_hole, HType::None(), false, false)
712DEFINE_GET_CONSTANT(Null, null, null, HType::Null(), false, true)
713
714#undef DEFINE_GET_CONSTANT
715
716#define DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT(Name, name) \
717bool HGraph::IsConstant##Name(HConstant* constant) { \
718 return constant_##name##_.is_set() && constant == constant_##name##_.get(); \
719}
720DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT(Undefined, undefined)
721DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT(0, 0)
722DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT(1, 1)
723DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT(Minus1, minus1)
724DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT(True, true)
725DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT(False, false)
726DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT(Hole, the_hole)
727DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT(Null, null)
728
729#undef DEFINE_IS_CONSTANT

732HConstant* HGraph::GetInvalidContext() {
733 return GetConstant(&constant_invalid_context_, 0xFFFFC0C7);
734}

736
737bool HGraph::IsStandardConstant(HConstant* constant) {
738 if (IsConstantUndefined(constant)) return true;
739 if (IsConstant0(constant)) return true;
740 if (IsConstant1(constant)) return true;
741 if (IsConstantMinus1(constant)) return true;
742 if (IsConstantTrue(constant)) return true;
743 if (IsConstantFalse(constant)) return true;
744 if (IsConstantHole(constant)) return true;
745 if (IsConstantNull(constant)) return true;
746 return false;
747}

761 : needs_compare_(false), first_true_block_(NULL__null), first_false_block_(NULL__null) {

764}

766
767void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::InitializeDontCreateBlocks(
768 HGraphBuilder* builder) {
769 builder_ = builder;
770 finished_ = false;
771 did_then_ = false;
772 did_else_ = false;
773 did_else_if_ = false;
774 did_and_ = false;
775 did_or_ = false;
776 captured_ = false;
777 pending_merge_block_ = false;
778 split_edge_merge_block_ = NULL__null;
779 merge_at_join_blocks_ = NULL__null;
780 normal_merge_at_join_block_count_ = 0;
781 deopt_merge_at_join_block_count_ = 0;
782}

784
785void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::Initialize(HGraphBuilder* builder) {
786 InitializeDontCreateBlocks(builder);
787 HEnvironment* env = builder->environment();
788 first_true_block_ = builder->CreateBasicBlock(env->Copy());
789 first_false_block_ = builder->CreateBasicBlock(env->Copy());
790}
791
792
793HControlInstruction* HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::AddCompare(
794 HControlInstruction* compare) {
795 DCHECK(did_then_ == did_else_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(did_then_ == did_else_)), 0))
) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 795, "Check failed: %s."
, "did_then_ == did_else_"); } } while (0);
796 if (did_else_) {
797 // Handle if-then-elseif
798 did_else_if_ = true;
799 did_else_ = false;
800 did_then_ = false;
801 did_and_ = false;
802 did_or_ = false;
803 pending_merge_block_ = false;
804 split_edge_merge_block_ = NULL__null;
805 HEnvironment* env = builder()->environment();
806 first_true_block_ = builder()->CreateBasicBlock(env->Copy());
807 first_false_block_ = builder()->CreateBasicBlock(env->Copy());
808 }
809 if (split_edge_merge_block_ != NULL__null) {
810 HEnvironment* env = first_false_block_->last_environment();
811 HBasicBlock* split_edge = builder()->CreateBasicBlock(env->Copy());
812 if (did_or_) {
813 compare->SetSuccessorAt(0, split_edge);
814 compare->SetSuccessorAt(1, first_false_block_);
815 } else {
816 compare->SetSuccessorAt(0, first_true_block_);
817 compare->SetSuccessorAt(1, split_edge);
818 }
819 builder()->GotoNoSimulate(split_edge, split_edge_merge_block_);
820 } else {
821 compare->SetSuccessorAt(0, first_true_block_);
822 compare->SetSuccessorAt(1, first_false_block_);
823 }
824 builder()->FinishCurrentBlock(compare);
825 needs_compare_ = false;
826 return compare;
827}

829
830void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::Or() {
831 DCHECK(!needs_compare_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!needs_compare_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 831, "Check failed: %s.", "!needs_compare_"
); } } while (0);
832 DCHECK(!did_and_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!did_and_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal(
"../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 832, "Check failed: %s.", "!did_and_"
); } } while (0);
833 did_or_ = true;
834 HEnvironment* env = first_false_block_->last_environment();
835 if (split_edge_merge_block_ == NULL__null) {
836 split_edge_merge_block_ = builder()->CreateBasicBlock(env->Copy());
837 builder()->GotoNoSimulate(first_true_block_, split_edge_merge_block_);
838 first_true_block_ = split_edge_merge_block_;
839 }
840 builder()->set_current_block(first_false_block_);
841 first_false_block_ = builder()->CreateBasicBlock(env->Copy());
842}
843
844
845void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::And() {
846 DCHECK(!needs_compare_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!needs_compare_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 846, "Check failed: %s.", "!needs_compare_"
); } } while (0);
847 DCHECK(!did_or_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!did_or_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 847, "Check failed: %s.", "!did_or_"); } } while (0);
848 did_and_ = true;
849 HEnvironment* env = first_false_block_->last_environment();
850 if (split_edge_merge_block_ == NULL__null) {
851 split_edge_merge_block_ = builder()->CreateBasicBlock(env->Copy());
852 builder()->GotoNoSimulate(first_false_block_, split_edge_merge_block_);
853 first_false_block_ = split_edge_merge_block_;
854 }
855 builder()->set_current_block(first_true_block_);
856 first_true_block_ = builder()->CreateBasicBlock(env->Copy());
857}

860void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::CaptureContinuation(
861 HIfContinuation* continuation) {
862 DCHECK(!did_else_if_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!did_else_if_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 862, "Check failed: %s.", "!did_else_if_"
); } } while (0);
863 DCHECK(!finished_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!finished_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 863, "Check failed: %s.", "!finished_"
); } } while (0);
864 DCHECK(!captured_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!captured_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 864, "Check failed: %s.", "!captured_"
); } } while (0);
865
866 HBasicBlock* true_block = NULL__null;
867 HBasicBlock* false_block = NULL__null;
868 Finish(&true_block, &false_block);
869 DCHECK(true_block != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(true_block != __null)), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 869, "Check failed: %s."
, "true_block != __null"); } } while (0);
870 DCHECK(false_block != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(false_block != __null)), 0)))
{ V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 870, "Check failed: %s."
, "false_block != __null"); } } while (0);
871 continuation->Capture(true_block, false_block);
872 captured_ = true;
873 builder()->set_current_block(NULL__null);
874 End();
875}

877
878void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::JoinContinuation(HIfContinuation* continuation) {
879 DCHECK(!did_else_if_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!did_else_if_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 879, "Check failed: %s.", "!did_else_if_"
); } } while (0);
880 DCHECK(!finished_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!finished_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 880, "Check failed: %s.", "!finished_"
); } } while (0);
881 DCHECK(!captured_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!captured_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 881, "Check failed: %s.", "!captured_"
); } } while (0);
882 HBasicBlock* true_block = NULL__null;
883 HBasicBlock* false_block = NULL__null;
884 Finish(&true_block, &false_block);
885 merge_at_join_blocks_ = NULL__null;
886 if (true_block != NULL__null && !true_block->IsFinished()) {
887 DCHECK(continuation->IsTrueReachable())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(continuation->IsTrueReachable
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 887, "Check failed: %s."
, "continuation->IsTrueReachable()"); } } while (0);
888 builder()->GotoNoSimulate(true_block, continuation->true_branch());
889 }
890 if (false_block != NULL__null && !false_block->IsFinished()) {
891 DCHECK(continuation->IsFalseReachable())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(continuation->IsFalseReachable
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 891, "Check failed: %s."
, "continuation->IsFalseReachable()"); } } while (0);
892 builder()->GotoNoSimulate(false_block, continuation->false_branch());
893 }
894 captured_ = true;
895 End();
896}
897
898
899void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::Then() {
900 DCHECK(!captured_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!captured_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 900, "Check failed: %s.", "!captured_"
); } } while (0);
901 DCHECK(!finished_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!finished_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 901, "Check failed: %s.", "!finished_"
); } } while (0);
902 did_then_ = true;
903 if (needs_compare_) {
904 // Handle if's without any expressions, they jump directly to the "else"
905 // branch. However, we must pretend that the "then" branch is reachable,
906 // so that the graph builder visits it and sees any live range extending
907 // constructs within it.
908 HConstant* constant_false = builder()->graph()->GetConstantFalse();
909 ToBooleanStub::Types boolean_type = ToBooleanStub::Types();
910 boolean_type.Add(ToBooleanStub::BOOLEAN);
911 HBranch* branch = builder()->New<HBranch>(
912 constant_false, boolean_type, first_true_block_, first_false_block_);
913 builder()->FinishCurrentBlock(branch);
914 }
915 builder()->set_current_block(first_true_block_);
916 pending_merge_block_ = true;
917}
918
919
920void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::Else() {
921 DCHECK(did_then_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(did_then_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal(
"../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 921, "Check failed: %s.", "did_then_"
); } } while (0);
922 DCHECK(!captured_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!captured_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 922, "Check failed: %s.", "!captured_"
); } } while (0);
923 DCHECK(!finished_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!finished_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 923, "Check failed: %s.", "!finished_"
); } } while (0);
924 AddMergeAtJoinBlock(false);
925 builder()->set_current_block(first_false_block_);
926 pending_merge_block_ = true;
927 did_else_ = true;
928}
929
930
931void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::Deopt(Deoptimizer::DeoptReason reason) {
932 DCHECK(did_then_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(did_then_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal(
"../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 932, "Check failed: %s.", "did_then_"
); } } while (0);
933 builder()->Add<HDeoptimize>(reason, Deoptimizer::EAGER);
934 AddMergeAtJoinBlock(true);
935}
936
937
938void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::Return(HValue* value) {
939 HValue* parameter_count = builder()->graph()->GetConstantMinus1();
940 builder()->FinishExitCurrentBlock(
941 builder()->New<HReturn>(value, parameter_count));
942 AddMergeAtJoinBlock(false);
943}
944
945
946void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::AddMergeAtJoinBlock(bool deopt) {
947 if (!pending_merge_block_) return;
948 HBasicBlock* block = builder()->current_block();
949 DCHECK(block == NULL || !block->IsFinished())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block == __null || !block->
IsFinished())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 949, "Check failed: %s.", "block == __null || !block->IsFinished()"
); } } while (0);
950 MergeAtJoinBlock* record = new (builder()->zone())
951 MergeAtJoinBlock(block, deopt, merge_at_join_blocks_);
952 merge_at_join_blocks_ = record;
953 if (block != NULL__null) {
954 DCHECK(block->end() == NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block->end() == __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 954, "Check failed: %s."
, "block->end() == __null"); } } while (0);
955 if (deopt) {
956 normal_merge_at_join_block_count_++;
957 } else {
958 deopt_merge_at_join_block_count_++;
959 }
960 }
961 builder()->set_current_block(NULL__null);
962 pending_merge_block_ = false;
963}
964
965
966void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::Finish() {
967 DCHECK(!finished_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!finished_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 967, "Check failed: %s.", "!finished_"
); } } while (0);
968 if (!did_then_) {
969 Then();
970 }
971 AddMergeAtJoinBlock(false);
972 if (!did_else_) {
973 Else();
974 AddMergeAtJoinBlock(false);
975 }
976 finished_ = true;
977}
978
979
980void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::Finish(HBasicBlock** then_continuation,
981 HBasicBlock** else_continuation) {
982 Finish();
983
984 MergeAtJoinBlock* else_record = merge_at_join_blocks_;
985 if (else_continuation != NULL__null) {
986 *else_continuation = else_record->block_;
987 }
988 MergeAtJoinBlock* then_record = else_record->next_;
989 if (then_continuation != NULL__null) {
990 *then_continuation = then_record->block_;
991 }
992 DCHECK(then_record->next_ == NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(then_record->next_ == __null
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 992, "Check failed: %s."
, "then_record->next_ == __null"); } } while (0);
993}
994
995
996void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::EndUnreachable() {
997 if (captured_) return;
998 Finish();
999 builder()->set_current_block(nullptr);
1000}
1001
1002
1003void HGraphBuilder::IfBuilder::End() {
1004 if (captured_) return;
1005 Finish();
1006
1007 int total_merged_blocks = normal_merge_at_join_block_count_ +
1008 deopt_merge_at_join_block_count_;
1009 DCHECK(total_merged_blocks >= 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(total_merged_blocks >= 1))
, 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 1009, "Check failed: %s."
, "total_merged_blocks >= 1"); } } while (0);
1010 HBasicBlock* merge_block =
1011 total_merged_blocks == 1 ? NULL__null : builder()->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
1012
1013 // Merge non-deopt blocks first to ensure environment has right size for
1014 // padding.
1015 MergeAtJoinBlock* current = merge_at_join_blocks_;
1016 while (current != NULL__null) {
1017 if (!current->deopt_ && current->block_ != NULL__null) {
1018 // If there is only one block that makes it through to the end of the
1019 // if, then just set it as the current block and continue rather then
1020 // creating an unnecessary merge block.
1021 if (total_merged_blocks == 1) {
1022 builder()->set_current_block(current->block_);
1023 return;
1024 }
1025 builder()->GotoNoSimulate(current->block_, merge_block);
1026 }
1027 current = current->next_;
1028 }
1029
1030 // Merge deopt blocks, padding when necessary.
1031 current = merge_at_join_blocks_;
1032 while (current != NULL__null) {
1033 if (current->deopt_ && current->block_ != NULL__null) {
1034 current->block_->FinishExit(
1035 HAbnormalExit::New(builder()->isolate(), builder()->zone(), NULL__null),
1036 SourcePosition::Unknown());
1037 }
1038 current = current->next_;
1039 }
1040 builder()->set_current_block(merge_block);
1041}

1044HGraphBuilder::LoopBuilder::LoopBuilder(HGraphBuilder* builder) {
1045 Initialize(builder, NULL__null, kWhileTrue, NULL__null);
1046}

1049HGraphBuilder::LoopBuilder::LoopBuilder(HGraphBuilder* builder, HValue* context,
1050 LoopBuilder::Direction direction) {
1051 Initialize(builder, context, direction, builder->graph()->GetConstant1());
1052}

1054
1055HGraphBuilder::LoopBuilder::LoopBuilder(HGraphBuilder* builder, HValue* context,
1056 LoopBuilder::Direction direction,
1057 HValue* increment_amount) {
1058 Initialize(builder, context, direction, increment_amount);
1059 increment_amount_ = increment_amount;
1060}
1061
1062
1063void HGraphBuilder::LoopBuilder::Initialize(HGraphBuilder* builder,
1064 HValue* context,
1065 Direction direction,
1066 HValue* increment_amount) {
1067 builder_ = builder;
1068 context_ = context;
1069 direction_ = direction;
1070 increment_amount_ = increment_amount;
1071
1072 finished_ = false;
1073 header_block_ = builder->CreateLoopHeaderBlock();
1074 body_block_ = NULL__null;
1075 exit_block_ = NULL__null;
1076 exit_trampoline_block_ = NULL__null;
1077}
1078
1079
1080HValue* HGraphBuilder::LoopBuilder::BeginBody(
1081 HValue* initial,
1082 HValue* terminating,
1083 Token::Value token) {
1084 DCHECK(direction_ != kWhileTrue)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(direction_ != kWhileTrue)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 1084, "Check failed: %s."
, "direction_ != kWhileTrue"); } } while (0);
1085 HEnvironment* env = builder_->environment();
1086 phi_ = header_block_->AddNewPhi(env->values()->length());
1087 phi_->AddInput(initial);
1088 env->Push(initial);
1089 builder_->GotoNoSimulate(header_block_);
1090
1091 HEnvironment* body_env = env->Copy();
1092 HEnvironment* exit_env = env->Copy();
1093 // Remove the phi from the expression stack
1094 body_env->Pop();
1095 exit_env->Pop();
1096 body_block_ = builder_->CreateBasicBlock(body_env);
1097 exit_block_ = builder_->CreateBasicBlock(exit_env);
1098
1099 builder_->set_current_block(header_block_);
1100 env->Pop();
1101 builder_->FinishCurrentBlock(builder_->New<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
1102 phi_, terminating, token, body_block_, exit_block_));
1103
1104 builder_->set_current_block(body_block_);
1105 if (direction_ == kPreIncrement || direction_ == kPreDecrement) {
1106 Isolate* isolate = builder_->isolate();
1107 HValue* one = builder_->graph()->GetConstant1();
1108 if (direction_ == kPreIncrement) {
1109 increment_ = HAdd::New(isolate, zone(), context_, phi_, one);
1110 } else {
1111 increment_ = HSub::New(isolate, zone(), context_, phi_, one);
1112 }
1113 increment_->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1114 builder_->AddInstruction(increment_);
1115 return increment_;
1116 } else {
1117 return phi_;
1118 }
1119}
1120
1121
1122void HGraphBuilder::LoopBuilder::BeginBody(int drop_count) {
1123 DCHECK(direction_ == kWhileTrue)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(direction_ == kWhileTrue)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 1123, "Check failed: %s."
, "direction_ == kWhileTrue"); } } while (0);
1124 HEnvironment* env = builder_->environment();
1125 builder_->GotoNoSimulate(header_block_);
1126 builder_->set_current_block(header_block_);
1127 env->Drop(drop_count);
1128}
1129
1130
1131void HGraphBuilder::LoopBuilder::Break() {
1132 if (exit_trampoline_block_ == NULL__null) {
1133 // Its the first time we saw a break.
1134 if (direction_ == kWhileTrue) {
1135 HEnvironment* env = builder_->environment()->Copy();
1136 exit_trampoline_block_ = builder_->CreateBasicBlock(env);
1137 } else {
1138 HEnvironment* env = exit_block_->last_environment()->Copy();
1139 exit_trampoline_block_ = builder_->CreateBasicBlock(env);
1140 builder_->GotoNoSimulate(exit_block_, exit_trampoline_block_);
1141 }
1142 }
1143
1144 builder_->GotoNoSimulate(exit_trampoline_block_);
1145 builder_->set_current_block(NULL__null);
1146}
1147
1148
1149void HGraphBuilder::LoopBuilder::EndBody() {
1150 DCHECK(!finished_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!finished_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 1150, "Check failed: %s.", "!finished_"
); } } while (0);
1151
1152 if (direction_ == kPostIncrement || direction_ == kPostDecrement) {
1153 Isolate* isolate = builder_->isolate();
1154 if (direction_ == kPostIncrement) {
1155 increment_ =
1156 HAdd::New(isolate, zone(), context_, phi_, increment_amount_);
1157 } else {
1158 increment_ =
1159 HSub::New(isolate, zone(), context_, phi_, increment_amount_);
1160 }
1161 increment_->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1162 builder_->AddInstruction(increment_);
1163 }
1164
1165 if (direction_ != kWhileTrue) {
1166 // Push the new increment value on the expression stack to merge into
1167 // the phi.
1168 builder_->environment()->Push(increment_);
1169 }
1170 HBasicBlock* last_block = builder_->current_block();
1171 builder_->GotoNoSimulate(last_block, header_block_);
1172 header_block_->loop_information()->RegisterBackEdge(last_block);
1173
1174 if (exit_trampoline_block_ != NULL__null) {
1175 builder_->set_current_block(exit_trampoline_block_);
1176 } else {
1177 builder_->set_current_block(exit_block_);
1178 }
1179 finished_ = true;
1180}

1182
1183HGraph* HGraphBuilder::CreateGraph() {
1184 graph_ = new (zone()) HGraph(info_, descriptor_);
1185 if (FLAG_hydrogen_stats) isolate()->GetHStatistics()->Initialize(info_);
1186 CompilationPhase phase("H_Block building", info_);
1187 set_current_block(graph()->entry_block());
1188 if (!BuildGraph()) return NULL__null;
1189 graph()->FinalizeUniqueness();
1190 return graph_;
1191}

1194HInstruction* HGraphBuilder::AddInstruction(HInstruction* instr) {
1195 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 1195, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
1196 DCHECK(!FLAG_hydrogen_track_positions ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!FLAG_hydrogen_track_positions
|| !position_.IsUnknown() || !info_->IsOptimizing())), 0)
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 1198, "Check failed: %s."
, "!FLAG_hydrogen_track_positions || !position_.IsUnknown() || !info_->IsOptimizing()"
); } } while (0)
1197 !position_.IsUnknown() ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!FLAG_hydrogen_track_positions
|| !position_.IsUnknown() || !info_->IsOptimizing())), 0)
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 1198, "Check failed: %s."
, "!FLAG_hydrogen_track_positions || !position_.IsUnknown() || !info_->IsOptimizing()"
); } } while (0)
1198 !info_->IsOptimizing())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!FLAG_hydrogen_track_positions
|| !position_.IsUnknown() || !info_->IsOptimizing())), 0)
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 1198, "Check failed: %s."
, "!FLAG_hydrogen_track_positions || !position_.IsUnknown() || !info_->IsOptimizing()"
); } } while (0);
1199 current_block()->AddInstruction(instr, source_position());
1200 if (graph()->IsInsideNoSideEffectsScope()) {
1201 instr->SetFlag(HValue::kHasNoObservableSideEffects);
1202 }
1203 return instr;
1204}

|| !info_->IsOptimizing() || !position_.IsUnknown())), 0)

1228void HGraphBuilder::AddIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter) {
1229 if (FLAG_native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
1230 HValue* reference = Add<HConstant>(ExternalReference(counter));

1234 new_value->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow); // Ignore counter overflow

1236 new_value, STORE_TO_INITIALIZED_ENTRY);

1306HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildWrapReceiver(HValue* object, HValue* function) {
1307 if (object->type().IsJSObject()) return object;
1308 if (function->IsConstant() &&
1309 HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate())->IsJSFunction()) {
1310 Handle<JSFunction> f = Handle<JSFunction>::cast(
1311 HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate()));
1312 SharedFunctionInfo* shared = f->shared();
1313 if (is_strict(shared->language_mode()) || shared->native()) return object;
1314 }
1315 return Add<HWrapReceiver>(object, function);

1318
1319HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildCheckAndGrowElementsCapacity(
1320 HValue* object, HValue* elements, ElementsKind kind, HValue* length,
1321 HValue* capacity, HValue* key) {
1322 HValue* max_gap = Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(JSObject::kMaxGap));
1323 HValue* max_capacity = AddUncasted<HAdd>(capacity, max_gap);
1324 Add<HBoundsCheck>(key, max_capacity);
1325
1326 HValue* new_capacity = BuildNewElementsCapacity(key);
1327 HValue* new_elements = BuildGrowElementsCapacity(object, elements, kind, kind,
1328 length, new_capacity);
1329 return new_elements;
1330}
1331
1332
1333HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildCheckForCapacityGrow(
1334 HValue* object,
1335 HValue* elements,
1336 ElementsKind kind,
1337 HValue* length,
1338 HValue* key,
1339 bool is_js_array,
1340 PropertyAccessType access_type) {
1341 IfBuilder length_checker(this);
1342
1343 Token::Value token = IsHoleyElementsKind(kind) ? Token::GTE : Token::EQ;
1344 length_checker.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(key, length, token);
1345
1346 length_checker.Then();
1347
1348 HValue* current_capacity = AddLoadFixedArrayLength(elements);
1349
1350 if (top_info()->IsStub()) {
1351 IfBuilder capacity_checker(this);
1352 capacity_checker.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(key, current_capacity,
1353 Token::GTE);
1354 capacity_checker.Then();
1355 HValue* new_elements = BuildCheckAndGrowElementsCapacity(
1356 object, elements, kind, length, current_capacity, key);
1357 environment()->Push(new_elements);
1358 capacity_checker.Else();
1359 environment()->Push(elements);
1360 capacity_checker.End();
1361 } else {
1362 HValue* result = Add<HMaybeGrowElements>(
1363 object, elements, key, current_capacity, is_js_array, kind);
1364 environment()->Push(result);
1365 }
1366
1367 if (is_js_array) {
1368 HValue* new_length = AddUncasted<HAdd>(key, graph_->GetConstant1());
1369 new_length->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1370
1371 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(kind),
1372 new_length);
1373 }
1374
1375 if (access_type == STORE && kind == FAST_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
1376 HValue* checked_elements = environment()->Top();
1377
1378 // Write zero to ensure that the new element is initialized with some smi.
1379 Add<HStoreKeyed>(checked_elements, key, graph()->GetConstant0(), nullptr,
1380 kind);
1381 }
1382
1383 length_checker.Else();
1384 Add<HBoundsCheck>(key, length);
1385
1386 environment()->Push(elements);
1387 length_checker.End();
1388
1389 return environment()->Pop();
1390}
1391
1392
1393HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildCopyElementsOnWrite(HValue* object,
1394 HValue* elements,
1395 ElementsKind kind,
1396 HValue* length) {
1397 Factory* factory = isolate()->factory();
1398
1399 IfBuilder cow_checker(this);
1400
1401 cow_checker.If<HCompareMap>(elements, factory->fixed_cow_array_map());
1402 cow_checker.Then();
1403
1404 HValue* capacity = AddLoadFixedArrayLength(elements);
1405
1406 HValue* new_elements = BuildGrowElementsCapacity(object, elements, kind,
1407 kind, length, capacity);
1408
1409 environment()->Push(new_elements);
1410
1411 cow_checker.Else();
1412
1413 environment()->Push(elements);
1414
1415 cow_checker.End();
1416
1417 return environment()->Pop();
1418}

1420
1421void HGraphBuilder::BuildTransitionElementsKind(HValue* object,
1422 HValue* map,
1423 ElementsKind from_kind,
1424 ElementsKind to_kind,
1425 bool is_jsarray) {
1426 DCHECK(!IsFastHoleyElementsKind(from_kind) ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!IsFastHoleyElementsKind(from_kind
) || IsFastHoleyElementsKind(to_kind))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 1427, "Check failed: %s.", "!IsFastHoleyElementsKind(from_kind) || IsFastHoleyElementsKind(to_kind)"
); } } while (0)
1427 IsFastHoleyElementsKind(to_kind))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!IsFastHoleyElementsKind(from_kind
) || IsFastHoleyElementsKind(to_kind))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 1427, "Check failed: %s.", "!IsFastHoleyElementsKind(from_kind) || IsFastHoleyElementsKind(to_kind)"
); } } while (0);
1428
1429 if (AllocationSite::GetMode(from_kind, to_kind) == TRACK_ALLOCATION_SITE) {
1430 Add<HTrapAllocationMemento>(object);
1431 }
1432
1433 if (!IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(from_kind, to_kind)) {
1434 HInstruction* elements = AddLoadElements(object);
1435
1436 HInstruction* empty_fixed_array = Add<HConstant>(
1437 isolate()->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1438
1439 IfBuilder if_builder(this);
1440
1441 if_builder.IfNot<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(elements, empty_fixed_array);
1442
1443 if_builder.Then();
1444
1445 HInstruction* elements_length = AddLoadFixedArrayLength(elements);
1446
1447 HInstruction* array_length =
1448 is_jsarray
1449 ? Add<HLoadNamedField>(object, nullptr,
1450 HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(from_kind))
1451 : elements_length;
1452
1453 BuildGrowElementsCapacity(object, elements, from_kind, to_kind,
1454 array_length, elements_length);
1455
1456 if_builder.End();
1457 }
1458
1459 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, HObjectAccess::ForMap(), map);
1460}
1461
1462
1463void HGraphBuilder::BuildJSObjectCheck(HValue* receiver,
1464 int bit_field_mask) {
1465 // Check that the object isn't a smi.
1466 Add<HCheckHeapObject>(receiver);
1467
1468 // Get the map of the receiver.
1469 HValue* map =
1470 Add<HLoadNamedField>(receiver, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMap());
1471
1472 // Check the instance type and if an access check is needed, this can be
1473 // done with a single load, since both bytes are adjacent in the map.
1474 HObjectAccess access(HObjectAccess::ForMapInstanceTypeAndBitField());
1475 HValue* instance_type_and_bit_field =
1476 Add<HLoadNamedField>(map, nullptr, access);
1477
1478 HValue* mask = Add<HConstant>(0x00FF | (bit_field_mask << 8));
1479 HValue* and_result = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_AND,
1480 instance_type_and_bit_field,
1481 mask);
1482 HValue* sub_result = AddUncasted<HSub>(and_result,
1483 Add<HConstant>(JS_OBJECT_TYPE));
1484 Add<HBoundsCheck>(sub_result,
1485 Add<HConstant>(LAST_JS_OBJECT_TYPE + 1 - JS_OBJECT_TYPE));
1486}
1487
1488
1489void HGraphBuilder::BuildKeyedIndexCheck(HValue* key,
1490 HIfContinuation* join_continuation) {
1491 // The sometimes unintuitively backward ordering of the ifs below is
1492 // convoluted, but necessary. All of the paths must guarantee that the
1493 // if-true of the continuation returns a smi element index and the if-false of
1494 // the continuation returns either a symbol or a unique string key. All other
1495 // object types cause a deopt to fall back to the runtime.
1496
1497 IfBuilder key_smi_if(this);
1498 key_smi_if.If<HIsSmiAndBranch>(key);
1499 key_smi_if.Then();
1500 {
1501 Push(key); // Nothing to do, just continue to true of continuation.
1502 }
1503 key_smi_if.Else();
1504 {
1505 HValue* map = Add<HLoadNamedField>(key, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMap());
1506 HValue* instance_type =
1507 Add<HLoadNamedField>(map, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMapInstanceType());
1508
1509 // Non-unique string, check for a string with a hash code that is actually
1510 // an index.
1511 STATIC_ASSERT(LAST_UNIQUE_NAME_TYPE == FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE)static_assert(LAST_UNIQUE_NAME_TYPE == FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE, "LAST_UNIQUE_NAME_TYPE == FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE"
);
1512 IfBuilder not_string_or_name_if(this);
1513 not_string_or_name_if.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
1514 instance_type,
1515 Add<HConstant>(LAST_UNIQUE_NAME_TYPE),
1516 Token::GT);
1517
1518 not_string_or_name_if.Then();
1519 {
1520 // Non-smi, non-Name, non-String: Try to convert to smi in case of
1521 // HeapNumber.
1522 // TODO(danno): This could call some variant of ToString
1523 Push(AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(key, Representation::Smi()));
1524 }
1525 not_string_or_name_if.Else();
1526 {
1527 // String or Name: check explicitly for Name, they can short-circuit
1528 // directly to unique non-index key path.
1529 IfBuilder not_symbol_if(this);
1530 not_symbol_if.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
1531 instance_type,
1532 Add<HConstant>(SYMBOL_TYPE),
1533 Token::NE);
1534
1535 not_symbol_if.Then();
1536 {
1537 // String: check whether the String is a String of an index. If it is,
1538 // extract the index value from the hash.
1539 HValue* hash = Add<HLoadNamedField>(key, nullptr,
1540 HObjectAccess::ForNameHashField());
1541 HValue* not_index_mask = Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int>(
1542 String::kContainsCachedArrayIndexMask));
1543
1544 HValue* not_index_test = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
1545 Token::BIT_AND, hash, not_index_mask);
1546
1547 IfBuilder string_index_if(this);
1548 string_index_if.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(not_index_test,
1549 graph()->GetConstant0(),
1550 Token::EQ);
1551 string_index_if.Then();
1552 {
1553 // String with index in hash: extract string and merge to index path.
1554 Push(BuildDecodeField<String::ArrayIndexValueBits>(hash));
1555 }
1556 string_index_if.Else();
1557 {
1558 // Key is a non-index String, check for uniqueness/internalization.
1559 // If it's not internalized yet, internalize it now.
1560 HValue* not_internalized_bit = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
1561 Token::BIT_AND,
1562 instance_type,
1563 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int>(kIsNotInternalizedMask)));
1564
1565 IfBuilder internalized(this);
1566 internalized.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(not_internalized_bit,
1567 graph()->GetConstant0(),
1568 Token::EQ);
1569 internalized.Then();
1570 Push(key);
1571
1572 internalized.Else();
1573 Add<HPushArguments>(key);
1574 HValue* intern_key = Add<HCallRuntime>(
1575 Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kInternalizeString), 1);
1576 Push(intern_key);
1577
1578 internalized.End();
1579 // Key guaranteed to be a unique string
1580 }
1581 string_index_if.JoinContinuation(join_continuation);
1582 }
1583 not_symbol_if.Else();
1584 {
1585 Push(key); // Key is symbol
1586 }
1587 not_symbol_if.JoinContinuation(join_continuation);
1588 }
1589 not_string_or_name_if.JoinContinuation(join_continuation);
1590 }
1591 key_smi_if.JoinContinuation(join_continuation);
1592}
1593
1594
1595void HGraphBuilder::BuildNonGlobalObjectCheck(HValue* receiver) {
1596 // Get the the instance type of the receiver, and make sure that it is
1597 // not one of the global object types.
1598 HValue* map =
1599 Add<HLoadNamedField>(receiver, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMap());
1600 HValue* instance_type =
1601 Add<HLoadNamedField>(map, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMapInstanceType());
1602 HValue* global_type = Add<HConstant>(JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE);
1603
1604 IfBuilder if_global_object(this);
1605 if_global_object.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(instance_type, global_type,
1606 Token::EQ);
1607 if_global_object.ThenDeopt(Deoptimizer::kReceiverWasAGlobalObject);
1608 if_global_object.End();
1609}

1611
1612void HGraphBuilder::BuildTestForDictionaryProperties(
1613 HValue* object,
1614 HIfContinuation* continuation) {
1615 HValue* properties = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
1616 object, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForPropertiesPointer());
1617 HValue* properties_map =
1618 Add<HLoadNamedField>(properties, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMap());
1619 HValue* hash_map = Add<HLoadRoot>(Heap::kHashTableMapRootIndex);
1620 IfBuilder builder(this);
1621 builder.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(properties_map, hash_map);
1622 builder.CaptureContinuation(continuation);
1623}

1625
1626HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildKeyedLookupCacheHash(HValue* object,
1627 HValue* key) {
1628 // Load the map of the receiver, compute the keyed lookup cache hash
1629 // based on 32 bits of the map pointer and the string hash.
1630 HValue* object_map =
1631 Add<HLoadNamedField>(object, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMapAsInteger32());
1632 HValue* shifted_map = AddUncasted<HShr>(
1633 object_map, Add<HConstant>(KeyedLookupCache::kMapHashShift));
1634 HValue* string_hash =
1635 Add<HLoadNamedField>(key, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForStringHashField());
1636 HValue* shifted_hash = AddUncasted<HShr>(
1637 string_hash, Add<HConstant>(String::kHashShift));
1638 HValue* xor_result = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_XOR, shifted_map,
1639 shifted_hash);
1640 int mask = (KeyedLookupCache::kCapacityMask & KeyedLookupCache::kHashMask);
1641 return AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_AND, xor_result,
1642 Add<HConstant>(mask));
1643}
1644
1645
1646HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildElementIndexHash(HValue* index) {
1647 int32_t seed_value = static_cast<uint32_t>(isolate()->heap()->HashSeed());
1648 HValue* seed = Add<HConstant>(seed_value);
1649 HValue* hash = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_XOR, index, seed);
1650
1651 // hash = ~hash + (hash << 15);
1652 HValue* shifted_hash = AddUncasted<HShl>(hash, Add<HConstant>(15));
1653 HValue* not_hash = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_XOR, hash,
1654 graph()->GetConstantMinus1());
1655 hash = AddUncasted<HAdd>(shifted_hash, not_hash);
1656
1657 // hash = hash ^ (hash >> 12);
1658 shifted_hash = AddUncasted<HShr>(hash, Add<HConstant>(12));
1659 hash = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_XOR, hash, shifted_hash);
1660
1661 // hash = hash + (hash << 2);
1662 shifted_hash = AddUncasted<HShl>(hash, Add<HConstant>(2));
1663 hash = AddUncasted<HAdd>(hash, shifted_hash);
1664
1665 // hash = hash ^ (hash >> 4);
1666 shifted_hash = AddUncasted<HShr>(hash, Add<HConstant>(4));
1667 hash = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_XOR, hash, shifted_hash);
1668
1669 // hash = hash * 2057;
1670 hash = AddUncasted<HMul>(hash, Add<HConstant>(2057));
1671 hash->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1672
1673 // hash = hash ^ (hash >> 16);
1674 shifted_hash = AddUncasted<HShr>(hash, Add<HConstant>(16));
1675 return AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_XOR, hash, shifted_hash);
1676}
1677
1678HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildUncheckedDictionaryElementLoad(HValue* receiver,
1679 HValue* elements,
1680 HValue* key,
1681 HValue* hash) {
1682 HValue* capacity =
1683 Add<HLoadKeyed>(elements, Add<HConstant>(NameDictionary::kCapacityIndex),
1684 nullptr, nullptr, FAST_ELEMENTS);
1685
1686 HValue* mask = AddUncasted<HSub>(capacity, graph()->GetConstant1());
1687 mask->ChangeRepresentation(Representation::Integer32());
1688 mask->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1689
1690 HValue* entry = hash;
1691 HValue* count = graph()->GetConstant1();
1692 Push(entry);
1693 Push(count);
1694
1695 HIfContinuation return_or_loop_continuation(graph()->CreateBasicBlock(),
1696 graph()->CreateBasicBlock());
1697 HIfContinuation found_key_match_continuation(graph()->CreateBasicBlock(),
1698 graph()->CreateBasicBlock());
1699 LoopBuilder probe_loop(this);
1700 probe_loop.BeginBody(2); // Drop entry, count from last environment to
1701 // appease live range building without simulates.
1702
1703 count = Pop();
1704 entry = Pop();
1705 entry = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_AND, entry, mask);
1706 int entry_size = SeededNumberDictionary::kEntrySize;
1707 HValue* base_index = AddUncasted<HMul>(entry, Add<HConstant>(entry_size));
1708 base_index->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1709 int start_offset = SeededNumberDictionary::kElementsStartIndex;
1710 HValue* key_index =
1711 AddUncasted<HAdd>(base_index, Add<HConstant>(start_offset));
1712 key_index->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1713
1714 HValue* candidate_key =
1715 Add<HLoadKeyed>(elements, key_index, nullptr, nullptr, FAST_ELEMENTS);
1716 IfBuilder if_undefined(this);
1717 if_undefined.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(candidate_key,
1718 graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
1719 if_undefined.Then();
1720 {
1721 // element == undefined means "not found". Call the runtime.
1722 // TODO(jkummerow): walk the prototype chain instead.
1723 Add<HPushArguments>(receiver, key);
1724 Push(Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kKeyedGetProperty),
1725 2));
1726 }
1727 if_undefined.Else();
1728 {
1729 IfBuilder if_match(this);
1730 if_match.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(candidate_key, key);
1731 if_match.Then();
1732 if_match.Else();
1733
1734 // Update non-internalized string in the dictionary with internalized key?
1735 IfBuilder if_update_with_internalized(this);
1736 HValue* smi_check =
1737 if_update_with_internalized.IfNot<HIsSmiAndBranch>(candidate_key);
1738 if_update_with_internalized.And();
1739 HValue* map = AddLoadMap(candidate_key, smi_check);
1740 HValue* instance_type =
1741 Add<HLoadNamedField>(map, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMapInstanceType());
1742 HValue* not_internalized_bit = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
1743 Token::BIT_AND, instance_type,
1744 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int>(kIsNotInternalizedMask)));
1745 if_update_with_internalized.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
1746 not_internalized_bit, graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::NE);
1747 if_update_with_internalized.And();
1748 if_update_with_internalized.IfNot<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(
1749 candidate_key, graph()->GetConstantHole());
1750 if_update_with_internalized.AndIf<HStringCompareAndBranch>(candidate_key,
1751 key, Token::EQ);
1752 if_update_with_internalized.Then();
1753 // Replace a key that is a non-internalized string by the equivalent
1754 // internalized string for faster further lookups.
1755 Add<HStoreKeyed>(elements, key_index, key, nullptr, FAST_ELEMENTS);
1756 if_update_with_internalized.Else();
1757
1758 if_update_with_internalized.JoinContinuation(&found_key_match_continuation);
1759 if_match.JoinContinuation(&found_key_match_continuation);
1760
1761 IfBuilder found_key_match(this, &found_key_match_continuation);
1762 found_key_match.Then();
1763 // Key at current probe matches. Relevant bits in the |details| field must
1764 // be zero, otherwise the dictionary element requires special handling.
1765 HValue* details_index =
1766 AddUncasted<HAdd>(base_index, Add<HConstant>(start_offset + 2));
1767 details_index->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1768 HValue* details = Add<HLoadKeyed>(elements, details_index, nullptr, nullptr,
1769 FAST_ELEMENTS);
1770 int details_mask = PropertyDetails::TypeField::kMask;
1771 details = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_AND, details,
1772 Add<HConstant>(details_mask));
1773 IfBuilder details_compare(this);
1774 details_compare.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
1775 details, graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::EQ);
1776 details_compare.Then();
1777 HValue* result_index =
1778 AddUncasted<HAdd>(base_index, Add<HConstant>(start_offset + 1));
1779 result_index->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1780 Push(Add<HLoadKeyed>(elements, result_index, nullptr, nullptr,
1781 FAST_ELEMENTS));
1782 details_compare.Else();
1783 Add<HPushArguments>(receiver, key);
1784 Push(Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kKeyedGetProperty),
1785 2));
1786 details_compare.End();
1787
1788 found_key_match.Else();
1789 found_key_match.JoinContinuation(&return_or_loop_continuation);
1790 }
1791 if_undefined.JoinContinuation(&return_or_loop_continuation);
1792
1793 IfBuilder return_or_loop(this, &return_or_loop_continuation);
1794 return_or_loop.Then();
1795 probe_loop.Break();
1796
1797 return_or_loop.Else();
1798 entry = AddUncasted<HAdd>(entry, count);
1799 entry->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1800 count = AddUncasted<HAdd>(count, graph()->GetConstant1());
1801 count->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
1802 Push(entry);
1803 Push(count);
1804
1805 probe_loop.EndBody();
1806
1807 return_or_loop.End();
1808
1809 return Pop();
1810}
