1812
1813HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildCreateIterResultObject(HValue* value,
1814 HValue* done) {
1815 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
1816
1817 // Allocate the JSIteratorResult object.
1818 HValue* result =
1819 Add<HAllocate>(Add<HConstant>(JSIteratorResult::kSize), HType::JSObject(),
1820 NOT_TENURED, JS_OBJECT_TYPE);
1821
1822 // Initialize the JSIteratorResult object.
1823 HValue* native_context = BuildGetNativeContext();
1824 HValue* map = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
1825 native_context, nullptr,
1826 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::ITERATOR_RESULT_MAP_INDEX));
1827 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForMap(), map);
1828 HValue* empty_fixed_array = Add<HLoadRoot>(Heap::kEmptyFixedArrayRootIndex);
1829 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForPropertiesPointer(),
1830 empty_fixed_array);
1831 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(),
1832 empty_fixed_array);
1833 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForObservableJSObjectOffset(
1834 JSIteratorResult::kValueOffset),
1835 value);
1836 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForObservableJSObjectOffset(
1837 JSIteratorResult::kDoneOffset),
1838 done);
1839 STATIC_ASSERT(JSIteratorResult::kSize == 5 * kPointerSize)static_assert(JSIteratorResult::kSize == 5 * kPointerSize, "JSIteratorResult::kSize == 5 * kPointerSize"
);
1840 return result;
1841}
1842
1843
1844HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildRegExpConstructResult(HValue* length,
1845 HValue* index,
1846 HValue* input) {
1847 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
1848 HConstant* max_length = Add<HConstant>(JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray);
1849 Add<HBoundsCheck>(length, max_length);
1850
1851 // Generate size calculation code here in order to make it dominate
1852 // the JSRegExpResult allocation.
1853 ElementsKind elements_kind = FAST_ELEMENTS;
1854 HValue* size = BuildCalculateElementsSize(elements_kind, length);
1855
1856 // Allocate the JSRegExpResult and the FixedArray in one step.
1857 HValue* result = Add<HAllocate>(
1858 Add<HConstant>(JSRegExpResult::kSize), HType::JSArray(),
1859 NOT_TENURED, JS_ARRAY_TYPE);
1860
1861 // Initialize the JSRegExpResult header.
1862 HValue* native_context = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
1863 context(), nullptr,
1864 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::NATIVE_CONTEXT_INDEX));
1865 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
1866 result, HObjectAccess::ForMap(),
1867 Add<HLoadNamedField>(
1868 native_context, nullptr,
1869 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::REGEXP_RESULT_MAP_INDEX)));
1870 HConstant* empty_fixed_array =
1871 Add<HConstant>(isolate()->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1872 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
1873 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayOffset(JSArray::kPropertiesOffset),
1874 empty_fixed_array);
1875 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
1876 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayOffset(JSArray::kElementsOffset),
1877 empty_fixed_array);
1878 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
1879 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayOffset(JSArray::kLengthOffset), length);
1880
1881 // Initialize the additional fields.
1882 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
1883 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayOffset(JSRegExpResult::kIndexOffset),
1884 index);
1885 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
1886 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayOffset(JSRegExpResult::kInputOffset),
1887 input);
1888
1889 // Allocate and initialize the elements header.
1890 HAllocate* elements = BuildAllocateElements(elements_kind, size);
1891 BuildInitializeElementsHeader(elements, elements_kind, length);
1892
1893 if (!elements->has_size_upper_bound()) {
1894 HConstant* size_in_bytes_upper_bound = EstablishElementsAllocationSize(
1895 elements_kind, max_length->Integer32Value());
1896 elements->set_size_upper_bound(size_in_bytes_upper_bound);
1897 }
1898
1899 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
1900 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayOffset(JSArray::kElementsOffset),
1901 elements);
1902
1903 // Initialize the elements contents with undefined.
1904 BuildFillElementsWithValue(
1905 elements, elements_kind, graph()->GetConstant0(), length,
1906 graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
1907
1908 return result;
1909}
1910
1911
1912HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildNumberToString(HValue* object, Type* type) {
1913 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
1914
1915 // Convert constant numbers at compile time.
1916 if (object->IsConstant() && HConstant::cast(object)->HasNumberValue()) {
1917 Handle<Object> number = HConstant::cast(object)->handle(isolate());
1918 Handle<String> result = isolate()->factory()->NumberToString(number);
1919 return Add<HConstant>(result);
1920 }
1921
1922 // Create a joinable continuation.
1923 HIfContinuation found(graph()->CreateBasicBlock(),
1924 graph()->CreateBasicBlock());
1925
1926 // Load the number string cache.
1927 HValue* number_string_cache =
1928 Add<HLoadRoot>(Heap::kNumberStringCacheRootIndex);
1929
1930 // Make the hash mask from the length of the number string cache. It
1931 // contains two elements (number and string) for each cache entry.
1932 HValue* mask = AddLoadFixedArrayLength(number_string_cache);
1933 mask->set_type(HType::Smi());
1934 mask = AddUncasted<HSar>(mask, graph()->GetConstant1());
1935 mask = AddUncasted<HSub>(mask, graph()->GetConstant1());
1936
1937 // Check whether object is a smi.
1938 IfBuilder if_objectissmi(this);
1939 if_objectissmi.If<HIsSmiAndBranch>(object);
1940 if_objectissmi.Then();
1941 {
1942 // Compute hash for smi similar to smi_get_hash().
1943 HValue* hash = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_AND, object, mask);
1944
1945 // Load the key.
1946 HValue* key_index = AddUncasted<HShl>(hash, graph()->GetConstant1());
1947 HValue* key = Add<HLoadKeyed>(number_string_cache, key_index, nullptr,
1948 nullptr, FAST_ELEMENTS, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
1949
1950 // Check if object == key.
1951 IfBuilder if_objectiskey(this);
1952 if_objectiskey.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(object, key);
1953 if_objectiskey.Then();
1954 {
1955 // Make the key_index available.
1956 Push(key_index);
1957 }
1958 if_objectiskey.JoinContinuation(&found);
1959 }
1960 if_objectissmi.Else();
1961 {
1962 if (type->Is(Type::SignedSmall())) {
1963 if_objectissmi.Deopt(Deoptimizer::kExpectedSmi);
1964 } else {
1965 // Check if the object is a heap number.
1966 IfBuilder if_objectisnumber(this);
1967 HValue* objectisnumber = if_objectisnumber.If<HCompareMap>(
1968 object, isolate()->factory()->heap_number_map());
1969 if_objectisnumber.Then();
1970 {
1971 // Compute hash for heap number similar to double_get_hash().
1972 HValue* low = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
1973 object, objectisnumber,
1974 HObjectAccess::ForHeapNumberValueLowestBits());
1975 HValue* high = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
1976 object, objectisnumber,
1977 HObjectAccess::ForHeapNumberValueHighestBits());
1978 HValue* hash = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_XOR, low, high);
1979 hash = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_AND, hash, mask);
1980
1981 // Load the key.
1982 HValue* key_index = AddUncasted<HShl>(hash, graph()->GetConstant1());
1983 HValue* key =
1984 Add<HLoadKeyed>(number_string_cache, key_index, nullptr, nullptr,
1985 FAST_ELEMENTS, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
1986
1987 // Check if the key is a heap number and compare it with the object.
1988 IfBuilder if_keyisnotsmi(this);
1989 HValue* keyisnotsmi = if_keyisnotsmi.IfNot<HIsSmiAndBranch>(key);
1990 if_keyisnotsmi.Then();
1991 {
1992 IfBuilder if_keyisheapnumber(this);
1993 if_keyisheapnumber.If<HCompareMap>(
1994 key, isolate()->factory()->heap_number_map());
1995 if_keyisheapnumber.Then();
1996 {
1997 // Check if values of key and object match.
1998 IfBuilder if_keyeqobject(this);
1999 if_keyeqobject.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2000 Add<HLoadNamedField>(key, keyisnotsmi,
2001 HObjectAccess::ForHeapNumberValue()),
2002 Add<HLoadNamedField>(object, objectisnumber,
2003 HObjectAccess::ForHeapNumberValue()),
2004 Token::EQ);
2005 if_keyeqobject.Then();
2006 {
2007 // Make the key_index available.
2008 Push(key_index);
2009 }
2010 if_keyeqobject.JoinContinuation(&found);
2011 }
2012 if_keyisheapnumber.JoinContinuation(&found);
2013 }
2014 if_keyisnotsmi.JoinContinuation(&found);
2015 }
2016 if_objectisnumber.Else();
2017 {
2018 if (type->Is(Type::Number())) {
2019 if_objectisnumber.Deopt(Deoptimizer::kExpectedHeapNumber);
2020 }
2021 }
2022 if_objectisnumber.JoinContinuation(&found);
2023 }
2024 }
2025 if_objectissmi.JoinContinuation(&found);
2026
2027 // Check for cache hit.
2028 IfBuilder if_found(this, &found);
2029 if_found.Then();
2030 {
2031 // Count number to string operation in native code.
2032 AddIncrementCounter(isolate()->counters()->number_to_string_native());
2033
2034 // Load the value in case of cache hit.
2035 HValue* key_index = Pop();
2036 HValue* value_index = AddUncasted<HAdd>(key_index, graph()->GetConstant1());
2037 Push(Add<HLoadKeyed>(number_string_cache, value_index, nullptr, nullptr,
2038 FAST_ELEMENTS, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE));
2039 }
2040 if_found.Else();
2041 {
2042 // Cache miss, fallback to runtime.
2043 Add<HPushArguments>(object);
2044 Push(Add<HCallRuntime>(
2045 Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kNumberToStringSkipCache),
2046 1));
2047 }
2048 if_found.End();
2049
2050 return Pop();
2051}
2052
2053HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildToNumber(HValue* input) {
2054 if (input->type().IsTaggedNumber()) {
2055 return input;
2056 }
2057 Callable callable = CodeFactory::ToNumber(isolate());
2058 HValue* stub = Add<HConstant>(callable.code());
2059 HValue* values[] = {context(), input};
2060 HCallWithDescriptor* instr =
2061 Add<HCallWithDescriptor>(stub, 0, callable.descriptor(),
2062 Vector<HValue*>(values, arraysize(values)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(values)))));
2063 instr->set_type(HType::TaggedNumber());
2064 return instr;
2065}
2066
2067
2068HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildToObject(HValue* receiver) {
2069 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
2070
2071 // Create a joinable continuation.
2072 HIfContinuation wrap(graph()->CreateBasicBlock(),
2073 graph()->CreateBasicBlock());
2074
2075 // Determine the proper global constructor function required to wrap
2076 // {receiver} into a JSValue, unless {receiver} is already a {JSReceiver}, in
2077 // which case we just return it. Deopts to Runtime::kToObject if {receiver}
2078 // is undefined or null.
2079 IfBuilder receiver_is_smi(this);
2080 receiver_is_smi.If<HIsSmiAndBranch>(receiver);
2081 receiver_is_smi.Then();
2082 {
2083 // Use global Number function.
2084 Push(Add<HConstant>(Context::NUMBER_FUNCTION_INDEX));
2085 }
2086 receiver_is_smi.Else();
2087 {
2088 // Determine {receiver} map and instance type.
2089 HValue* receiver_map =
2090 Add<HLoadNamedField>(receiver, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMap());
2091 HValue* receiver_instance_type = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
2092 receiver_map, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMapInstanceType());
2093
2094 // First check whether {receiver} is already a spec object (fast case).
2095 IfBuilder receiver_is_not_spec_object(this);
2096 receiver_is_not_spec_object.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2097 receiver_instance_type, Add<HConstant>(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE),
2098 Token::LT);
2099 receiver_is_not_spec_object.Then();
2100 {
2101 // Load the constructor function index from the {receiver} map.
2102 HValue* constructor_function_index = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
2103 receiver_map, nullptr,
2104 HObjectAccess::ForMapInObjectPropertiesOrConstructorFunctionIndex());
2105
2106 // Check if {receiver} has a constructor (null and undefined have no
2107 // constructors, so we deoptimize to the runtime to throw an exception).
2108 IfBuilder constructor_function_index_is_invalid(this);
2109 constructor_function_index_is_invalid.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2110 constructor_function_index,
2111 Add<HConstant>(Map::kNoConstructorFunctionIndex), Token::EQ);
2112 constructor_function_index_is_invalid.ThenDeopt(
2113 Deoptimizer::kUndefinedOrNullInToObject);
2114 constructor_function_index_is_invalid.End();
2115
2116 // Use the global constructor function.
2117 Push(constructor_function_index);
2118 }
2119 receiver_is_not_spec_object.JoinContinuation(&wrap);
2120 }
2121 receiver_is_smi.JoinContinuation(&wrap);
2122
2123 // Wrap the receiver if necessary.
2124 IfBuilder if_wrap(this, &wrap);
2125 if_wrap.Then();
2126 {
2127 // Grab the constructor function index.
2128 HValue* constructor_index = Pop();
2129
2130 // Load native context.
2131 HValue* native_context = BuildGetNativeContext();
2132
2133 // Determine the initial map for the global constructor.
2134 HValue* constructor = Add<HLoadKeyed>(native_context, constructor_index,
2135 nullptr, nullptr, FAST_ELEMENTS);
2136 HValue* constructor_initial_map = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
2137 constructor, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForPrototypeOrInitialMap());
2138 // Allocate and initialize a JSValue wrapper.
2139 HValue* value =
2140 BuildAllocate(Add<HConstant>(JSValue::kSize), HType::JSObject(),
2141 JS_VALUE_TYPE, HAllocationMode());
2142 Add<HStoreNamedField>(value, HObjectAccess::ForMap(),
2143 constructor_initial_map);
2144 HValue* empty_fixed_array = Add<HLoadRoot>(Heap::kEmptyFixedArrayRootIndex);
2145 Add<HStoreNamedField>(value, HObjectAccess::ForPropertiesPointer(),
2146 empty_fixed_array);
2147 Add<HStoreNamedField>(value, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(),
2148 empty_fixed_array);
2149 Add<HStoreNamedField>(value, HObjectAccess::ForObservableJSObjectOffset(
2150 JSValue::kValueOffset),
2151 receiver);
2152 Push(value);
2153 }
2154 if_wrap.Else();
2155 { Push(receiver); }
2156 if_wrap.End();
2157 return Pop();
2158}
2159
2160
2161HAllocate* HGraphBuilder::BuildAllocate(
2162 HValue* object_size,
2163 HType type,
2164 InstanceType instance_type,
2165 HAllocationMode allocation_mode) {
2166 // Compute the effective allocation size.
2167 HValue* size = object_size;
2168 if (allocation_mode.CreateAllocationMementos()) {
2169 size = AddUncasted<HAdd>(size, Add<HConstant>(AllocationMemento::kSize));
2170 size->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
2171 }
2172
2173 // Perform the actual allocation.
2174 HAllocate* object = Add<HAllocate>(
2175 size, type, allocation_mode.GetPretenureMode(),
2176 instance_type, allocation_mode.feedback_site());
2177
2178 // Setup the allocation memento.
2179 if (allocation_mode.CreateAllocationMementos()) {
2180 BuildCreateAllocationMemento(
2181 object, object_size, allocation_mode.current_site());
2182 }
2183
2184 return object;
2185}

2187
2188HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildAddStringLengths(HValue* left_length,
2189 HValue* right_length) {
2190 // Compute the combined string length and check against max string length.
2191 HValue* length = AddUncasted<HAdd>(left_length, right_length);
2192 // Check that length <= kMaxLength <=> length < MaxLength + 1.
2193 HValue* max_length = Add<HConstant>(String::kMaxLength + 1);
2194 Add<HBoundsCheck>(length, max_length);
2195 return length;
2196}
2197
2198
2199HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildCreateConsString(
2200 HValue* length,
2201 HValue* left,
2202 HValue* right,
2203 HAllocationMode allocation_mode) {
2204 // Determine the string instance types.
2205 HInstruction* left_instance_type = AddLoadStringInstanceType(left);
2206 HInstruction* right_instance_type = AddLoadStringInstanceType(right);
2207
2208 // Allocate the cons string object. HAllocate does not care whether we
2209 // pass CONS_STRING_TYPE or CONS_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE here, so we just use
2210 // CONS_STRING_TYPE here. Below we decide whether the cons string is
2211 // one-byte or two-byte and set the appropriate map.
2212 DCHECK(HAllocate::CompatibleInstanceTypes(CONS_STRING_TYPE,do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(HAllocate::CompatibleInstanceTypes
(CONS_STRING_TYPE, CONS_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE))), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2213, "Check failed: %s.", "HAllocate::CompatibleInstanceTypes(CONS_STRING_TYPE, CONS_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE)"
); } } while (0)
2213 CONS_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(HAllocate::CompatibleInstanceTypes
(CONS_STRING_TYPE, CONS_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE))), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2213, "Check failed: %s.", "HAllocate::CompatibleInstanceTypes(CONS_STRING_TYPE, CONS_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE)"
); } } while (0);
2214 HAllocate* result = BuildAllocate(Add<HConstant>(ConsString::kSize),
2215 HType::String(), CONS_STRING_TYPE,
2216 allocation_mode);
2217
2218 // Compute intersection and difference of instance types.
2219 HValue* anded_instance_types = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2220 Token::BIT_AND, left_instance_type, right_instance_type);
2221 HValue* xored_instance_types = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2222 Token::BIT_XOR, left_instance_type, right_instance_type);
2223
2224 // We create a one-byte cons string if
2225 // 1. both strings are one-byte, or
2226 // 2. at least one of the strings is two-byte, but happens to contain only
2227 // one-byte characters.
2228 // To do this, we check
2229 // 1. if both strings are one-byte, or if the one-byte data hint is set in
2230 // both strings, or
2231 // 2. if one of the strings has the one-byte data hint set and the other
2232 // string is one-byte.
2233 IfBuilder if_onebyte(this);
2234 STATIC_ASSERT(kOneByteStringTag != 0)static_assert(kOneByteStringTag != 0, "kOneByteStringTag != 0"
);
2235 STATIC_ASSERT(kOneByteDataHintMask != 0)static_assert(kOneByteDataHintMask != 0, "kOneByteDataHintMask != 0"
);
2236 if_onebyte.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2237 AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2238 Token::BIT_AND, anded_instance_types,
2239 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(
2240 kStringEncodingMask | kOneByteDataHintMask))),
2241 graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::NE);
2242 if_onebyte.Or();
2243 STATIC_ASSERT(kOneByteStringTag != 0 &&static_assert(kOneByteStringTag != 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag
!= 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag != kOneByteStringTag, "kOneByteStringTag != 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag != 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag != kOneByteStringTag"
)
2244 kOneByteDataHintTag != 0 &&static_assert(kOneByteStringTag != 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag
!= 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag != kOneByteStringTag, "kOneByteStringTag != 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag != 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag != kOneByteStringTag"
)
2245 kOneByteDataHintTag != kOneByteStringTag)static_assert(kOneByteStringTag != 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag
!= 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag != kOneByteStringTag, "kOneByteStringTag != 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag != 0 && kOneByteDataHintTag != kOneByteStringTag"
);
2246 if_onebyte.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2247 AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2248 Token::BIT_AND, xored_instance_types,
2249 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(
2250 kOneByteStringTag | kOneByteDataHintTag))),
2251 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(
2252 kOneByteStringTag | kOneByteDataHintTag)), Token::EQ);
2253 if_onebyte.Then();
2254 {
2255 // We can safely skip the write barrier for storing the map here.
2256 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
2257 result, HObjectAccess::ForMap(),
2258 Add<HConstant>(isolate()->factory()->cons_one_byte_string_map()));
2259 }
2260 if_onebyte.Else();
2261 {
2262 // We can safely skip the write barrier for storing the map here.
2263 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
2264 result, HObjectAccess::ForMap(),
2265 Add<HConstant>(isolate()->factory()->cons_string_map()));
2266 }
2267 if_onebyte.End();
2268
2269 // Initialize the cons string fields.
2270 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForStringHashField(),
2271 Add<HConstant>(String::kEmptyHashField));
2272 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForStringLength(), length);
2273 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForConsStringFirst(), left);
2274 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForConsStringSecond(), right);
2275
2276 // Count the native string addition.
2277 AddIncrementCounter(isolate()->counters()->string_add_native());
2278
2279 return result;
2280}

2282
2283void HGraphBuilder::BuildCopySeqStringChars(HValue* src,
2284 HValue* src_offset,
2285 String::Encoding src_encoding,
2286 HValue* dst,
2287 HValue* dst_offset,
2288 String::Encoding dst_encoding,
2289 HValue* length) {
2290 DCHECK(dst_encoding != String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(dst_encoding != String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING
|| src_encoding == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2291, "Check failed: %s.", "dst_encoding != String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING || src_encoding == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING"
); } } while (0)
2291 src_encoding == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(dst_encoding != String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING
|| src_encoding == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2291, "Check failed: %s.", "dst_encoding != String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING || src_encoding == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING"
); } } while (0);
2292 LoopBuilder loop(this, context(), LoopBuilder::kPostIncrement);
2293 HValue* index = loop.BeginBody(graph()->GetConstant0(), length, Token::LT);
2294 {
2295 HValue* src_index = AddUncasted<HAdd>(src_offset, index);
2296 HValue* value =
2297 AddUncasted<HSeqStringGetChar>(src_encoding, src, src_index);
2298 HValue* dst_index = AddUncasted<HAdd>(dst_offset, index);
2299 Add<HSeqStringSetChar>(dst_encoding, dst, dst_index, value);
2300 }
2301 loop.EndBody();
2302}

2305HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildObjectSizeAlignment(
2306 HValue* unaligned_size, int header_size) {
2307 DCHECK((header_size & kObjectAlignmentMask) == 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((header_size & kObjectAlignmentMask
) == 0)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2307
, "Check failed: %s.", "(header_size & kObjectAlignmentMask) == 0"
); } } while (0);
2308 HValue* size = AddUncasted<HAdd>(
2309 unaligned_size, Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(
2310 header_size + kObjectAlignmentMask)));
2311 size->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
2312 return AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2313 Token::BIT_AND, size, Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(
2314 ~kObjectAlignmentMask)));
2315}
2316
2317
2318HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildUncheckedStringAdd(
2319 HValue* left,
2320 HValue* right,
2321 HAllocationMode allocation_mode) {
2322 // Determine the string lengths.
2323 HValue* left_length = AddLoadStringLength(left);
2324 HValue* right_length = AddLoadStringLength(right);
2325
2326 // Compute the combined string length.
2327 HValue* length = BuildAddStringLengths(left_length, right_length);
2328
2329 // Do some manual constant folding here.
2330 if (left_length->IsConstant()) {
2331 HConstant* c_left_length = HConstant::cast(left_length);
2332 DCHECK_NE(0, c_left_length->Integer32Value())do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckNEImpl( (0), (c_left_length
->Integer32Value()), "0" " " "!=" " " "c_left_length->Integer32Value()"
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2332, "Check failed: %s."
, _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0);
2333 if (c_left_length->Integer32Value() + 1 >= ConsString::kMinLength) {
2334 // The right string contains at least one character.
2335 return BuildCreateConsString(length, left, right, allocation_mode);
2336 }
2337 } else if (right_length->IsConstant()) {
2338 HConstant* c_right_length = HConstant::cast(right_length);
2339 DCHECK_NE(0, c_right_length->Integer32Value())do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckNEImpl( (0), (c_right_length
->Integer32Value()), "0" " " "!=" " " "c_right_length->Integer32Value()"
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2339, "Check failed: %s."
, _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0);
2340 if (c_right_length->Integer32Value() + 1 >= ConsString::kMinLength) {
2341 // The left string contains at least one character.
2342 return BuildCreateConsString(length, left, right, allocation_mode);
2343 }
2344 }
2345
2346 // Check if we should create a cons string.
2347 IfBuilder if_createcons(this);
2348 if_createcons.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2349 length, Add<HConstant>(ConsString::kMinLength), Token::GTE);
2350 if_createcons.Then();
2351 {
2352 // Create a cons string.
2353 Push(BuildCreateConsString(length, left, right, allocation_mode));
2354 }
2355 if_createcons.Else();
2356 {
2357 // Determine the string instance types.
2358 HValue* left_instance_type = AddLoadStringInstanceType(left);
2359 HValue* right_instance_type = AddLoadStringInstanceType(right);
2360
2361 // Compute union and difference of instance types.
2362 HValue* ored_instance_types = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2363 Token::BIT_OR, left_instance_type, right_instance_type);
2364 HValue* xored_instance_types = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2365 Token::BIT_XOR, left_instance_type, right_instance_type);
2366
2367 // Check if both strings have the same encoding and both are
2368 // sequential.
2369 IfBuilder if_sameencodingandsequential(this);
2370 if_sameencodingandsequential.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2371 AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2372 Token::BIT_AND, xored_instance_types,
2373 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(kStringEncodingMask))),
2374 graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::EQ);
2375 if_sameencodingandsequential.And();
2376 STATIC_ASSERT(kSeqStringTag == 0)static_assert(kSeqStringTag == 0, "kSeqStringTag == 0");
2377 if_sameencodingandsequential.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2378 AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2379 Token::BIT_AND, ored_instance_types,
2380 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(kStringRepresentationMask))),
2381 graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::EQ);
2382 if_sameencodingandsequential.Then();
2383 {
2384 HConstant* string_map =
2385 Add<HConstant>(isolate()->factory()->string_map());
2386 HConstant* one_byte_string_map =
2387 Add<HConstant>(isolate()->factory()->one_byte_string_map());
2388
2389 // Determine map and size depending on whether result is one-byte string.
2390 IfBuilder if_onebyte(this);
2391 STATIC_ASSERT(kOneByteStringTag != 0)static_assert(kOneByteStringTag != 0, "kOneByteStringTag != 0"
);
2392 if_onebyte.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2393 AddUncasted<HBitwise>(
2394 Token::BIT_AND, ored_instance_types,
2395 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(kStringEncodingMask))),
2396 graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::NE);
2397 if_onebyte.Then();
2398 {
2399 // Allocate sequential one-byte string object.
2400 Push(length);
2401 Push(one_byte_string_map);
2402 }
2403 if_onebyte.Else();
2404 {
2405 // Allocate sequential two-byte string object.
2406 HValue* size = AddUncasted<HShl>(length, graph()->GetConstant1());
2407 size->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
2408 size->SetFlag(HValue::kUint32);
2409 Push(size);
2410 Push(string_map);
2411 }
2412 if_onebyte.End();
2413 HValue* map = Pop();
2414
2415 // Calculate the number of bytes needed for the characters in the
2416 // string while observing object alignment.
2417 STATIC_ASSERT((SeqString::kHeaderSize & kObjectAlignmentMask) == 0)static_assert((SeqString::kHeaderSize & kObjectAlignmentMask
) == 0, "(SeqString::kHeaderSize & kObjectAlignmentMask) == 0"
);
2418 HValue* size = BuildObjectSizeAlignment(Pop(), SeqString::kHeaderSize);
2419
2420 IfBuilder if_size(this);
2421 if_size.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2422 size, Add<HConstant>(Page::kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize), Token::LT);
2423 if_size.Then();
2424 {
2425 // Allocate the string object. HAllocate does not care whether we pass
2426 // STRING_TYPE or ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE here, so we just use STRING_TYPE.
2427 HAllocate* result =
2428 BuildAllocate(size, HType::String(), STRING_TYPE, allocation_mode);
2429 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForMap(), map);
2430
2431 // Initialize the string fields.
2432 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForStringHashField(),
2433 Add<HConstant>(String::kEmptyHashField));
2434 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForStringLength(), length);
2435
2436 // Copy characters to the result string.
2437 IfBuilder if_twobyte(this);
2438 if_twobyte.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(map, string_map);
2439 if_twobyte.Then();
2440 {
2441 // Copy characters from the left string.
2442 BuildCopySeqStringChars(
2443 left, graph()->GetConstant0(), String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING, result,
2444 graph()->GetConstant0(), String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING, left_length);
2445
2446 // Copy characters from the right string.
2447 BuildCopySeqStringChars(
2448 right, graph()->GetConstant0(), String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING, result,
2449 left_length, String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING, right_length);
2450 }
2451 if_twobyte.Else();
2452 {
2453 // Copy characters from the left string.
2454 BuildCopySeqStringChars(
2455 left, graph()->GetConstant0(), String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING, result,
2456 graph()->GetConstant0(), String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING, left_length);
2457
2458 // Copy characters from the right string.
2459 BuildCopySeqStringChars(
2460 right, graph()->GetConstant0(), String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING, result,
2461 left_length, String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING, right_length);
2462 }
2463 if_twobyte.End();
2464
2465 // Count the native string addition.
2466 AddIncrementCounter(isolate()->counters()->string_add_native());
2467
2468 // Return the sequential string.
2469 Push(result);
2470 }
2471 if_size.Else();
2472 {
2473 // Fallback to the runtime to add the two strings. The string has to be
2474 // allocated in LO space.
2475 Add<HPushArguments>(left, right);
2476 Push(Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kStringAdd), 2));
2477 }
2478 if_size.End();
2479 }
2480 if_sameencodingandsequential.Else();
2481 {
2482 // Fallback to the runtime to add the two strings.
2483 Add<HPushArguments>(left, right);
2484 Push(Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kStringAdd), 2));
2485 }
2486 if_sameencodingandsequential.End();
2487 }
2488 if_createcons.End();
2489
2490 return Pop();
2491}
2492
2493
2494HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildStringAdd(
2495 HValue* left,
2496 HValue* right,
2497 HAllocationMode allocation_mode) {
2498 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
2499
2500 // Determine string lengths.
2501 HValue* left_length = AddLoadStringLength(left);
2502 HValue* right_length = AddLoadStringLength(right);
2503
2504 // Check if left string is empty.
2505 IfBuilder if_leftempty(this);
2506 if_leftempty.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2507 left_length, graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::EQ);
2508 if_leftempty.Then();
2509 {
2510 // Count the native string addition.
2511 AddIncrementCounter(isolate()->counters()->string_add_native());
2512
2513 // Just return the right string.
2514 Push(right);
2515 }
2516 if_leftempty.Else();
2517 {
2518 // Check if right string is empty.
2519 IfBuilder if_rightempty(this);
2520 if_rightempty.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2521 right_length, graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::EQ);
2522 if_rightempty.Then();
2523 {
2524 // Count the native string addition.
2525 AddIncrementCounter(isolate()->counters()->string_add_native());
2526
2527 // Just return the left string.
2528 Push(left);
2529 }
2530 if_rightempty.Else();
2531 {
2532 // Add the two non-empty strings.
2533 Push(BuildUncheckedStringAdd(left, right, allocation_mode));
2534 }
2535 if_rightempty.End();
2536 }
2537 if_leftempty.End();
2538
2539 return Pop();
2540}

2542
2543HInstruction* HGraphBuilder::BuildUncheckedMonomorphicElementAccess(
2544 HValue* checked_object,
2545 HValue* key,
2546 HValue* val,
2547 bool is_js_array,
2548 ElementsKind elements_kind,
2549 PropertyAccessType access_type,
2550 LoadKeyedHoleMode load_mode,
2551 KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode) {
2552 DCHECK(top_info()->IsStub() || checked_object->IsCompareMap() ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(top_info()->IsStub() || checked_object
->IsCompareMap() || checked_object->IsCheckMaps())), 0)
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2553, "Check failed: %s."
, "top_info()->IsStub() || checked_object->IsCompareMap() || checked_object->IsCheckMaps()"
); } } while (0)
2553 checked_object->IsCheckMaps())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(top_info()->IsStub() || checked_object
->IsCompareMap() || checked_object->IsCheckMaps())), 0)
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2553, "Check failed: %s."
, "top_info()->IsStub() || checked_object->IsCompareMap() || checked_object->IsCheckMaps()"
); } } while (0);
2554 DCHECK(!IsFixedTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind) || !is_js_array)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!IsFixedTypedArrayElementsKind
(elements_kind) || !is_js_array)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 2554, "Check failed: %s.", "!IsFixedTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind) || !is_js_array"
); } } while (0);
2555 // No GVNFlag is necessary for ElementsKind if there is an explicit dependency
2556 // on a HElementsTransition instruction. The flag can also be removed if the
2557 // map to check has FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS, since there can be no further
2558 // ElementsKind transitions. Finally, the dependency can be removed for stores
2559 // for FAST_ELEMENTS, since a transition to HOLEY elements won't change the
2560 // generated store code.
2561 if ((elements_kind == FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS) ||
2562 (elements_kind == FAST_ELEMENTS && access_type == STORE)) {
2563 checked_object->ClearDependsOnFlag(kElementsKind);
2564 }
2565
2566 bool fast_smi_only_elements = IsFastSmiElementsKind(elements_kind);
2567 bool fast_elements = IsFastObjectElementsKind(elements_kind);
2568 HValue* elements = AddLoadElements(checked_object);
2569 if (access_type == STORE && (fast_elements || fast_smi_only_elements) &&
2570 store_mode != STORE_NO_TRANSITION_HANDLE_COW) {
2571 HCheckMaps* check_cow_map = Add<HCheckMaps>(
2572 elements, isolate()->factory()->fixed_array_map());
2573 check_cow_map->ClearDependsOnFlag(kElementsKind);
2574 }
2575 HInstruction* length = NULL__null;
2576 if (is_js_array) {
2577 length = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
2578 checked_object->ActualValue(), checked_object,
2579 HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(elements_kind));
2580 } else {
2581 length = AddLoadFixedArrayLength(elements);
2582 }
2583 length->set_type(HType::Smi());
2584 HValue* checked_key = NULL__null;
2585 if (IsFixedTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
2586 checked_object = Add<HCheckArrayBufferNotNeutered>(checked_object);
2587
2588 HValue* external_pointer = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
2589 elements, nullptr,
2590 HObjectAccess::ForFixedTypedArrayBaseExternalPointer());
2591 HValue* base_pointer = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
2592 elements, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForFixedTypedArrayBaseBasePointer());
2593 HValue* backing_store = AddUncasted<HAdd>(external_pointer, base_pointer,
2594 AddOfExternalAndTagged);
2595
2596 if (store_mode == STORE_NO_TRANSITION_IGNORE_OUT_OF_BOUNDS) {
2597 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
2598 IfBuilder length_checker(this);
2599 length_checker.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(key, length, Token::LT);
2600 length_checker.Then();
2601 IfBuilder negative_checker(this);
2602 HValue* bounds_check = negative_checker.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
2603 key, graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::GTE);
2604 negative_checker.Then();
2605 HInstruction* result = AddElementAccess(
2606 backing_store, key, val, bounds_check, checked_object->ActualValue(),
2607 elements_kind, access_type);
2608 negative_checker.ElseDeopt(Deoptimizer::kNegativeKeyEncountered);
2609 negative_checker.End();
2610 length_checker.End();
2611 return result;
2612 } else {
2613 DCHECK(store_mode == STANDARD_STORE)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(store_mode == STANDARD_STORE)
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2613, "Check failed: %s."
, "store_mode == STANDARD_STORE"); } } while (0);
2614 checked_key = Add<HBoundsCheck>(key, length);
2615 return AddElementAccess(backing_store, checked_key, val, checked_object,
2616 checked_object->ActualValue(), elements_kind,
2617 access_type);
2618 }
2619 }
2620 DCHECK(fast_smi_only_elements ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(fast_smi_only_elements || fast_elements
|| IsFastDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind))), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2622, "Check failed: %s.", "fast_smi_only_elements || fast_elements || IsFastDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)"
); } } while (0)
2621 fast_elements ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(fast_smi_only_elements || fast_elements
|| IsFastDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind))), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2622, "Check failed: %s.", "fast_smi_only_elements || fast_elements || IsFastDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)"
); } } while (0)
2622 IsFastDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(fast_smi_only_elements || fast_elements
|| IsFastDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind))), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2622, "Check failed: %s.", "fast_smi_only_elements || fast_elements || IsFastDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)"
); } } while (0);
2623
2624 // In case val is stored into a fast smi array, assure that the value is a smi
2625 // before manipulating the backing store. Otherwise the actual store may
2626 // deopt, leaving the backing store in an invalid state.
2627 if (access_type == STORE && IsFastSmiElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
2628 !val->type().IsSmi()) {
2629 val = AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(val, Representation::Smi());
2630 }
2631
2632 if (IsGrowStoreMode(store_mode)) {
2633 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
2634 Representation representation = HStoreKeyed::RequiredValueRepresentation(
2635 elements_kind, STORE_TO_INITIALIZED_ENTRY);
2636 val = AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(val, representation);
2637 elements = BuildCheckForCapacityGrow(checked_object, elements,
2638 elements_kind, length, key,
2639 is_js_array, access_type);
2640 checked_key = key;
2641 } else {
2642 checked_key = Add<HBoundsCheck>(key, length);
2643
2644 if (access_type == STORE && (fast_elements || fast_smi_only_elements)) {
2645 if (store_mode == STORE_NO_TRANSITION_HANDLE_COW) {
2646 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
2647 elements = BuildCopyElementsOnWrite(checked_object, elements,
2648 elements_kind, length);
2649 } else {
2650 HCheckMaps* check_cow_map = Add<HCheckMaps>(
2651 elements, isolate()->factory()->fixed_array_map());
2652 check_cow_map->ClearDependsOnFlag(kElementsKind);
2653 }
2654 }
2655 }
2656 return AddElementAccess(elements, checked_key, val, checked_object, nullptr,
2657 elements_kind, access_type, load_mode);
2658}

2660
2661HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildAllocateArrayFromLength(
2662 JSArrayBuilder* array_builder,
2663 HValue* length_argument) {
2664 if (length_argument->IsConstant() &&
2665 HConstant::cast(length_argument)->HasSmiValue()) {
2666 int array_length = HConstant::cast(length_argument)->Integer32Value();
2667 if (array_length == 0) {
2668 return array_builder->AllocateEmptyArray();
2669 } else {
2670 return array_builder->AllocateArray(length_argument,
2671 array_length,
2672 length_argument);
2673 }
2674 }
2675
2676 HValue* constant_zero = graph()->GetConstant0();
2677 HConstant* max_alloc_length =
2678 Add<HConstant>(JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray);
2679 HInstruction* checked_length = Add<HBoundsCheck>(length_argument,
2680 max_alloc_length);
2681 IfBuilder if_builder(this);
2682 if_builder.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(checked_length, constant_zero,
2683 Token::EQ);
2684 if_builder.Then();
2685 const int initial_capacity = JSArray::kPreallocatedArrayElements;
2686 HConstant* initial_capacity_node = Add<HConstant>(initial_capacity);
2687 Push(initial_capacity_node); // capacity
2688 Push(constant_zero); // length
2689 if_builder.Else();
2690 if (!(top_info()->IsStub()) &&
2691 IsFastPackedElementsKind(array_builder->kind())) {
2692 // We'll come back later with better (holey) feedback.
2693 if_builder.Deopt(
2694 Deoptimizer::kHoleyArrayDespitePackedElements_kindFeedback);
2695 } else {
2696 Push(checked_length); // capacity
2697 Push(checked_length); // length
2698 }
2699 if_builder.End();
2700
2701 // Figure out total size
2702 HValue* length = Pop();
2703 HValue* capacity = Pop();
2704 return array_builder->AllocateArray(capacity, max_alloc_length, length);
2705}

2707
2708HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildCalculateElementsSize(ElementsKind kind,
2709 HValue* capacity) {
2710 int elements_size = IsFastDoubleElementsKind(kind)
2711 ? kDoubleSize
2712 : kPointerSize;
2713
2714 HConstant* elements_size_value = Add<HConstant>(elements_size);
2715 HInstruction* mul =
2716 HMul::NewImul(isolate(), zone(), context(), capacity->ActualValue(),
2717 elements_size_value);
2718 AddInstruction(mul);
2719 mul->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
2720
2721 STATIC_ASSERT(FixedDoubleArray::kHeaderSize == FixedArray::kHeaderSize)static_assert(FixedDoubleArray::kHeaderSize == FixedArray::kHeaderSize
, "FixedDoubleArray::kHeaderSize == FixedArray::kHeaderSize");
2722
2723 HConstant* header_size = Add<HConstant>(FixedArray::kHeaderSize);
2724 HValue* total_size = AddUncasted<HAdd>(mul, header_size);
2725 total_size->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
2726 return total_size;
2727}

2777HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildAllocateAndInitializeArray(ElementsKind kind,
2778 HValue* capacity) {
2779 // The HForceRepresentation is to prevent possible deopt on int-smi
2780 // conversion after allocation but before the new object fields are set.
2781 capacity = AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(capacity, Representation::Smi());
2782 HValue* size_in_bytes = BuildCalculateElementsSize(kind, capacity);
2783 HValue* new_array = BuildAllocateElements(kind, size_in_bytes);
2784 BuildInitializeElementsHeader(new_array, kind, capacity);
2785 return new_array;
2786}

2789void HGraphBuilder::BuildJSArrayHeader(HValue* array,
2790 HValue* array_map,
2791 HValue* elements,
2792 AllocationSiteMode mode,
2793 ElementsKind elements_kind,
2794 HValue* allocation_site_payload,
2795 HValue* length_field) {
2796 Add<HStoreNamedField>(array, HObjectAccess::ForMap(), array_map);
2797
2798 HConstant* empty_fixed_array =
2799 Add<HConstant>(isolate()->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
2800
2801 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
2802 array, HObjectAccess::ForPropertiesPointer(), empty_fixed_array);
2803
2804 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
2805 array, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(),
2806 elements != NULL__null ? elements : empty_fixed_array);
2807
2808 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
2809 array, HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(elements_kind), length_field);
2810
2811 if (mode == TRACK_ALLOCATION_SITE) {
2812 BuildCreateAllocationMemento(
2813 array, Add<HConstant>(JSArray::kSize), allocation_site_payload);
2814 }
2815}

2818HInstruction* HGraphBuilder::AddElementAccess(
2819 HValue* elements, HValue* checked_key, HValue* val, HValue* dependency,
2820 HValue* backing_store_owner, ElementsKind elements_kind,
2821 PropertyAccessType access_type, LoadKeyedHoleMode load_mode) {
2822 if (access_type == STORE) {
2823 DCHECK(val != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(val != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2823, "Check failed: %s.", "val != __null"
); } } while (0);
2824 if (elements_kind == UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS) {
2825 val = Add<HClampToUint8>(val);
2826 }
2827 return Add<HStoreKeyed>(elements, checked_key, val, backing_store_owner,
2828 elements_kind, STORE_TO_INITIALIZED_ENTRY);
2829 }
2830
2831 DCHECK(access_type == LOAD)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(access_type == LOAD)), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2831, "Check failed: %s."
, "access_type == LOAD"); } } while (0);
2832 DCHECK(val == NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(val == __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 2832, "Check failed: %s.", "val == __null"
); } } while (0);
2833 HLoadKeyed* load =
2834 Add<HLoadKeyed>(elements, checked_key, dependency, backing_store_owner,
2835 elements_kind, load_mode);
2836 if (elements_kind == UINT32_ELEMENTS) {
2837 graph()->RecordUint32Instruction(load);
2838 }
2839 return load;
2840}

2871
2872HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildNewElementsCapacity(HValue* old_capacity) {
2873 HValue* half_old_capacity = AddUncasted<HShr>(old_capacity,
2874 graph_->GetConstant1());
2875
2876 HValue* new_capacity = AddUncasted<HAdd>(half_old_capacity, old_capacity);
2877 new_capacity->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
2878
2879 HValue* min_growth = Add<HConstant>(16);
2880
2881 new_capacity = AddUncasted<HAdd>(new_capacity, min_growth);
2882 new_capacity->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
2883
2884 return new_capacity;
2885}

2887
2888HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildGrowElementsCapacity(HValue* object,
2889 HValue* elements,
2890 ElementsKind kind,
2891 ElementsKind new_kind,
2892 HValue* length,
2893 HValue* new_capacity) {
2894 Add<HBoundsCheck>(new_capacity, Add<HConstant>(
2895 (Page::kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize - FixedArray::kHeaderSize) >>
2896 ElementsKindToShiftSize(new_kind)));
2897
2898 HValue* new_elements =
2899 BuildAllocateAndInitializeArray(new_kind, new_capacity);
2900
2901 BuildCopyElements(elements, kind, new_elements,
2902 new_kind, length, new_capacity);
2903
2904 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(),
2905 new_elements);
2906
2907 return new_elements;
2908}

2910
2911void HGraphBuilder::BuildFillElementsWithValue(HValue* elements,
2912 ElementsKind elements_kind,
2913 HValue* from,
2914 HValue* to,
2915 HValue* value) {
2916 if (to == NULL__null) {
2917 to = AddLoadFixedArrayLength(elements);
2918 }
2919
2920 // Special loop unfolding case
2921 STATIC_ASSERT(JSArray::kPreallocatedArrayElements <=static_assert(JSArray::kPreallocatedArrayElements <= kElementLoopUnrollThreshold
, "JSArray::kPreallocatedArrayElements <= kElementLoopUnrollThreshold"
)
2922 kElementLoopUnrollThreshold)static_assert(JSArray::kPreallocatedArrayElements <= kElementLoopUnrollThreshold
, "JSArray::kPreallocatedArrayElements <= kElementLoopUnrollThreshold"
);
2923 int initial_capacity = -1;
2924 if (from->IsInteger32Constant() && to->IsInteger32Constant()) {
2925 int constant_from = from->GetInteger32Constant();
2926 int constant_to = to->GetInteger32Constant();
2927
2928 if (constant_from == 0 && constant_to <= kElementLoopUnrollThreshold) {
2929 initial_capacity = constant_to;
2930 }
2931 }
2932
2933 if (initial_capacity >= 0) {
2934 for (int i = 0; i < initial_capacity; i++) {
2935 HInstruction* key = Add<HConstant>(i);
2936 Add<HStoreKeyed>(elements, key, value, nullptr, elements_kind);
2937 }
2938 } else {
2939 // Carefully loop backwards so that the "from" remains live through the loop
2940 // rather than the to. This often corresponds to keeping length live rather
2941 // then capacity, which helps register allocation, since length is used more
2942 // other than capacity after filling with holes.
2943 LoopBuilder builder(this, context(), LoopBuilder::kPostDecrement);
2944
2945 HValue* key = builder.BeginBody(to, from, Token::GT);
2946
2947 HValue* adjusted_key = AddUncasted<HSub>(key, graph()->GetConstant1());
2948 adjusted_key->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
2949
2950 Add<HStoreKeyed>(elements, adjusted_key, value, nullptr, elements_kind);
2951
2952 builder.EndBody();
2953 }
2954}
2955
2956
2957void HGraphBuilder::BuildFillElementsWithHole(HValue* elements,
2958 ElementsKind elements_kind,
2959 HValue* from,
2960 HValue* to) {
2961 // Fast elements kinds need to be initialized in case statements below cause a
2962 // garbage collection.
2963
2964 HValue* hole = IsFastSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind)
2965 ? graph()->GetConstantHole()
2966 : Add<HConstant>(HConstant::kHoleNaN);
2967
2968 // Since we're about to store a hole value, the store instruction below must
2969 // assume an elements kind that supports heap object values.
2970 if (IsFastSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
2971 elements_kind = FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS;
2972 }
2973
2974 BuildFillElementsWithValue(elements, elements_kind, from, to, hole);
2975}
2976
2977
2978void HGraphBuilder::BuildCopyProperties(HValue* from_properties,
2979 HValue* to_properties, HValue* length,
2980 HValue* capacity) {
2981 ElementsKind kind = FAST_ELEMENTS;
2982
2983 BuildFillElementsWithValue(to_properties, kind, length, capacity,
2984 graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
2985
2986 LoopBuilder builder(this, context(), LoopBuilder::kPostDecrement);
2987
2988 HValue* key = builder.BeginBody(length, graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::GT);
2989
2990 key = AddUncasted<HSub>(key, graph()->GetConstant1());
2991 key->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
2992
2993 HValue* element =
2994 Add<HLoadKeyed>(from_properties, key, nullptr, nullptr, kind);
2995
2996 Add<HStoreKeyed>(to_properties, key, element, nullptr, kind);
2997
2998 builder.EndBody();
2999}
3000
3001
3002void HGraphBuilder::BuildCopyElements(HValue* from_elements,
3003 ElementsKind from_elements_kind,
3004 HValue* to_elements,
3005 ElementsKind to_elements_kind,
3006 HValue* length,
3007 HValue* capacity) {
3008 int constant_capacity = -1;
3009 if (capacity != NULL__null &&
3010 capacity->IsConstant() &&
3011 HConstant::cast(capacity)->HasInteger32Value()) {
3012 int constant_candidate = HConstant::cast(capacity)->Integer32Value();
3013 if (constant_candidate <= kElementLoopUnrollThreshold) {
3014 constant_capacity = constant_candidate;
3015 }
3016 }
3017
3018 bool pre_fill_with_holes =
3019 IsFastDoubleElementsKind(from_elements_kind) &&
3020 IsFastObjectElementsKind(to_elements_kind);
3021 if (pre_fill_with_holes) {
3022 // If the copy might trigger a GC, make sure that the FixedArray is
3023 // pre-initialized with holes to make sure that it's always in a
3024 // consistent state.
3025 BuildFillElementsWithHole(to_elements, to_elements_kind,
3026 graph()->GetConstant0(), NULL__null);
3027 }
3028
3029 if (constant_capacity != -1) {
3030 // Unroll the loop for small elements kinds.
3031 for (int i = 0; i < constant_capacity; i++) {
3032 HValue* key_constant = Add<HConstant>(i);
3033 HInstruction* value = Add<HLoadKeyed>(
3034 from_elements, key_constant, nullptr, nullptr, from_elements_kind);
3035 Add<HStoreKeyed>(to_elements, key_constant, value, nullptr,
3036 to_elements_kind);
3037 }
3038 } else {
3039 if (!pre_fill_with_holes &&
3040 (capacity == NULL__null || !length->Equals(capacity))) {
3041 BuildFillElementsWithHole(to_elements, to_elements_kind,
3042 length, NULL__null);
3043 }
3044
3045 LoopBuilder builder(this, context(), LoopBuilder::kPostDecrement);
3046
3047 HValue* key = builder.BeginBody(length, graph()->GetConstant0(),
3048 Token::GT);
3049
3050 key = AddUncasted<HSub>(key, graph()->GetConstant1());
3051 key->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
3052
3053 HValue* element = Add<HLoadKeyed>(from_elements, key, nullptr, nullptr,
3054 from_elements_kind, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
3055
3056 ElementsKind kind = (IsHoleyElementsKind(from_elements_kind) &&
3057 IsFastSmiElementsKind(to_elements_kind))
3058 ? FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS : to_elements_kind;
3059
3060 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(from_elements_kind) &&
3061 from_elements_kind != to_elements_kind) {
3062 IfBuilder if_hole(this);
3063 if_hole.If<HCompareHoleAndBranch>(element);
3064 if_hole.Then();
3065 HConstant* hole_constant = IsFastDoubleElementsKind(to_elements_kind)
3066 ? Add<HConstant>(HConstant::kHoleNaN)
3067 : graph()->GetConstantHole();
3068 Add<HStoreKeyed>(to_elements, key, hole_constant, nullptr, kind);
3069 if_hole.Else();
3070 HStoreKeyed* store =
3071 Add<HStoreKeyed>(to_elements, key, element, nullptr, kind);
3072 store->SetFlag(HValue::kAllowUndefinedAsNaN);
3073 if_hole.End();
3074 } else {
3075 HStoreKeyed* store =
3076 Add<HStoreKeyed>(to_elements, key, element, nullptr, kind);
3077 store->SetFlag(HValue::kAllowUndefinedAsNaN);
3078 }
3079
3080 builder.EndBody();
3081 }
3082
3083 Counters* counters = isolate()->counters();
3084 AddIncrementCounter(counters->inlined_copied_elements());
3085}

3097

3099 map,
3100 elements,
3101 mode,
3102 FAST_ELEMENTS,
3103 allocation_site,

3109HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildCloneShallowArrayEmpty(HValue* boilerplate,
3110 HValue* allocation_site,
3111 AllocationSiteMode mode) {

3113
3114 HValue* map = AddLoadMap(boilerplate);
3115
3116 BuildJSArrayHeader(array,
3117 map,

3119 mode,

3125
3126
3127HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildCloneShallowArrayNonEmpty(HValue* boilerplate,
3128 HValue* allocation_site,
3129 AllocationSiteMode mode,
3130 ElementsKind kind) {
3131 HValue* boilerplate_elements = AddLoadElements(boilerplate);
3132 HValue* capacity = AddLoadFixedArrayLength(boilerplate_elements);
3133
3134 // Generate size calculation code here in order to make it dominate
3135 // the JSArray allocation.
3136 HValue* elements_size = BuildCalculateElementsSize(kind, capacity);
3137
3138 // Create empty JSArray object for now, store elimination should remove
3139 // redundant initialization of elements and length fields and at the same
3140 // time the object will be fully prepared for GC if it happens during
3141 // elements allocation.
3142 HValue* result = BuildCloneShallowArrayEmpty(
3143 boilerplate, allocation_site, mode);
3144
3145 HAllocate* elements = BuildAllocateElements(kind, elements_size);
3146
3147 // This function implicitly relies on the fact that the
3148 // FastCloneShallowArrayStub is called only for literals shorter than
3149 // JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray.
3150 // Can't add HBoundsCheck here because otherwise the stub will eager a frame.
3151 HConstant* size_upper_bound = EstablishElementsAllocationSize(
3152 kind, JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray);
3153 elements->set_size_upper_bound(size_upper_bound);
3154
3155 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(), elements);
3156
3157 // The allocation for the cloned array above causes register pressure on
3158 // machines with low register counts. Force a reload of the boilerplate
3159 // elements here to free up a register for the allocation to avoid unnecessary
3160 // spillage.
3161 boilerplate_elements = AddLoadElements(boilerplate);
3162 boilerplate_elements->SetFlag(HValue::kCantBeReplaced);
3163
3164 // Copy the elements array header.
3165 for (int i = 0; i < FixedArrayBase::kHeaderSize; i += kPointerSize) {
3166 HObjectAccess access = HObjectAccess::ForFixedArrayHeader(i);
3167 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
3168 elements, access,
3169 Add<HLoadNamedField>(boilerplate_elements, nullptr, access));
3170 }
3171
3172 // And the result of the length
3173 HValue* length = AddLoadArrayLength(boilerplate, kind);
3174 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(kind), length);
3175
3176 BuildCopyElements(boilerplate_elements, kind, elements,
3177 kind, length, NULL__null);
3178 return result;
3179}
3180
3181
3182void HGraphBuilder::BuildCompareNil(HValue* value, Type* type,
3183 HIfContinuation* continuation,
3184 MapEmbedding map_embedding) {
3185 IfBuilder if_nil(this);
3186
3187 if (type->Maybe(Type::Undetectable())) {
3188 if_nil.If<HIsUndetectableAndBranch>(value);
3189 } else {
3190 bool maybe_null = type->Maybe(Type::Null());
3191 if (maybe_null) {
3192 if_nil.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(value, graph()->GetConstantNull());
3193 }
3194
3195 if (type->Maybe(Type::Undefined())) {
3196 if (maybe_null) if_nil.Or();
3197 if_nil.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(value,
3198 graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
3199 }
3200
3201 if_nil.Then();
3202 if_nil.Else();
3203
3204 if (type->NumClasses() == 1) {
3205 BuildCheckHeapObject(value);
3206 // For ICs, the map checked below is a sentinel map that gets replaced by
3207 // the monomorphic map when the code is used as a template to generate a
3208 // new IC. For optimized functions, there is no sentinel map, the map
3209 // emitted below is the actual monomorphic map.
3210 if (map_embedding == kEmbedMapsViaWeakCells) {
3211 HValue* cell =
3212 Add<HConstant>(Map::WeakCellForMap(type->Classes().Current()));
3213 HValue* expected_map = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
3214 cell, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForWeakCellValue());
3215 HValue* map =
3216 Add<HLoadNamedField>(value, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMap());
3217 IfBuilder map_check(this);
3218 map_check.IfNot<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(expected_map, map);
3219 map_check.ThenDeopt(Deoptimizer::kUnknownMap);
3220 map_check.End();
3221 } else {
3222 DCHECK(map_embedding == kEmbedMapsDirectly)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(map_embedding == kEmbedMapsDirectly
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3222, "Check failed: %s."
, "map_embedding == kEmbedMapsDirectly"); } } while (0);
3223 Add<HCheckMaps>(value, type->Classes().Current());
3224 }
3225 } else {
3226 if_nil.Deopt(Deoptimizer::kTooManyUndetectableTypes);
3227 }
3228 }
3229
3230 if_nil.CaptureContinuation(continuation);
3231}

3234void HGraphBuilder::BuildCreateAllocationMemento(
3235 HValue* previous_object,
3236 HValue* previous_object_size,
3237 HValue* allocation_site) {
3238 DCHECK(allocation_site != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(allocation_site != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3238, "Check failed: %s."
, "allocation_site != __null"); } } while (0);
3239 HInnerAllocatedObject* allocation_memento = Add<HInnerAllocatedObject>(
3240 previous_object, previous_object_size, HType::HeapObject());
3241 AddStoreMapConstant(
3242 allocation_memento, isolate()->factory()->allocation_memento_map());
3243 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
3244 allocation_memento,
3245 HObjectAccess::ForAllocationMementoSite(),
3246 allocation_site);
3247 if (FLAG_allocation_site_pretenuring) {
3248 HValue* memento_create_count =
3249 Add<HLoadNamedField>(allocation_site, nullptr,
3250 HObjectAccess::ForAllocationSiteOffset(
3251 AllocationSite::kPretenureCreateCountOffset));
3252 memento_create_count = AddUncasted<HAdd>(
3253 memento_create_count, graph()->GetConstant1());
3254 // This smi value is reset to zero after every gc, overflow isn't a problem
3255 // since the counter is bounded by the new space size.
3256 memento_create_count->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
3257 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
3258 allocation_site, HObjectAccess::ForAllocationSiteOffset(
3259 AllocationSite::kPretenureCreateCountOffset), memento_create_count);
3260 }
3261}

3290
3291HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildGetParentContext(HValue* depth, int depth_value) {
3292 HValue* script_context = context();
3293 if (depth != NULL__null) {
3294 HValue* zero = graph()->GetConstant0();
3295
3296 Push(script_context);
3297 Push(depth);
3298
3299 LoopBuilder loop(this);
3300 loop.BeginBody(2); // Drop script_context and depth from last environment
3301 // to appease live range building without simulates.
3302 depth = Pop();
3303 script_context = Pop();
3304
3305 script_context = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
3306 script_context, nullptr,
3307 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
3308 depth = AddUncasted<HSub>(depth, graph()->GetConstant1());
3309 depth->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
3310
3311 IfBuilder if_break(this);
3312 if_break.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch, HValue*>(depth, zero, Token::EQ);
3313 if_break.Then();
3314 {
3315 Push(script_context); // The result.
3316 loop.Break();
3317 }
3318 if_break.Else();
3319 {
3320 Push(script_context);
3321 Push(depth);
3322 }
3323 loop.EndBody();
3324 if_break.End();
3325
3326 script_context = Pop();
3327 } else if (depth_value > 0) {
3328 // Unroll the above loop.
3329 for (int i = 0; i < depth_value; i++) {
3330 script_context = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
3331 script_context, nullptr,
3332 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
3333 }
3334 }
3335 return script_context;
3336}

3347
3348HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildArrayBufferViewFieldAccessor(HValue* object,
3349 HValue* checked_object,
3350 FieldIndex index) {
3351 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
3352 HObjectAccess access = HObjectAccess::ForObservableJSObjectOffset(
3353 index.offset(), Representation::Tagged());
3354 HInstruction* buffer = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
3355 object, checked_object, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer());
3356 HInstruction* field = Add<HLoadNamedField>(object, checked_object, access);
3357
3358 HInstruction* flags = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
3359 buffer, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferBitField());
3360 HValue* was_neutered_mask =
3361 Add<HConstant>(1 << JSArrayBuffer::WasNeutered::kShift);
3362 HValue* was_neutered_test =
3363 AddUncasted<HBitwise>(Token::BIT_AND, flags, was_neutered_mask);
3364
3365 IfBuilder if_was_neutered(this);
3366 if_was_neutered.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
3367 was_neutered_test, graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::NE);
3368 if_was_neutered.Then();
3369 Push(graph()->GetConstant0());
3370 if_was_neutered.Else();
3371 Push(field);
3372 if_was_neutered.End();
3373
3374 return Pop();
3375}

3406
3407HValue* HGraphBuilder::JSArrayBuilder::EmitMapCode() {
3408 if (!builder()->top_info()->IsStub()) {
3409 // A constant map is fine.
3410 Handle<Map> map(builder()->isolate()->get_initial_js_array_map(kind_),
3411 builder()->isolate());
3412 return builder()->Add<HConstant>(map);
3413 }
3414
3415 if (constructor_function_ != NULL__null && kind_ == GetInitialFastElementsKind()) {
3416 // No need for a context lookup if the kind_ matches the initial
3417 // map, because we can just load the map in that case.
3418 HObjectAccess access = HObjectAccess::ForPrototypeOrInitialMap();
3419 return builder()->Add<HLoadNamedField>(constructor_function_, nullptr,
3420 access);
3421 }
3422
3423 // TODO(mvstanton): we should always have a constructor function if we
3424 // are creating a stub.
3425 HInstruction* native_context = constructor_function_ != NULL__null
3426 ? builder()->BuildGetNativeContext(constructor_function_)
3427 : builder()->BuildGetNativeContext();
3428
3429 HObjectAccess access =
3430 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::ArrayMapIndex(kind_));
3431 return builder()->Add<HLoadNamedField>(native_context, nullptr, access);
3432}

3437 HObjectAccess access = HObjectAccess::ForPrototypeOrInitialMap();
3438 return builder()->Add<HLoadNamedField>(constructor_function_, nullptr,
3439 access);
3440}

3462
3463HAllocate* HGraphBuilder::JSArrayBuilder::AllocateArray(
3464 HValue* capacity,
3465 int capacity_upper_bound,
3466 HValue* length_field,
3467 FillMode fill_mode) {
3468 HConstant* elememts_size_upper_bound = capacity->IsInteger32Constant()
3469 ? HConstant::cast(capacity)
3470 : builder()->EstablishElementsAllocationSize(kind_, capacity_upper_bound);
3471
3472 HAllocate* array = AllocateArray(capacity, length_field, fill_mode);
3473 if (!elements_location_->has_size_upper_bound()) {
3474 elements_location_->set_size_upper_bound(elememts_size_upper_bound);
3475 }
3476 return array;
3477}
3478
3479
3480HAllocate* HGraphBuilder::JSArrayBuilder::AllocateArray(
3481 HValue* capacity,
3482 HValue* length_field,
3483 FillMode fill_mode) {
3484 // These HForceRepresentations are because we store these as fields in the
3485 // objects we construct, and an int32-to-smi HChange could deopt. Accept
3486 // the deopt possibility now, before allocation occurs.
3487 capacity =
3488 builder()->AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(capacity,
3489 Representation::Smi());
3490 length_field =
3491 builder()->AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(length_field,
3492 Representation::Smi());
3493
3494 // Generate size calculation code here in order to make it dominate
3495 // the JSArray allocation.
3496 HValue* elements_size =
3497 builder()->BuildCalculateElementsSize(kind_, capacity);
3498
3499 // Bail out for large objects.
3500 HValue* max_regular_heap_object_size =
3501 builder()->Add<HConstant>(Page::kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize);
3502 builder()->Add<HBoundsCheck>(elements_size, max_regular_heap_object_size);
3503
3504 // Allocate (dealing with failure appropriately)
3505 HAllocate* array_object = builder()->AllocateJSArrayObject(mode_);
3506
3507 // Fill in the fields: map, properties, length
3508 HValue* map;
3509 if (allocation_site_payload_ == NULL__null) {
3510 map = EmitInternalMapCode();
3511 } else {
3512 map = EmitMapCode();
3513 }
3514
3515 builder()->BuildJSArrayHeader(array_object,
3516 map,
3517 NULL__null, // set elements to empty fixed array
3518 mode_,
3519 kind_,
3520 allocation_site_payload_,
3521 length_field);
3522
3523 // Allocate and initialize the elements
3524 elements_location_ = builder()->BuildAllocateElements(kind_, elements_size);
3525
3526 builder()->BuildInitializeElementsHeader(elements_location_, kind_, capacity);
3527
3528 // Set the elements
3529 builder()->Add<HStoreNamedField>(
3530 array_object, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(), elements_location_);
3531
3532 if (fill_mode == FILL_WITH_HOLE) {
3533 builder()->BuildFillElementsWithHole(elements_location_, kind_,
3534 graph()->GetConstant0(), capacity);
3535 }
3536
3537 return array_object;
3538}

3548HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HOptimizedGraphBuilder(CompilationInfo* info)
3549 : HGraphBuilder(info, CallInterfaceDescriptor()),

3568HBasicBlock* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::CreateJoin(HBasicBlock* first,
3569 HBasicBlock* second,
3570 BailoutId join_id) {
3571 if (first == NULL__null) {
3572 return second;
3573 } else if (second == NULL__null) {
3574 return first;
3575 } else {
3576 HBasicBlock* join_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
3577 Goto(first, join_block);
3578 Goto(second, join_block);
3579 join_block->SetJoinId(join_id);
3580 return join_block;
3581 }
3582}

3585HBasicBlock* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::JoinContinue(IterationStatement* statement,
3586 HBasicBlock* exit_block,
3587 HBasicBlock* continue_block) {
3588 if (continue_block != NULL__null) {
3589 if (exit_block != NULL__null) Goto(exit_block, continue_block);
3590 continue_block->SetJoinId(statement->ContinueId());
3591 return continue_block;
3592 }
3593 return exit_block;
3594}

3596
3597HBasicBlock* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::CreateLoop(IterationStatement* statement,
3598 HBasicBlock* loop_entry,
3599 HBasicBlock* body_exit,
3600 HBasicBlock* loop_successor,
3601 HBasicBlock* break_block) {
3602 if (body_exit != NULL__null) Goto(body_exit, loop_entry);
3603 loop_entry->PostProcessLoopHeader(statement);
3604 if (break_block != NULL__null) {
3605 if (loop_successor != NULL__null) Goto(loop_successor, break_block);
3606 break_block->SetJoinId(statement->ExitId());
3607 return break_block;
3608 }
3609 return loop_successor;
3610}

3659 maximum_environment_size_(0),
3660 no_side_effects_scope_count_(0),
3661 disallow_adding_new_values_(false) {
3662 if (info->IsStub()) {
3663 // For stubs, explicitly add the context to the environment.
3664 start_environment_ = new (zone_)
3665 HEnvironment(zone_, descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount() + 1);
3666 } else {
3667 if (info->is_tracking_positions()) {
3668 info->TraceInlinedFunction(info->shared_info(), SourcePosition::Unknown(),
3669 InlinedFunctionInfo::kNoParentId);
3670 }
3671 start_environment_ =
3672 new(zone_) HEnvironment(NULL__null, info->scope(), info->closure(), zone_);
3673 }
3674 start_environment_->set_ast_id(BailoutId::FunctionContext());
3675 entry_block_ = CreateBasicBlock();
3676 entry_block_->SetInitialEnvironment(start_environment_);
3677}
3678
3679
3680HBasicBlock* HGraph::CreateBasicBlock() {
3681 HBasicBlock* result = new(zone()) HBasicBlock(this);
3682 blocks_.Add(result, zone());
3683 return result;
3684}

3686
3687void HGraph::FinalizeUniqueness() {
3688 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
3689 for (int i = 0; i < blocks()->length(); ++i) {
3690 for (HInstructionIterator it(blocks()->at(i)); !it.Done(); it.Advance()) {
3691 it.Current()->FinalizeUniqueness();
3692 }
3693 }
3694}
