3696
3697int HGraph::SourcePositionToScriptPosition(SourcePosition pos) {
3698 return (FLAG_hydrogen_track_positions && !pos.IsUnknown())
3699 ? info()->start_position_for(pos.inlining_id()) + pos.position()
3700 : pos.raw();
3701}
3702
3703
3704// Block ordering was implemented with two mutually recursive methods,
3705// HGraph::Postorder and HGraph::PostorderLoopBlocks.
3706// The recursion could lead to stack overflow so the algorithm has been
3707// implemented iteratively.
3708// At a high level the algorithm looks like this:
3709//
3710// Postorder(block, loop_header) : {
3711// if (block has already been visited or is of another loop) return;
3712// mark block as visited;
3713// if (block is a loop header) {
3714// VisitLoopMembers(block, loop_header);
3715// VisitSuccessorsOfLoopHeader(block);
3716// } else {
3717// VisitSuccessors(block)
3718// }
3719// put block in result list;
3720// }
3721//
3722// VisitLoopMembers(block, outer_loop_header) {
3723// foreach (block b in block loop members) {
3724// VisitSuccessorsOfLoopMember(b, outer_loop_header);
3725// if (b is loop header) VisitLoopMembers(b);
3726// }
3727// }
3728//
3729// VisitSuccessorsOfLoopMember(block, outer_loop_header) {
3730// foreach (block b in block successors) Postorder(b, outer_loop_header)
3731// }
3732//
3733// VisitSuccessorsOfLoopHeader(block) {
3734// foreach (block b in block successors) Postorder(b, block)
3735// }
3736//
3737// VisitSuccessors(block, loop_header) {
3738// foreach (block b in block successors) Postorder(b, loop_header)
3739// }
3740//
3741// The ordering is started calling Postorder(entry, NULL).
3742//
3743// Each instance of PostorderProcessor represents the "stack frame" of the
3744// recursion, and particularly keeps the state of the loop (iteration) of the
3745// "Visit..." function it represents.
3746// To recycle memory we keep all the frames in a double linked list but
3747// this means that we cannot use constructors to initialize the frames.
3748//
3749class PostorderProcessor : public ZoneObject {
3750 public:
3751 // Back link (towards the stack bottom).
3752 PostorderProcessor* parent() {return father_; }
3753 // Forward link (towards the stack top).
3754 PostorderProcessor* child() {return child_; }
3755 HBasicBlock* block() { return block_; }
3756 HLoopInformation* loop() { return loop_; }
3757 HBasicBlock* loop_header() { return loop_header_; }
3758
3759 static PostorderProcessor* CreateEntryProcessor(Zone* zone,
3760 HBasicBlock* block) {
3761 PostorderProcessor* result = new(zone) PostorderProcessor(NULL__null);
3762 return result->SetupSuccessors(zone, block, NULL__null);
3763 }
3764
3765 PostorderProcessor* PerformStep(Zone* zone,
3766 ZoneList<HBasicBlock*>* order) {
3767 PostorderProcessor* next =
3768 PerformNonBacktrackingStep(zone, order);
3769 if (next != NULL__null) {
3770 return next;
3771 } else {
3772 return Backtrack(zone, order);
3773 }
3774 }
3775
3776 private:
3777 explicit PostorderProcessor(PostorderProcessor* father)
3778 : father_(father), child_(NULL__null), successor_iterator(NULL__null) { }
3779
3780 // Each enum value states the cycle whose state is kept by this instance.
3781 enum LoopKind {
3782 NONE,
3783 SUCCESSORS,
3784 SUCCESSORS_OF_LOOP_HEADER,
3785 LOOP_MEMBERS,
3786 SUCCESSORS_OF_LOOP_MEMBER
3787 };
3788
3789 // Each "Setup..." method is like a constructor for a cycle state.
3790 PostorderProcessor* SetupSuccessors(Zone* zone,
3791 HBasicBlock* block,
3792 HBasicBlock* loop_header) {
3793 if (block == NULL__null || block->IsOrdered() ||
3794 block->parent_loop_header() != loop_header) {
3795 kind_ = NONE;
3796 block_ = NULL__null;
3797 loop_ = NULL__null;
3798 loop_header_ = NULL__null;
3799 return this;
3800 } else {
3801 block_ = block;
3802 loop_ = NULL__null;
3803 block->MarkAsOrdered();
3804
3805 if (block->IsLoopHeader()) {
3806 kind_ = SUCCESSORS_OF_LOOP_HEADER;
3807 loop_header_ = block;
3808 InitializeSuccessors();
3809 PostorderProcessor* result = Push(zone);
3810 return result->SetupLoopMembers(zone, block, block->loop_information(),
3811 loop_header);
3812 } else {
3813 DCHECK(block->IsFinished())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block->IsFinished())), 0))
) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3813, "Check failed: %s."
, "block->IsFinished()"); } } while (0);
3814 kind_ = SUCCESSORS;
3815 loop_header_ = loop_header;
3816 InitializeSuccessors();
3817 return this;
3818 }
3819 }
3820 }
3821
3822 PostorderProcessor* SetupLoopMembers(Zone* zone,
3823 HBasicBlock* block,
3824 HLoopInformation* loop,
3825 HBasicBlock* loop_header) {
3826 kind_ = LOOP_MEMBERS;
3827 block_ = block;
3828 loop_ = loop;
3829 loop_header_ = loop_header;
3830 InitializeLoopMembers();
3831 return this;
3832 }
3833
3834 PostorderProcessor* SetupSuccessorsOfLoopMember(
3835 HBasicBlock* block,
3836 HLoopInformation* loop,
3837 HBasicBlock* loop_header) {
3838 kind_ = SUCCESSORS_OF_LOOP_MEMBER;
3839 block_ = block;
3840 loop_ = loop;
3841 loop_header_ = loop_header;
3842 InitializeSuccessors();
3843 return this;
3844 }
3845
3846 // This method "allocates" a new stack frame.
3847 PostorderProcessor* Push(Zone* zone) {
3848 if (child_ == NULL__null) {
3849 child_ = new(zone) PostorderProcessor(this);
3850 }
3851 return child_;
3852 }
3853
3854 void ClosePostorder(ZoneList<HBasicBlock*>* order, Zone* zone) {
3855 DCHECK(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor() == NULL ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor
() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor
()) || block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3857, "Check failed: %s."
, "block_->end()->FirstSuccessor() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()) || block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0)
3856 order->Contains(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()) ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor
() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor
()) || block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3857, "Check failed: %s."
, "block_->end()->FirstSuccessor() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()) || block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0)
3857 block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor
() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor
()) || block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3857, "Check failed: %s."
, "block_->end()->FirstSuccessor() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()) || block_->end()->FirstSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0);
3858 DCHECK(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor() == NULL ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor
() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor
()) || block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3860, "Check failed: %s."
, "block_->end()->SecondSuccessor() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()) || block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0)
3859 order->Contains(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()) ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor
() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor
()) || block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3860, "Check failed: %s."
, "block_->end()->SecondSuccessor() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()) || block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0)
3860 block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor
() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor
()) || block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3860, "Check failed: %s."
, "block_->end()->SecondSuccessor() == __null || order->Contains(block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()) || block_->end()->SecondSuccessor()->IsLoopHeader()"
); } } while (0);
3861 order->Add(block_, zone);
3862 }
3863
3864 // This method is the basic block to walk up the stack.
3865 PostorderProcessor* Pop(Zone* zone,
3866 ZoneList<HBasicBlock*>* order) {
3867 switch (kind_) {
3868 case SUCCESSORS:
3869 case SUCCESSORS_OF_LOOP_HEADER:
3870 ClosePostorder(order, zone);
3871 return father_;
3872 case LOOP_MEMBERS:
3873 return father_;
3874 case SUCCESSORS_OF_LOOP_MEMBER:
3875 if (block()->IsLoopHeader() && block() != loop_->loop_header()) {
3876 // In this case we need to perform a LOOP_MEMBERS cycle so we
3877 // initialize it and return this instead of father.
3878 return SetupLoopMembers(zone, block(),
3879 block()->loop_information(), loop_header_);
3880 } else {
3881 return father_;
3882 }
3883 case NONE:
3884 return father_;
3885 }
3886 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3886, "unreachable code"
);
3887 return NULL__null;
3888 }
3889
3890 // Walks up the stack.
3891 PostorderProcessor* Backtrack(Zone* zone,
3892 ZoneList<HBasicBlock*>* order) {
3893 PostorderProcessor* parent = Pop(zone, order);
3894 while (parent != NULL__null) {
3895 PostorderProcessor* next =
3896 parent->PerformNonBacktrackingStep(zone, order);
3897 if (next != NULL__null) {
3898 return next;
3899 } else {
3900 parent = parent->Pop(zone, order);
3901 }
3902 }
3903 return NULL__null;
3904 }
3905
3906 PostorderProcessor* PerformNonBacktrackingStep(
3907 Zone* zone,
3908 ZoneList<HBasicBlock*>* order) {
3909 HBasicBlock* next_block;
3910 switch (kind_) {
3911 case SUCCESSORS:
3912 next_block = AdvanceSuccessors();
3913 if (next_block != NULL__null) {
3914 PostorderProcessor* result = Push(zone);
3915 return result->SetupSuccessors(zone, next_block, loop_header_);
3916 }
3917 break;
3918 case SUCCESSORS_OF_LOOP_HEADER:
3919 next_block = AdvanceSuccessors();
3920 if (next_block != NULL__null) {
3921 PostorderProcessor* result = Push(zone);
3922 return result->SetupSuccessors(zone, next_block, block());
3923 }
3924 break;
3925 case LOOP_MEMBERS:
3926 next_block = AdvanceLoopMembers();
3927 if (next_block != NULL__null) {
3928 PostorderProcessor* result = Push(zone);
3929 return result->SetupSuccessorsOfLoopMember(next_block,
3930 loop_, loop_header_);
3931 }
3932 break;
3933 case SUCCESSORS_OF_LOOP_MEMBER:
3934 next_block = AdvanceSuccessors();
3935 if (next_block != NULL__null) {
3936 PostorderProcessor* result = Push(zone);
3937 return result->SetupSuccessors(zone, next_block, loop_header_);
3938 }
3939 break;
3940 case NONE:
3941 return NULL__null;
3942 }
3943 return NULL__null;
3944 }
3945
3946 // The following two methods implement a "foreach b in successors" cycle.
3947 void InitializeSuccessors() {
3948 loop_index = 0;
3949 loop_length = 0;
3950 successor_iterator = HSuccessorIterator(block_->end());
3951 }
3952
3953 HBasicBlock* AdvanceSuccessors() {
3954 if (!successor_iterator.Done()) {
3955 HBasicBlock* result = successor_iterator.Current();
3956 successor_iterator.Advance();
3957 return result;
3958 }
3959 return NULL__null;
3960 }
3961
3962 // The following two methods implement a "foreach b in loop members" cycle.
3963 void InitializeLoopMembers() {
3964 loop_index = 0;
3965 loop_length = loop_->blocks()->length();
3966 }
3967
3968 HBasicBlock* AdvanceLoopMembers() {
3969 if (loop_index < loop_length) {
3970 HBasicBlock* result = loop_->blocks()->at(loop_index);
3971 loop_index++;
3972 return result;
3973 } else {
3974 return NULL__null;
3975 }
3976 }
3977
3978 LoopKind kind_;
3979 PostorderProcessor* father_;
3980 PostorderProcessor* child_;
3981 HLoopInformation* loop_;
3982 HBasicBlock* block_;
3983 HBasicBlock* loop_header_;
3984 int loop_index;
3985 int loop_length;
3986 HSuccessorIterator successor_iterator;
3987};
3988
3989
3990void HGraph::OrderBlocks() {
3991 CompilationPhase phase("H_Block ordering", info());
3992
3993#ifdef DEBUG1
3994 // Initially the blocks must not be ordered.
3995 for (int i = 0; i < blocks_.length(); ++i) {
3996 DCHECK(!blocks_[i]->IsOrdered())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!blocks_[i]->IsOrdered()))
, 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 3996, "Check failed: %s."
, "!blocks_[i]->IsOrdered()"); } } while (0);
3997 }
3998#endif
3999
4000 PostorderProcessor* postorder =
4001 PostorderProcessor::CreateEntryProcessor(zone(), blocks_[0]);
4002 blocks_.Rewind(0);
4003 while (postorder) {
4004 postorder = postorder->PerformStep(zone(), &blocks_);
4005 }
4006
4007#ifdef DEBUG1
4008 // Now all blocks must be marked as ordered.
4009 for (int i = 0; i < blocks_.length(); ++i) {
4010 DCHECK(blocks_[i]->IsOrdered())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(blocks_[i]->IsOrdered())),
0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4010, "Check failed: %s."
, "blocks_[i]->IsOrdered()"); } } while (0);
4011 }
4012#endif
4013
4014 // Reverse block list and assign block IDs.
4015 for (int i = 0, j = blocks_.length(); --j >= i; ++i) {
4016 HBasicBlock* bi = blocks_[i];
4017 HBasicBlock* bj = blocks_[j];
4018 bi->set_block_id(j);
4019 bj->set_block_id(i);
4020 blocks_[i] = bj;
4021 blocks_[j] = bi;
4022 }
4023}
4024
4025
4026void HGraph::AssignDominators() {
4027 HPhase phase("H_Assign dominators", this);
4028 for (int i = 0; i < blocks_.length(); ++i) {
4029 HBasicBlock* block = blocks_[i];
4030 if (block->IsLoopHeader()) {
4031 // Only the first predecessor of a loop header is from outside the loop.
4032 // All others are back edges, and thus cannot dominate the loop header.
4033 block->AssignCommonDominator(block->predecessors()->first());
4034 block->AssignLoopSuccessorDominators();
4035 } else {
4036 for (int j = blocks_[i]->predecessors()->length() - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
4037 blocks_[i]->AssignCommonDominator(blocks_[i]->predecessors()->at(j));
4038 }
4039 }
4040 }
4041}
4042
4043
4044bool HGraph::CheckArgumentsPhiUses() {
4045 int block_count = blocks_.length();
4046 for (int i = 0; i < block_count; ++i) {
4047 for (int j = 0; j < blocks_[i]->phis()->length(); ++j) {
4048 HPhi* phi = blocks_[i]->phis()->at(j);
4049 // We don't support phi uses of arguments for now.
4050 if (phi->CheckFlag(HValue::kIsArguments)) return false;
4051 }
4052 }
4053 return true;
4054}
4055
4056
4057bool HGraph::CheckConstPhiUses() {
4058 int block_count = blocks_.length();
4059 for (int i = 0; i < block_count; ++i) {
4060 for (int j = 0; j < blocks_[i]->phis()->length(); ++j) {
4061 HPhi* phi = blocks_[i]->phis()->at(j);
4062 // Check for the hole value (from an uninitialized const).
4063 for (int k = 0; k < phi->OperandCount(); k++) {
4064 if (phi->OperandAt(k) == GetConstantHole()) return false;
4065 }
4066 }
4067 }
4068 return true;
4069}
4070
4071
4072void HGraph::CollectPhis() {
4073 int block_count = blocks_.length();
4074 phi_list_ = new(zone()) ZoneList<HPhi*>(block_count, zone());
4075 for (int i = 0; i < block_count; ++i) {
4076 for (int j = 0; j < blocks_[i]->phis()->length(); ++j) {
4077 HPhi* phi = blocks_[i]->phis()->at(j);
4078 phi_list_->Add(phi, zone());
4079 }
4080 }
4081}

4084// Implementation of utility class to encapsulate the translation state for
4085// a (possibly inlined) function.
4086FunctionState::FunctionState(HOptimizedGraphBuilder* owner,
4087 CompilationInfo* info, InliningKind inlining_kind,
4088 int inlining_id)
4089 : owner_(owner),
4090 compilation_info_(info),
4091 call_context_(NULL__null),
4092 inlining_kind_(inlining_kind),
4093 function_return_(NULL__null),
4094 test_context_(NULL__null),
4095 entry_(NULL__null),
4096 arguments_object_(NULL__null),
4097 arguments_elements_(NULL__null),
4098 inlining_id_(inlining_id),
4099 outer_source_position_(SourcePosition::Unknown()),
4100 outer_(owner->function_state()) {
4101 if (outer_ != NULL__null) {
4102 // State for an inline function.
4103 if (owner->ast_context()->IsTest()) {
4104 HBasicBlock* if_true = owner->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4105 HBasicBlock* if_false = owner->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4106 if_true->MarkAsInlineReturnTarget(owner->current_block());
4107 if_false->MarkAsInlineReturnTarget(owner->current_block());
4108 TestContext* outer_test_context = TestContext::cast(owner->ast_context());
4109 Expression* cond = outer_test_context->condition();
4110 // The AstContext constructor pushed on the context stack. This newed
4111 // instance is the reason that AstContext can't be BASE_EMBEDDED.
4112 test_context_ = new TestContext(owner, cond, if_true, if_false);
4113 } else {
4114 function_return_ = owner->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4115 function_return()->MarkAsInlineReturnTarget(owner->current_block());
4116 }
4117 // Set this after possibly allocating a new TestContext above.
4118 call_context_ = owner->ast_context();
4119 }
4120
4121 // Push on the state stack.
4122 owner->set_function_state(this);
4123
4124 if (compilation_info_->is_tracking_positions()) {
4125 outer_source_position_ = owner->source_position();
4126 owner->EnterInlinedSource(
4127 info->shared_info()->start_position(),
4128 inlining_id);
4129 owner->SetSourcePosition(info->shared_info()->start_position());
4130 }
4131}
4132
4133
4134FunctionState::~FunctionState() {
4135 delete test_context_;
4136 owner_->set_function_state(outer_);
4137
4138 if (compilation_info_->is_tracking_positions()) {
4139 owner_->set_source_position(outer_source_position_);
4140 owner_->EnterInlinedSource(
4141 outer_->compilation_info()->shared_info()->start_position(),
4142 outer_->inlining_id());
4143 }
4144}

()->length() == original_length_ + 1 && owner()->
environment()->frame_type() == JS_FUNCTION))), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4179, "Check failed: %s.", "owner()->HasStackOverflow() || owner()->current_block() == __null || (owner()->environment()->length() == original_length_ + 1 && owner()->environment()->frame_type() == JS_FUNCTION)"
); } } while (0)
4179 owner()->environment()->frame_type() == JS_FUNCTION))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(owner()->HasStackOverflow(
) || owner()->current_block() == __null || (owner()->environment
()->length() == original_length_ + 1 && owner()->
environment()->frame_type() == JS_FUNCTION))), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4179, "Check failed: %s.", "owner()->HasStackOverflow() || owner()->current_block() == __null || (owner()->environment()->length() == original_length_ + 1 && owner()->environment()->frame_type() == JS_FUNCTION)"
); } } while (0);
4180}

4187
4188void ValueContext::ReturnValue(HValue* value) {
4189 // The value is tracked in the bailout environment, and communicated
4190 // through the environment as the result of the expression.
4191 if (value->CheckFlag(HValue::kIsArguments)) {
4192 if (flag_ == ARGUMENTS_FAKED) {
4193 value = owner()->graph()->GetConstantUndefined();
4194 } else if (!arguments_allowed()) {
4195 owner()->Bailout(kBadValueContextForArgumentsValue);
4196 }
4197 }
4198 owner()->Push(value);
4199}

4207void EffectContext::ReturnInstruction(HInstruction* instr, BailoutId ast_id) {
4208 DCHECK(!instr->IsControlInstruction())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!instr->IsControlInstruction
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4208, "Check failed: %s."
, "!instr->IsControlInstruction()"); } } while (0);
4209 owner()->AddInstruction(instr);
4210 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
4211 owner()->Add<HSimulate>(ast_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
4212 }
4213}

4215
4216void EffectContext::ReturnControl(HControlInstruction* instr,
4217 BailoutId ast_id) {
4218 DCHECK(!instr->HasObservableSideEffects())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!instr->HasObservableSideEffects
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4218, "Check failed: %s."
, "!instr->HasObservableSideEffects()"); } } while (0);
4219 HBasicBlock* empty_true = owner()->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4220 HBasicBlock* empty_false = owner()->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4221 instr->SetSuccessorAt(0, empty_true);
4222 instr->SetSuccessorAt(1, empty_false);
4223 owner()->FinishCurrentBlock(instr);
4224 HBasicBlock* join = owner()->CreateJoin(empty_true, empty_false, ast_id);
4225 owner()->set_current_block(join);
4226}

4228
4229void EffectContext::ReturnContinuation(HIfContinuation* continuation,
4230 BailoutId ast_id) {
4231 HBasicBlock* true_branch = NULL__null;
4232 HBasicBlock* false_branch = NULL__null;
4233 continuation->Continue(&true_branch, &false_branch);
4234 if (!continuation->IsTrueReachable()) {
4235 owner()->set_current_block(false_branch);
4236 } else if (!continuation->IsFalseReachable()) {
4237 owner()->set_current_block(true_branch);
4238 } else {
4239 HBasicBlock* join = owner()->CreateJoin(true_branch, false_branch, ast_id);
4240 owner()->set_current_block(join);
4241 }
4242}

4245void ValueContext::ReturnInstruction(HInstruction* instr, BailoutId ast_id) {
4246 DCHECK(!instr->IsControlInstruction())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!instr->IsControlInstruction
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4246, "Check failed: %s."
, "!instr->IsControlInstruction()"); } } while (0);
4247 if (!arguments_allowed() && instr->CheckFlag(HValue::kIsArguments)) {
4248 return owner()->Bailout(kBadValueContextForArgumentsObjectValue);
4249 }
4250 owner()->AddInstruction(instr);
4251 owner()->Push(instr);
4252 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
4253 owner()->Add<HSimulate>(ast_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
4254 }
4255}

4257
4258void ValueContext::ReturnControl(HControlInstruction* instr, BailoutId ast_id) {
4259 DCHECK(!instr->HasObservableSideEffects())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!instr->HasObservableSideEffects
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4259, "Check failed: %s."
, "!instr->HasObservableSideEffects()"); } } while (0);
4260 if (!arguments_allowed() && instr->CheckFlag(HValue::kIsArguments)) {
4261 return owner()->Bailout(kBadValueContextForArgumentsObjectValue);
4262 }
4263 HBasicBlock* materialize_false = owner()->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4264 HBasicBlock* materialize_true = owner()->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4265 instr->SetSuccessorAt(0, materialize_true);
4266 instr->SetSuccessorAt(1, materialize_false);
4267 owner()->FinishCurrentBlock(instr);
4268 owner()->set_current_block(materialize_true);
4269 owner()->Push(owner()->graph()->GetConstantTrue());
4270 owner()->set_current_block(materialize_false);
4271 owner()->Push(owner()->graph()->GetConstantFalse());
4272 HBasicBlock* join =
4273 owner()->CreateJoin(materialize_true, materialize_false, ast_id);
4274 owner()->set_current_block(join);
4275}

4277
4278void ValueContext::ReturnContinuation(HIfContinuation* continuation,
4279 BailoutId ast_id) {
4280 HBasicBlock* materialize_true = NULL__null;
4281 HBasicBlock* materialize_false = NULL__null;
4282 continuation->Continue(&materialize_true, &materialize_false);
4283 if (continuation->IsTrueReachable()) {
4284 owner()->set_current_block(materialize_true);
4285 owner()->Push(owner()->graph()->GetConstantTrue());
4286 owner()->set_current_block(materialize_true);
4287 }
4288 if (continuation->IsFalseReachable()) {
4289 owner()->set_current_block(materialize_false);
4290 owner()->Push(owner()->graph()->GetConstantFalse());
4291 owner()->set_current_block(materialize_false);
4292 }
4293 if (continuation->TrueAndFalseReachable()) {
4294 HBasicBlock* join =
4295 owner()->CreateJoin(materialize_true, materialize_false, ast_id);
4296 owner()->set_current_block(join);
4297 }
4298}

4301void TestContext::ReturnInstruction(HInstruction* instr, BailoutId ast_id) {
4302 DCHECK(!instr->IsControlInstruction())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!instr->IsControlInstruction
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4302, "Check failed: %s."
, "!instr->IsControlInstruction()"); } } while (0);
4303 HOptimizedGraphBuilder* builder = owner();
4304 builder->AddInstruction(instr);

4306 // this one isn't actually needed (and wouldn't work if it were targeted).
4307 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
4308 builder->Push(instr);
4309 builder->Add<HSimulate>(ast_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
4310 builder->Pop();
4311 }
4312 BuildBranch(instr);
4313}

())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4317, "Check failed: %s."
, "!instr->HasObservableSideEffects()"); } } while (0);

4343
4344void TestContext::BuildBranch(HValue* value) {
4345 // We expect the graph to be in edge-split form: there is no edge that
4346 // connects a branch node to a join node. We conservatively ensure that
4347 // property by always adding an empty block on the outgoing edges of this
4348 // branch.
4349 HOptimizedGraphBuilder* builder = owner();
4350 if (value != NULL__null && value->CheckFlag(HValue::kIsArguments)) {
4351 builder->Bailout(kArgumentsObjectValueInATestContext);
4352 }
4353 ToBooleanStub::Types expected(condition()->to_boolean_types());
4354 ReturnControl(owner()->New<HBranch>(value, expected), BailoutId::None());
4355}

4357
4358// HOptimizedGraphBuilder infrastructure for bailing out and checking bailouts.
4359#define CHECK_BAILOUT(call) \
4360 do { \
4361 call; \
4362 if (HasStackOverflow()) return; \
4363 } while (false)
4364
4365
4366#define CHECK_ALIVE(call) \
4367 do { \
4368 call; \
4369 if (HasStackOverflow() || current_block() == NULL__null) return; \
4370 } while (false)
4371
4372
4373#define CHECK_ALIVE_OR_RETURN(call, value)do { call; if (HasStackOverflow() || current_block() == __null
) return value; } while (false) \
4374 do { \
4375 call; \
4376 if (HasStackOverflow() || current_block() == NULL__null) return value; \
4377 } while (false)
4378

4380void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::Bailout(BailoutReason reason) {
4381 current_info()->AbortOptimization(reason);
4382 SetStackOverflow();
4383}

4428
4429
4430bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildGraph() {
4431 if (IsSubclassConstructor(current_info()->literal()->kind())) {
4432 Bailout(kSuperReference);
4433 return false;
4434 }
4435
4436 Scope* scope = current_info()->scope();
4437 SetUpScope(scope);
4438
4439 // Add an edge to the body entry. This is warty: the graph's start
4440 // environment will be used by the Lithium translation as the initial
4441 // environment on graph entry, but it has now been mutated by the
4442 // Hydrogen translation of the instructions in the start block. This
4443 // environment uses values which have not been defined yet. These
4444 // Hydrogen instructions will then be replayed by the Lithium
4445 // translation, so they cannot have an environment effect. The edge to
4446 // the body's entry block (along with some special logic for the start
4447 // block in HInstruction::InsertAfter) seals the start block from
4448 // getting unwanted instructions inserted.
4449 //
4450 // TODO(kmillikin): Fix this. Stop mutating the initial environment.
4451 // Make the Hydrogen instructions in the initial block into Hydrogen
4452 // values (but not instructions), present in the initial environment and
4453 // not replayed by the Lithium translation.
4454 HEnvironment* initial_env = environment()->CopyWithoutHistory();
4455 HBasicBlock* body_entry = CreateBasicBlock(initial_env);
4456 Goto(body_entry);
4457 body_entry->SetJoinId(BailoutId::FunctionEntry());
4458 set_current_block(body_entry);
4459
4460 VisitDeclarations(scope->declarations());
4461 Add<HSimulate>(BailoutId::Declarations());
4462
4463 Add<HStackCheck>(HStackCheck::kFunctionEntry);
4464
4465 VisitStatements(current_info()->literal()->body());
4466 if (HasStackOverflow()) return false;
4467
4468 if (current_block() != NULL__null) {
4469 Add<HReturn>(graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
4470 set_current_block(NULL__null);
4471 }
4472
4473 // If the checksum of the number of type info changes is the same as the
4474 // last time this function was compiled, then this recompile is likely not
4475 // due to missing/inadequate type feedback, but rather too aggressive
4476 // optimization. Disable optimistic LICM in that case.
4477 Handle<Code> unoptimized_code(current_info()->shared_info()->code());
4478 DCHECK(unoptimized_code->kind() == Code::FUNCTION)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(unoptimized_code->kind() ==
Code::FUNCTION)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 4478, "Check failed: %s.", "unoptimized_code->kind() == Code::FUNCTION"
); } } while (0);
4479 Handle<TypeFeedbackInfo> type_info(
4480 TypeFeedbackInfo::cast(unoptimized_code->type_feedback_info()));
4481 int checksum = type_info->own_type_change_checksum();
4482 int composite_checksum = graph()->update_type_change_checksum(checksum);
4483 graph()->set_use_optimistic_licm(
4484 !type_info->matches_inlined_type_change_checksum(composite_checksum));
4485 type_info->set_inlined_type_change_checksum(composite_checksum);
4486
4487 // Perform any necessary OSR-specific cleanups or changes to the graph.
4488 osr()->FinishGraph();
4489
4490 return true;
4491}
4492
4493
4494bool HGraph::Optimize(BailoutReason* bailout_reason) {
4495 OrderBlocks();
4496 AssignDominators();
4497
4498 // We need to create a HConstant "zero" now so that GVN will fold every
4499 // zero-valued constant in the graph together.
4500 // The constant is needed to make idef-based bounds check work: the pass
4501 // evaluates relations with "zero" and that zero cannot be created after GVN.
4502 GetConstant0();
4503
4504#ifdef DEBUG1
4505 // Do a full verify after building the graph and computing dominators.
4506 Verify(true);
4507#endif
4508
4509 if (FLAG_analyze_environment_liveness && maximum_environment_size() != 0) {
4510 Run<HEnvironmentLivenessAnalysisPhase>();
4511 }
4512
4513 if (!CheckConstPhiUses()) {
4514 *bailout_reason = kUnsupportedPhiUseOfConstVariable;
4515 return false;
4516 }
4517 Run<HRedundantPhiEliminationPhase>();
4518 if (!CheckArgumentsPhiUses()) {
4519 *bailout_reason = kUnsupportedPhiUseOfArguments;
4520 return false;
4521 }
4522
4523 // Find and mark unreachable code to simplify optimizations, especially gvn,
4524 // where unreachable code could unnecessarily defeat LICM.
4525 Run<HMarkUnreachableBlocksPhase>();
4526
4527 if (FLAG_dead_code_elimination) Run<HDeadCodeEliminationPhase>();
4528 if (FLAG_use_escape_analysis) Run<HEscapeAnalysisPhase>();
4529
4530 if (FLAG_load_elimination) Run<HLoadEliminationPhase>();
4531
4532 CollectPhis();
4533
4534 if (has_osr()) osr()->FinishOsrValues();
4535
4536 Run<HInferRepresentationPhase>();
4537
4538 // Remove HSimulate instructions that have turned out not to be needed
4539 // after all by folding them into the following HSimulate.
4540 // This must happen after inferring representations.
4541 Run<HMergeRemovableSimulatesPhase>();
4542
4543 Run<HMarkDeoptimizeOnUndefinedPhase>();
4544 Run<HRepresentationChangesPhase>();
4545
4546 Run<HInferTypesPhase>();
4547
4548 // Must be performed before canonicalization to ensure that Canonicalize
4549 // will not remove semantically meaningful ToInt32 operations e.g. BIT_OR with
4550 // zero.
4551 Run<HUint32AnalysisPhase>();
4552
4553 if (FLAG_use_canonicalizing) Run<HCanonicalizePhase>();
4554
4555 if (FLAG_use_gvn) Run<HGlobalValueNumberingPhase>();
4556
4557 if (FLAG_check_elimination) Run<HCheckEliminationPhase>();
4558
4559 if (FLAG_store_elimination) Run<HStoreEliminationPhase>();
4560
4561 Run<HRangeAnalysisPhase>();
4562
4563 Run<HComputeChangeUndefinedToNaN>();
4564
4565 // Eliminate redundant stack checks on backwards branches.
4566 Run<HStackCheckEliminationPhase>();
4567
4568 if (FLAG_array_bounds_checks_elimination) Run<HBoundsCheckEliminationPhase>();
4569 if (FLAG_array_bounds_checks_hoisting) Run<HBoundsCheckHoistingPhase>();
4570 if (FLAG_array_index_dehoisting) Run<HDehoistIndexComputationsPhase>();
4571 if (FLAG_dead_code_elimination) Run<HDeadCodeEliminationPhase>();
4572
4573 RestoreActualValues();
4574
4575 // Find unreachable code a second time, GVN and other optimizations may have
4576 // made blocks unreachable that were previously reachable.
4577 Run<HMarkUnreachableBlocksPhase>();
4578
4579 return true;
4580}
4581
4582
4583void HGraph::RestoreActualValues() {
4584 HPhase phase("H_Restore actual values", this);
4585
4586 for (int block_index = 0; block_index < blocks()->length(); block_index++) {
4587 HBasicBlock* block = blocks()->at(block_index);
4588
4589#ifdef DEBUG1
4590 for (int i = 0; i < block->phis()->length(); i++) {
4591 HPhi* phi = block->phis()->at(i);
4592 DCHECK(phi->ActualValue() == phi)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(phi->ActualValue() == phi)
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4592, "Check failed: %s."
, "phi->ActualValue() == phi"); } } while (0);
4593 }
4594#endif
4595
4596 for (HInstructionIterator it(block); !it.Done(); it.Advance()) {
4597 HInstruction* instruction = it.Current();
4598 if (instruction->ActualValue() == instruction) continue;
4599 if (instruction->CheckFlag(HValue::kIsDead)) {
4600 // The instruction was marked as deleted but left in the graph
4601 // as a control flow dependency point for subsequent
4602 // instructions.
4603 instruction->DeleteAndReplaceWith(instruction->ActualValue());
4604 } else {
4605 DCHECK(instruction->IsInformativeDefinition())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(instruction->IsInformativeDefinition
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4605, "Check failed: %s."
, "instruction->IsInformativeDefinition()"); } } while (0);
4606 if (instruction->IsPurelyInformativeDefinition()) {
4607 instruction->DeleteAndReplaceWith(instruction->RedefinedOperand());
4608 } else {
4609 instruction->ReplaceAllUsesWith(instruction->ActualValue());
4610 }
4611 }
4612 }
4613 }
4614}

4616
4617void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(int count) {
4618 ZoneList<HValue*> arguments(count, zone());
4619 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
4620 arguments.Add(Pop(), zone());
4621 }
4622
4623 HPushArguments* push_args = New<HPushArguments>();
4624 while (!arguments.is_empty()) {
4625 push_args->AddInput(arguments.RemoveLast());
4626 }
4627 AddInstruction(push_args);
4628}
4629
4630
4631template <class Instruction>
4632HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PreProcessCall(Instruction* call) {
4633 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(call->argument_count());
4634 return call;
4635}
4636
4637
4638void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::SetUpScope(Scope* scope) {
4639 HEnvironment* prolog_env = environment();
4640 int parameter_count = environment()->parameter_count();
4641 ZoneList<HValue*> parameters(parameter_count, zone());
4642 for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count; ++i) {
4643 HInstruction* parameter = Add<HParameter>(static_cast<unsigned>(i));
4644 parameters.Add(parameter, zone());
4645 environment()->Bind(i, parameter);
4646 }
4647
4648 HConstant* undefined_constant = graph()->GetConstantUndefined();
4649 // Initialize specials and locals to undefined.
4650 for (int i = parameter_count + 1; i < environment()->length(); ++i) {
4651 environment()->Bind(i, undefined_constant);
4652 }
4653 Add<HPrologue>();
4654
4655 HEnvironment* initial_env = environment()->CopyWithoutHistory();
4656 HBasicBlock* body_entry = CreateBasicBlock(initial_env);
4657 GotoNoSimulate(body_entry);
4658 set_current_block(body_entry);
4659
4660 // Initialize context of prolog environment to undefined.
4661 prolog_env->BindContext(undefined_constant);
4662
4663 // First special is HContext.
4664 HInstruction* context = Add<HContext>();
4665 environment()->BindContext(context);
4666
4667 // Create an arguments object containing the initial parameters. Set the
4668 // initial values of parameters including "this" having parameter index 0.
4669 DCHECK_EQ(scope->num_parameters() + 1, parameter_count)do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (scope->
num_parameters() + 1), (parameter_count), "scope->num_parameters() + 1"
" " "==" " " "parameter_count")) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 4669, "Check failed: %s.", _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; }
} while (0);
4670 HArgumentsObject* arguments_object = New<HArgumentsObject>(parameter_count);
4671 for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count; ++i) {
4672 HValue* parameter = parameters.at(i);
4673 arguments_object->AddArgument(parameter, zone());
4674 }
4675
4676 AddInstruction(arguments_object);
4677
4678 // Handle the arguments and arguments shadow variables specially (they do
4679 // not have declarations).
4680 if (scope->arguments() != NULL__null) {
4681 environment()->Bind(scope->arguments(), arguments_object);
4682 }
4683
4684 int rest_index;
4685 Variable* rest = scope->rest_parameter(&rest_index);
4686 if (rest) {
4687 return Bailout(kRestParameter);
4688 }
4689
4690 if (scope->this_function_var() != nullptr ||
4691 scope->new_target_var() != nullptr) {
4692 return Bailout(kSuperReference);
4693 }
4694
4695 // Trace the call.
4696 if (FLAG_trace && top_info()->IsOptimizing()) {
4697 Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kTraceEnter), 0);
4698 }
4699}
4700
4701
4702void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitStatements(ZoneList<Statement*>* statements) {
4703 for (int i = 0; i < statements->length(); i++) {
4704 Statement* stmt = statements->at(i);
4705 CHECK_ALIVE(Visit(stmt));
4706 if (stmt->IsJump()) break;
4707 }
4708}
4709
4710
4711void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitBlock(Block* stmt) {
4712 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4712, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
4713 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4713, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
4714 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4714, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
4715
4716 Scope* outer_scope = scope();
4717 Scope* scope = stmt->scope();
4718 BreakAndContinueInfo break_info(stmt, outer_scope);
4719
4720 { BreakAndContinueScope push(&break_info, this);
4721 if (scope != NULL__null) {
4722 if (scope->NeedsContext()) {
4723 // Load the function object.
4724 Scope* declaration_scope = scope->DeclarationScope();
4725 HInstruction* function;
4726 HValue* outer_context = environment()->context();
4727 if (declaration_scope->is_script_scope() ||
4728 declaration_scope->is_eval_scope()) {
4729 function = new (zone())
4730 HLoadContextSlot(outer_context, Context::CLOSURE_INDEX,
4731 HLoadContextSlot::kNoCheck);
4732 } else {
4733 function = New<HThisFunction>();
4734 }
4735 AddInstruction(function);
4736 // Allocate a block context and store it to the stack frame.
4737 HValue* scope_info = Add<HConstant>(scope->GetScopeInfo(isolate()));
4738 Add<HPushArguments>(scope_info, function);
4739 HInstruction* inner_context = Add<HCallRuntime>(
4740 Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kPushBlockContext), 2);
4741 inner_context->SetFlag(HValue::kHasNoObservableSideEffects);
4742 HInstruction* instr = Add<HStoreFrameContext>(inner_context);
4743 set_scope(scope);
4744 environment()->BindContext(inner_context);
4745 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
4746 AddSimulate(stmt->EntryId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
4747 }
4748 }
4749 VisitDeclarations(scope->declarations());
4750 AddSimulate(stmt->DeclsId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
4751 }
4752 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitStatements(stmt->statements()));
4753 }
4754 set_scope(outer_scope);
4755 if (scope != NULL__null && current_block() != NULL__null &&
4756 scope->ContextLocalCount() > 0) {
4757 HValue* inner_context = environment()->context();
4758 HValue* outer_context = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
4759 inner_context, nullptr,
4760 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
4761
4762 HInstruction* instr = Add<HStoreFrameContext>(outer_context);
4763 environment()->BindContext(outer_context);
4764 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
4765 AddSimulate(stmt->ExitId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
4766 }
4767 }
4768 HBasicBlock* break_block = break_info.break_block();
4769 if (break_block != NULL__null) {
4770 if (current_block() != NULL__null) Goto(break_block);
4771 break_block->SetJoinId(stmt->ExitId());
4772 set_current_block(break_block);
4773 }
4774}

V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4779, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
4780 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4780, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);

())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4781, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
4782 VisitForEffect(stmt->expression());
4783}

4798
4799void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitIfStatement(IfStatement* stmt) {
4800 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4800, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
4801 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4801, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
4802 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4802, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
4803 if (stmt->condition()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
4804 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->ThenId());
4805 Visit(stmt->then_statement());
4806 } else if (stmt->condition()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
4807 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->ElseId());
4808 Visit(stmt->else_statement());
4809 } else {
4810 HBasicBlock* cond_true = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4811 HBasicBlock* cond_false = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4812 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(stmt->condition(), cond_true, cond_false));
4813
4814 if (cond_true->HasPredecessor()) {
4815 cond_true->SetJoinId(stmt->ThenId());
4816 set_current_block(cond_true);
4817 CHECK_BAILOUT(Visit(stmt->then_statement()));
4818 cond_true = current_block();
4819 } else {
4820 cond_true = NULL__null;
4821 }
4822
4823 if (cond_false->HasPredecessor()) {
4824 cond_false->SetJoinId(stmt->ElseId());
4825 set_current_block(cond_false);
4826 CHECK_BAILOUT(Visit(stmt->else_statement()));
4827 cond_false = current_block();
4828 } else {
4829 cond_false = NULL__null;
4830 }
4831
4832 HBasicBlock* join = CreateJoin(cond_true, cond_false, stmt->IfId());
4833 set_current_block(join);
4834 }
4835}
4836
4837
4838HBasicBlock* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BreakAndContinueScope::Get(
4839 BreakableStatement* stmt,
4840 BreakType type,
4841 Scope** scope,
4842 int* drop_extra) {
4843 *drop_extra = 0;
4844 BreakAndContinueScope* current = this;
4845 while (current != NULL__null && current->info()->target() != stmt) {
4846 *drop_extra += current->info()->drop_extra();
4847 current = current->next();
4848 }
4849 DCHECK(current != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4849, "Check failed: %s.", "current != __null"
); } } while (0); // Always found (unless stack is malformed).
4850 *scope = current->info()->scope();
4851
4852 if (type == BREAK) {
4853 *drop_extra += current->info()->drop_extra();
4854 }
4855
4856 HBasicBlock* block = NULL__null;
4857 switch (type) {
4858 case BREAK:
4859 block = current->info()->break_block();
4860 if (block == NULL__null) {
4861 block = current->owner()->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4862 current->info()->set_break_block(block);
4863 }
4864 break;
4865
4866 case CONTINUE:
4867 block = current->info()->continue_block();
4868 if (block == NULL__null) {
4869 block = current->owner()->graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4870 current->info()->set_continue_block(block);
4871 }
4872 break;
4873 }
4874
4875 return block;
4876}
4877
4878
4879void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitContinueStatement(
4880 ContinueStatement* stmt) {
4881 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4881, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
4882 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4882, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
4883 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4883, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
4884 Scope* outer_scope = NULL__null;
4885 Scope* inner_scope = scope();
4886 int drop_extra = 0;
4887 HBasicBlock* continue_block = break_scope()->Get(
4888 stmt->target(), BreakAndContinueScope::CONTINUE,
4889 &outer_scope, &drop_extra);
4890 HValue* context = environment()->context();
4891 Drop(drop_extra);
4892 int context_pop_count = inner_scope->ContextChainLength(outer_scope);
4893 if (context_pop_count > 0) {
4894 while (context_pop_count-- > 0) {
4895 HInstruction* context_instruction = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
4896 context, nullptr,
4897 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
4898 context = context_instruction;
4899 }
4900 HInstruction* instr = Add<HStoreFrameContext>(context);
4901 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
4902 AddSimulate(stmt->target()->EntryId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
4903 }
4904 environment()->BindContext(context);
4905 }
4906
4907 Goto(continue_block);
4908 set_current_block(NULL__null);
4909}

4912void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitBreakStatement(BreakStatement* stmt) {
4913 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4913, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
4914 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4914, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
4915 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4915, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
4916 Scope* outer_scope = NULL__null;
4917 Scope* inner_scope = scope();
4918 int drop_extra = 0;
4919 HBasicBlock* break_block = break_scope()->Get(
4920 stmt->target(), BreakAndContinueScope::BREAK,
4921 &outer_scope, &drop_extra);
4922 HValue* context = environment()->context();
4923 Drop(drop_extra);
4924 int context_pop_count = inner_scope->ContextChainLength(outer_scope);
4925 if (context_pop_count > 0) {
4926 while (context_pop_count-- > 0) {
4927 HInstruction* context_instruction = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
4928 context, nullptr,
4929 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
4930 context = context_instruction;
4931 }
4932 HInstruction* instr = Add<HStoreFrameContext>(context);
4933 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
4934 AddSimulate(stmt->target()->ExitId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
4935 }
4936 environment()->BindContext(context);
4937 }
4938 Goto(break_block);
4939 set_current_block(NULL__null);
4940}

4942
4943void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitReturnStatement(ReturnStatement* stmt) {
4944 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4944, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
4945 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4945, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
4946 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4946, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
4947 FunctionState* state = function_state();
4948 AstContext* context = call_context();
4949 if (context == NULL__null) {
4950 // Not an inlined return, so an actual one.
4951 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(stmt->expression()));
4952 HValue* result = environment()->Pop();
4953 Add<HReturn>(result);
4954 } else if (state->inlining_kind() == CONSTRUCT_CALL_RETURN) {
4955 // Return from an inlined construct call. In a test context the return value
4956 // will always evaluate to true, in a value context the return value needs
4957 // to be a JSObject.
4958 if (context->IsTest()) {
4959 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForEffect(stmt->expression()));
4960 context->ReturnValue(graph()->GetConstantTrue());
4961 } else if (context->IsEffect()) {
4962 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForEffect(stmt->expression()));
4963 Goto(function_return(), state);
4964 } else {
4965 DCHECK(context->IsValue())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(context->IsValue())), 0)))
{ V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4965, "Check failed: %s."
, "context->IsValue()"); } } while (0);
4966 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(stmt->expression()));
4967 HValue* return_value = Pop();
4968 HValue* receiver = environment()->arguments_environment()->Lookup(0);
4969 HHasInstanceTypeAndBranch* typecheck =
4970 New<HHasInstanceTypeAndBranch>(return_value,
4971 FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE,
4972 LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
4973 HBasicBlock* if_spec_object = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4974 HBasicBlock* not_spec_object = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
4975 typecheck->SetSuccessorAt(0, if_spec_object);
4976 typecheck->SetSuccessorAt(1, not_spec_object);
4977 FinishCurrentBlock(typecheck);
4978 AddLeaveInlined(if_spec_object, return_value, state);
4979 AddLeaveInlined(not_spec_object, receiver, state);
4980 }
4981 } else if (state->inlining_kind() == SETTER_CALL_RETURN) {
4982 // Return from an inlined setter call. The returned value is never used, the
4983 // value of an assignment is always the value of the RHS of the assignment.
4984 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForEffect(stmt->expression()));
4985 if (context->IsTest()) {
4986 HValue* rhs = environment()->arguments_environment()->Lookup(1);
4987 context->ReturnValue(rhs);
4988 } else if (context->IsEffect()) {
4989 Goto(function_return(), state);
4990 } else {
4991 DCHECK(context->IsValue())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(context->IsValue())), 0)))
{ V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 4991, "Check failed: %s."
, "context->IsValue()"); } } while (0);
4992 HValue* rhs = environment()->arguments_environment()->Lookup(1);
4993 AddLeaveInlined(rhs, state);
4994 }
4995 } else {
4996 // Return from a normal inlined function. Visit the subexpression in the
4997 // expression context of the call.
4998 if (context->IsTest()) {
4999 TestContext* test = TestContext::cast(context);
5000 VisitForControl(stmt->expression(), test->if_true(), test->if_false());
5001 } else if (context->IsEffect()) {
5002 // Visit in value context and ignore the result. This is needed to keep
5003 // environment in sync with full-codegen since some visitors (e.g.
5004 // VisitCountOperation) use the operand stack differently depending on
5005 // context.
5006 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(stmt->expression()));
5007 Pop();
5008 Goto(function_return(), state);
5009 } else {
5010 DCHECK(context->IsValue())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(context->IsValue())), 0)))
{ V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5010, "Check failed: %s."
, "context->IsValue()"); } } while (0);
5011 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(stmt->expression()));
5012 AddLeaveInlined(Pop(), state);
5013 }
5014 }
5015 set_current_block(NULL__null);
5016}
5017

5019void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitWithStatement(WithStatement* stmt) {
5020 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5020, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5021 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5021, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5022 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5022, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5023 return Bailout(kWithStatement);
5024}

5026
5027void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitSwitchStatement(SwitchStatement* stmt) {
5028 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5028, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5029 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5029, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5030 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5030, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5031
5032 ZoneList<CaseClause*>* clauses = stmt->cases();
5033 int clause_count = clauses->length();
5034 ZoneList<HBasicBlock*> body_blocks(clause_count, zone());
5035
5036 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(stmt->tag()));
5037 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->EntryId());
5038 HValue* tag_value = Top();
5039 Type* tag_type = stmt->tag()->bounds().lower;
5040
5041 // 1. Build all the tests, with dangling true branches
5042 BailoutId default_id = BailoutId::None();
5043 for (int i = 0; i < clause_count; ++i) {
5044 CaseClause* clause = clauses->at(i);
5045 if (clause->is_default()) {
5046 body_blocks.Add(NULL__null, zone());
5047 if (default_id.IsNone()) default_id = clause->EntryId();
5048 continue;
5049 }
5050
5051 // Generate a compare and branch.
5052 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForValue(clause->label()));
5053 if (current_block() == NULL__null) return Bailout(kUnsupportedSwitchStatement);
5054 HValue* label_value = Pop();
5055
5056 Type* label_type = clause->label()->bounds().lower;
5057 Type* combined_type = clause->compare_type();
5058 HControlInstruction* compare = BuildCompareInstruction(
5059 Token::EQ_STRICT, tag_value, label_value, tag_type, label_type,
5060 combined_type,
5061 ScriptPositionToSourcePosition(stmt->tag()->position()),
5062 ScriptPositionToSourcePosition(clause->label()->position()),
5063 PUSH_BEFORE_SIMULATE, clause->id());
5064
5065 HBasicBlock* next_test_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5066 HBasicBlock* body_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5067 body_blocks.Add(body_block, zone());
5068 compare->SetSuccessorAt(0, body_block);
5069 compare->SetSuccessorAt(1, next_test_block);
5070 FinishCurrentBlock(compare);
5071
5072 set_current_block(body_block);
5073 Drop(1); // tag_value
5074
5075 set_current_block(next_test_block);
5076 }
5077
5078 // Save the current block to use for the default or to join with the
5079 // exit.
5080 HBasicBlock* last_block = current_block();
5081 Drop(1); // tag_value
5082
5083 // 2. Loop over the clauses and the linked list of tests in lockstep,
5084 // translating the clause bodies.
5085 HBasicBlock* fall_through_block = NULL__null;
5086
5087 BreakAndContinueInfo break_info(stmt, scope());
5088 { BreakAndContinueScope push(&break_info, this);
5089 for (int i = 0; i < clause_count; ++i) {
5090 CaseClause* clause = clauses->at(i);
5091
5092 // Identify the block where normal (non-fall-through) control flow
5093 // goes to.
5094 HBasicBlock* normal_block = NULL__null;
5095 if (clause->is_default()) {
5096 if (last_block == NULL__null) continue;
5097 normal_block = last_block;
5098 last_block = NULL__null; // Cleared to indicate we've handled it.
5099 } else {
5100 normal_block = body_blocks[i];
5101 }
5102
5103 if (fall_through_block == NULL__null) {
5104 set_current_block(normal_block);
5105 } else {
5106 HBasicBlock* join = CreateJoin(fall_through_block,
5107 normal_block,
5108 clause->EntryId());
5109 set_current_block(join);
5110 }
5111
5112 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitStatements(clause->statements()));
5113 fall_through_block = current_block();
5114 }
5115 }
5116
5117 // Create an up-to-3-way join. Use the break block if it exists since
5118 // it's already a join block.
5119 HBasicBlock* break_block = break_info.break_block();
5120 if (break_block == NULL__null) {
5121 set_current_block(CreateJoin(fall_through_block,
5122 last_block,
5123 stmt->ExitId()));
5124 } else {
5125 if (fall_through_block != NULL__null) Goto(fall_through_block, break_block);
5126 if (last_block != NULL__null) Goto(last_block, break_block);
5127 break_block->SetJoinId(stmt->ExitId());
5128 set_current_block(break_block);
5129 }
5130}
5131
5132
5133void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitLoopBody(IterationStatement* stmt,
5134 HBasicBlock* loop_entry) {
5135 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->StackCheckId());
5136 HStackCheck* stack_check =
5137 HStackCheck::cast(Add<HStackCheck>(HStackCheck::kBackwardsBranch));
5138 DCHECK(loop_entry->IsLoopHeader())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(loop_entry->IsLoopHeader()
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5138, "Check failed: %s."
, "loop_entry->IsLoopHeader()"); } } while (0);
5139 loop_entry->loop_information()->set_stack_check(stack_check);
5140 CHECK_BAILOUT(Visit(stmt->body()));
5141}
5142
5143
5144void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitDoWhileStatement(DoWhileStatement* stmt) {
5145 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5145, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5146 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5146, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5147 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5147, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5148 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5148, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5149 HBasicBlock* loop_entry = BuildLoopEntry(stmt);
5150
5151 BreakAndContinueInfo break_info(stmt, scope());
5152 {
5153 BreakAndContinueScope push(&break_info, this);
5154 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitLoopBody(stmt, loop_entry));
5155 }
5156 HBasicBlock* body_exit =
5157 JoinContinue(stmt, current_block(), break_info.continue_block());
5158 HBasicBlock* loop_successor = NULL__null;
5159 if (body_exit != NULL__null && !stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
5160 set_current_block(body_exit);
5161 loop_successor = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5162 if (stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
5163 loop_entry->loop_information()->stack_check()->Eliminate();
5164 Goto(loop_successor);
5165 body_exit = NULL__null;
5166 } else {
5167 // The block for a true condition, the actual predecessor block of the
5168 // back edge.
5169 body_exit = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5170 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(stmt->cond(), body_exit, loop_successor));
5171 }
5172 if (body_exit != NULL__null && body_exit->HasPredecessor()) {
5173 body_exit->SetJoinId(stmt->BackEdgeId());
5174 } else {
5175 body_exit = NULL__null;
5176 }
5177 if (loop_successor->HasPredecessor()) {
5178 loop_successor->SetJoinId(stmt->ExitId());
5179 } else {
5180 loop_successor = NULL__null;
5181 }
5182 }
5183 HBasicBlock* loop_exit = CreateLoop(stmt,
5184 loop_entry,
5185 body_exit,
5186 loop_successor,
5187 break_info.break_block());
5188 set_current_block(loop_exit);
5189}
5190
5191
5192void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitWhileStatement(WhileStatement* stmt) {
5193 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5193, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5194 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5194, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5195 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5195, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5196 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5196, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5197 HBasicBlock* loop_entry = BuildLoopEntry(stmt);
5198
5199 // If the condition is constant true, do not generate a branch.
5200 HBasicBlock* loop_successor = NULL__null;
5201 if (!stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
5202 HBasicBlock* body_entry = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5203 loop_successor = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5204 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(stmt->cond(), body_entry, loop_successor));
5205 if (body_entry->HasPredecessor()) {
5206 body_entry->SetJoinId(stmt->BodyId());
5207 set_current_block(body_entry);
5208 }
5209 if (loop_successor->HasPredecessor()) {
5210 loop_successor->SetJoinId(stmt->ExitId());
5211 } else {
5212 loop_successor = NULL__null;
5213 }
5214 }
5215
5216 BreakAndContinueInfo break_info(stmt, scope());
5217 if (current_block() != NULL__null) {
5218 BreakAndContinueScope push(&break_info, this);
5219 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitLoopBody(stmt, loop_entry));
5220 }
5221 HBasicBlock* body_exit =
5222 JoinContinue(stmt, current_block(), break_info.continue_block());
5223 HBasicBlock* loop_exit = CreateLoop(stmt,
5224 loop_entry,
5225 body_exit,
5226 loop_successor,
5227 break_info.break_block());
5228 set_current_block(loop_exit);
5229}
5230
5231
5232void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitForStatement(ForStatement* stmt) {
5233 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5233, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5234 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5234, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5235 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5235, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5236 if (stmt->init() != NULL__null) {
5237 CHECK_ALIVE(Visit(stmt->init()));
5238 }
5239 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5239, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5240 HBasicBlock* loop_entry = BuildLoopEntry(stmt);
5241
5242 HBasicBlock* loop_successor = NULL__null;
5243 if (stmt->cond() != NULL__null) {
5244 HBasicBlock* body_entry = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5245 loop_successor = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5246 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(stmt->cond(), body_entry, loop_successor));
5247 if (body_entry->HasPredecessor()) {
5248 body_entry->SetJoinId(stmt->BodyId());
5249 set_current_block(body_entry);
5250 }
5251 if (loop_successor->HasPredecessor()) {
5252 loop_successor->SetJoinId(stmt->ExitId());
5253 } else {
5254 loop_successor = NULL__null;
5255 }
5256 }
5257
5258 BreakAndContinueInfo break_info(stmt, scope());
5259 if (current_block() != NULL__null) {
5260 BreakAndContinueScope push(&break_info, this);
5261 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitLoopBody(stmt, loop_entry));
5262 }
5263 HBasicBlock* body_exit =
5264 JoinContinue(stmt, current_block(), break_info.continue_block());
5265
5266 if (stmt->next() != NULL__null && body_exit != NULL__null) {
5267 set_current_block(body_exit);
5268 CHECK_BAILOUT(Visit(stmt->next()));
5269 body_exit = current_block();
5270 }
5271
5272 HBasicBlock* loop_exit = CreateLoop(stmt,
5273 loop_entry,
5274 body_exit,
5275 loop_successor,
5276 break_info.break_block());
5277 set_current_block(loop_exit);
5278}
5279
5280
5281void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitForInStatement(ForInStatement* stmt) {
5282 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5282, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5283 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5283, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5284 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5284, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5285
5286 if (!stmt->each()->IsVariableProxy() ||
5287 !stmt->each()->AsVariableProxy()->var()->IsStackLocal()) {
5288 return Bailout(kForInStatementWithNonLocalEachVariable);
5289 }
5290
5291 Variable* each_var = stmt->each()->AsVariableProxy()->var();
5292
5293 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(stmt->enumerable()));
5294 HValue* enumerable = Top(); // Leave enumerable at the top.
5295
5296 IfBuilder if_undefined_or_null(this);
5297 if_undefined_or_null.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(
5298 enumerable, graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
5299 if_undefined_or_null.Or();
5300 if_undefined_or_null.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(
5301 enumerable, graph()->GetConstantNull());
5302 if_undefined_or_null.ThenDeopt(Deoptimizer::kUndefinedOrNullInForIn);
5303 if_undefined_or_null.End();
5304 BuildForInBody(stmt, each_var, enumerable);
5305}
5306
5307
5308void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildForInBody(ForInStatement* stmt,
5309 Variable* each_var,
5310 HValue* enumerable) {
5311 Handle<Map> meta_map = isolate()->factory()->meta_map();
5312 bool fast = stmt->for_in_type() == ForInStatement::FAST_FOR_IN;
5313 BuildCheckHeapObject(enumerable);
5314 Add<HCheckInstanceType>(enumerable, HCheckInstanceType::IS_JS_RECEIVER);
5315 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->ToObjectId());
5316 if (fast) {
5317 HForInPrepareMap* map = Add<HForInPrepareMap>(enumerable);
5318 Push(map);
5319 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->EnumId());
5320 Drop(1);
5321 Add<HCheckMaps>(map, meta_map);
5322
5323 HForInCacheArray* array = Add<HForInCacheArray>(
5324 enumerable, map, DescriptorArray::kEnumCacheBridgeCacheIndex);
5325 HValue* enum_length = BuildEnumLength(map);
5326
5327 HForInCacheArray* index_cache = Add<HForInCacheArray>(
5328 enumerable, map, DescriptorArray::kEnumCacheBridgeIndicesCacheIndex);
5329 array->set_index_cache(index_cache);
5330
5331 Push(map);
5332 Push(array);
5333 Push(enum_length);
5334 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->PrepareId());
5335 } else {
5336 Runtime::FunctionId function_id = Runtime::kForInEnumerate;
5337 Add<HPushArguments>(enumerable);
5338 HCallRuntime* array =
5339 Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(function_id), 1);
5340 Push(array);
5341 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->EnumId());
5342 Drop(1);
5343
5344 IfBuilder if_fast(this);
5345 if_fast.If<HCompareMap>(array, meta_map);
5346 if_fast.Then();
5347 {
5348 HValue* cache_map = array;
5349 HForInCacheArray* cache = Add<HForInCacheArray>(
5350 enumerable, cache_map, DescriptorArray::kEnumCacheBridgeCacheIndex);
5351 HValue* enum_length = BuildEnumLength(cache_map);
5352 Push(cache_map);
5353 Push(cache);
5354 Push(enum_length);
5355 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->PrepareId(), FIXED_SIMULATE);
5356 }
5357 if_fast.Else();
5358 {
5359 Push(graph()->GetConstant1());
5360 Push(array);
5361 Push(AddLoadFixedArrayLength(array));
5362 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->PrepareId(), FIXED_SIMULATE);
5363 }
5364 }
5365
5366 Push(graph()->GetConstant0());
5367
5368 HBasicBlock* loop_entry = BuildLoopEntry(stmt);
5369
5370 // Reload the values to ensure we have up-to-date values inside of the loop.
5371 // This is relevant especially for OSR where the values don't come from the
5372 // computation above, but from the OSR entry block.
5373 HValue* index = environment()->ExpressionStackAt(0);
5374 HValue* limit = environment()->ExpressionStackAt(1);
5375 HValue* array = environment()->ExpressionStackAt(2);
5376 HValue* type = environment()->ExpressionStackAt(3);
5377 enumerable = environment()->ExpressionStackAt(4);
5378
5379 // Check that we still have more keys.
5380 HCompareNumericAndBranch* compare_index =
5381 New<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(index, limit, Token::LT);
5382 compare_index->set_observed_input_representation(
5383 Representation::Smi(), Representation::Smi());
5384
5385 HBasicBlock* loop_body = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5386 HBasicBlock* loop_successor = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5387
5388 compare_index->SetSuccessorAt(0, loop_body);
5389 compare_index->SetSuccessorAt(1, loop_successor);
5390 FinishCurrentBlock(compare_index);
5391
5392 set_current_block(loop_successor);
5393 Drop(5);
5394
5395 set_current_block(loop_body);
5396
5397 // Compute the next enumerated value.
5398 HValue* key = Add<HLoadKeyed>(array, index, index, nullptr, FAST_ELEMENTS);
5399
5400 HBasicBlock* continue_block = nullptr;
5401 if (fast) {
5402 // Check if expected map still matches that of the enumerable.
5403 Add<HCheckMapValue>(enumerable, type);
5404 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->FilterId());
5405 } else {
5406 // We need the continue block here to be able to skip over invalidated keys.
5407 continue_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5408
5409 // We cannot use the IfBuilder here, since we need to be able to jump
5410 // over the loop body in case of undefined result from %ForInFilter,
5411 // and the poor soul that is the IfBuilder get's really confused about
5412 // such "advanced control flow requirements".
5413 HBasicBlock* if_fast = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5414 HBasicBlock* if_slow = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5415 HBasicBlock* if_slow_pass = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5416 HBasicBlock* if_slow_skip = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5417 HBasicBlock* if_join = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5418
5419 // Check if expected map still matches that of the enumerable.
5420 HValue* enumerable_map =
5421 Add<HLoadNamedField>(enumerable, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMap());
5422 FinishCurrentBlock(
5423 New<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(enumerable_map, type, if_fast, if_slow));
5424 set_current_block(if_fast);
5425 {
5426 // The enum cache for enumerable is still valid, no need to check key.
5427 Push(key);
5428 Goto(if_join);
5429 }
5430 set_current_block(if_slow);
5431 {
5432 // Check if key is still valid for enumerable.
5433 Add<HPushArguments>(enumerable, key);
5434 Runtime::FunctionId function_id = Runtime::kForInFilter;
5435 Push(Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(function_id), 2));
5436 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->FilterId());
5437 FinishCurrentBlock(New<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(
5438 Top(), graph()->GetConstantUndefined(), if_slow_skip, if_slow_pass));
5439 }
5440 set_current_block(if_slow_pass);
5441 { Goto(if_join); }
5442 set_current_block(if_slow_skip);
5443 {
5444 // The key is no longer valid for enumerable, skip it.
5445 Drop(1);
5446 Goto(continue_block);
5447 }
5448 if_join->SetJoinId(stmt->FilterId());
5449 set_current_block(if_join);
5450 key = Pop();
5451 }
5452
5453 Bind(each_var, key);
5454 Add<HSimulate>(stmt->AssignmentId());
5455
5456 BreakAndContinueInfo break_info(stmt, scope(), 5);
5457 break_info.set_continue_block(continue_block);
5458 {
5459 BreakAndContinueScope push(&break_info, this);
5460 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitLoopBody(stmt, loop_entry));
5461 }
5462
5463 HBasicBlock* body_exit =
5464 JoinContinue(stmt, current_block(), break_info.continue_block());
5465
5466 if (body_exit != NULL__null) {
5467 set_current_block(body_exit);
5468
5469 HValue* current_index = Pop();
5470 HValue* increment =
5471 AddUncasted<HAdd>(current_index, graph()->GetConstant1());
5472 increment->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
5473 Push(increment);
5474 body_exit = current_block();
5475 }
5476
5477 HBasicBlock* loop_exit = CreateLoop(stmt,
5478 loop_entry,
5479 body_exit,
5480 loop_successor,
5481 break_info.break_block());
5482
5483 set_current_block(loop_exit);
5484}

5524
5525void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitFunctionLiteral(FunctionLiteral* expr) {
5526 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5526, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5527 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5527, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5528 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5528, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5529 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(
5530 expr, current_info()->script(), top_info());
5531 // We also have a stack overflow if the recursive compilation did.
5532 if (HasStackOverflow()) return;
5533 // Use the fast case closure allocation code that allocates in new
5534 // space for nested functions that don't need literals cloning.
5535 HConstant* shared_info_value = Add<HConstant>(shared_info);
5536 HInstruction* instr;
5537 if (!expr->pretenure() && shared_info->num_literals() == 0) {
5538 FastNewClosureStub stub(isolate(), shared_info->language_mode(),
5539 shared_info->kind());
5540 FastNewClosureDescriptor descriptor(isolate());
5541 HValue* values[] = {context(), shared_info_value};
5542 HConstant* stub_value = Add<HConstant>(stub.GetCode());
5543 instr = New<HCallWithDescriptor>(stub_value, 0, descriptor,
5544 Vector<HValue*>(values, arraysize(values)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(values)))),
5545 NORMAL_CALL);
5546 } else {
5547 Add<HPushArguments>(shared_info_value);
5548 Runtime::FunctionId function_id =
5549 expr->pretenure() ? Runtime::kNewClosure_Tenured : Runtime::kNewClosure;
5550 instr = New<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(function_id), 1);
5551 }
5552 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());
5553}
