5580
5581void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitConditional(Conditional* expr) {
5582 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5582, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5583 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5583, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5584 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5584, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5585 HBasicBlock* cond_true = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5586 HBasicBlock* cond_false = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
5587 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(expr->condition(), cond_true, cond_false));
5588
5589 // Visit the true and false subexpressions in the same AST context as the
5590 // whole expression.
5591 if (cond_true->HasPredecessor()) {
5592 cond_true->SetJoinId(expr->ThenId());
5593 set_current_block(cond_true);
5594 CHECK_BAILOUT(Visit(expr->then_expression()));
5595 cond_true = current_block();
5596 } else {
5597 cond_true = NULL__null;
5598 }
5599
5600 if (cond_false->HasPredecessor()) {
5601 cond_false->SetJoinId(expr->ElseId());
5602 set_current_block(cond_false);
5603 CHECK_BAILOUT(Visit(expr->else_expression()));
5604 cond_false = current_block();
5605 } else {
5606 cond_false = NULL__null;
5607 }
5608
5609 if (!ast_context()->IsTest()) {
5610 HBasicBlock* join = CreateJoin(cond_true, cond_false, expr->id());
5611 set_current_block(join);
5612 if (join != NULL__null && !ast_context()->IsEffect()) {
5613 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
5614 }
5615 }
5616}
5617
5618
5619HOptimizedGraphBuilder::GlobalPropertyAccess
5620HOptimizedGraphBuilder::LookupGlobalProperty(Variable* var, LookupIterator* it,
5621 PropertyAccessType access_type) {
5622 if (var->is_this() || !current_info()->has_global_object()) {
5623 return kUseGeneric;
5624 }
5625
5626 switch (it->state()) {
5627 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
5628 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
5629 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
5630 case LookupIterator::INTEGER_INDEXED_EXOTIC:
5631 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
5632 return kUseGeneric;
5633 case LookupIterator::DATA:
5634 if (access_type == STORE && it->IsReadOnly()) return kUseGeneric;
5635 return kUseCell;
5636 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
5637 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
5638 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5638, "unreachable code"
);
5639 }
5640 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5640, "unreachable code"
);
5641 return kUseGeneric;
5642}
5643
5644
5645HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildContextChainWalk(Variable* var) {
5646 DCHECK(var->IsContextSlot())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(var->IsContextSlot())), 0)
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5646, "Check failed: %s."
, "var->IsContextSlot()"); } } while (0);
5647 HValue* context = environment()->context();
5648 int length = scope()->ContextChainLength(var->scope());
5649 while (length-- > 0) {
5650 context = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
5651 context, nullptr,
5652 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
5653 }
5654 return context;
5655}
5656
5657
5658void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitVariableProxy(VariableProxy* expr) {
5659 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5659, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5660 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5660, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5661 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5661, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5662 Variable* variable = expr->var();
5663 switch (variable->location()) {
5664 case VariableLocation::GLOBAL:
5665 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED: {
5666 if (IsLexicalVariableMode(variable->mode())) {
5667 // TODO(rossberg): should this be an DCHECK?
5668 return Bailout(kReferenceToGlobalLexicalVariable);
5669 }
5670 // Handle known global constants like 'undefined' specially to avoid a
5671 // load from a global cell for them.
5672 Handle<Object> constant_value =
5673 isolate()->factory()->GlobalConstantFor(variable->name());
5674 if (!constant_value.is_null()) {
5675 HConstant* instr = New<HConstant>(constant_value);
5676 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());
5677 }
5678
5679 Handle<JSGlobalObject> global(current_info()->global_object());
5680
5681 // Lookup in script contexts.
5682 {
5683 Handle<ScriptContextTable> script_contexts(
5684 global->native_context()->script_context_table());
5685 ScriptContextTable::LookupResult lookup;
5686 if (ScriptContextTable::Lookup(script_contexts, variable->name(),
5687 &lookup)) {
5688 Handle<Context> script_context = ScriptContextTable::GetContext(
5689 script_contexts, lookup.context_index);
5690 Handle<Object> current_value =
5691 FixedArray::get(*script_context, lookup.slot_index, isolate());
5692
5693 // If the values is not the hole, it will stay initialized,
5694 // so no need to generate a check.
5695 if (*current_value == *isolate()->factory()->the_hole_value()) {
5696 return Bailout(kReferenceToUninitializedVariable);
5697 }
5698 HInstruction* result = New<HLoadNamedField>(
5699 Add<HConstant>(script_context), nullptr,
5700 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(lookup.slot_index));
5701 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
5702 }
5703 }
5704
5705 LookupIterator it(global, variable->name(), LookupIterator::OWN);
5706 GlobalPropertyAccess type = LookupGlobalProperty(variable, &it, LOAD);
5707
5708 if (type == kUseCell) {
5709 Handle<PropertyCell> cell = it.GetPropertyCell();
5710 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumePropertyCell(cell);
5711 auto cell_type = it.property_details().cell_type();
5712 if (cell_type == PropertyCellType::kConstant ||
5713 cell_type == PropertyCellType::kUndefined) {
5714 Handle<Object> constant_object(cell->value(), isolate());
5715 if (constant_object->IsConsString()) {
5716 constant_object =
5717 String::Flatten(Handle<String>::cast(constant_object));
5718 }
5719 HConstant* constant = New<HConstant>(constant_object);
5720 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(constant, expr->id());
5721 } else {
5722 auto access = HObjectAccess::ForPropertyCellValue();
5723 UniqueSet<Map>* field_maps = nullptr;
5724 if (cell_type == PropertyCellType::kConstantType) {
5725 switch (cell->GetConstantType()) {
5726 case PropertyCellConstantType::kSmi:
5727 access = access.WithRepresentation(Representation::Smi());
5728 break;
5729 case PropertyCellConstantType::kStableMap: {
5730 // Check that the map really is stable. The heap object could
5731 // have mutated without the cell updating state. In that case,
5732 // make no promises about the loaded value except that it's a
5733 // heap object.
5734 access =
5735 access.WithRepresentation(Representation::HeapObject());
5736 Handle<Map> map(HeapObject::cast(cell->value())->map());
5737 if (map->is_stable()) {
5738 field_maps = new (zone())
5739 UniqueSet<Map>(Unique<Map>::CreateImmovable(map), zone());
5740 }
5741 break;
5742 }
5743 }
5744 }
5745 HConstant* cell_constant = Add<HConstant>(cell);
5746 HLoadNamedField* instr;
5747 if (field_maps == nullptr) {
5748 instr = New<HLoadNamedField>(cell_constant, nullptr, access);
5749 } else {
5750 instr = New<HLoadNamedField>(cell_constant, nullptr, access,
5751 field_maps, HType::HeapObject());
5752 }
5753 instr->ClearDependsOnFlag(kInobjectFields);
5754 instr->SetDependsOnFlag(kGlobalVars);
5755 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());
5756 }
5757 } else {
5758 HValue* global_object = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
5759 BuildGetNativeContext(), nullptr,
5760 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX));
5761 HLoadGlobalGeneric* instr = New<HLoadGlobalGeneric>(
5762 global_object, variable->name(), ast_context()->typeof_mode());
5763 instr->SetVectorAndSlot(handle(current_feedback_vector(), isolate()),
5764 expr->VariableFeedbackSlot());
5765 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());
5766 }
5767 }
5768
5769 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
5770 case VariableLocation::LOCAL: {
5771 HValue* value = LookupAndMakeLive(variable);
5772 if (value == graph()->GetConstantHole()) {
5773 DCHECK(IsDeclaredVariableMode(variable->mode()) &&do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsDeclaredVariableMode(variable
->mode()) && variable->mode() != VAR)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5774, "Check failed: %s.", "IsDeclaredVariableMode(variable->mode()) && variable->mode() != VAR"
); } } while (0)
5774 variable->mode() != VAR)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsDeclaredVariableMode(variable
->mode()) && variable->mode() != VAR)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5774, "Check failed: %s.", "IsDeclaredVariableMode(variable->mode()) && variable->mode() != VAR"
); } } while (0);
5775 return Bailout(kReferenceToUninitializedVariable);
5776 }
5777 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(value);
5778 }
5779
5780 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
5781 HValue* context = BuildContextChainWalk(variable);
5782 HLoadContextSlot::Mode mode;
5783 switch (variable->mode()) {
5784 case LET:
5785 case CONST:
5786 mode = HLoadContextSlot::kCheckDeoptimize;
5787 break;
5788 case CONST_LEGACY:
5789 mode = HLoadContextSlot::kCheckReturnUndefined;
5790 break;
5791 default:
5792 mode = HLoadContextSlot::kNoCheck;
5793 break;
5794 }
5795 HLoadContextSlot* instr =
5796 new(zone()) HLoadContextSlot(context, variable->index(), mode);
5797 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());
5798 }
5799
5800 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP:
5801 return Bailout(kReferenceToAVariableWhichRequiresDynamicLookup);
5802 }
5803}

5806void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitLiteral(Literal* expr) {

V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5807, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5808 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5808, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5809 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5809, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5810 HConstant* instr = New<HConstant>(expr->value());
5811 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());

5815void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitRegExpLiteral(RegExpLiteral* expr) {
5816 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5816, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5817 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5817, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5818 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5818, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5819 Callable callable = CodeFactory::FastCloneRegExp(isolate());
5820 HValue* values[] = {
5821 context(), AddThisFunction(), Add<HConstant>(expr->literal_index()),
5822 Add<HConstant>(expr->pattern()), Add<HConstant>(expr->flags())};
5823 HConstant* stub_value = Add<HConstant>(callable.code());
5824 HInstruction* instr = New<HCallWithDescriptor>(
5825 stub_value, 0, callable.descriptor(),
5826 Vector<HValue*>(values, arraysize(values)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(values)))), NORMAL_CALL);
5827 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());
5828}

5830
5831static bool CanInlinePropertyAccess(Handle<Map> map) {
5832 if (map->instance_type() == HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE) return true;
5833 if (map->instance_type() < FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE) return true;
5834 return map->IsJSObjectMap() && !map->is_dictionary_map() &&
5835 !map->has_named_interceptor() &&
5836 // TODO(verwaest): Whitelist contexts to which we have access.
5837 !map->is_access_check_needed();
5838}
5839
5840
5841// Determines whether the given array or object literal boilerplate satisfies
5842// all limits to be considered for fast deep-copying and computes the total
5843// size of all objects that are part of the graph.
5844static bool IsFastLiteral(Handle<JSObject> boilerplate,
5845 int max_depth,
5846 int* max_properties) {
5847 if (boilerplate->map()->is_deprecated() &&
5848 !JSObject::TryMigrateInstance(boilerplate)) {
5849 return false;
5850 }
5851
5852 DCHECK(max_depth >= 0 && *max_properties >= 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(max_depth >= 0 && *
max_properties >= 0)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 5852, "Check failed: %s.", "max_depth >= 0 && *max_properties >= 0"
); } } while (0);
5853 if (max_depth == 0) return false;
5854
5855 Isolate* isolate = boilerplate->GetIsolate();
5856 Handle<FixedArrayBase> elements(boilerplate->elements());
5857 if (elements->length() > 0 &&
5858 elements->map() != isolate->heap()->fixed_cow_array_map()) {
5859 if (boilerplate->HasFastSmiOrObjectElements()) {
5860 Handle<FixedArray> fast_elements = Handle<FixedArray>::cast(elements);
5861 int length = elements->length();
5862 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5863 if ((*max_properties)-- == 0) return false;
5864 Handle<Object> value(fast_elements->get(i), isolate);
5865 if (value->IsJSObject()) {
5866 Handle<JSObject> value_object = Handle<JSObject>::cast(value);
5867 if (!IsFastLiteral(value_object,
5868 max_depth - 1,
5869 max_properties)) {
5870 return false;
5871 }
5872 }
5873 }
5874 } else if (!boilerplate->HasFastDoubleElements()) {
5875 return false;
5876 }
5877 }
5878
5879 Handle<FixedArray> properties(boilerplate->properties());
5880 if (properties->length() > 0) {
5881 return false;
5882 } else {
5883 Handle<DescriptorArray> descriptors(
5884 boilerplate->map()->instance_descriptors());
5885 int limit = boilerplate->map()->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
5886 for (int i = 0; i < limit; i++) {
5887 PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
5888 if (details.type() != DATA) continue;
5889 if ((*max_properties)-- == 0) return false;
5890 FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(boilerplate->map(), i);
5891 if (boilerplate->IsUnboxedDoubleField(field_index)) continue;
5892 Handle<Object> value(boilerplate->RawFastPropertyAt(field_index),
5893 isolate);
5894 if (value->IsJSObject()) {
5895 Handle<JSObject> value_object = Handle<JSObject>::cast(value);
5896 if (!IsFastLiteral(value_object,
5897 max_depth - 1,
5898 max_properties)) {
5899 return false;
5900 }
5901 }
5902 }
5903 }
5904 return true;
5905}
5906
5907
5908void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitObjectLiteral(ObjectLiteral* expr) {
5909 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5909, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
5910 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5910, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
5911 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5911, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
5912
5913 Handle<JSFunction> closure = function_state()->compilation_info()->closure();
5914 HInstruction* literal;
5915
5916 // Check whether to use fast or slow deep-copying for boilerplate.
5917 int max_properties = kMaxFastLiteralProperties;
5918 Handle<Object> literals_cell(
5919 closure->literals()->literal(expr->literal_index()), isolate());
5920 Handle<AllocationSite> site;
5921 Handle<JSObject> boilerplate;
5922 if (!literals_cell->IsUndefined()) {
5923 // Retrieve the boilerplate
5924 site = Handle<AllocationSite>::cast(literals_cell);
5925 boilerplate = Handle<JSObject>(JSObject::cast(site->transition_info()),
5926 isolate());
5927 }
5928
5929 if (!boilerplate.is_null() &&
5930 IsFastLiteral(boilerplate, kMaxFastLiteralDepth, &max_properties)) {
5931 AllocationSiteUsageContext site_context(isolate(), site, false);
5932 site_context.EnterNewScope();
5933 literal = BuildFastLiteral(boilerplate, &site_context);
5934 site_context.ExitScope(site, boilerplate);
5935 } else {
5936 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
5937 Handle<FixedArray> constant_properties = expr->constant_properties();
5938 int literal_index = expr->literal_index();
5939 int flags = expr->ComputeFlags(true);
5940
5941 Add<HPushArguments>(AddThisFunction(), Add<HConstant>(literal_index),
5942 Add<HConstant>(constant_properties),
5943 Add<HConstant>(flags));
5944
5945 Runtime::FunctionId function_id = Runtime::kCreateObjectLiteral;
5946 literal = Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(function_id), 4);
5947 }
5948
5949 // The object is expected in the bailout environment during computation
5950 // of the property values and is the value of the entire expression.
5951 Push(literal);
5952 for (int i = 0; i < expr->properties()->length(); i++) {
5953 ObjectLiteral::Property* property = expr->properties()->at(i);
5954 if (property->is_computed_name()) return Bailout(kComputedPropertyName);
5955 if (property->IsCompileTimeValue()) continue;
5956
5957 Literal* key = property->key()->AsLiteral();
5958 Expression* value = property->value();
5959
5960 switch (property->kind()) {
5961 case ObjectLiteral::Property::MATERIALIZED_LITERAL:
5962 DCHECK(!CompileTimeValue::IsCompileTimeValue(value))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!CompileTimeValue::IsCompileTimeValue
(value))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5962
, "Check failed: %s.", "!CompileTimeValue::IsCompileTimeValue(value)"
); } } while (0);
5963 // Fall through.
5964 case ObjectLiteral::Property::COMPUTED:
5965 // It is safe to use [[Put]] here because the boilerplate already
5966 // contains computed properties with an uninitialized value.
5967 if (key->value()->IsInternalizedString()) {
5968 if (property->emit_store()) {
5969 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(value));
5970 HValue* value = Pop();
5971
5972 Handle<Map> map = property->GetReceiverType();
5973 Handle<String> name = key->AsPropertyName();
5974 HValue* store;
5975 FeedbackVectorSlot slot = property->GetSlot();
5976 if (map.is_null()) {
5977 // If we don't know the monomorphic type, do a generic store.
5978 CHECK_ALIVE(store = BuildNamedGeneric(STORE, NULL__null, slot, literal,
5979 name, value));
5980 } else {
5981 PropertyAccessInfo info(this, STORE, map, name);
5982 if (info.CanAccessMonomorphic()) {
5983 HValue* checked_literal = Add<HCheckMaps>(literal, map);
5984 DCHECK(!info.IsAccessorConstant())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!info.IsAccessorConstant())),
0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5984, "Check failed: %s."
, "!info.IsAccessorConstant()"); } } while (0);
5985 store = BuildMonomorphicAccess(
5986 &info, literal, checked_literal, value,
5987 BailoutId::None(), BailoutId::None());
5988 } else {
5989 CHECK_ALIVE(store = BuildNamedGeneric(STORE, NULL__null, slot,
5990 literal, name, value));
5991 }
5992 }
5993 if (store->IsInstruction()) {
5994 AddInstruction(HInstruction::cast(store));
5995 }
5996 DCHECK(store->HasObservableSideEffects())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(store->HasObservableSideEffects
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 5996, "Check failed: %s."
, "store->HasObservableSideEffects()"); } } while (0);
5997 Add<HSimulate>(key->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
5998
5999 // Add [[HomeObject]] to function literals.
6000 if (FunctionLiteral::NeedsHomeObject(property->value())) {
6001 Handle<Symbol> sym = isolate()->factory()->home_object_symbol();
6002 HInstruction* store_home = BuildNamedGeneric(
6003 STORE, NULL__null, property->GetSlot(1), value, sym, literal);
6004 AddInstruction(store_home);
6005 DCHECK(store_home->HasObservableSideEffects())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(store_home->HasObservableSideEffects
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6005, "Check failed: %s."
, "store_home->HasObservableSideEffects()"); } } while (0);
6006 Add<HSimulate>(property->value()->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
6007 }
6008 } else {
6009 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForEffect(value));
6010 }
6011 break;
6012 }
6013 // Fall through.
6014 case ObjectLiteral::Property::PROTOTYPE:
6015 case ObjectLiteral::Property::SETTER:
6016 case ObjectLiteral::Property::GETTER:
6017 return Bailout(kObjectLiteralWithComplexProperty);
6018 default: UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6018, "unreachable code"
);
6019 }
6020 }
6021
6022 if (expr->has_function()) {
6023 // Return the result of the transformation to fast properties
6024 // instead of the original since this operation changes the map
6025 // of the object. This makes sure that the original object won't
6026 // be used by other optimized code before it is transformed
6027 // (e.g. because of code motion).
6028 HToFastProperties* result = Add<HToFastProperties>(Pop());
6029 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(result);
6030 } else {
6031 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
6032 }
6033}
6034
6035
6036void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitArrayLiteral(ArrayLiteral* expr) {
6037 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6037, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
6038 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6038, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
6039 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6039, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
6040 ZoneList<Expression*>* subexprs = expr->values();
6041 int length = subexprs->length();
6042 HInstruction* literal;
6043
6044 Handle<AllocationSite> site;
6045 Handle<LiteralsArray> literals(environment()->closure()->literals(),
6046 isolate());
6047 bool uninitialized = false;
6048 Handle<Object> literals_cell(literals->literal(expr->literal_index()),
6049 isolate());
6050 Handle<JSObject> boilerplate_object;
6051 if (literals_cell->IsUndefined()) {
6052 uninitialized = true;
6053 Handle<Object> raw_boilerplate;
6054 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(do { if (!(Runtime::CreateArrayLiteralBoilerplate( isolate(),
literals, expr->constant_elements(), is_strong(function_language_mode
()))).ToHandle(&raw_boilerplate)) { do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!((isolate())->has_pending_exception())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6059, "Check failed: %s.", "(isolate())->has_pending_exception()"
); } } while (0); return Bailout(kArrayBoilerplateCreationFailed
); } } while (false)
6055 isolate(), raw_boilerplate,do { if (!(Runtime::CreateArrayLiteralBoilerplate( isolate(),
literals, expr->constant_elements(), is_strong(function_language_mode
()))).ToHandle(&raw_boilerplate)) { do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!((isolate())->has_pending_exception())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6059, "Check failed: %s.", "(isolate())->has_pending_exception()"
); } } while (0); return Bailout(kArrayBoilerplateCreationFailed
); } } while (false)
6056 Runtime::CreateArrayLiteralBoilerplate(do { if (!(Runtime::CreateArrayLiteralBoilerplate( isolate(),
literals, expr->constant_elements(), is_strong(function_language_mode
()))).ToHandle(&raw_boilerplate)) { do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!((isolate())->has_pending_exception())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6059, "Check failed: %s.", "(isolate())->has_pending_exception()"
); } } while (0); return Bailout(kArrayBoilerplateCreationFailed
); } } while (false)
6057 isolate(), literals, expr->constant_elements(),do { if (!(Runtime::CreateArrayLiteralBoilerplate( isolate(),
literals, expr->constant_elements(), is_strong(function_language_mode
()))).ToHandle(&raw_boilerplate)) { do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!((isolate())->has_pending_exception())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6059, "Check failed: %s.", "(isolate())->has_pending_exception()"
); } } while (0); return Bailout(kArrayBoilerplateCreationFailed
); } } while (false)
6058 is_strong(function_language_mode())),do { if (!(Runtime::CreateArrayLiteralBoilerplate( isolate(),
literals, expr->constant_elements(), is_strong(function_language_mode
()))).ToHandle(&raw_boilerplate)) { do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!((isolate())->has_pending_exception())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6059, "Check failed: %s.", "(isolate())->has_pending_exception()"
); } } while (0); return Bailout(kArrayBoilerplateCreationFailed
); } } while (false)
6059 Bailout(kArrayBoilerplateCreationFailed))do { if (!(Runtime::CreateArrayLiteralBoilerplate( isolate(),
literals, expr->constant_elements(), is_strong(function_language_mode
()))).ToHandle(&raw_boilerplate)) { do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!((isolate())->has_pending_exception())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6059, "Check failed: %s.", "(isolate())->has_pending_exception()"
); } } while (0); return Bailout(kArrayBoilerplateCreationFailed
); } } while (false);
6060
6061 boilerplate_object = Handle<JSObject>::cast(raw_boilerplate);
6062 AllocationSiteCreationContext creation_context(isolate());
6063 site = creation_context.EnterNewScope();
6064 if (JSObject::DeepWalk(boilerplate_object, &creation_context).is_null()) {
6065 return Bailout(kArrayBoilerplateCreationFailed);
6066 }
6067 creation_context.ExitScope(site, boilerplate_object);
6068 literals->set_literal(expr->literal_index(), *site);
6069
6070 if (boilerplate_object->elements()->map() ==
6071 isolate()->heap()->fixed_cow_array_map()) {
6072 isolate()->counters()->cow_arrays_created_runtime()->Increment();
6073 }
6074 } else {
6075 DCHECK(literals_cell->IsAllocationSite())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(literals_cell->IsAllocationSite
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6075, "Check failed: %s."
, "literals_cell->IsAllocationSite()"); } } while (0);
6076 site = Handle<AllocationSite>::cast(literals_cell);
6077 boilerplate_object = Handle<JSObject>(
6078 JSObject::cast(site->transition_info()), isolate());
6079 }
6080
6081 DCHECK(!boilerplate_object.is_null())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!boilerplate_object.is_null()
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6081, "Check failed: %s."
, "!boilerplate_object.is_null()"); } } while (0);
6082 DCHECK(site->SitePointsToLiteral())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(site->SitePointsToLiteral(
))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6082, "Check failed: %s."
, "site->SitePointsToLiteral()"); } } while (0);
6083
6084 ElementsKind boilerplate_elements_kind =
6085 boilerplate_object->GetElementsKind();
6086
6087 // Check whether to use fast or slow deep-copying for boilerplate.
6088 int max_properties = kMaxFastLiteralProperties;
6089 if (IsFastLiteral(boilerplate_object,
6090 kMaxFastLiteralDepth,
6091 &max_properties)) {
6092 AllocationSiteUsageContext site_context(isolate(), site, false);
6093 site_context.EnterNewScope();
6094 literal = BuildFastLiteral(boilerplate_object, &site_context);
6095 site_context.ExitScope(site, boilerplate_object);
6096 } else {
6097 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
6098 // Boilerplate already exists and constant elements are never accessed,
6099 // pass an empty fixed array to the runtime function instead.
6100 Handle<FixedArray> constants = isolate()->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
6101 int literal_index = expr->literal_index();
6102 int flags = expr->ComputeFlags(true);
6103
6104 Add<HPushArguments>(AddThisFunction(), Add<HConstant>(literal_index),
6105 Add<HConstant>(constants), Add<HConstant>(flags));
6106
6107 Runtime::FunctionId function_id = Runtime::kCreateArrayLiteral;
6108 literal = Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(function_id), 4);
6109
6110 // Register to deopt if the boilerplate ElementsKind changes.
6111 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumeTransitionStable(site);
6112 }
6113
6114 // The array is expected in the bailout environment during computation
6115 // of the property values and is the value of the entire expression.
6116 Push(literal);
6117
6118 HInstruction* elements = NULL__null;
6119
6120 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
6121 Expression* subexpr = subexprs->at(i);
6122 DCHECK(!subexpr->IsSpread())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!subexpr->IsSpread())), 0)
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6122, "Check failed: %s."
, "!subexpr->IsSpread()"); } } while (0);
6123
6124 // If the subexpression is a literal or a simple materialized literal it
6125 // is already set in the cloned array.
6126 if (CompileTimeValue::IsCompileTimeValue(subexpr)) continue;
6127
6128 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(subexpr));
6129 HValue* value = Pop();
6130 if (!Smi::IsValid(i)) return Bailout(kNonSmiKeyInArrayLiteral);
6131
6132 elements = AddLoadElements(literal);
6133
6134 HValue* key = Add<HConstant>(i);
6135
6136 switch (boilerplate_elements_kind) {
6137 case FAST_SMI_ELEMENTS:
6138 case FAST_HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
6139 case FAST_ELEMENTS:
6140 case FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
6141 case FAST_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
6142 case FAST_HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: {
6143 HStoreKeyed* instr = Add<HStoreKeyed>(elements, key, value, nullptr,
6144 boilerplate_elements_kind);
6145 instr->SetUninitialized(uninitialized);
6146 break;
6147 }
6148 default:
6149 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6149, "unreachable code"
);
6150 break;
6151 }
6152
6153 Add<HSimulate>(expr->GetIdForElement(i));
6154 }
6155
6156 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
6157}

6160HCheckMaps* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::AddCheckMap(HValue* object,
6161 Handle<Map> map) {
6162 BuildCheckHeapObject(object);
6163 return Add<HCheckMaps>(object, map);

6166
6167HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildLoadNamedField(
6168 PropertyAccessInfo* info,
6169 HValue* checked_object) {
6170 // See if this is a load for an immutable property
6171 if (checked_object->ActualValue()->IsConstant()) {
6172 Handle<Object> object(
6173 HConstant::cast(checked_object->ActualValue())->handle(isolate()));
6174
6175 if (object->IsJSObject()) {
6176 LookupIterator it(object, info->name(),
6177 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
6178 Handle<Object> value = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(&it);
6179 if (it.IsFound() && it.IsReadOnly() && !it.IsConfigurable()) {
6180 return New<HConstant>(value);
6181 }
6182 }
6183 }
6184
6185 HObjectAccess access = info->access();
6186 if (access.representation().IsDouble() &&
6187 (!FLAG_unbox_double_fields || !access.IsInobject())) {
6188 // Load the heap number.
6189 checked_object = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
6190 checked_object, nullptr,
6191 access.WithRepresentation(Representation::Tagged()));
6192 // Load the double value from it.
6193 access = HObjectAccess::ForHeapNumberValue();
6194 }
6195
6196 SmallMapList* map_list = info->field_maps();
6197 if (map_list->length() == 0) {
6198 return New<HLoadNamedField>(checked_object, checked_object, access);
6199 }
6200
6201 UniqueSet<Map>* maps = new(zone()) UniqueSet<Map>(map_list->length(), zone());
6202 for (int i = 0; i < map_list->length(); ++i) {
6203 maps->Add(Unique<Map>::CreateImmovable(map_list->at(i)), zone());
6204 }
6205 return New<HLoadNamedField>(
6206 checked_object, checked_object, access, maps, info->field_type());
6207}
6208
6209
6210HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildStoreNamedField(
6211 PropertyAccessInfo* info,
6212 HValue* checked_object,
6213 HValue* value) {
6214 bool transition_to_field = info->IsTransition();
6215 // TODO(verwaest): Move this logic into PropertyAccessInfo.
6216 HObjectAccess field_access = info->access();
6217
6218 HStoreNamedField *instr;
6219 if (field_access.representation().IsDouble() &&
6220 (!FLAG_unbox_double_fields || !field_access.IsInobject())) {
6221 HObjectAccess heap_number_access =
6222 field_access.WithRepresentation(Representation::Tagged());
6223 if (transition_to_field) {
6224 // The store requires a mutable HeapNumber to be allocated.
6225 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_side_effects(this);
6226 HInstruction* heap_number_size = Add<HConstant>(HeapNumber::kSize);
6227
6228 // TODO(hpayer): Allocation site pretenuring support.
6229 HInstruction* heap_number = Add<HAllocate>(heap_number_size,
6230 HType::HeapObject(),
6231 NOT_TENURED,
6232 MUTABLE_HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE);
6233 AddStoreMapConstant(
6234 heap_number, isolate()->factory()->mutable_heap_number_map());
6235 Add<HStoreNamedField>(heap_number, HObjectAccess::ForHeapNumberValue(),
6236 value);
6237 instr = New<HStoreNamedField>(checked_object->ActualValue(),
6238 heap_number_access,
6239 heap_number);
6240 } else {
6241 // Already holds a HeapNumber; load the box and write its value field.
6242 HInstruction* heap_number =
6243 Add<HLoadNamedField>(checked_object, nullptr, heap_number_access);
6244 instr = New<HStoreNamedField>(heap_number,
6245 HObjectAccess::ForHeapNumberValue(),
6246 value, STORE_TO_INITIALIZED_ENTRY);
6247 }
6248 } else {
6249 if (field_access.representation().IsHeapObject()) {
6250 BuildCheckHeapObject(value);
6251 }
6252
6253 if (!info->field_maps()->is_empty()) {
6254 DCHECK(field_access.representation().IsHeapObject())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(field_access.representation()
.IsHeapObject())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 6254, "Check failed: %s.", "field_access.representation().IsHeapObject()"
); } } while (0);
6255 value = Add<HCheckMaps>(value, info->field_maps());
6256 }
6257
6258 // This is a normal store.
6259 instr = New<HStoreNamedField>(
6260 checked_object->ActualValue(), field_access, value,
6261 transition_to_field ? INITIALIZING_STORE : STORE_TO_INITIALIZED_ENTRY);
6262 }
6263
6264 if (transition_to_field) {
6265 Handle<Map> transition(info->transition());
6266 DCHECK(!transition->is_deprecated())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!transition->is_deprecated
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6266, "Check failed: %s."
, "!transition->is_deprecated()"); } } while (0);
6267 instr->SetTransition(Add<HConstant>(transition));
6268 }
6269 return instr;
6270}

6272Handle<FieldType>
6273HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::GetFieldTypeFromMap(
6274 Handle<Map> map) const {
6275 DCHECK(IsFound())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsFound())), 0))) { V8_Fatal(
"../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6275, "Check failed: %s.", "IsFound()"
); } } while (0);
6276 DCHECK(number_ < map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(number_ < map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6276, "Check failed: %s."
, "number_ < map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors()"); } } while
(0);
6277 return handle(map->instance_descriptors()->GetFieldType(number_), isolate());
6278}
6279
6280bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::IsCompatible(
6281 PropertyAccessInfo* info) {
6282 if (!CanInlinePropertyAccess(map_)) return false;
6283
6284 // Currently only handle Type::Number as a polymorphic case.
6285 // TODO(verwaest): Support monomorphic handling of numbers with a HCheckNumber
6286 // instruction.
6287 if (IsNumberType()) return false;
6288
6289 // Values are only compatible for monomorphic load if they all behave the same
6290 // regarding value wrappers.
6291 if (IsValueWrapped() != info->IsValueWrapped()) return false;
6292
6293 if (!LookupDescriptor()) return false;
6294
6295 if (!IsFound()) {
6296 return (!info->IsFound() || info->has_holder()) &&
6297 map()->prototype() == info->map()->prototype();
6298 }
6299
6300 // Mismatch if the other access info found the property in the prototype
6301 // chain.
6302 if (info->has_holder()) return false;
6303
6304 if (IsAccessorConstant()) {
6305 return accessor_.is_identical_to(info->accessor_) &&
6306 api_holder_.is_identical_to(info->api_holder_);
6307 }
6308
6309 if (IsDataConstant()) {
6310 return constant_.is_identical_to(info->constant_);
6311 }
6312
6313 DCHECK(IsData())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsData())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 6313, "Check failed: %s.", "IsData()"); } } while (0);
6314 if (!info->IsData()) return false;
6315
6316 Representation r = access_.representation();
6317 if (IsLoad()) {
6318 if (!info->access_.representation().IsCompatibleForLoad(r)) return false;
6319 } else {
6320 if (!info->access_.representation().IsCompatibleForStore(r)) return false;
6321 }
6322 if (info->access_.offset() != access_.offset()) return false;
6323 if (info->access_.IsInobject() != access_.IsInobject()) return false;
6324 if (IsLoad()) {
6325 if (field_maps_.is_empty()) {
6326 info->field_maps_.Clear();
6327 } else if (!info->field_maps_.is_empty()) {
6328 for (int i = 0; i < field_maps_.length(); ++i) {
6329 info->field_maps_.AddMapIfMissing(field_maps_.at(i), info->zone());
6330 }
6331 info->field_maps_.Sort();
6332 }
6333 } else {
6334 // We can only merge stores that agree on their field maps. The comparison
6335 // below is safe, since we keep the field maps sorted.
6336 if (field_maps_.length() != info->field_maps_.length()) return false;
6337 for (int i = 0; i < field_maps_.length(); ++i) {
6338 if (!field_maps_.at(i).is_identical_to(info->field_maps_.at(i))) {
6339 return false;
6340 }
6341 }
6342 }
6343 info->GeneralizeRepresentation(r);
6344 info->field_type_ = info->field_type_.Combine(field_type_);
6345 return true;
6346}
6347
6348
6349bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::LookupDescriptor() {
6350 if (!map_->IsJSObjectMap()) return true;
6351 LookupDescriptor(*map_, *name_);
6352 return LoadResult(map_);
6353}
6354
6355
6356bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::LoadResult(Handle<Map> map) {
6357 if (!IsLoad() && IsProperty() && IsReadOnly()) {
6358 return false;
6359 }
6360
6361 if (IsData()) {
6362 // Construct the object field access.
6363 int index = GetLocalFieldIndexFromMap(map);
6364 access_ = HObjectAccess::ForField(map, index, representation(), name_);
6365
6366 // Load field map for heap objects.
6367 return LoadFieldMaps(map);
6368 } else if (IsAccessorConstant()) {
6369 Handle<Object> accessors = GetAccessorsFromMap(map);
6370 if (!accessors->IsAccessorPair()) return false;
6371 Object* raw_accessor =
6372 IsLoad() ? Handle<AccessorPair>::cast(accessors)->getter()
6373 : Handle<AccessorPair>::cast(accessors)->setter();
6374 if (!raw_accessor->IsJSFunction() &&
6375 !raw_accessor->IsFunctionTemplateInfo())
6376 return false;
6377 Handle<Object> accessor = handle(HeapObject::cast(raw_accessor));
6378 CallOptimization call_optimization(accessor);
6379 if (call_optimization.is_simple_api_call()) {
6380 CallOptimization::HolderLookup holder_lookup;
6381 api_holder_ =
6382 call_optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(map_, &holder_lookup);
6383 }
6384 accessor_ = accessor;
6385 } else if (IsDataConstant()) {
6386 constant_ = GetConstantFromMap(map);
6387 }
6388
6389 return true;
6390}
6391
6392
6393bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::LoadFieldMaps(
6394 Handle<Map> map) {
6395 // Clear any previously collected field maps/type.
6396 field_maps_.Clear();
6397 field_type_ = HType::Tagged();
6398
6399 // Figure out the field type from the accessor map.
6400 Handle<FieldType> field_type = GetFieldTypeFromMap(map);
6401
6402 // Collect the (stable) maps from the field type.
6403 if (field_type->IsClass()) {
6404 DCHECK(access_.representation().IsHeapObject())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(access_.representation().IsHeapObject
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6404, "Check failed: %s."
, "access_.representation().IsHeapObject()"); } } while (0);
6405 Handle<Map> field_map = field_type->AsClass();
6406 if (field_map->is_stable()) {
6407 field_maps_.Add(field_map, zone());
6408 }
6409 }
6410
6411 if (field_maps_.is_empty()) {
6412 // Store is not safe if the field map was cleared.
6413 return IsLoad() || !field_type->IsNone();
6414 }
6415
6416 // Determine field HType from field type.
6417 field_type_ = HType::FromFieldType(field_type, zone());
6418 DCHECK(field_type_.IsHeapObject())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(field_type_.IsHeapObject())),
0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6418, "Check failed: %s."
, "field_type_.IsHeapObject()"); } } while (0);
6419
6420 // Add dependency on the map that introduced the field.
6421 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumeFieldType(GetFieldOwnerFromMap(map));
6422 return true;
6423}
6424
6425
6426bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::LookupInPrototypes() {
6427 Handle<Map> map = this->map();
6428 if (name_->IsPrivate()) {
6429 NotFound();
6430 return !map->has_hidden_prototype();
6431 }
6432
6433 while (map->prototype()->IsJSObject()) {
6434 holder_ = handle(JSObject::cast(map->prototype()));
6435 if (holder_->map()->is_deprecated()) {
6436 JSObject::TryMigrateInstance(holder_);
6437 }
6438 map = Handle<Map>(holder_->map());
6439 if (!CanInlinePropertyAccess(map)) {
6440 NotFound();
6441 return false;
6442 }
6443 LookupDescriptor(*map, *name_);
6444 if (IsFound()) return LoadResult(map);
6445 }
6446
6447 NotFound();
6448 return !map->prototype()->IsJSReceiver();
6449}

6451
6452bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::IsIntegerIndexedExotic() {
6453 InstanceType instance_type = map_->instance_type();
6454 return instance_type == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE && name_->IsString() &&
6455 IsSpecialIndex(isolate()->unicode_cache(), String::cast(*name_));
6456}

6458
6459bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::CanAccessMonomorphic() {
6460 if (!CanInlinePropertyAccess(map_)) return false;
6461 if (IsJSObjectFieldAccessor()) return IsLoad();
6462 if (IsJSArrayBufferViewFieldAccessor()) return IsLoad();
6463 if (map_->IsJSFunctionMap() && map_->is_constructor() &&
6464 !map_->has_non_instance_prototype() &&
6465 name_.is_identical_to(isolate()->factory()->prototype_string())) {
6466 return IsLoad();
6467 }
6468 if (!LookupDescriptor()) return false;
6469 if (IsFound()) return IsLoad() || !IsReadOnly();
6470 if (IsIntegerIndexedExotic()) return false;
6471 if (!LookupInPrototypes()) return false;
6472 if (IsLoad()) return true;
6473
6474 if (IsAccessorConstant()) return true;
6475 LookupTransition(*map_, *name_, NONE);
6476 if (IsTransitionToData() && map_->unused_property_fields() > 0) {
6477 // Construct the object field access.
6478 int descriptor = transition()->LastAdded();
6479 int index =
6480 transition()->instance_descriptors()->GetFieldIndex(descriptor) -
6481 map_->GetInObjectProperties();
6482 PropertyDetails details =
6483 transition()->instance_descriptors()->GetDetails(descriptor);
6484 Representation representation = details.representation();
6485 access_ = HObjectAccess::ForField(map_, index, representation, name_);
6486
6487 // Load field map for heap objects.
6488 return LoadFieldMaps(transition());
6489 }
6490 return false;
6491}
6492
6493
6494bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::CanAccessAsMonomorphic(
6495 SmallMapList* maps) {
6496 DCHECK(map_.is_identical_to(maps->first()))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(map_.is_identical_to(maps->
first()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6496
, "Check failed: %s.", "map_.is_identical_to(maps->first())"
); } } while (0);
6497 if (!CanAccessMonomorphic()) return false;
6498 STATIC_ASSERT(kMaxLoadPolymorphism == kMaxStorePolymorphism)static_assert(kMaxLoadPolymorphism == kMaxStorePolymorphism, "kMaxLoadPolymorphism == kMaxStorePolymorphism"
);
6499 if (maps->length() > kMaxLoadPolymorphism) return false;
6500 HObjectAccess access = HObjectAccess::ForMap(); // bogus default
6501 if (GetJSObjectFieldAccess(&access)) {
6502 for (int i = 1; i < maps->length(); ++i) {
6503 PropertyAccessInfo test_info(builder_, access_type_, maps->at(i), name_);
6504 HObjectAccess test_access = HObjectAccess::ForMap(); // bogus default
6505 if (!test_info.GetJSObjectFieldAccess(&test_access)) return false;
6506 if (!access.Equals(test_access)) return false;
6507 }
6508 return true;
6509 }
6510 if (GetJSArrayBufferViewFieldAccess(&access)) {
6511 for (int i = 1; i < maps->length(); ++i) {
6512 PropertyAccessInfo test_info(builder_, access_type_, maps->at(i), name_);
6513 HObjectAccess test_access = HObjectAccess::ForMap(); // bogus default
6514 if (!test_info.GetJSArrayBufferViewFieldAccess(&test_access)) {
6515 return false;
6516 }
6517 if (!access.Equals(test_access)) return false;
6518 }
6519 return true;
6520 }
6521
6522 // Currently only handle numbers as a polymorphic case.
6523 // TODO(verwaest): Support monomorphic handling of numbers with a HCheckNumber
6524 // instruction.
6525 if (IsNumberType()) return false;
6526
6527 // Multiple maps cannot transition to the same target map.
6528 DCHECK(!IsLoad() || !IsTransition())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!IsLoad() || !IsTransition())
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6528, "Check failed: %s."
, "!IsLoad() || !IsTransition()"); } } while (0);
6529 if (IsTransition() && maps->length() > 1) return false;
6530
6531 for (int i = 1; i < maps->length(); ++i) {
6532 PropertyAccessInfo test_info(builder_, access_type_, maps->at(i), name_);
6533 if (!test_info.IsCompatible(this)) return false;
6534 }
6535
6536 return true;
6537}

6540Handle<Map> HOptimizedGraphBuilder::PropertyAccessInfo::map() {
6541 Handle<JSFunction> ctor;
6542 if (Map::GetConstructorFunction(
6543 map_, handle(current_info()->closure()->context()->native_context()))
6544 .ToHandle(&ctor)) {
6545 return handle(ctor->initial_map());
6546 }
6547 return map_;
6548}

6563
6564HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildMonomorphicAccess(
6565 PropertyAccessInfo* info, HValue* object, HValue* checked_object,
6566 HValue* value, BailoutId ast_id, BailoutId return_id,
6567 bool can_inline_accessor) {
6568 HObjectAccess access = HObjectAccess::ForMap(); // bogus default
6569 if (info->GetJSObjectFieldAccess(&access)) {
6570 DCHECK(info->IsLoad())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(info->IsLoad())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6570, "Check failed: %s.", "info->IsLoad()"
); } } while (0);
6571 return New<HLoadNamedField>(object, checked_object, access);
6572 }
6573
6574 if (info->GetJSArrayBufferViewFieldAccess(&access)) {
6575 DCHECK(info->IsLoad())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(info->IsLoad())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6575, "Check failed: %s.", "info->IsLoad()"
); } } while (0);
6576 checked_object = Add<HCheckArrayBufferNotNeutered>(checked_object);
6577 return New<HLoadNamedField>(object, checked_object, access);
6578 }
6579
6580 if (info->name().is_identical_to(isolate()->factory()->prototype_string()) &&
6581 info->map()->IsJSFunctionMap() && info->map()->is_constructor()) {
6582 DCHECK(!info->map()->has_non_instance_prototype())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!info->map()->has_non_instance_prototype
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6582, "Check failed: %s."
, "!info->map()->has_non_instance_prototype()"); } } while
(0);
6583 return New<HLoadFunctionPrototype>(checked_object);
6584 }
6585
6586 HValue* checked_holder = checked_object;
6587 if (info->has_holder()) {
6588 Handle<JSObject> prototype(JSObject::cast(info->map()->prototype()));
6589 checked_holder = BuildCheckPrototypeMaps(prototype, info->holder());
6590 }
6591
6592 if (!info->IsFound()) {
6593 DCHECK(info->IsLoad())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(info->IsLoad())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6593, "Check failed: %s.", "info->IsLoad()"
); } } while (0);
6594 if (is_strong(function_language_mode())) {
6595 return New<HCallRuntime>(
6596 Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kThrowStrongModeImplicitConversion),
6597 0);
6598 } else {
6599 return graph()->GetConstantUndefined();
6600 }
6601 }
6602
6603 if (info->IsData()) {
6604 if (info->IsLoad()) {
6605 return BuildLoadNamedField(info, checked_holder);
6606 } else {
6607 return BuildStoreNamedField(info, checked_object, value);
6608 }
6609 }
6610
6611 if (info->IsTransition()) {
6612 DCHECK(!info->IsLoad())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!info->IsLoad())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6612, "Check failed: %s.", "!info->IsLoad()"
); } } while (0);
6613 return BuildStoreNamedField(info, checked_object, value);
6614 }
6615
6616 if (info->IsAccessorConstant()) {
6617 Push(checked_object);
6618 int argument_count = 1;
6619 if (!info->IsLoad()) {
6620 argument_count = 2;
6621 Push(value);
6622 }
6623
6624 if (info->accessor()->IsJSFunction() &&
6625 info->NeedsWrappingFor(Handle<JSFunction>::cast(info->accessor()))) {
6626 HValue* function = Add<HConstant>(info->accessor());
6627 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argument_count);
6628 return New<HCallFunction>(function, argument_count,
6629 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined);
6630 } else if (FLAG_inline_accessors && can_inline_accessor) {
6631 bool success = info->IsLoad()
6632 ? TryInlineGetter(info->accessor(), info->map(), ast_id, return_id)
6633 : TryInlineSetter(
6634 info->accessor(), info->map(), ast_id, return_id, value);
6635 if (success || HasStackOverflow()) return NULL__null;
6636 }
6637
6638 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argument_count);
6639 if (!info->accessor()->IsJSFunction()) {
6640 Bailout(kInliningBailedOut);
6641 return nullptr;
6642 }
6643 return BuildCallConstantFunction(Handle<JSFunction>::cast(info->accessor()),
6644 argument_count);
6645 }
6646
6647 DCHECK(info->IsDataConstant())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(info->IsDataConstant())), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6647, "Check failed: %s."
, "info->IsDataConstant()"); } } while (0);
6648 if (info->IsLoad()) {
6649 return New<HConstant>(info->constant());
6650 } else {
6651 return New<HCheckValue>(value, Handle<JSFunction>::cast(info->constant()));
6652 }
6653}
6654
6655
6656void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandlePolymorphicNamedFieldAccess(
6657 PropertyAccessType access_type, Expression* expr, FeedbackVectorSlot slot,
6658 BailoutId ast_id, BailoutId return_id, HValue* object, HValue* value,
6659 SmallMapList* maps, Handle<Name> name) {
6660 // Something did not match; must use a polymorphic load.
6661 int count = 0;
6662 HBasicBlock* join = NULL__null;
6663 HBasicBlock* number_block = NULL__null;
6664 bool handled_string = false;
6665
6666 bool handle_smi = false;
6667 STATIC_ASSERT(kMaxLoadPolymorphism == kMaxStorePolymorphism)static_assert(kMaxLoadPolymorphism == kMaxStorePolymorphism, "kMaxLoadPolymorphism == kMaxStorePolymorphism"
);
6668 int i;
6669 for (i = 0; i < maps->length() && count < kMaxLoadPolymorphism; ++i) {
6670 PropertyAccessInfo info(this, access_type, maps->at(i), name);
6671 if (info.IsStringType()) {
6672 if (handled_string) continue;
6673 handled_string = true;
6674 }
6675 if (info.CanAccessMonomorphic()) {
6676 count++;
6677 if (info.IsNumberType()) {
6678 handle_smi = true;
6679 break;
6680 }
6681 }
6682 }
6683
6684 if (i < maps->length()) {
6685 count = -1;
6686 maps->Clear();
6687 } else {
6688 count = 0;
6689 }
6690 HControlInstruction* smi_check = NULL__null;
6691 handled_string = false;
6692
6693 for (i = 0; i < maps->length() && count < kMaxLoadPolymorphism; ++i) {
6694 PropertyAccessInfo info(this, access_type, maps->at(i), name);
6695 if (info.IsStringType()) {
6696 if (handled_string) continue;
6697 handled_string = true;
6698 }
6699 if (!info.CanAccessMonomorphic()) continue;
6700
6701 if (count == 0) {
6702 join = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
6703 if (handle_smi) {
6704 HBasicBlock* empty_smi_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
6705 HBasicBlock* not_smi_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
6706 number_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
6707 smi_check = New<HIsSmiAndBranch>(
6708 object, empty_smi_block, not_smi_block);
6709 FinishCurrentBlock(smi_check);
6710 GotoNoSimulate(empty_smi_block, number_block);
6711 set_current_block(not_smi_block);
6712 } else {
6713 BuildCheckHeapObject(object);
6714 }
6715 }
6716 ++count;
6717 HBasicBlock* if_true = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
6718 HBasicBlock* if_false = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
6719 HUnaryControlInstruction* compare;
6720
6721 HValue* dependency;
6722 if (info.IsNumberType()) {
6723 Handle<Map> heap_number_map = isolate()->factory()->heap_number_map();
6724 compare = New<HCompareMap>(object, heap_number_map, if_true, if_false);
6725 dependency = smi_check;
6726 } else if (info.IsStringType()) {
6727 compare = New<HIsStringAndBranch>(object, if_true, if_false);
6728 dependency = compare;
6729 } else {
6730 compare = New<HCompareMap>(object, info.map(), if_true, if_false);
6731 dependency = compare;
6732 }
6733 FinishCurrentBlock(compare);
6734
6735 if (info.IsNumberType()) {
6736 GotoNoSimulate(if_true, number_block);
6737 if_true = number_block;
6738 }
6739
6740 set_current_block(if_true);
6741
6742 HValue* access =
6743 BuildMonomorphicAccess(&info, object, dependency, value, ast_id,
6744 return_id, FLAG_polymorphic_inlining);
6745
6746 HValue* result = NULL__null;
6747 switch (access_type) {
6748 case LOAD:
6749 result = access;
6750 break;
6751 case STORE:
6752 result = value;
6753 break;
6754 }
6755
6756 if (access == NULL__null) {
6757 if (HasStackOverflow()) return;
6758 } else {
6759 if (access->IsInstruction()) {
6760 HInstruction* instr = HInstruction::cast(access);
6761 if (!instr->IsLinked()) AddInstruction(instr);
6762 }
6763 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(result);
6764 }
6765
6766 if (current_block() != NULL__null) Goto(join);
6767 set_current_block(if_false);
6768 }
6769
6770 // Finish up. Unconditionally deoptimize if we've handled all the maps we
6771 // know about and do not want to handle ones we've never seen. Otherwise
6772 // use a generic IC.
6773 if (count == maps->length() && FLAG_deoptimize_uncommon_cases) {
6774 FinishExitWithHardDeoptimization(
6775 Deoptimizer::kUnknownMapInPolymorphicAccess);
6776 } else {
6777 HInstruction* instr =
6778 BuildNamedGeneric(access_type, expr, slot, object, name, value);
6779 AddInstruction(instr);
6780 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(access_type == LOAD ? instr : value);
6781
6782 if (join != NULL__null) {
6783 Goto(join);
6784 } else {
6785 Add<HSimulate>(ast_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
6786 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
6787 return;
6788 }
6789 }
6790
6791 DCHECK(join != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(join != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6791, "Check failed: %s.", "join != __null"
); } } while (0);
6792 if (join->HasPredecessor()) {
6793 join->SetJoinId(ast_id);
6794 set_current_block(join);
6795 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
6796 } else {
6797 set_current_block(NULL__null);
6798 }
6799}

6801static bool ComputeReceiverTypes(Expression* expr, HValue* receiver,
6802 SmallMapList** t,
6803 HOptimizedGraphBuilder* builder) {
6804 Zone* zone = builder->zone();
6805 SmallMapList* maps = expr->GetReceiverTypes();
6
←
'maps' initialized here
→
6806 *t = maps;
6807 bool monomorphic = expr->IsMonomorphic();
6808 if (maps != NULL__null && receiver->HasMonomorphicJSObjectType()) {
7
←
Assuming pointer value is null
→
6809 if (maps->length() > 0) {
6810 Map* root_map = receiver->GetMonomorphicJSObjectMap()->FindRootMap();
6811 maps->FilterForPossibleTransitions(root_map);
6812 monomorphic = maps->length() == 1;
6813 } else {
6814 // No type feedback, see if we can infer the type. This is safely
6815 // possible if the receiver had a known map at some point, and no
6816 // map-changing stores have happened to it since.
6817 Handle<Map> candidate_map = receiver->GetMonomorphicJSObjectMap();
6818 if (candidate_map->is_observed()) return false;
6819 for (HInstruction* current = builder->current_block()->last();
6820 current != nullptr; current = current->previous()) {
6821 if (current->IsBlockEntry()) break;
6822 if (current->CheckChangesFlag(kMaps)) {
6823 // Only allow map changes that store the candidate map. We don't
6824 // need to care which object the map is being written into.
6825 if (!current->IsStoreNamedField()) break;
6826 HStoreNamedField* map_change = HStoreNamedField::cast(current);
6827 if (!map_change->value()->IsConstant()) break;
6828 HConstant* map_constant = HConstant::cast(map_change->value());
6829 if (!map_constant->representation().IsTagged()) break;
6830 Handle<Object> map = map_constant->handle(builder->isolate());
6831 if (!map.is_identical_to(candidate_map)) break;
6832 }
6833 if (current == receiver) {
6834 // We made it all the way back to the receiver without encountering
6835 // a map change! So we can assume that the receiver still has the
6836 // candidate_map we know about.
6837 maps->Add(candidate_map, zone);
6838 monomorphic = true;
6839 break;
6840 }
6841 }
6842 }
6843 }
6844 return monomorphic && CanInlinePropertyAccess(maps->first());
8
←
Called C++ object pointer is null
6845}

6859 bool is_uninitialized) {

); } } while (0);

6900void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandlePropertyAssignment(Assignment* expr) {
6901 Property* prop = expr->target()->AsProperty();
6902 DCHECK(prop != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(prop != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6902, "Check failed: %s.", "prop != __null"
); } } while (0);
6903 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->obj()));
6904 if (!prop->key()->IsPropertyName()) {
6905 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->key()));
6906 }
6907 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->value()));
6908 BuildStore(expr, prop, expr->AssignmentSlot(), expr->id(),
6909 expr->AssignmentId(), expr->IsUninitialized());

6913// Because not every expression has a position and there is not common
6914// superclass of Assignment and CountOperation, we cannot just pass the
6915// owning expression instead of position and ast_id separately.
6916void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandleGlobalVariableAssignment(
6917 Variable* var, HValue* value, FeedbackVectorSlot slot, BailoutId ast_id) {
6918 Handle<JSGlobalObject> global(current_info()->global_object());
6919
6920 // Lookup in script contexts.
6921 {
6922 Handle<ScriptContextTable> script_contexts(
6923 global->native_context()->script_context_table());
6924 ScriptContextTable::LookupResult lookup;
6925 if (ScriptContextTable::Lookup(script_contexts, var->name(), &lookup)) {
6926 if (lookup.mode == CONST) {
6927 return Bailout(kNonInitializerAssignmentToConst);
6928 }
6929 Handle<Context> script_context =
6930 ScriptContextTable::GetContext(script_contexts, lookup.context_index);
6931
6932 Handle<Object> current_value =
6933 FixedArray::get(*script_context, lookup.slot_index, isolate());
6934
6935 // If the values is not the hole, it will stay initialized,
6936 // so no need to generate a check.
6937 if (*current_value == *isolate()->factory()->the_hole_value()) {
6938 return Bailout(kReferenceToUninitializedVariable);
6939 }
6940
6941 HStoreNamedField* instr = Add<HStoreNamedField>(
6942 Add<HConstant>(script_context),
6943 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(lookup.slot_index), value);
6944 USE(instr);
6945 DCHECK(instr->HasObservableSideEffects())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(instr->HasObservableSideEffects
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 6945, "Check failed: %s."
, "instr->HasObservableSideEffects()"); } } while (0);
6946 Add<HSimulate>(ast_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
6947 return;
6948 }
6949 }
6950
6951 LookupIterator it(global, var->name(), LookupIterator::OWN);
6952 GlobalPropertyAccess type = LookupGlobalProperty(var, &it, STORE);
6953 if (type == kUseCell) {
6954 Handle<PropertyCell> cell = it.GetPropertyCell();
6955 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumePropertyCell(cell);
6956 auto cell_type = it.property_details().cell_type();
6957 if (cell_type == PropertyCellType::kConstant ||
6958 cell_type == PropertyCellType::kUndefined) {
6959 Handle<Object> constant(cell->value(), isolate());
6960 if (value->IsConstant()) {
6961 HConstant* c_value = HConstant::cast(value);
6962 if (!constant.is_identical_to(c_value->handle(isolate()))) {
6963 Add<HDeoptimize>(Deoptimizer::kConstantGlobalVariableAssignment,
6964 Deoptimizer::EAGER);
6965 }
6966 } else {
6967 HValue* c_constant = Add<HConstant>(constant);
6968 IfBuilder builder(this);
6969 if (constant->IsNumber()) {
6970 builder.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(value, c_constant, Token::EQ);
6971 } else {
6972 builder.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(value, c_constant);
6973 }
6974 builder.Then();
6975 builder.Else();
6976 Add<HDeoptimize>(Deoptimizer::kConstantGlobalVariableAssignment,
6977 Deoptimizer::EAGER);
6978 builder.End();
6979 }
6980 }
6981 HConstant* cell_constant = Add<HConstant>(cell);
6982 auto access = HObjectAccess::ForPropertyCellValue();
6983 if (cell_type == PropertyCellType::kConstantType) {
6984 switch (cell->GetConstantType()) {
6985 case PropertyCellConstantType::kSmi:
6986 access = access.WithRepresentation(Representation::Smi());
6987 break;
6988 case PropertyCellConstantType::kStableMap: {
6989 // The map may no longer be stable, deopt if it's ever different from
6990 // what is currently there, which will allow for restablization.
6991 Handle<Map> map(HeapObject::cast(cell->value())->map());
6992 Add<HCheckHeapObject>(value);
6993 value = Add<HCheckMaps>(value, map);
6994 access = access.WithRepresentation(Representation::HeapObject());
6995 break;
6996 }
6997 }
6998 }
6999 HInstruction* instr = Add<HStoreNamedField>(cell_constant, access, value);
7000 instr->ClearChangesFlag(kInobjectFields);
7001 instr->SetChangesFlag(kGlobalVars);
7002 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
7003 Add<HSimulate>(ast_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
7004 }
7005 } else {
7006 HValue* global_object = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
7007 BuildGetNativeContext(), nullptr,
7008 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX));
7009 HStoreNamedGeneric* instr =
7010 Add<HStoreNamedGeneric>(global_object, var->name(), value,
7011 function_language_mode(), PREMONOMORPHIC);
7012 Handle<TypeFeedbackVector> vector =
7013 handle(current_feedback_vector(), isolate());
7014 instr->SetVectorAndSlot(vector, slot);
7015 USE(instr);
7016 DCHECK(instr->HasObservableSideEffects())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(instr->HasObservableSideEffects
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7016, "Check failed: %s."
, "instr->HasObservableSideEffects()"); } } while (0);
7017 Add<HSimulate>(ast_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
7018 }
7019}
7020
7021
7022void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandleCompoundAssignment(Assignment* expr) {
7023 Expression* target = expr->target();
7024 VariableProxy* proxy = target->AsVariableProxy();
7025 Property* prop = target->AsProperty();
7026 DCHECK(proxy == NULL || prop == NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(proxy == __null || prop == __null
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7026, "Check failed: %s."
, "proxy == __null || prop == __null"); } } while (0);
7027
7028 // We have a second position recorded in the FullCodeGenerator to have
7029 // type feedback for the binary operation.
7030 BinaryOperation* operation = expr->binary_operation();
7031
7032 if (proxy != NULL__null) {
7033 Variable* var = proxy->var();
7034 if (var->mode() == LET) {
7035 return Bailout(kUnsupportedLetCompoundAssignment);
7036 }
7037
7038 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(operation));
7039
7040 switch (var->location()) {
7041 case VariableLocation::GLOBAL:
7042 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
7043 HandleGlobalVariableAssignment(var, Top(), expr->AssignmentSlot(),
7044 expr->AssignmentId());
7045 break;
7046
7047 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
7048 case VariableLocation::LOCAL:
7049 if (var->mode() == CONST_LEGACY) {
7050 return Bailout(kUnsupportedConstCompoundAssignment);
7051 }
7052 if (var->mode() == CONST) {
7053 return Bailout(kNonInitializerAssignmentToConst);
7054 }
7055 BindIfLive(var, Top());
7056 break;
7057
7058 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
7059 // Bail out if we try to mutate a parameter value in a function
7060 // using the arguments object. We do not (yet) correctly handle the
7061 // arguments property of the function.
7062 if (current_info()->scope()->arguments() != NULL__null) {
7063 // Parameters will be allocated to context slots. We have no
7064 // direct way to detect that the variable is a parameter so we do
7065 // a linear search of the parameter variables.
7066 int count = current_info()->scope()->num_parameters();
7067 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
7068 if (var == current_info()->scope()->parameter(i)) {
7069 Bailout(kAssignmentToParameterFunctionUsesArgumentsObject);
7070 }
7071 }
7072 }
7073
7074 HStoreContextSlot::Mode mode;
7075
7076 switch (var->mode()) {
7077 case LET:
7078 mode = HStoreContextSlot::kCheckDeoptimize;
7079 break;
7080 case CONST:
7081 return Bailout(kNonInitializerAssignmentToConst);
7082 case CONST_LEGACY:
7083 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
7084 default:
7085 mode = HStoreContextSlot::kNoCheck;
7086 }
7087
7088 HValue* context = BuildContextChainWalk(var);
7089 HStoreContextSlot* instr = Add<HStoreContextSlot>(
7090 context, var->index(), mode, Top());
7091 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
7092 Add<HSimulate>(expr->AssignmentId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
7093 }
7094 break;
7095 }
7096
7097 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP:
7098 return Bailout(kCompoundAssignmentToLookupSlot);
7099 }
7100 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
7101
7102 } else if (prop != NULL__null) {
7103 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->obj()));
7104 HValue* object = Top();
7105 HValue* key = NULL__null;
7106 if (!prop->key()->IsPropertyName() || prop->IsStringAccess()) {
7107 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->key()));
7108 key = Top();
7109 }
7110
7111 CHECK_ALIVE(PushLoad(prop, object, key));
7112
7113 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->value()));
7114 HValue* right = Pop();
7115 HValue* left = Pop();
7116
7117 Push(BuildBinaryOperation(operation, left, right, PUSH_BEFORE_SIMULATE));
7118
7119 BuildStore(expr, prop, expr->AssignmentSlot(), expr->id(),
7120 expr->AssignmentId(), expr->IsUninitialized());
7121 } else {
7122 return Bailout(kInvalidLhsInCompoundAssignment);
7123 }
7124}
7125
7126
7127void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitAssignment(Assignment* expr) {
7128 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7128, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
7129 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7129, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
7130 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7130, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
7131
7132 VariableProxy* proxy = expr->target()->AsVariableProxy();
7133 Property* prop = expr->target()->AsProperty();
7134 DCHECK(proxy == NULL || prop == NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(proxy == __null || prop == __null
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7134, "Check failed: %s."
, "proxy == __null || prop == __null"); } } while (0);
7135
7136 if (expr->is_compound()) {
7137 HandleCompoundAssignment(expr);
7138 return;
7139 }
7140
7141 if (prop != NULL__null) {
7142 HandlePropertyAssignment(expr);
7143 } else if (proxy != NULL__null) {
7144 Variable* var = proxy->var();
7145
7146 if (var->mode() == CONST) {
7147 if (expr->op() != Token::INIT) {
7148 return Bailout(kNonInitializerAssignmentToConst);
7149 }
7150 } else if (var->mode() == CONST_LEGACY) {
7151 if (expr->op() != Token::INIT) {
7152 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->value()));
7153 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
7154 }
7155
7156 if (var->IsStackAllocated()) {
7157 // We insert a use of the old value to detect unsupported uses of const
7158 // variables (e.g. initialization inside a loop).
7159 HValue* old_value = environment()->Lookup(var);
7160 Add<HUseConst>(old_value);
7161 }
7162 }
7163
7164 if (proxy->IsArguments()) return Bailout(kAssignmentToArguments);
7165
7166 // Handle the assignment.
7167 switch (var->location()) {
7168 case VariableLocation::GLOBAL:
7169 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
7170 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->value()));
7171 HandleGlobalVariableAssignment(var, Top(), expr->AssignmentSlot(),
7172 expr->AssignmentId());
7173 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
7174
7175 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
7176 case VariableLocation::LOCAL: {
7177 // Perform an initialization check for let declared variables
7178 // or parameters.
7179 if (var->mode() == LET && expr->op() == Token::ASSIGN) {
7180 HValue* env_value = environment()->Lookup(var);
7181 if (env_value == graph()->GetConstantHole()) {
7182 return Bailout(kAssignmentToLetVariableBeforeInitialization);
7183 }
7184 }
7185 // We do not allow the arguments object to occur in a context where it
7186 // may escape, but assignments to stack-allocated locals are
7187 // permitted.
7188 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->value(), ARGUMENTS_ALLOWED));
7189 HValue* value = Pop();
7190 BindIfLive(var, value);
7191 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(value);
7192 }
7193
7194 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
7195 // Bail out if we try to mutate a parameter value in a function using
7196 // the arguments object. We do not (yet) correctly handle the
7197 // arguments property of the function.
7198 if (current_info()->scope()->arguments() != NULL__null) {
7199 // Parameters will rewrite to context slots. We have no direct way
7200 // to detect that the variable is a parameter.
7201 int count = current_info()->scope()->num_parameters();
7202 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
7203 if (var == current_info()->scope()->parameter(i)) {
7204 return Bailout(kAssignmentToParameterInArgumentsObject);
7205 }
7206 }
7207 }
7208
7209 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->value()));
7210 HStoreContextSlot::Mode mode;
7211 if (expr->op() == Token::ASSIGN) {
7212 switch (var->mode()) {
7213 case LET:
7214 mode = HStoreContextSlot::kCheckDeoptimize;
7215 break;
7216 case CONST:
7217 // This case is checked statically so no need to
7218 // perform checks here
7219 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7219, "unreachable code"
);
7220 case CONST_LEGACY:
7221 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
7222 default:
7223 mode = HStoreContextSlot::kNoCheck;
7224 }
7225 } else {
7226 DCHECK_EQ(Token::INIT, expr->op())do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (Token::
INIT), (expr->op()), "Token::INIT" " " "==" " " "expr->op()"
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7226, "Check failed: %s."
, _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0);
7227 if (var->mode() == CONST_LEGACY) {
7228 mode = HStoreContextSlot::kCheckIgnoreAssignment;
7229 } else {
7230 mode = HStoreContextSlot::kNoCheck;
7231 }
7232 }
7233
7234 HValue* context = BuildContextChainWalk(var);
7235 HStoreContextSlot* instr = Add<HStoreContextSlot>(
7236 context, var->index(), mode, Top());
7237 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
7238 Add<HSimulate>(expr->AssignmentId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
7239 }
7240 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
7241 }
7242
7243 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP:
7244 return Bailout(kAssignmentToLOOKUPVariable);
7245 }
7246 } else {
7247 return Bailout(kInvalidLeftHandSideInAssignment);
7248 }
7249}
7250
7251
7252void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitYield(Yield* expr) {
7253 // Generators are not optimized, so we should never get here.
7254 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7254, "unreachable code"
);
7255}
7256
7257
7258void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitThrow(Throw* expr) {
7259 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7259, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
7260 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7260, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
7261 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7261, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
7262 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) {
7263 // The parser turns invalid left-hand sides in assignments into throw
7264 // statements, which may not be in effect contexts. We might still try
7265 // to optimize such functions; bail out now if we do.
7266 return Bailout(kInvalidLeftHandSideInAssignment);
7267 }
7268 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->exception()));
7269
7270 HValue* value = environment()->Pop();
7271 if (!top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) SetSourcePosition(expr->position());
7272 Add<HPushArguments>(value);
7273 Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kThrow), 1);
7274 Add<HSimulate>(expr->id());
7275
7276 // If the throw definitely exits the function, we can finish with a dummy
7277 // control flow at this point. This is not the case if the throw is inside
7278 // an inlined function which may be replaced.
7279 if (call_context() == NULL__null) {
7280 FinishExitCurrentBlock(New<HAbnormalExit>());
7281 }
7282}

7290 }
7291 }

7293 Add<HLoadNamedField>(string, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMap()), nullptr,
7294 HObjectAccess::ForMapInstanceType());
7295}
