7314
7315HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildNamedGeneric(
7316 PropertyAccessType access_type, Expression* expr, FeedbackVectorSlot slot,
7317 HValue* object, Handle<Name> name, HValue* value, bool is_uninitialized) {
7318 if (is_uninitialized) {
7319 Add<HDeoptimize>(
7320 Deoptimizer::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericNamedAccess,
7321 Deoptimizer::SOFT);
7322 }
7323 if (access_type == LOAD) {
7324 Handle<TypeFeedbackVector> vector =
7325 handle(current_feedback_vector(), isolate());
7326
7327 if (!expr->AsProperty()->key()->IsPropertyName()) {
7328 // It's possible that a keyed load of a constant string was converted
7329 // to a named load. Here, at the last minute, we need to make sure to
7330 // use a generic Keyed Load if we are using the type vector, because
7331 // it has to share information with full code.
7332 HConstant* key = Add<HConstant>(name);
7333 HLoadKeyedGeneric* result =
7334 New<HLoadKeyedGeneric>(object, key, PREMONOMORPHIC);
7335 result->SetVectorAndSlot(vector, slot);
7336 return result;
7337 }
7338
7339 HLoadNamedGeneric* result =
7340 New<HLoadNamedGeneric>(object, name, PREMONOMORPHIC);
7341 result->SetVectorAndSlot(vector, slot);
7342 return result;
7343 } else {
7344 if (current_feedback_vector()->GetKind(slot) ==
7345 FeedbackVectorSlotKind::KEYED_STORE_IC) {
7346 // It's possible that a keyed store of a constant string was converted
7347 // to a named store. Here, at the last minute, we need to make sure to
7348 // use a generic Keyed Store if we are using the type vector, because
7349 // it has to share information with full code.
7350 HConstant* key = Add<HConstant>(name);
7351 HStoreKeyedGeneric* result = New<HStoreKeyedGeneric>(
7352 object, key, value, function_language_mode(), PREMONOMORPHIC);
7353 Handle<TypeFeedbackVector> vector =
7354 handle(current_feedback_vector(), isolate());
7355 result->SetVectorAndSlot(vector, slot);
7356 return result;
7357 }
7358
7359 HStoreNamedGeneric* result = New<HStoreNamedGeneric>(
7360 object, name, value, function_language_mode(), PREMONOMORPHIC);
7361 Handle<TypeFeedbackVector> vector =
7362 handle(current_feedback_vector(), isolate());
7363 result->SetVectorAndSlot(vector, slot);
7364 return result;
7365 }
7366}
7367
7368
7369HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildKeyedGeneric(
7370 PropertyAccessType access_type, Expression* expr, FeedbackVectorSlot slot,
7371 HValue* object, HValue* key, HValue* value) {
7372 if (access_type == LOAD) {
7373 InlineCacheState initial_state = expr->AsProperty()->GetInlineCacheState();
7374 HLoadKeyedGeneric* result =
7375 New<HLoadKeyedGeneric>(object, key, initial_state);
7376 // HLoadKeyedGeneric with vector ics benefits from being encoded as
7377 // MEGAMORPHIC because the vector/slot combo becomes unnecessary.
7378 if (initial_state != MEGAMORPHIC) {
7379 // We need to pass vector information.
7380 Handle<TypeFeedbackVector> vector =
7381 handle(current_feedback_vector(), isolate());
7382 result->SetVectorAndSlot(vector, slot);
7383 }
7384 return result;
7385 } else {
7386 HStoreKeyedGeneric* result = New<HStoreKeyedGeneric>(
7387 object, key, value, function_language_mode(), PREMONOMORPHIC);
7388 Handle<TypeFeedbackVector> vector =
7389 handle(current_feedback_vector(), isolate());
7390 result->SetVectorAndSlot(vector, slot);
7391 return result;
7392 }
7393}
7394
7395
7396LoadKeyedHoleMode HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildKeyedHoleMode(Handle<Map> map) {
7397 // Loads from a "stock" fast holey double arrays can elide the hole check.
7398 // Loads from a "stock" fast holey array can convert the hole to undefined
7399 // with impunity.
7400 LoadKeyedHoleMode load_mode = NEVER_RETURN_HOLE;
7401 bool holey_double_elements =
7402 *map == isolate()->get_initial_js_array_map(FAST_HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
7403 bool holey_elements =
7404 *map == isolate()->get_initial_js_array_map(FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
7405 if ((holey_double_elements || holey_elements) &&
7406 isolate()->IsFastArrayConstructorPrototypeChainIntact()) {
7407 load_mode =
7408 holey_double_elements ? ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE : CONVERT_HOLE_TO_UNDEFINED;
7409
7410 Handle<JSObject> prototype(JSObject::cast(map->prototype()), isolate());
7411 Handle<JSObject> object_prototype = isolate()->initial_object_prototype();
7412 BuildCheckPrototypeMaps(prototype, object_prototype);
7413 graph()->MarkDependsOnEmptyArrayProtoElements();
7414 }
7415 return load_mode;
7416}
7417
7418
7419HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildMonomorphicElementAccess(
7420 HValue* object,
7421 HValue* key,
7422 HValue* val,
7423 HValue* dependency,
7424 Handle<Map> map,
7425 PropertyAccessType access_type,
7426 KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode) {
7427 HCheckMaps* checked_object = Add<HCheckMaps>(object, map, dependency);
7428
7429 if (access_type == STORE && map->prototype()->IsJSObject()) {
7430 // monomorphic stores need a prototype chain check because shape
7431 // changes could allow callbacks on elements in the chain that
7432 // aren't compatible with monomorphic keyed stores.
7433 PrototypeIterator iter(map);
7434 JSObject* holder = NULL__null;
7435 while (!iter.IsAtEnd()) {
7436 // JSProxies can't occur here because we wouldn't have installed a
7437 // non-generic IC if there were any.
7438 holder = *PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<JSObject>(iter);
7439 iter.Advance();
7440 }
7441 DCHECK(holder && holder->IsJSObject())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(holder && holder->
IsJSObject())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 7441, "Check failed: %s.", "holder && holder->IsJSObject()"
); } } while (0);
7442
7443 BuildCheckPrototypeMaps(handle(JSObject::cast(map->prototype())),
7444 Handle<JSObject>(holder));
7445 }
7446
7447 LoadKeyedHoleMode load_mode = BuildKeyedHoleMode(map);
7448 return BuildUncheckedMonomorphicElementAccess(
7449 checked_object, key, val,
7450 map->instance_type() == JS_ARRAY_TYPE,
7451 map->elements_kind(), access_type,
7452 load_mode, store_mode);
7453}
7454
7455
7456static bool CanInlineElementAccess(Handle<Map> map) {
7457 return map->IsJSObjectMap() &&
7458 (map->has_fast_elements() || map->has_fixed_typed_array_elements()) &&
7459 !map->has_indexed_interceptor() && !map->is_access_check_needed();
7460}
7461
7462
7463HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryBuildConsolidatedElementLoad(
7464 HValue* object,
7465 HValue* key,
7466 HValue* val,
7467 SmallMapList* maps) {
7468 // For polymorphic loads of similar elements kinds (i.e. all tagged or all
7469 // double), always use the "worst case" code without a transition. This is
7470 // much faster than transitioning the elements to the worst case, trading a
7471 // HTransitionElements for a HCheckMaps, and avoiding mutation of the array.
7472 bool has_double_maps = false;
7473 bool has_smi_or_object_maps = false;
7474 bool has_js_array_access = false;
7475 bool has_non_js_array_access = false;
7476 bool has_seen_holey_elements = false;
7477 Handle<Map> most_general_consolidated_map;
7478 for (int i = 0; i < maps->length(); ++i) {
7479 Handle<Map> map = maps->at(i);
7480 if (!CanInlineElementAccess(map)) return NULL__null;
7481 // Don't allow mixing of JSArrays with JSObjects.
7482 if (map->instance_type() == JS_ARRAY_TYPE) {
7483 if (has_non_js_array_access) return NULL__null;
7484 has_js_array_access = true;
7485 } else if (has_js_array_access) {
7486 return NULL__null;
7487 } else {
7488 has_non_js_array_access = true;
7489 }
7490 // Don't allow mixed, incompatible elements kinds.
7491 if (map->has_fast_double_elements()) {
7492 if (has_smi_or_object_maps) return NULL__null;
7493 has_double_maps = true;
7494 } else if (map->has_fast_smi_or_object_elements()) {
7495 if (has_double_maps) return NULL__null;
7496 has_smi_or_object_maps = true;
7497 } else {
7498 return NULL__null;
7499 }
7500 // Remember if we've ever seen holey elements.
7501 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(map->elements_kind())) {
7502 has_seen_holey_elements = true;
7503 }
7504 // Remember the most general elements kind, the code for its load will
7505 // properly handle all of the more specific cases.
7506 if ((i == 0) || IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(
7507 most_general_consolidated_map->elements_kind(),
7508 map->elements_kind())) {
7509 most_general_consolidated_map = map;
7510 }
7511 }
7512 if (!has_double_maps && !has_smi_or_object_maps) return NULL__null;
7513
7514 HCheckMaps* checked_object = Add<HCheckMaps>(object, maps);
7515 // FAST_ELEMENTS is considered more general than FAST_HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS.
7516 // If we've seen both, the consolidated load must use FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
7517 ElementsKind consolidated_elements_kind = has_seen_holey_elements
7518 ? GetHoleyElementsKind(most_general_consolidated_map->elements_kind())
7519 : most_general_consolidated_map->elements_kind();
7520 LoadKeyedHoleMode load_mode = NEVER_RETURN_HOLE;
7521 if (has_seen_holey_elements) {
7522 // Make sure that all of the maps we are handling have the initial array
7523 // prototype.
7524 bool saw_non_array_prototype = false;
7525 for (int i = 0; i < maps->length(); ++i) {
7526 Handle<Map> map = maps->at(i);
7527 if (map->prototype() != *isolate()->initial_array_prototype()) {
7528 // We can't guarantee that loading the hole is safe. The prototype may
7529 // have an element at this position.
7530 saw_non_array_prototype = true;
7531 break;
7532 }
7533 }
7534
7535 if (!saw_non_array_prototype) {
7536 Handle<Map> holey_map = handle(
7537 isolate()->get_initial_js_array_map(consolidated_elements_kind));
7538 load_mode = BuildKeyedHoleMode(holey_map);
7539 if (load_mode != NEVER_RETURN_HOLE) {
7540 for (int i = 0; i < maps->length(); ++i) {
7541 Handle<Map> map = maps->at(i);
7542 // The prototype check was already done for the holey map in
7543 // BuildKeyedHoleMode.
7544 if (!map.is_identical_to(holey_map)) {
7545 Handle<JSObject> prototype(JSObject::cast(map->prototype()),
7546 isolate());
7547 Handle<JSObject> object_prototype =
7548 isolate()->initial_object_prototype();
7549 BuildCheckPrototypeMaps(prototype, object_prototype);
7550 }
7551 }
7552 }
7553 }
7554 }
7555 HInstruction* instr = BuildUncheckedMonomorphicElementAccess(
7556 checked_object, key, val,
7557 most_general_consolidated_map->instance_type() == JS_ARRAY_TYPE,
7558 consolidated_elements_kind, LOAD, load_mode, STANDARD_STORE);
7559 return instr;
7560}
7561
7562
7563HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandlePolymorphicElementAccess(
7564 Expression* expr, FeedbackVectorSlot slot, HValue* object, HValue* key,
7565 HValue* val, SmallMapList* maps, PropertyAccessType access_type,
7566 KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode, bool* has_side_effects) {
7567 *has_side_effects = false;
7568 BuildCheckHeapObject(object);
7569
7570 if (access_type == LOAD) {
7571 HInstruction* consolidated_load =
7572 TryBuildConsolidatedElementLoad(object, key, val, maps);
7573 if (consolidated_load != NULL__null) {
7574 *has_side_effects |= consolidated_load->HasObservableSideEffects();
7575 return consolidated_load;
7576 }
7577 }
7578
7579 // Elements_kind transition support.
7580 MapHandleList transition_target(maps->length());
7581 // Collect possible transition targets.
7582 MapHandleList possible_transitioned_maps(maps->length());
7583 for (int i = 0; i < maps->length(); ++i) {
7584 Handle<Map> map = maps->at(i);
7585 // Loads from strings or loads with a mix of string and non-string maps
7586 // shouldn't be handled polymorphically.
7587 DCHECK(access_type != LOAD || !map->IsStringMap())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(access_type != LOAD || !map->
IsStringMap())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 7587, "Check failed: %s.", "access_type != LOAD || !map->IsStringMap()"
); } } while (0);
7588 ElementsKind elements_kind = map->elements_kind();
7589 if (CanInlineElementAccess(map) && IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
7590 elements_kind != GetInitialFastElementsKind()) {
7591 possible_transitioned_maps.Add(map);
7592 }
7593 if (IsSloppyArgumentsElements(elements_kind)) {
7594 HInstruction* result =
7595 BuildKeyedGeneric(access_type, expr, slot, object, key, val);
7596 *has_side_effects = result->HasObservableSideEffects();
7597 return AddInstruction(result);
7598 }
7599 }
7600 // Get transition target for each map (NULL == no transition).
7601 for (int i = 0; i < maps->length(); ++i) {
7602 Handle<Map> map = maps->at(i);
7603 Map* transitioned_map =
7604 map->FindElementsKindTransitionedMap(&possible_transitioned_maps);
7605 if (transitioned_map != nullptr) {
7606 transition_target.Add(handle(transitioned_map));
7607 } else {
7608 transition_target.Add(Handle<Map>());
7609 }
7610 }
7611
7612 MapHandleList untransitionable_maps(maps->length());
7613 HTransitionElementsKind* transition = NULL__null;
7614 for (int i = 0; i < maps->length(); ++i) {
7615 Handle<Map> map = maps->at(i);
7616 DCHECK(map->IsMap())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(map->IsMap())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7616, "Check failed: %s.", "map->IsMap()"
); } } while (0);
7617 if (!transition_target.at(i).is_null()) {
7618 DCHECK(Map::IsValidElementsTransition(do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(Map::IsValidElementsTransition
( map->elements_kind(), transition_target.at(i)->elements_kind
()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7620,
"Check failed: %s.", "Map::IsValidElementsTransition( map->elements_kind(), transition_target.at(i)->elements_kind())"
); } } while (0)
7619 map->elements_kind(),do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(Map::IsValidElementsTransition
( map->elements_kind(), transition_target.at(i)->elements_kind
()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7620,
"Check failed: %s.", "Map::IsValidElementsTransition( map->elements_kind(), transition_target.at(i)->elements_kind())"
); } } while (0)
7620 transition_target.at(i)->elements_kind()))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(Map::IsValidElementsTransition
( map->elements_kind(), transition_target.at(i)->elements_kind
()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7620,
"Check failed: %s.", "Map::IsValidElementsTransition( map->elements_kind(), transition_target.at(i)->elements_kind())"
); } } while (0);
7621 transition = Add<HTransitionElementsKind>(object, map,
7622 transition_target.at(i));
7623 } else {
7624 untransitionable_maps.Add(map);
7625 }
7626 }
7627
7628 // If only one map is left after transitioning, handle this case
7629 // monomorphically.
7630 DCHECK(untransitionable_maps.length() >= 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(untransitionable_maps.length(
) >= 1)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc",
7630, "Check failed: %s.", "untransitionable_maps.length() >= 1"
); } } while (0);
7631 if (untransitionable_maps.length() == 1) {
7632 Handle<Map> untransitionable_map = untransitionable_maps[0];
7633 HInstruction* instr = NULL__null;
7634 if (!CanInlineElementAccess(untransitionable_map)) {
7635 instr = AddInstruction(
7636 BuildKeyedGeneric(access_type, expr, slot, object, key, val));
7637 } else {
7638 instr = BuildMonomorphicElementAccess(
7639 object, key, val, transition, untransitionable_map, access_type,
7640 store_mode);
7641 }
7642 *has_side_effects |= instr->HasObservableSideEffects();
7643 return access_type == STORE ? val : instr;
7644 }
7645
7646 HBasicBlock* join = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
7647
7648 for (int i = 0; i < untransitionable_maps.length(); ++i) {
7649 Handle<Map> map = untransitionable_maps[i];
7650 ElementsKind elements_kind = map->elements_kind();
7651 HBasicBlock* this_map = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
7652 HBasicBlock* other_map = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
7653 HCompareMap* mapcompare =
7654 New<HCompareMap>(object, map, this_map, other_map);
7655 FinishCurrentBlock(mapcompare);
7656
7657 set_current_block(this_map);
7658 HInstruction* access = NULL__null;
7659 if (!CanInlineElementAccess(map)) {
7660 access = AddInstruction(
7661 BuildKeyedGeneric(access_type, expr, slot, object, key, val));
7662 } else {
7663 DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind) ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind
) || IsFixedTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind))), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7664, "Check failed: %s.", "IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind) || IsFixedTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)"
); } } while (0)
7664 IsFixedTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind
) || IsFixedTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind))), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7664, "Check failed: %s.", "IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind) || IsFixedTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)"
); } } while (0);
7665 LoadKeyedHoleMode load_mode = BuildKeyedHoleMode(map);
7666 // Happily, mapcompare is a checked object.
7667 access = BuildUncheckedMonomorphicElementAccess(
7668 mapcompare, key, val,
7669 map->instance_type() == JS_ARRAY_TYPE,
7670 elements_kind, access_type,
7671 load_mode,
7672 store_mode);
7673 }
7674 *has_side_effects |= access->HasObservableSideEffects();
7675 // The caller will use has_side_effects and add a correct Simulate.
7676 access->SetFlag(HValue::kHasNoObservableSideEffects);
7677 if (access_type == LOAD) {
7678 Push(access);
7679 }
7680 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
7681 GotoNoSimulate(join);
7682 set_current_block(other_map);
7683 }
7684
7685 // Ensure that we visited at least one map above that goes to join. This is
7686 // necessary because FinishExitWithHardDeoptimization does an AbnormalExit
7687 // rather than joining the join block. If this becomes an issue, insert a
7688 // generic access in the case length() == 0.
7689 DCHECK(join->predecessors()->length() > 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(join->predecessors()->length
() > 0)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc",
7689, "Check failed: %s.", "join->predecessors()->length() > 0"
); } } while (0);
7690 // Deopt if none of the cases matched.
7691 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
7692 FinishExitWithHardDeoptimization(
7693 Deoptimizer::kUnknownMapInPolymorphicElementAccess);
7694 set_current_block(join);
7695 return access_type == STORE ? val : Pop();
7696}

7698
7699HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandleKeyedElementAccess(
7700 HValue* obj, HValue* key, HValue* val, Expression* expr,
7701 FeedbackVectorSlot slot, BailoutId ast_id, BailoutId return_id,
7702 PropertyAccessType access_type, bool* has_side_effects) {
7703 // A keyed name access with type feedback may contain the name.
7704 Handle<TypeFeedbackVector> vector =
7705 handle(current_feedback_vector(), isolate());
7706 HValue* expected_key = key;
7707 if (!key->ActualValue()->IsConstant()) {
7708 Name* name = nullptr;
7709 if (access_type == LOAD) {
7710 KeyedLoadICNexus nexus(vector, slot);
7711 name = nexus.FindFirstName();
7712 } else {
7713 KeyedStoreICNexus nexus(vector, slot);
7714 name = nexus.FindFirstName();
7715 }
7716 if (name != nullptr) {
7717 Handle<Name> handle_name(name);
7718 expected_key = Add<HConstant>(handle_name);
7719 // We need a check against the key.
7720 bool in_new_space = isolate()->heap()->InNewSpace(*handle_name);
7721 Unique<Name> unique_name = Unique<Name>::CreateUninitialized(handle_name);
7722 Add<HCheckValue>(key, unique_name, in_new_space);
7723 }
7724 }
7725 if (expected_key->ActualValue()->IsConstant()) {
7726 Handle<Object> constant =
7727 HConstant::cast(expected_key->ActualValue())->handle(isolate());
7728 uint32_t array_index;
7729 if ((constant->IsString() &&
7730 !Handle<String>::cast(constant)->AsArrayIndex(&array_index)) ||
7731 constant->IsSymbol()) {
7732 if (!constant->IsUniqueName()) {
7733 constant = isolate()->factory()->InternalizeString(
7734 Handle<String>::cast(constant));
7735 }
7736 HValue* access =
7737 BuildNamedAccess(access_type, ast_id, return_id, expr, slot, obj,
7738 Handle<Name>::cast(constant), val, false);
7739 if (access == NULL__null || access->IsPhi() ||
7740 HInstruction::cast(access)->IsLinked()) {
7741 *has_side_effects = false;
7742 } else {
7743 HInstruction* instr = HInstruction::cast(access);
7744 AddInstruction(instr);
7745 *has_side_effects = instr->HasObservableSideEffects();
7746 }
7747 return access;
7748 }
7749 }
7750
7751 DCHECK(!expr->IsPropertyName())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!expr->IsPropertyName())),
0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 7751, "Check failed: %s."
, "!expr->IsPropertyName()"); } } while (0);
7752 HInstruction* instr = NULL__null;
7753
7754 SmallMapList* maps;
7755 bool monomorphic = ComputeReceiverTypes(expr, obj, &maps, this);
7756
7757 bool force_generic = false;
7758 if (expr->GetKeyType() == PROPERTY) {
7759 // Non-Generic accesses assume that elements are being accessed, and will
7760 // deopt for non-index keys, which the IC knows will occur.
7761 // TODO(jkummerow): Consider adding proper support for property accesses.
7762 force_generic = true;
7763 monomorphic = false;
7764 } else if (access_type == STORE &&
7765 (monomorphic || (maps != NULL__null && !maps->is_empty()))) {
7766 // Stores can't be mono/polymorphic if their prototype chain has dictionary
7767 // elements. However a receiver map that has dictionary elements itself
7768 // should be left to normal mono/poly behavior (the other maps may benefit
7769 // from highly optimized stores).
7770 for (int i = 0; i < maps->length(); i++) {
7771 Handle<Map> current_map = maps->at(i);
7772 if (current_map->DictionaryElementsInPrototypeChainOnly()) {
7773 force_generic = true;
7774 monomorphic = false;
7775 break;
7776 }
7777 }
7778 } else if (access_type == LOAD && !monomorphic &&
7779 (maps != NULL__null && !maps->is_empty())) {
7780 // Polymorphic loads have to go generic if any of the maps are strings.
7781 // If some, but not all of the maps are strings, we should go generic
7782 // because polymorphic access wants to key on ElementsKind and isn't
7783 // compatible with strings.
7784 for (int i = 0; i < maps->length(); i++) {
7785 Handle<Map> current_map = maps->at(i);
7786 if (current_map->IsStringMap()) {
7787 force_generic = true;
7788 break;
7789 }
7790 }
7791 }
7792
7793 if (monomorphic) {
7794 Handle<Map> map = maps->first();
7795 if (!CanInlineElementAccess(map)) {
7796 instr = AddInstruction(
7797 BuildKeyedGeneric(access_type, expr, slot, obj, key, val));
7798 } else {
7799 BuildCheckHeapObject(obj);
7800 instr = BuildMonomorphicElementAccess(
7801 obj, key, val, NULL__null, map, access_type, expr->GetStoreMode());
7802 }
7803 } else if (!force_generic && (maps != NULL__null && !maps->is_empty())) {
7804 return HandlePolymorphicElementAccess(expr, slot, obj, key, val, maps,
7805 access_type, expr->GetStoreMode(),
7806 has_side_effects);
7807 } else {
7808 if (access_type == STORE) {
7809 if (expr->IsAssignment() &&
7810 expr->AsAssignment()->HasNoTypeInformation()) {
7811 Add<HDeoptimize>(Deoptimizer::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForKeyedStore,
7812 Deoptimizer::SOFT);
7813 }
7814 } else {
7815 if (expr->AsProperty()->HasNoTypeInformation()) {
7816 Add<HDeoptimize>(Deoptimizer::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForKeyedLoad,
7817 Deoptimizer::SOFT);
7818 }
7819 }
7820 instr = AddInstruction(
7821 BuildKeyedGeneric(access_type, expr, slot, obj, key, val));
7822 }
7823 *has_side_effects = instr->HasObservableSideEffects();
7824 return instr;
7825}

7827
7828void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::EnsureArgumentsArePushedForAccess() {
7829 // Outermost function already has arguments on the stack.
7830 if (function_state()->outer() == NULL__null) return;
7831
7832 if (function_state()->arguments_pushed()) return;
7833
7834 // Push arguments when entering inlined function.
7835 HEnterInlined* entry = function_state()->entry();
7836 entry->set_arguments_pushed();
7837
7838 HArgumentsObject* arguments = entry->arguments_object();
7839 const ZoneList<HValue*>* arguments_values = arguments->arguments_values();
7840
7841 HInstruction* insert_after = entry;
7842 for (int i = 0; i < arguments_values->length(); i++) {
7843 HValue* argument = arguments_values->at(i);
7844 HInstruction* push_argument = New<HPushArguments>(argument);
7845 push_argument->InsertAfter(insert_after);
7846 insert_after = push_argument;
7847 }
7848
7849 HArgumentsElements* arguments_elements = New<HArgumentsElements>(true);
7850 arguments_elements->ClearFlag(HValue::kUseGVN);
7851 arguments_elements->InsertAfter(insert_after);
7852 function_state()->set_arguments_elements(arguments_elements);
7853}

7856bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryArgumentsAccess(Property* expr) {
7857 VariableProxy* proxy = expr->obj()->AsVariableProxy();
7858 if (proxy == NULL__null) return false;
7859 if (!proxy->var()->IsStackAllocated()) return false;
7860 if (!environment()->Lookup(proxy->var())->CheckFlag(HValue::kIsArguments)) {
7861 return false;
7862 }
7863
7864 HInstruction* result = NULL__null;
7865 if (expr->key()->IsPropertyName()) {
7866 Handle<String> name = expr->key()->AsLiteral()->AsPropertyName();
7867 if (!String::Equals(name, isolate()->factory()->length_string())) {
7868 return false;
7869 }
7870
7871 if (function_state()->outer() == NULL__null) {
7872 HInstruction* elements = Add<HArgumentsElements>(false);
7873 result = New<HArgumentsLength>(elements);
7874 } else {
7875 // Number of arguments without receiver.
7876 int argument_count = environment()->
7877 arguments_environment()->parameter_count() - 1;
7878 result = New<HConstant>(argument_count);
7879 }
7880 } else {
7881 CHECK_ALIVE_OR_RETURN(VisitForValue(expr->obj(), ARGUMENTS_ALLOWED), true)do { VisitForValue(expr->obj(), ARGUMENTS_ALLOWED); if (HasStackOverflow
() || current_block() == __null) return true; } while (false);
7882 CHECK_ALIVE_OR_RETURN(VisitForValue(expr->key()), true)do { VisitForValue(expr->key()); if (HasStackOverflow() ||
current_block() == __null) return true; } while (false);
7883 HValue* key = Pop();
7884 Drop(1); // Arguments object.
7885 if (function_state()->outer() == NULL__null) {
7886 HInstruction* elements = Add<HArgumentsElements>(false);
7887 HInstruction* length = Add<HArgumentsLength>(elements);
7888 HInstruction* checked_key = Add<HBoundsCheck>(key, length);
7889 result = New<HAccessArgumentsAt>(elements, length, checked_key);
7890 } else {
7891 EnsureArgumentsArePushedForAccess();
7892
7893 // Number of arguments without receiver.
7894 HInstruction* elements = function_state()->arguments_elements();
7895 int argument_count = environment()->
7896 arguments_environment()->parameter_count() - 1;
7897 HInstruction* length = Add<HConstant>(argument_count);
7898 HInstruction* checked_key = Add<HBoundsCheck>(key, length);
7899 result = New<HAccessArgumentsAt>(elements, length, checked_key);
7900 }
7901 }
7902 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
7903 return true;
7904}

7951
7952void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildLoad(Property* expr,
7953 BailoutId ast_id) {
7954 HInstruction* instr = NULL__null;
7955 if (expr->IsStringAccess() && expr->GetKeyType() == ELEMENT) {
7956 HValue* index = Pop();
7957 HValue* string = Pop();
7958 HInstruction* char_code = BuildStringCharCodeAt(string, index);
7959 AddInstruction(char_code);
7960 instr = NewUncasted<HStringCharFromCode>(char_code);
7961
7962 } else if (expr->key()->IsPropertyName()) {
7963 Handle<String> name = expr->key()->AsLiteral()->AsPropertyName();
7964 HValue* object = Pop();
7965
7966 HValue* value = BuildNamedAccess(LOAD, ast_id, expr->LoadId(), expr,
7967 expr->PropertyFeedbackSlot(), object, name,
7968 NULL__null, expr->IsUninitialized());
7969 if (value == NULL__null) return;
7970 if (value->IsPhi()) return ast_context()->ReturnValue(value);
7971 instr = HInstruction::cast(value);
7972 if (instr->IsLinked()) return ast_context()->ReturnValue(instr);
7973
7974 } else {
7975 HValue* key = Pop();
7976 HValue* obj = Pop();
7977
7978 bool has_side_effects = false;
7979 HValue* load = HandleKeyedElementAccess(
7980 obj, key, NULL__null, expr, expr->PropertyFeedbackSlot(), ast_id,
7981 expr->LoadId(), LOAD, &has_side_effects);
7982 if (has_side_effects) {
7983 if (ast_context()->IsEffect()) {
7984 Add<HSimulate>(ast_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
7985 } else {
7986 Push(load);
7987 Add<HSimulate>(ast_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
7988 Drop(1);
7989 }
7990 }
7991 if (load == NULL__null) return;
7992 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(load);
7993 }
7994 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, ast_id);
7995}

8069HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildCallConstantFunction(
8070 Handle<JSFunction> jsfun, int argument_count) {
8071 HValue* target = Add<HConstant>(jsfun);
8072 // For constant functions, we try to avoid calling the
8073 // argument adaptor and instead call the function directly
8074 int formal_parameter_count =
8075 jsfun->shared()->internal_formal_parameter_count();
8076 bool dont_adapt_arguments =
8077 (formal_parameter_count ==
8078 SharedFunctionInfo::kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel);
8079 int arity = argument_count - 1;
8080 bool can_invoke_directly =
8081 dont_adapt_arguments || formal_parameter_count == arity;
8082 if (can_invoke_directly) {
8083 if (jsfun.is_identical_to(current_info()->closure())) {
8084 graph()->MarkRecursive();
8085 }
8086 return NewPlainFunctionCall(target, argument_count);
8087 } else {
8088 HValue* param_count_value = Add<HConstant>(formal_parameter_count);
8089 HValue* context = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
8090 target, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForFunctionContextPointer());
8091 return NewArgumentAdaptorCall(target, context,
8092 argument_count, param_count_value);
8093 }
8094 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8094, "unreachable code"
);
8095 return NULL__null;

8099class FunctionSorter {
8100 public:
8101 explicit FunctionSorter(int index = 0, int ticks = 0, int size = 0)
8102 : index_(index), ticks_(ticks), size_(size) {}
8103
8104 int index() const { return index_; }
8105 int ticks() const { return ticks_; }
8106 int size() const { return size_; }
8107
8108 private:
8109 int index_;
8110 int ticks_;
8111 int size_;
8112};
8113
8114
8115inline bool operator<(const FunctionSorter& lhs, const FunctionSorter& rhs) {
8116 int diff = lhs.ticks() - rhs.ticks();
8117 if (diff != 0) return diff > 0;
8118 return lhs.size() < rhs.size();
8119}

8122void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandlePolymorphicCallNamed(Call* expr,
8123 HValue* receiver,
8124 SmallMapList* maps,
8125 Handle<String> name) {
8126 int argument_count = expr->arguments()->length() + 1; // Includes receiver.
8127 FunctionSorter order[kMaxCallPolymorphism];
8128
8129 bool handle_smi = false;
8130 bool handled_string = false;
8131 int ordered_functions = 0;
8132
8133 int i;
8134 for (i = 0; i < maps->length() && ordered_functions < kMaxCallPolymorphism;
8135 ++i) {
8136 PropertyAccessInfo info(this, LOAD, maps->at(i), name);
8137 if (info.CanAccessMonomorphic() && info.IsDataConstant() &&
8138 info.constant()->IsJSFunction()) {
8139 if (info.IsStringType()) {
8140 if (handled_string) continue;
8141 handled_string = true;
8142 }
8143 Handle<JSFunction> target = Handle<JSFunction>::cast(info.constant());
8144 if (info.IsNumberType()) {
8145 handle_smi = true;
8146 }
8147 expr->set_target(target);
8148 order[ordered_functions++] = FunctionSorter(
8149 i, target->shared()->profiler_ticks(), InliningAstSize(target));
8150 }
8151 }
8152
8153 std::sort(order, order + ordered_functions);
8154
8155 if (i < maps->length()) {
8156 maps->Clear();
8157 ordered_functions = -1;
8158 }
8159
8160 HBasicBlock* number_block = NULL__null;
8161 HBasicBlock* join = NULL__null;
8162 handled_string = false;
8163 int count = 0;
8164
8165 for (int fn = 0; fn < ordered_functions; ++fn) {
8166 int i = order[fn].index();
8167 PropertyAccessInfo info(this, LOAD, maps->at(i), name);
8168 if (info.IsStringType()) {
8169 if (handled_string) continue;
8170 handled_string = true;
8171 }
8172 // Reloads the target.
8173 info.CanAccessMonomorphic();
8174 Handle<JSFunction> target = Handle<JSFunction>::cast(info.constant());
8175
8176 expr->set_target(target);
8177 if (count == 0) {
8178 // Only needed once.
8179 join = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
8180 if (handle_smi) {
8181 HBasicBlock* empty_smi_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
8182 HBasicBlock* not_smi_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
8183 number_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
8184 FinishCurrentBlock(New<HIsSmiAndBranch>(
8185 receiver, empty_smi_block, not_smi_block));
8186 GotoNoSimulate(empty_smi_block, number_block);
8187 set_current_block(not_smi_block);
8188 } else {
8189 BuildCheckHeapObject(receiver);
8190 }
8191 }
8192 ++count;
8193 HBasicBlock* if_true = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
8194 HBasicBlock* if_false = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
8195 HUnaryControlInstruction* compare;
8196
8197 Handle<Map> map = info.map();
8198 if (info.IsNumberType()) {
8199 Handle<Map> heap_number_map = isolate()->factory()->heap_number_map();
8200 compare = New<HCompareMap>(receiver, heap_number_map, if_true, if_false);
8201 } else if (info.IsStringType()) {
8202 compare = New<HIsStringAndBranch>(receiver, if_true, if_false);
8203 } else {
8204 compare = New<HCompareMap>(receiver, map, if_true, if_false);
8205 }
8206 FinishCurrentBlock(compare);
8207
8208 if (info.IsNumberType()) {
8209 GotoNoSimulate(if_true, number_block);
8210 if_true = number_block;
8211 }
8212
8213 set_current_block(if_true);
8214
8215 AddCheckPrototypeMaps(info.holder(), map);
8216
8217 HValue* function = Add<HConstant>(expr->target());
8218 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(0, function);
8219 Push(receiver);
8220 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitExpressions(expr->arguments()));
8221 bool needs_wrapping = info.NeedsWrappingFor(target);
8222 bool try_inline = FLAG_polymorphic_inlining && !needs_wrapping;
8223 if (FLAG_trace_inlining && try_inline) {
8224 Handle<JSFunction> caller = current_info()->closure();
8225 base::SmartArrayPointer<char> caller_name =
8226 caller->shared()->DebugName()->ToCString();
8227 PrintF("Trying to inline the polymorphic call to %s from %s\n",
8228 name->ToCString().get(),
8229 caller_name.get());
8230 }
8231 if (try_inline && TryInlineCall(expr)) {
8232 // Trying to inline will signal that we should bailout from the
8233 // entire compilation by setting stack overflow on the visitor.
8234 if (HasStackOverflow()) return;
8235 } else {
8236 // Since HWrapReceiver currently cannot actually wrap numbers and strings,
8237 // use the regular CallFunctionStub for method calls to wrap the receiver.
8238 // TODO(verwaest): Support creation of value wrappers directly in
8239 // HWrapReceiver.
8240 HInstruction* call =
8241 needs_wrapping ? NewUncasted<HCallFunction>(
8242 function, argument_count,
8243 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined)
8244 : BuildCallConstantFunction(target, argument_count);
8245 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argument_count);
8246 AddInstruction(call);
8247 Drop(1); // Drop the function.
8248 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(call);
8249 }
8250
8251 if (current_block() != NULL__null) Goto(join);
8252 set_current_block(if_false);
8253 }
8254
8255 // Finish up. Unconditionally deoptimize if we've handled all the maps we
8256 // know about and do not want to handle ones we've never seen. Otherwise
8257 // use a generic IC.
8258 if (ordered_functions == maps->length() && FLAG_deoptimize_uncommon_cases) {
8259 FinishExitWithHardDeoptimization(Deoptimizer::kUnknownMapInPolymorphicCall);
8260 } else {
8261 Property* prop = expr->expression()->AsProperty();
8262 HInstruction* function =
8263 BuildNamedGeneric(LOAD, prop, prop->PropertyFeedbackSlot(), receiver,
8264 name, NULL__null, prop->IsUninitialized());
8265 AddInstruction(function);
8266 Push(function);
8267 AddSimulate(prop->LoadId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
8268
8269 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(1, function);
8270 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(0, receiver);
8271 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitExpressions(expr->arguments()));
8272
8273 HInstruction* call = New<HCallFunction>(
8274 function, argument_count, ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined);
8275
8276 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argument_count);
8277
8278 Drop(1); // Function.
8279
8280 if (join != NULL__null) {
8281 AddInstruction(call);
8282 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(call);
8283 Goto(join);
8284 } else {
8285 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(call, expr->id());
8286 }
8287 }
8288
8289 // We assume that control flow is always live after an expression. So
8290 // even without predecessors to the join block, we set it as the exit
8291 // block and continue by adding instructions there.
8292 DCHECK(join != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(join != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8292, "Check failed: %s.", "join != __null"
); } } while (0);
8293 if (join->HasPredecessor()) {
8294 set_current_block(join);
8295 join->SetJoinId(expr->id());
8296 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
8297 } else {
8298 set_current_block(NULL__null);
8299 }
8300}
8301
8302
8303void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TraceInline(Handle<JSFunction> target,
8304 Handle<JSFunction> caller,
8305 const char* reason) {
8306 if (FLAG_trace_inlining) {
8307 base::SmartArrayPointer<char> target_name =
8308 target->shared()->DebugName()->ToCString();
8309 base::SmartArrayPointer<char> caller_name =
8310 caller->shared()->DebugName()->ToCString();
8311 if (reason == NULL__null) {
8312 PrintF("Inlined %s called from %s.\n", target_name.get(),
8313 caller_name.get());
8314 } else {
8315 PrintF("Did not inline %s called from %s (%s).\n",
8316 target_name.get(), caller_name.get(), reason);
8317 }
8318 }
8319}
8320
8321
8322static const int kNotInlinable = 1000000000;
8323
8324
8325int HOptimizedGraphBuilder::InliningAstSize(Handle<JSFunction> target) {
8326 if (!FLAG_use_inlining) return kNotInlinable;
8327
8328 // Precondition: call is monomorphic and we have found a target with the
8329 // appropriate arity.
8330 Handle<JSFunction> caller = current_info()->closure();
8331 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> target_shared(target->shared());
8332
8333 // Always inline functions that force inlining.
8334 if (target_shared->force_inline()) {
8335 return 0;
8336 }
8337 if (target->shared()->IsBuiltin()) {
8338 return kNotInlinable;
8339 }
8340
8341 if (target_shared->IsApiFunction()) {
8342 TraceInline(target, caller, "target is api function");
8343 return kNotInlinable;
8344 }
8345
8346 // Do a quick check on source code length to avoid parsing large
8347 // inlining candidates.
8348 if (target_shared->SourceSize() >
8349 Min(FLAG_max_inlined_source_size, kUnlimitedMaxInlinedSourceSize)) {
8350 TraceInline(target, caller, "target text too big");
8351 return kNotInlinable;
8352 }
8353
8354 // Target must be inlineable.
8355 BailoutReason noopt_reason = target_shared->disable_optimization_reason();
8356 if (!target_shared->IsInlineable() && noopt_reason != kHydrogenFilter) {
8357 TraceInline(target, caller, "target not inlineable");
8358 return kNotInlinable;
8359 }
8360 if (noopt_reason != kNoReason && noopt_reason != kHydrogenFilter) {
8361 TraceInline(target, caller, "target contains unsupported syntax [early]");
8362 return kNotInlinable;
8363 }
8364
8365 int nodes_added = target_shared->ast_node_count();
8366 return nodes_added;
8367}
8368
8369
8370bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInline(Handle<JSFunction> target,
8371 int arguments_count,
8372 HValue* implicit_return_value,
8373 BailoutId ast_id, BailoutId return_id,
8374 InliningKind inlining_kind) {
8375 if (target->context()->native_context() !=
8376 top_info()->closure()->context()->native_context()) {
8377 return false;
8378 }
8379 int nodes_added = InliningAstSize(target);
8380 if (nodes_added == kNotInlinable) return false;
8381
8382 Handle<JSFunction> caller = current_info()->closure();
8383
8384 if (nodes_added > Min(FLAG_max_inlined_nodes, kUnlimitedMaxInlinedNodes)) {
8385 TraceInline(target, caller, "target AST is too large [early]");
8386 return false;
8387 }
8388
8389 // Don't inline deeper than the maximum number of inlining levels.
8390 HEnvironment* env = environment();
8391 int current_level = 1;
8392 while (env->outer() != NULL__null) {
8393 if (current_level == FLAG_max_inlining_levels) {
8394 TraceInline(target, caller, "inline depth limit reached");
8395 return false;
8396 }
8397 if (env->outer()->frame_type() == JS_FUNCTION) {
8398 current_level++;
8399 }
8400 env = env->outer();
8401 }
8402
8403 // Don't inline recursive functions.
8404 for (FunctionState* state = function_state();
8405 state != NULL__null;
8406 state = state->outer()) {
8407 if (*state->compilation_info()->closure() == *target) {
8408 TraceInline(target, caller, "target is recursive");
8409 return false;
8410 }
8411 }
8412
8413 // We don't want to add more than a certain number of nodes from inlining.
8414 // Always inline small methods (<= 10 nodes).
8415 if (inlined_count_ > Min(FLAG_max_inlined_nodes_cumulative,
8416 kUnlimitedMaxInlinedNodesCumulative)) {
8417 TraceInline(target, caller, "cumulative AST node limit reached");
8418 return false;
8419 }
8420
8421 // Parse and allocate variables.
8422 // Use the same AstValueFactory for creating strings in the sub-compilation
8423 // step, but don't transfer ownership to target_info.
8424 ParseInfo parse_info(zone(), target);
8425 parse_info.set_ast_value_factory(
8426 top_info()->parse_info()->ast_value_factory());
8427 parse_info.set_ast_value_factory_owned(false);
8428
8429 CompilationInfo target_info(&parse_info);
8430 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> target_shared(target->shared());
8431
8432 if (inlining_kind != CONSTRUCT_CALL_RETURN &&
8433 IsClassConstructor(target_shared->kind())) {
8434 TraceInline(target, caller, "target is classConstructor");
8435 return false;
8436 }
8437
8438 if (target_shared->HasDebugInfo()) {
8439 TraceInline(target, caller, "target is being debugged");
8440 return false;
8441 }
8442 if (!Compiler::ParseAndAnalyze(target_info.parse_info())) {
8443 if (target_info.isolate()->has_pending_exception()) {
8444 // Parse or scope error, never optimize this function.
8445 SetStackOverflow();
8446 target_shared->DisableOptimization(kParseScopeError);
8447 }
8448 TraceInline(target, caller, "parse failure");
8449 return false;
8450 }
8451
8452 if (target_info.scope()->num_heap_slots() > 0) {
8453 TraceInline(target, caller, "target has context-allocated variables");
8454 return false;
8455 }
8456
8457 int rest_index;
8458 Variable* rest = target_info.scope()->rest_parameter(&rest_index);
8459 if (rest) {
8460 TraceInline(target, caller, "target uses rest parameters");
8461 return false;
8462 }
8463
8464 FunctionLiteral* function = target_info.literal();
8465
8466 // The following conditions must be checked again after re-parsing, because
8467 // earlier the information might not have been complete due to lazy parsing.
8468 nodes_added = function->ast_node_count();
8469 if (nodes_added > Min(FLAG_max_inlined_nodes, kUnlimitedMaxInlinedNodes)) {
8470 TraceInline(target, caller, "target AST is too large [late]");
8471 return false;
8472 }
8473 if (function->dont_optimize()) {
8474 TraceInline(target, caller, "target contains unsupported syntax [late]");
8475 return false;
8476 }
8477
8478 // If the function uses the arguments object check that inlining of functions
8479 // with arguments object is enabled and the arguments-variable is
8480 // stack allocated.
8481 if (function->scope()->arguments() != NULL__null) {
8482 if (!FLAG_inline_arguments) {
8483 TraceInline(target, caller, "target uses arguments object");
8484 return false;
8485 }
8486 }
8487
8488 // Unsupported variable references present.
8489 if (function->scope()->this_function_var() != nullptr ||
8490 function->scope()->new_target_var() != nullptr) {
8491 TraceInline(target, caller, "target uses new target or this function");
8492 return false;
8493 }
8494
8495 // All declarations must be inlineable.
8496 ZoneList<Declaration*>* decls = target_info.scope()->declarations();
8497 int decl_count = decls->length();
8498 for (int i = 0; i < decl_count; ++i) {
8499 if (!decls->at(i)->IsInlineable()) {
8500 TraceInline(target, caller, "target has non-trivial declaration");
8501 return false;
8502 }
8503 }
8504
8505 // In strong mode it is an error to call a function with too few arguments.
8506 // In that case do not inline because then the arity check would be skipped.
8507 if (is_strong(function->language_mode()) &&
8508 arguments_count < function->parameter_count()) {
8509 TraceInline(target, caller,
8510 "too few arguments passed to a strong function");
8511 return false;
8512 }
8513
8514 // Generate the deoptimization data for the unoptimized version of
8515 // the target function if we don't already have it.
8516 if (!Compiler::EnsureDeoptimizationSupport(&target_info)) {
8517 TraceInline(target, caller, "could not generate deoptimization info");
8518 return false;
8519 }
8520 // Remember that we inlined this function. This needs to be called right
8521 // after the EnsureDeoptimizationSupport call so that the code flusher
8522 // does not remove the code with the deoptimization support.
8523 top_info()->AddInlinedFunction(target_info.shared_info());
8524
8525 // ----------------------------------------------------------------
8526 // After this point, we've made a decision to inline this function (so
8527 // TryInline should always return true).
8528
8529 // Type-check the inlined function.
8530 DCHECK(target_shared->has_deoptimization_support())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(target_shared->has_deoptimization_support
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8530, "Check failed: %s."
, "target_shared->has_deoptimization_support()"); } } while
(0);
8531 AstTyper(target_info.isolate(), target_info.zone(), target_info.closure(),
8532 target_info.scope(), target_info.osr_ast_id(), target_info.literal())
8533 .Run();
8534
8535 int inlining_id = 0;
8536 if (top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) {
8537 inlining_id = top_info()->TraceInlinedFunction(
8538 target_shared, source_position(), function_state()->inlining_id());
8539 }
8540
8541 // Save the pending call context. Set up new one for the inlined function.
8542 // The function state is new-allocated because we need to delete it
8543 // in two different places.
8544 FunctionState* target_state =
8545 new FunctionState(this, &target_info, inlining_kind, inlining_id);
8546
8547 HConstant* undefined = graph()->GetConstantUndefined();
8548
8549 HEnvironment* inner_env =
8550 environment()->CopyForInlining(target,
8551 arguments_count,
8552 function,
8553 undefined,
8554 function_state()->inlining_kind());
8555
8556 HConstant* context = Add<HConstant>(Handle<Context>(target->context()));
8557 inner_env->BindContext(context);
8558
8559 // Create a dematerialized arguments object for the function, also copy the
8560 // current arguments values to use them for materialization.
8561 HEnvironment* arguments_env = inner_env->arguments_environment();
8562 int parameter_count = arguments_env->parameter_count();
8563 HArgumentsObject* arguments_object = Add<HArgumentsObject>(parameter_count);
8564 for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count; i++) {
8565 arguments_object->AddArgument(arguments_env->Lookup(i), zone());
8566 }
8567
8568 // If the function uses arguments object then bind bind one.
8569 if (function->scope()->arguments() != NULL__null) {
8570 DCHECK(function->scope()->arguments()->IsStackAllocated())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(function->scope()->arguments
()->IsStackAllocated())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 8570, "Check failed: %s.", "function->scope()->arguments()->IsStackAllocated()"
); } } while (0);
8571 inner_env->Bind(function->scope()->arguments(), arguments_object);
8572 }
8573
8574 // Capture the state before invoking the inlined function for deopt in the
8575 // inlined function. This simulate has no bailout-id since it's not directly
8576 // reachable for deopt, and is only used to capture the state. If the simulate
8577 // becomes reachable by merging, the ast id of the simulate merged into it is
8578 // adopted.
8579 Add<HSimulate>(BailoutId::None());
8580
8581 current_block()->UpdateEnvironment(inner_env);
8582 Scope* saved_scope = scope();
8583 set_scope(target_info.scope());
8584 HEnterInlined* enter_inlined =
8585 Add<HEnterInlined>(return_id, target, context, arguments_count, function,
8586 function_state()->inlining_kind(),
8587 function->scope()->arguments(), arguments_object);
8588 if (top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) {
8589 enter_inlined->set_inlining_id(inlining_id);
8590 }
8591 function_state()->set_entry(enter_inlined);
8592
8593 VisitDeclarations(target_info.scope()->declarations());
8594 VisitStatements(function->body());
8595 set_scope(saved_scope);
8596 if (HasStackOverflow()) {
8597 // Bail out if the inline function did, as we cannot residualize a call
8598 // instead, but do not disable optimization for the outer function.
8599 TraceInline(target, caller, "inline graph construction failed");
8600 target_shared->DisableOptimization(kInliningBailedOut);
8601 current_info()->RetryOptimization(kInliningBailedOut);
8602 delete target_state;
8603 return true;
8604 }
8605
8606 // Update inlined nodes count.
8607 inlined_count_ += nodes_added;
8608
8609 Handle<Code> unoptimized_code(target_shared->code());
8610 DCHECK(unoptimized_code->kind() == Code::FUNCTION)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(unoptimized_code->kind() ==
Code::FUNCTION)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 8610, "Check failed: %s.", "unoptimized_code->kind() == Code::FUNCTION"
); } } while (0);
8611 Handle<TypeFeedbackInfo> type_info(
8612 TypeFeedbackInfo::cast(unoptimized_code->type_feedback_info()));
8613 graph()->update_type_change_checksum(type_info->own_type_change_checksum());
8614
8615 TraceInline(target, caller, NULL__null);
8616
8617 if (current_block() != NULL__null) {
8618 FunctionState* state = function_state();
8619 if (state->inlining_kind() == CONSTRUCT_CALL_RETURN) {
8620 // Falling off the end of an inlined construct call. In a test context the
8621 // return value will always evaluate to true, in a value context the
8622 // return value is the newly allocated receiver.
8623 if (call_context()->IsTest()) {
8624 inlined_test_context()->ReturnValue(graph()->GetConstantTrue());
8625 } else if (call_context()->IsEffect()) {
8626 Goto(function_return(), state);
8627 } else {
8628 DCHECK(call_context()->IsValue())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(call_context()->IsValue())
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8628, "Check failed: %s."
, "call_context()->IsValue()"); } } while (0);
8629 AddLeaveInlined(implicit_return_value, state);
8630 }
8631 } else if (state->inlining_kind() == SETTER_CALL_RETURN) {
8632 // Falling off the end of an inlined setter call. The returned value is
8633 // never used, the value of an assignment is always the value of the RHS
8634 // of the assignment.
8635 if (call_context()->IsTest()) {
8636 inlined_test_context()->ReturnValue(implicit_return_value);
8637 } else if (call_context()->IsEffect()) {
8638 Goto(function_return(), state);
8639 } else {
8640 DCHECK(call_context()->IsValue())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(call_context()->IsValue())
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8640, "Check failed: %s."
, "call_context()->IsValue()"); } } while (0);
8641 AddLeaveInlined(implicit_return_value, state);
8642 }
8643 } else {
8644 // Falling off the end of a normal inlined function. This basically means
8645 // returning undefined.
8646 if (call_context()->IsTest()) {
8647 inlined_test_context()->ReturnValue(graph()->GetConstantFalse());
8648 } else if (call_context()->IsEffect()) {
8649 Goto(function_return(), state);
8650 } else {
8651 DCHECK(call_context()->IsValue())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(call_context()->IsValue())
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8651, "Check failed: %s."
, "call_context()->IsValue()"); } } while (0);
8652 AddLeaveInlined(undefined, state);
8653 }
8654 }
8655 }
8656
8657 // Fix up the function exits.
8658 if (inlined_test_context() != NULL__null) {
8659 HBasicBlock* if_true = inlined_test_context()->if_true();
8660 HBasicBlock* if_false = inlined_test_context()->if_false();
8661
8662 HEnterInlined* entry = function_state()->entry();
8663
8664 // Pop the return test context from the expression context stack.
8665 DCHECK(ast_context() == inlined_test_context())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ast_context() == inlined_test_context
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8665, "Check failed: %s."
, "ast_context() == inlined_test_context()"); } } while (0);
8666 ClearInlinedTestContext();
8667 delete target_state;
8668
8669 // Forward to the real test context.
8670 if (if_true->HasPredecessor()) {
8671 entry->RegisterReturnTarget(if_true, zone());
8672 if_true->SetJoinId(ast_id);
8673 HBasicBlock* true_target = TestContext::cast(ast_context())->if_true();
8674 Goto(if_true, true_target, function_state());
8675 }
8676 if (if_false->HasPredecessor()) {
8677 entry->RegisterReturnTarget(if_false, zone());
8678 if_false->SetJoinId(ast_id);
8679 HBasicBlock* false_target = TestContext::cast(ast_context())->if_false();
8680 Goto(if_false, false_target, function_state());
8681 }
8682 set_current_block(NULL__null);
8683 return true;
8684
8685 } else if (function_return()->HasPredecessor()) {
8686 function_state()->entry()->RegisterReturnTarget(function_return(), zone());
8687 function_return()->SetJoinId(ast_id);
8688 set_current_block(function_return());
8689 } else {
8690 set_current_block(NULL__null);
8691 }
8692 delete target_state;
8693 return true;
8694}
8695
8696
8697bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineCall(Call* expr) {
8698 return TryInline(expr->target(), expr->arguments()->length(), NULL__null,
8699 expr->id(), expr->ReturnId(), NORMAL_RETURN);
8700}
8701
8702
8703bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineConstruct(CallNew* expr,
8704 HValue* implicit_return_value) {
8705 return TryInline(expr->target(), expr->arguments()->length(),
8706 implicit_return_value, expr->id(), expr->ReturnId(),
8707 CONSTRUCT_CALL_RETURN);
8708}
8709
8710bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineGetter(Handle<Object> getter,
8711 Handle<Map> receiver_map,
8712 BailoutId ast_id,
8713 BailoutId return_id) {
8714 if (TryInlineApiGetter(getter, receiver_map, ast_id)) return true;
8715 return getter->IsJSFunction() &&
8716 TryInline(Handle<JSFunction>::cast(getter), 0, NULL__null, ast_id, return_id,
8717 GETTER_CALL_RETURN);
8718}
8719
8720bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineSetter(Handle<Object> setter,
8721 Handle<Map> receiver_map,
8722 BailoutId id,
8723 BailoutId assignment_id,
8724 HValue* implicit_return_value) {
8725 if (TryInlineApiSetter(setter, receiver_map, id)) return true;
8726 return setter->IsJSFunction() &&
8727 TryInline(Handle<JSFunction>::cast(setter), 1, implicit_return_value,
8728 id, assignment_id, SETTER_CALL_RETURN);
8729}
8730
8731
8732bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineIndirectCall(Handle<JSFunction> function,
8733 Call* expr,
8734 int arguments_count) {
8735 return TryInline(function, arguments_count, NULL__null, expr->id(),
8736 expr->ReturnId(), NORMAL_RETURN);
8737}
8738
8739
8740bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineBuiltinFunctionCall(Call* expr) {
8741 if (!expr->target()->shared()->HasBuiltinFunctionId()) return false;
8742 BuiltinFunctionId id = expr->target()->shared()->builtin_function_id();
8743 switch (id) {
8744 case kMathExp:
8745 if (!FLAG_fast_math) break;
8746 // Fall through if FLAG_fast_math.
8747 case kMathRound:
8748 case kMathFround:
8749 case kMathFloor:
8750 case kMathAbs:
8751 case kMathSqrt:
8752 case kMathLog:
8753 case kMathClz32:
8754 if (expr->arguments()->length() == 1) {
8755 HValue* argument = Pop();
8756 Drop(2); // Receiver and function.
8757 HInstruction* op = NewUncasted<HUnaryMathOperation>(argument, id);
8758 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(op, expr->id());
8759 return true;
8760 }
8761 break;
8762 case kMathImul:
8763 if (expr->arguments()->length() == 2) {
8764 HValue* right = Pop();
8765 HValue* left = Pop();
8766 Drop(2); // Receiver and function.
8767 HInstruction* op =
8768 HMul::NewImul(isolate(), zone(), context(), left, right);
8769 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(op, expr->id());
8770 return true;
8771 }
8772 break;
8773 default:
8774 // Not supported for inlining yet.
8775 break;
8776 }
8777 return false;
8778}
8779
8780
8781// static
8782bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::IsReadOnlyLengthDescriptor(
8783 Handle<Map> jsarray_map) {
8784 DCHECK(!jsarray_map->is_dictionary_map())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!jsarray_map->is_dictionary_map
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8784, "Check failed: %s."
, "!jsarray_map->is_dictionary_map()"); } } while (0);
8785 Isolate* isolate = jsarray_map->GetIsolate();
8786 Handle<Name> length_string = isolate->factory()->length_string();
8787 DescriptorArray* descriptors = jsarray_map->instance_descriptors();
8788 int number =
8789 descriptors->SearchWithCache(isolate, *length_string, *jsarray_map);
8790 DCHECK_NE(DescriptorArray::kNotFound, number)do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckNEImpl( (DescriptorArray
::kNotFound), (number), "DescriptorArray::kNotFound" " " "!="
" " "number")) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8790
, "Check failed: %s.", _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while
(0);
8791 return descriptors->GetDetails(number).IsReadOnly();
8792}
8793
8794
8795// static
8796bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::CanInlineArrayResizeOperation(
8797 Handle<Map> receiver_map) {
8798 return !receiver_map.is_null() && receiver_map->prototype()->IsJSObject() &&
8799 receiver_map->instance_type() == JS_ARRAY_TYPE &&
8800 IsFastElementsKind(receiver_map->elements_kind()) &&
8801 !receiver_map->is_dictionary_map() && !receiver_map->is_observed() &&
8802 receiver_map->is_extensible() &&
8803 (!receiver_map->is_prototype_map() || receiver_map->is_stable()) &&
8804 !IsReadOnlyLengthDescriptor(receiver_map);
8805}
8806
8807
8808bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineBuiltinMethodCall(
8809 Call* expr, Handle<JSFunction> function, Handle<Map> receiver_map,
8810 int args_count_no_receiver) {
8811 if (!function->shared()->HasBuiltinFunctionId()) return false;
8812 BuiltinFunctionId id = function->shared()->builtin_function_id();
8813 int argument_count = args_count_no_receiver + 1; // Plus receiver.
8814
8815 if (receiver_map.is_null()) {
8816 HValue* receiver = environment()->ExpressionStackAt(args_count_no_receiver);
8817 if (receiver->IsConstant() &&
8818 HConstant::cast(receiver)->handle(isolate())->IsHeapObject()) {
8819 receiver_map =
8820 handle(Handle<HeapObject>::cast(
8821 HConstant::cast(receiver)->handle(isolate()))->map());
8822 }
8823 }
8824 // Try to inline calls like Math.* as operations in the calling function.
8825 switch (id) {
8826 case kStringCharCodeAt:
8827 case kStringCharAt:
8828 if (argument_count == 2) {
8829 HValue* index = Pop();
8830 HValue* string = Pop();
8831 Drop(1); // Function.
8832 HInstruction* char_code =
8833 BuildStringCharCodeAt(string, index);
8834 if (id == kStringCharCodeAt) {
8835 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(char_code, expr->id());
8836 return true;
8837 }
8838 AddInstruction(char_code);
8839 HInstruction* result = NewUncasted<HStringCharFromCode>(char_code);
8840 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
8841 return true;
8842 }
8843 break;
8844 case kStringFromCharCode:
8845 if (argument_count == 2) {
8846 HValue* argument = Pop();
8847 Drop(2); // Receiver and function.
8848 HInstruction* result = NewUncasted<HStringCharFromCode>(argument);
8849 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
8850 return true;
8851 }
8852 break;
8853 case kMathExp:
8854 if (!FLAG_fast_math) break;
8855 // Fall through if FLAG_fast_math.
8856 case kMathRound:
8857 case kMathFround:
8858 case kMathFloor:
8859 case kMathAbs:
8860 case kMathSqrt:
8861 case kMathLog:
8862 case kMathClz32:
8863 if (argument_count == 2) {
8864 HValue* argument = Pop();
8865 Drop(2); // Receiver and function.
8866 HInstruction* op = NewUncasted<HUnaryMathOperation>(argument, id);
8867 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(op, expr->id());
8868 return true;
8869 }
8870 break;
8871 case kMathPow:
8872 if (argument_count == 3) {
8873 HValue* right = Pop();
8874 HValue* left = Pop();
8875 Drop(2); // Receiver and function.
8876 HInstruction* result = NULL__null;
8877 // Use sqrt() if exponent is 0.5 or -0.5.
8878 if (right->IsConstant() && HConstant::cast(right)->HasDoubleValue()) {
8879 double exponent = HConstant::cast(right)->DoubleValue();
8880 if (exponent == 0.5) {
8881 result = NewUncasted<HUnaryMathOperation>(left, kMathPowHalf);
8882 } else if (exponent == -0.5) {
8883 HValue* one = graph()->GetConstant1();
8884 HInstruction* sqrt = AddUncasted<HUnaryMathOperation>(
8885 left, kMathPowHalf);
8886 // MathPowHalf doesn't have side effects so there's no need for
8887 // an environment simulation here.
8888 DCHECK(!sqrt->HasObservableSideEffects())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!sqrt->HasObservableSideEffects
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 8888, "Check failed: %s."
, "!sqrt->HasObservableSideEffects()"); } } while (0);
8889 result = NewUncasted<HDiv>(one, sqrt);
8890 } else if (exponent == 2.0) {
8891 result = NewUncasted<HMul>(left, left);
8892 }
8893 }
8894
8895 if (result == NULL__null) {
8896 result = NewUncasted<HPower>(left, right);
8897 }
8898 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
8899 return true;
8900 }
8901 break;
8902 case kMathMax:
8903 case kMathMin:
8904 if (argument_count == 3) {
8905 HValue* right = Pop();
8906 HValue* left = Pop();
8907 Drop(2); // Receiver and function.
8908 HMathMinMax::Operation op = (id == kMathMin) ? HMathMinMax::kMathMin
8909 : HMathMinMax::kMathMax;
8910 HInstruction* result = NewUncasted<HMathMinMax>(left, right, op);
8911 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
8912 return true;
8913 }
8914 break;
8915 case kMathImul:
8916 if (argument_count == 3) {
8917 HValue* right = Pop();
8918 HValue* left = Pop();
8919 Drop(2); // Receiver and function.
8920 HInstruction* result =
8921 HMul::NewImul(isolate(), zone(), context(), left, right);
8922 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
8923 return true;
8924 }
8925 break;
8926 case kArrayPop: {
8927 if (!CanInlineArrayResizeOperation(receiver_map)) return false;
8928 ElementsKind elements_kind = receiver_map->elements_kind();
8929
8930 Drop(args_count_no_receiver);
8931 HValue* result;
8932 HValue* reduced_length;
8933 HValue* receiver = Pop();
8934
8935 HValue* checked_object = AddCheckMap(receiver, receiver_map);
8936 HValue* length =
8937 Add<HLoadNamedField>(checked_object, nullptr,
8938 HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(elements_kind));
8939
8940 Drop(1); // Function.
8941
8942 { NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
8943 IfBuilder length_checker(this);
8944
8945 HValue* bounds_check = length_checker.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
8946 length, graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::EQ);
8947 length_checker.Then();
8948
8949 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
8950
8951 length_checker.Else();
8952 HValue* elements = AddLoadElements(checked_object);
8953 // Ensure that we aren't popping from a copy-on-write array.
8954 if (IsFastSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
8955 elements = BuildCopyElementsOnWrite(checked_object, elements,
8956 elements_kind, length);
8957 }
8958 reduced_length = AddUncasted<HSub>(length, graph()->GetConstant1());
8959 result = AddElementAccess(elements, reduced_length, nullptr,
8960 bounds_check, nullptr, elements_kind, LOAD);
8961 HValue* hole = IsFastSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind)
8962 ? graph()->GetConstantHole()
8963 : Add<HConstant>(HConstant::kHoleNaN);
8964 if (IsFastSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
8965 elements_kind = FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS;
8966 }
8967 AddElementAccess(elements, reduced_length, hole, bounds_check, nullptr,
8968 elements_kind, STORE);
8969 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
8970 checked_object, HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(elements_kind),
8971 reduced_length, STORE_TO_INITIALIZED_ENTRY);
8972
8973 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(result);
8974
8975 length_checker.End();
8976 }
8977 result = ast_context()->IsEffect() ? graph()->GetConstant0() : Top();
8978 Add<HSimulate>(expr->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
8979 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Drop(1);
8980
8981 ast_context()->ReturnValue(result);
8982 return true;
8983 }
8984 case kArrayPush: {
8985 if (!CanInlineArrayResizeOperation(receiver_map)) return false;
8986 ElementsKind elements_kind = receiver_map->elements_kind();
8987
8988 // If there may be elements accessors in the prototype chain, the fast
8989 // inlined version can't be used.
8990 if (receiver_map->DictionaryElementsInPrototypeChainOnly()) return false;
8991 // If there currently can be no elements accessors on the prototype chain,
8992 // it doesn't mean that there won't be any later. Install a full prototype
8993 // chain check to trap element accessors being installed on the prototype
8994 // chain, which would cause elements to go to dictionary mode and result
8995 // in a map change.
8996 Handle<JSObject> prototype(JSObject::cast(receiver_map->prototype()));
8997 BuildCheckPrototypeMaps(prototype, Handle<JSObject>());
8998
8999 // Protect against adding elements to the Array prototype, which needs to
9000 // route through appropriate bottlenecks.
9001 if (isolate()->IsFastArrayConstructorPrototypeChainIntact() &&
9002 !prototype->IsJSArray()) {
9003 return false;
9004 }
9005
9006 const int argc = args_count_no_receiver;
9007 if (argc != 1) return false;
9008
9009 HValue* value_to_push = Pop();
9010 HValue* array = Pop();
9011 Drop(1); // Drop function.
9012
9013 HInstruction* new_size = NULL__null;
9014 HValue* length = NULL__null;
9015
9016 {
9017 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
9018
9019 length = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
9020 array, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(elements_kind));
9021
9022 new_size = AddUncasted<HAdd>(length, graph()->GetConstant1());
9023
9024 bool is_array = receiver_map->instance_type() == JS_ARRAY_TYPE;
9025 HValue* checked_array = Add<HCheckMaps>(array, receiver_map);
9026 BuildUncheckedMonomorphicElementAccess(
9027 checked_array, length, value_to_push, is_array, elements_kind,
9028 STORE, NEVER_RETURN_HOLE, STORE_AND_GROW_NO_TRANSITION);
9029
9030 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(new_size);
9031 Add<HSimulate>(expr->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
9032 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Drop(1);
9033 }
9034
9035 ast_context()->ReturnValue(new_size);
9036 return true;
9037 }
9038 case kArrayShift: {
9039 if (!CanInlineArrayResizeOperation(receiver_map)) return false;
9040 ElementsKind kind = receiver_map->elements_kind();
9041
9042 // If there may be elements accessors in the prototype chain, the fast
9043 // inlined version can't be used.
9044 if (receiver_map->DictionaryElementsInPrototypeChainOnly()) return false;
9045
9046 // If there currently can be no elements accessors on the prototype chain,
9047 // it doesn't mean that there won't be any later. Install a full prototype
9048 // chain check to trap element accessors being installed on the prototype
9049 // chain, which would cause elements to go to dictionary mode and result
9050 // in a map change.
9051 BuildCheckPrototypeMaps(
9052 handle(JSObject::cast(receiver_map->prototype()), isolate()),
9053 Handle<JSObject>::null());
9054
9055 // Threshold for fast inlined Array.shift().
9056 HConstant* inline_threshold = Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(16));
9057
9058 Drop(args_count_no_receiver);
9059 HValue* receiver = Pop();
9060 HValue* function = Pop();
9061 HValue* result;
9062
9063 {
9064 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
9065
9066 HValue* length = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
9067 receiver, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(kind));
9068
9069 IfBuilder if_lengthiszero(this);
9070 HValue* lengthiszero = if_lengthiszero.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
9071 length, graph()->GetConstant0(), Token::EQ);
9072 if_lengthiszero.Then();
9073 {
9074 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
9075 }
9076 if_lengthiszero.Else();
9077 {
9078 HValue* elements = AddLoadElements(receiver);
9079
9080 // Check if we can use the fast inlined Array.shift().
9081 IfBuilder if_inline(this);
9082 if_inline.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
9083 length, inline_threshold, Token::LTE);
9084 if (IsFastSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)) {
9085 // We cannot handle copy-on-write backing stores here.
9086 if_inline.AndIf<HCompareMap>(
9087 elements, isolate()->factory()->fixed_array_map());
9088 }
9089 if_inline.Then();
9090 {
9091 // Remember the result.
9092 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) {
9093 Push(AddElementAccess(elements, graph()->GetConstant0(), nullptr,
9094 lengthiszero, nullptr, kind, LOAD));
9095 }
9096
9097 // Compute the new length.
9098 HValue* new_length = AddUncasted<HSub>(
9099 length, graph()->GetConstant1());
9100 new_length->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
9101
9102 // Copy the remaining elements.
9103 LoopBuilder loop(this, context(), LoopBuilder::kPostIncrement);
9104 {
9105 HValue* new_key = loop.BeginBody(
9106 graph()->GetConstant0(), new_length, Token::LT);
9107 HValue* key = AddUncasted<HAdd>(new_key, graph()->GetConstant1());
9108 key->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
9109 ElementsKind copy_kind =
9110 kind == FAST_HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS ? FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS : kind;
9111 HValue* element =
9112 AddUncasted<HLoadKeyed>(elements, key, lengthiszero, nullptr,
9113 copy_kind, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
9114 HStoreKeyed* store = Add<HStoreKeyed>(elements, new_key, element,
9115 nullptr, copy_kind);
9116 store->SetFlag(HValue::kAllowUndefinedAsNaN);
9117 }
9118 loop.EndBody();
9119
9120 // Put a hole at the end.
9121 HValue* hole = IsFastSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)
9122 ? graph()->GetConstantHole()
9123 : Add<HConstant>(HConstant::kHoleNaN);
9124 if (IsFastSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)) kind = FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS;
9125 Add<HStoreKeyed>(elements, new_length, hole, nullptr, kind,
9126 INITIALIZING_STORE);
9127
9128 // Remember new length.
9129 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
9130 receiver, HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(kind),
9131 new_length, STORE_TO_INITIALIZED_ENTRY);
9132 }
9133 if_inline.Else();
9134 {
9135 Add<HPushArguments>(receiver);
9136 result = Add<HCallJSFunction>(function, 1);
9137 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(result);
9138 }
9139 if_inline.End();
9140 }
9141 if_lengthiszero.End();
9142 }
9143 result = ast_context()->IsEffect() ? graph()->GetConstant0() : Top();
9144 Add<HSimulate>(expr->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
9145 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Drop(1);
9146 ast_context()->ReturnValue(result);
9147 return true;
9148 }
9149 case kArrayIndexOf:
9150 case kArrayLastIndexOf: {
9151 if (receiver_map.is_null()) return false;
9152 if (receiver_map->instance_type() != JS_ARRAY_TYPE) return false;
9153 if (!receiver_map->prototype()->IsJSObject()) return false;
9154 ElementsKind kind = receiver_map->elements_kind();
9155 if (!IsFastElementsKind(kind)) return false;
9156 if (receiver_map->is_observed()) return false;
9157 if (argument_count != 2) return false;
9158 if (!receiver_map->is_extensible()) return false;
9159
9160 // If there may be elements accessors in the prototype chain, the fast
9161 // inlined version can't be used.
9162 if (receiver_map->DictionaryElementsInPrototypeChainOnly()) return false;
9163
9164 // If there currently can be no elements accessors on the prototype chain,
9165 // it doesn't mean that there won't be any later. Install a full prototype
9166 // chain check to trap element accessors being installed on the prototype
9167 // chain, which would cause elements to go to dictionary mode and result
9168 // in a map change.
9169 BuildCheckPrototypeMaps(
9170 handle(JSObject::cast(receiver_map->prototype()), isolate()),
9171 Handle<JSObject>::null());
9172
9173 HValue* search_element = Pop();
9174 HValue* receiver = Pop();
9175 Drop(1); // Drop function.
9176
9177 ArrayIndexOfMode mode = (id == kArrayIndexOf)
9178 ? kFirstIndexOf : kLastIndexOf;
9179 HValue* index = BuildArrayIndexOf(receiver, search_element, kind, mode);
9180
9181 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Push(index);
9182 Add<HSimulate>(expr->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
9183 if (!ast_context()->IsEffect()) Drop(1);
9184 ast_context()->ReturnValue(index);
9185 return true;
9186 }
9187 default:
9188 // Not yet supported for inlining.
9189 break;
9190 }
9191 return false;
9192}

9195bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineApiFunctionCall(Call* expr,
9196 HValue* receiver) {
9197 Handle<JSFunction> function = expr->target();
9198 int argc = expr->arguments()->length();
9199 SmallMapList receiver_maps;
9200 return TryInlineApiCall(function,
9201 receiver,
9202 &receiver_maps,
9203 argc,
9204 expr->id(),
9205 kCallApiFunction);
9206}
