9209bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineApiMethodCall(
9210 Call* expr,
9211 HValue* receiver,
9212 SmallMapList* receiver_maps) {
9213 Handle<JSFunction> function = expr->target();
9214 int argc = expr->arguments()->length();
9215 return TryInlineApiCall(function,
9216 receiver,
9217 receiver_maps,
9218 argc,
9219 expr->id(),
9220 kCallApiMethod);
9221}
9222
9223bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineApiGetter(Handle<Object> function,
9224 Handle<Map> receiver_map,
9225 BailoutId ast_id) {
9226 SmallMapList receiver_maps(1, zone());
9227 receiver_maps.Add(receiver_map, zone());
9228 return TryInlineApiCall(function,
9229 NULL__null, // Receiver is on expression stack.
9230 &receiver_maps,
9231 0,
9232 ast_id,
9233 kCallApiGetter);
9234}
9235
9236bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineApiSetter(Handle<Object> function,
9237 Handle<Map> receiver_map,
9238 BailoutId ast_id) {
9239 SmallMapList receiver_maps(1, zone());
9240 receiver_maps.Add(receiver_map, zone());
9241 return TryInlineApiCall(function,
9242 NULL__null, // Receiver is on expression stack.
9243 &receiver_maps,
9244 1,
9245 ast_id,
9246 kCallApiSetter);
9247}
9248
9249bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryInlineApiCall(Handle<Object> function,
9250 HValue* receiver,
9251 SmallMapList* receiver_maps,
9252 int argc, BailoutId ast_id,
9253 ApiCallType call_type) {
9254 if (function->IsJSFunction() &&
9255 Handle<JSFunction>::cast(function)->context()->native_context() !=
9256 top_info()->closure()->context()->native_context()) {
9257 return false;
9258 }
9259 CallOptimization optimization(function);
9260 if (!optimization.is_simple_api_call()) return false;
9261 Handle<Map> holder_map;
9262 for (int i = 0; i < receiver_maps->length(); ++i) {
9263 auto map = receiver_maps->at(i);
9264 // Don't inline calls to receivers requiring accesschecks.
9265 if (map->is_access_check_needed()) return false;
9266 }
9267 if (call_type == kCallApiFunction) {
9268 // Cannot embed a direct reference to the global proxy map
9269 // as it maybe dropped on deserialization.
9270 CHECK(!isolate()->serializer_enabled())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!isolate()->serializer_enabled
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9270, "Check failed: %s."
, "!isolate()->serializer_enabled()"); } } while (0);
9271 DCHECK(function->IsJSFunction())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(function->IsJSFunction()))
, 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9271, "Check failed: %s."
, "function->IsJSFunction()"); } } while (0);
9272 DCHECK_EQ(0, receiver_maps->length())do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (0), (receiver_maps
->length()), "0" " " "==" " " "receiver_maps->length()"
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9272, "Check failed: %s."
, _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0);
9273 receiver_maps->Add(
9274 handle(Handle<JSFunction>::cast(function)->global_proxy()->map()),
9275 zone());
9276 }
9277 CallOptimization::HolderLookup holder_lookup =
9278 CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound;
9279 Handle<JSObject> api_holder = optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(
9280 receiver_maps->first(), &holder_lookup);
9281 if (holder_lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound) return false;
9282
9283 if (FLAG_trace_inlining) {
9284 PrintF("Inlining api function ");
9285 function->ShortPrint();
9286 PrintF("\n");
9287 }
9288
9289 bool is_function = false;
9290 bool is_store = false;
9291 switch (call_type) {
9292 case kCallApiFunction:
9293 case kCallApiMethod:
9294 // Need to check that none of the receiver maps could have changed.
9295 Add<HCheckMaps>(receiver, receiver_maps);
9296 // Need to ensure the chain between receiver and api_holder is intact.
9297 if (holder_lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound) {
9298 AddCheckPrototypeMaps(api_holder, receiver_maps->first());
9299 } else {
9300 DCHECK_EQ(holder_lookup, CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver)do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (holder_lookup
), (CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver), "holder_lookup" " "
"==" " " "CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver")) { V8_Fatal(
"../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9300, "Check failed: %s.", _msg
->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0);
9301 }
9302 // Includes receiver.
9303 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argc + 1);
9304 is_function = true;
9305 break;
9306 case kCallApiGetter:
9307 // Receiver and prototype chain cannot have changed.
9308 DCHECK_EQ(0, argc)do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (0), (argc
), "0" " " "==" " " "argc")) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 9308, "Check failed: %s.", _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; }
} while (0);
9309 DCHECK_NULL(receiver)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((receiver) == nullptr)), 0)))
{ V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9309, "Check failed: %s."
, "(receiver) == nullptr"); } } while (0);
9310 // Receiver is on expression stack.
9311 receiver = Pop();
9312 Add<HPushArguments>(receiver);
9313 break;
9314 case kCallApiSetter:
9315 {
9316 is_store = true;
9317 // Receiver and prototype chain cannot have changed.
9318 DCHECK_EQ(1, argc)do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (1), (argc
), "1" " " "==" " " "argc")) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 9318, "Check failed: %s.", _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; }
} while (0);
9319 DCHECK_NULL(receiver)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((receiver) == nullptr)), 0)))
{ V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9319, "Check failed: %s."
, "(receiver) == nullptr"); } } while (0);
9320 // Receiver and value are on expression stack.
9321 HValue* value = Pop();
9322 receiver = Pop();
9323 Add<HPushArguments>(receiver, value);
9324 break;
9325 }
9326 }
9327
9328 HValue* holder = NULL__null;
9329 switch (holder_lookup) {
9330 case CallOptimization::kHolderFound:
9331 holder = Add<HConstant>(api_holder);
9332 break;
9333 case CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver:
9334 holder = receiver;
9335 break;
9336 case CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound:
9337 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9337, "unreachable code"
);
9338 break;
9339 }
9340 Handle<CallHandlerInfo> api_call_info = optimization.api_call_info();
9341 Handle<Object> call_data_obj(api_call_info->data(), isolate());
9342 bool call_data_undefined = call_data_obj->IsUndefined();
9343 HValue* call_data = Add<HConstant>(call_data_obj);
9344 ApiFunction fun(v8::ToCData<Address>(api_call_info->callback()));
9345 ExternalReference ref = ExternalReference(&fun,
9346 ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL,
9347 isolate());
9348 HValue* api_function_address = Add<HConstant>(ExternalReference(ref));
9349
9350 HValue* op_vals[] = {context(), Add<HConstant>(function), call_data, holder,
9351 api_function_address, nullptr};
9352
9353 HInstruction* call = nullptr;
9354 if (!is_function) {
9355 CallApiAccessorStub stub(isolate(), is_store, call_data_undefined,
9356 !optimization.is_constant_call());
9357 Handle<Code> code = stub.GetCode();
9358 HConstant* code_value = Add<HConstant>(code);
9359 ApiAccessorDescriptor descriptor(isolate());
9360 call = New<HCallWithDescriptor>(
9361 code_value, argc + 1, descriptor,
9362 Vector<HValue*>(op_vals, arraysize(op_vals)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(op_vals))) - 1));
9363 } else if (argc <= CallApiFunctionWithFixedArgsStub::kMaxFixedArgs) {
9364 CallApiFunctionWithFixedArgsStub stub(isolate(), argc, call_data_undefined);
9365 Handle<Code> code = stub.GetCode();
9366 HConstant* code_value = Add<HConstant>(code);
9367 ApiFunctionWithFixedArgsDescriptor descriptor(isolate());
9368 call = New<HCallWithDescriptor>(
9369 code_value, argc + 1, descriptor,
9370 Vector<HValue*>(op_vals, arraysize(op_vals)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(op_vals))) - 1));
9371 Drop(1); // Drop function.
9372 } else {
9373 op_vals[arraysize(op_vals)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(op_vals))) - 1] = Add<HConstant>(argc);
9374 CallApiFunctionStub stub(isolate(), call_data_undefined);
9375 Handle<Code> code = stub.GetCode();
9376 HConstant* code_value = Add<HConstant>(code);
9377 ApiFunctionDescriptor descriptor(isolate());
9378 call =
9379 New<HCallWithDescriptor>(code_value, argc + 1, descriptor,
9380 Vector<HValue*>(op_vals, arraysize(op_vals)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(op_vals)))));
9381 Drop(1); // Drop function.
9382 }
9383
9384 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(call, ast_id);
9385 return true;
9386}
9387
9388
9389void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandleIndirectCall(Call* expr, HValue* function,
9390 int arguments_count) {
9391 Handle<JSFunction> known_function;
9392 int args_count_no_receiver = arguments_count - 1;
9393 if (function->IsConstant() &&
9394 HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate())->IsJSFunction()) {
9395 known_function =
9396 Handle<JSFunction>::cast(HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate()));
9397 if (TryInlineBuiltinMethodCall(expr, known_function, Handle<Map>(),
9398 args_count_no_receiver)) {
9399 if (FLAG_trace_inlining) {
9400 PrintF("Inlining builtin ");
9401 known_function->ShortPrint();
9402 PrintF("\n");
9403 }
9404 return;
9405 }
9406
9407 if (TryInlineIndirectCall(known_function, expr, args_count_no_receiver)) {
9408 return;
9409 }
9410 }
9411
9412 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(arguments_count);
9413 HInvokeFunction* call =
9414 New<HInvokeFunction>(function, known_function, arguments_count);
9415 Drop(1); // Function
9416 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(call, expr->id());
9417}
9418
9419
9420bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryIndirectCall(Call* expr) {
9421 DCHECK(expr->expression()->IsProperty())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(expr->expression()->IsProperty
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9421, "Check failed: %s."
, "expr->expression()->IsProperty()"); } } while (0);
9422
9423 if (!expr->IsMonomorphic()) {
9424 return false;
9425 }
9426 Handle<Map> function_map = expr->GetReceiverTypes()->first();
9427 if (function_map->instance_type() != JS_FUNCTION_TYPE ||
9428 !expr->target()->shared()->HasBuiltinFunctionId()) {
9429 return false;
9430 }
9431
9432 switch (expr->target()->shared()->builtin_function_id()) {
9433 case kFunctionCall: {
9434 if (expr->arguments()->length() == 0) return false;
9435 BuildFunctionCall(expr);
9436 return true;
9437 }
9438 case kFunctionApply: {
9439 // For .apply, only the pattern f.apply(receiver, arguments)
9440 // is supported.
9441 if (current_info()->scope()->arguments() == NULL__null) return false;
9442
9443 if (!CanBeFunctionApplyArguments(expr)) return false;
9444
9445 BuildFunctionApply(expr);
9446 return true;
9447 }
9448 default: { return false; }
9449 }
9450 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9450, "unreachable code"
);
9451}
9452
9453
9454// f.apply(...)
9455void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildFunctionApply(Call* expr) {
9456 ZoneList<Expression*>* args = expr->arguments();
9457 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(args->at(0)));
9458 HValue* receiver = Pop(); // receiver
9459 HValue* function = Pop(); // f
9460 Drop(1); // apply
9461
9462 Handle<Map> function_map = expr->GetReceiverTypes()->first();
9463 HValue* checked_function = AddCheckMap(function, function_map);
9464
9465 if (function_state()->outer() == NULL__null) {
9466 HInstruction* elements = Add<HArgumentsElements>(false);
9467 HInstruction* length = Add<HArgumentsLength>(elements);
9468 HValue* wrapped_receiver = BuildWrapReceiver(receiver, checked_function);
9469 HInstruction* result = New<HApplyArguments>(function,
9470 wrapped_receiver,
9471 length,
9472 elements);
9473 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
9474 } else {
9475 // We are inside inlined function and we know exactly what is inside
9476 // arguments object. But we need to be able to materialize at deopt.
9477 DCHECK_EQ(environment()->arguments_environment()->parameter_count(),do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (environment
()->arguments_environment()->parameter_count()), (function_state
()->entry()->arguments_object()->arguments_count()),
"environment()->arguments_environment()->parameter_count()"
" " "==" " " "function_state()->entry()->arguments_object()->arguments_count()"
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9478, "Check failed: %s."
, _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0)
9478 function_state()->entry()->arguments_object()->arguments_count())do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (environment
()->arguments_environment()->parameter_count()), (function_state
()->entry()->arguments_object()->arguments_count()),
"environment()->arguments_environment()->parameter_count()"
" " "==" " " "function_state()->entry()->arguments_object()->arguments_count()"
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9478, "Check failed: %s."
, _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0);
9479 HArgumentsObject* args = function_state()->entry()->arguments_object();
9480 const ZoneList<HValue*>* arguments_values = args->arguments_values();
9481 int arguments_count = arguments_values->length();
9482 Push(function);
9483 Push(BuildWrapReceiver(receiver, checked_function));
9484 for (int i = 1; i < arguments_count; i++) {
9485 Push(arguments_values->at(i));
9486 }
9487 HandleIndirectCall(expr, function, arguments_count);
9488 }
9489}
9490
9491
9492// f.call(...)
9493void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildFunctionCall(Call* expr) {
9494 HValue* function = Top(); // f
9495 Handle<Map> function_map = expr->GetReceiverTypes()->first();
9496 HValue* checked_function = AddCheckMap(function, function_map);
9497
9498 // f and call are on the stack in the unoptimized code
9499 // during evaluation of the arguments.
9500 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitExpressions(expr->arguments()));
9501
9502 int args_length = expr->arguments()->length();
9503 int receiver_index = args_length - 1;
9504 // Patch the receiver.
9505 HValue* receiver = BuildWrapReceiver(
9506 environment()->ExpressionStackAt(receiver_index), checked_function);
9507 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(receiver_index, receiver);
9508
9509 // Call must not be on the stack from now on.
9510 int call_index = args_length + 1;
9511 environment()->RemoveExpressionStackAt(call_index);
9512
9513 HandleIndirectCall(expr, function, args_length);
9514}
9515
9516
9517HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::ImplicitReceiverFor(HValue* function,
9518 Handle<JSFunction> target) {
9519 SharedFunctionInfo* shared = target->shared();
9520 if (is_sloppy(shared->language_mode()) && !shared->native()) {
9521 // Cannot embed a direct reference to the global proxy
9522 // as is it dropped on deserialization.
9523 CHECK(!isolate()->serializer_enabled())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!isolate()->serializer_enabled
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9523, "Check failed: %s."
, "!isolate()->serializer_enabled()"); } } while (0);
9524 Handle<JSObject> global_proxy(target->context()->global_proxy());
9525 return Add<HConstant>(global_proxy);
9526 }
9527 return graph()->GetConstantUndefined();
9528}
9529
9530
9531void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildArrayCall(Expression* expression,
9532 int arguments_count,
9533 HValue* function,
9534 Handle<AllocationSite> site) {
9535 Add<HCheckValue>(function, array_function());
9536
9537 if (IsCallArrayInlineable(arguments_count, site)) {
9538 BuildInlinedCallArray(expression, arguments_count, site);
9539 return;
9540 }
9541
9542 HInstruction* call = PreProcessCall(New<HCallNewArray>(
9543 function, arguments_count + 1, site->GetElementsKind(), site));
9544 if (expression->IsCall()) {
9545 Drop(1);
9546 }
9547 ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(call, expression->id());
9548}
9549
9550
9551HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildArrayIndexOf(HValue* receiver,
9552 HValue* search_element,
9553 ElementsKind kind,
9554 ArrayIndexOfMode mode) {
9555 DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(kind))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsFastElementsKind(kind))), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9555, "Check failed: %s."
, "IsFastElementsKind(kind)"); } } while (0);
9556
9557 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
9558
9559 HValue* elements = AddLoadElements(receiver);
9560 HValue* length = AddLoadArrayLength(receiver, kind);
9561
9562 HValue* initial;
9563 HValue* terminating;
9564 Token::Value token;
9565 LoopBuilder::Direction direction;
9566 if (mode == kFirstIndexOf) {
9567 initial = graph()->GetConstant0();
9568 terminating = length;
9569 token = Token::LT;
9570 direction = LoopBuilder::kPostIncrement;
9571 } else {
9572 DCHECK_EQ(kLastIndexOf, mode)do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (kLastIndexOf
), (mode), "kLastIndexOf" " " "==" " " "mode")) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 9572, "Check failed: %s.", _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; }
} while (0);
9573 initial = length;
9574 terminating = graph()->GetConstant0();
9575 token = Token::GT;
9576 direction = LoopBuilder::kPreDecrement;
9577 }
9578
9579 Push(graph()->GetConstantMinus1());
9580 if (IsFastDoubleElementsKind(kind) || IsFastSmiElementsKind(kind)) {
9581 // Make sure that we can actually compare numbers correctly below, see
9582 // https://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=407946 for details.
9583 search_element = AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(
9584 search_element, IsFastSmiElementsKind(kind) ? Representation::Smi()
9585 : Representation::Double());
9586
9587 LoopBuilder loop(this, context(), direction);
9588 {
9589 HValue* index = loop.BeginBody(initial, terminating, token);
9590 HValue* element = AddUncasted<HLoadKeyed>(
9591 elements, index, nullptr, nullptr, kind, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
9592 IfBuilder if_issame(this);
9593 if_issame.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(element, search_element,
9594 Token::EQ_STRICT);
9595 if_issame.Then();
9596 {
9597 Drop(1);
9598 Push(index);
9599 loop.Break();
9600 }
9601 if_issame.End();
9602 }
9603 loop.EndBody();
9604 } else {
9605 IfBuilder if_isstring(this);
9606 if_isstring.If<HIsStringAndBranch>(search_element);
9607 if_isstring.Then();
9608 {
9609 LoopBuilder loop(this, context(), direction);
9610 {
9611 HValue* index = loop.BeginBody(initial, terminating, token);
9612 HValue* element = AddUncasted<HLoadKeyed>(
9613 elements, index, nullptr, nullptr, kind, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
9614 IfBuilder if_issame(this);
9615 if_issame.If<HIsStringAndBranch>(element);
9616 if_issame.AndIf<HStringCompareAndBranch>(
9617 element, search_element, Token::EQ_STRICT);
9618 if_issame.Then();
9619 {
9620 Drop(1);
9621 Push(index);
9622 loop.Break();
9623 }
9624 if_issame.End();
9625 }
9626 loop.EndBody();
9627 }
9628 if_isstring.Else();
9629 {
9630 IfBuilder if_isnumber(this);
9631 if_isnumber.If<HIsSmiAndBranch>(search_element);
9632 if_isnumber.OrIf<HCompareMap>(
9633 search_element, isolate()->factory()->heap_number_map());
9634 if_isnumber.Then();
9635 {
9636 HValue* search_number =
9637 AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(search_element,
9638 Representation::Double());
9639 LoopBuilder loop(this, context(), direction);
9640 {
9641 HValue* index = loop.BeginBody(initial, terminating, token);
9642 HValue* element = AddUncasted<HLoadKeyed>(
9643 elements, index, nullptr, nullptr, kind, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
9644
9645 IfBuilder if_element_isnumber(this);
9646 if_element_isnumber.If<HIsSmiAndBranch>(element);
9647 if_element_isnumber.OrIf<HCompareMap>(
9648 element, isolate()->factory()->heap_number_map());
9649 if_element_isnumber.Then();
9650 {
9651 HValue* number =
9652 AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(element,
9653 Representation::Double());
9654 IfBuilder if_issame(this);
9655 if_issame.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
9656 number, search_number, Token::EQ_STRICT);
9657 if_issame.Then();
9658 {
9659 Drop(1);
9660 Push(index);
9661 loop.Break();
9662 }
9663 if_issame.End();
9664 }
9665 if_element_isnumber.End();
9666 }
9667 loop.EndBody();
9668 }
9669 if_isnumber.Else();
9670 {
9671 LoopBuilder loop(this, context(), direction);
9672 {
9673 HValue* index = loop.BeginBody(initial, terminating, token);
9674 HValue* element = AddUncasted<HLoadKeyed>(
9675 elements, index, nullptr, nullptr, kind, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
9676 IfBuilder if_issame(this);
9677 if_issame.If<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(
9678 element, search_element);
9679 if_issame.Then();
9680 {
9681 Drop(1);
9682 Push(index);
9683 loop.Break();
9684 }
9685 if_issame.End();
9686 }
9687 loop.EndBody();
9688 }
9689 if_isnumber.End();
9690 }
9691 if_isstring.End();
9692 }
9693
9694 return Pop();
9695}

9697
9698bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryHandleArrayCall(Call* expr, HValue* function) {
9699 if (!array_function().is_identical_to(expr->target())) {
9700 return false;
9701 }
9702
9703 Handle<AllocationSite> site = expr->allocation_site();
9704 if (site.is_null()) return false;
9705
9706 BuildArrayCall(expr,
9707 expr->arguments()->length(),
9708 function,
9709 site);
9710 return true;
9711}
9712
9713
9714bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::TryHandleArrayCallNew(CallNew* expr,
9715 HValue* function) {
9716 if (!array_function().is_identical_to(expr->target())) {
9717 return false;
9718 }
9719
9720 Handle<AllocationSite> site = expr->allocation_site();
9721 if (site.is_null()) return false;
9722
9723 BuildArrayCall(expr, expr->arguments()->length(), function, site);
9724 return true;
9725}
9726
9727
9728bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::CanBeFunctionApplyArguments(Call* expr) {
9729 ZoneList<Expression*>* args = expr->arguments();
9730 if (args->length() != 2) return false;
9731 VariableProxy* arg_two = args->at(1)->AsVariableProxy();
9732 if (arg_two == NULL__null || !arg_two->var()->IsStackAllocated()) return false;
9733 HValue* arg_two_value = LookupAndMakeLive(arg_two->var());
9734 if (!arg_two_value->CheckFlag(HValue::kIsArguments)) return false;
9735 return true;
9736}
9737
9738
9739void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitCall(Call* expr) {
9740 if (expr->tail_call_mode() == TailCallMode::kAllow) {
9741 return Bailout(kTailCall);
9742 }
9743 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9743, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
9744 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9744, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
9745 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9745, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block()->HasPredecessor()"); } } while (0);
9746 if (!top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) SetSourcePosition(expr->position());
9747 Expression* callee = expr->expression();
9748 int argument_count = expr->arguments()->length() + 1; // Plus receiver.
9749 HInstruction* call = NULL__null;
9750
9751 Property* prop = callee->AsProperty();
9752 if (prop != NULL__null) {
9753 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->obj()));
9754 HValue* receiver = Top();
9755
9756 SmallMapList* maps;
9757 ComputeReceiverTypes(expr, receiver, &maps, this);
9758
9759 if (prop->key()->IsPropertyName() && maps->length() > 0) {
9760 Handle<String> name = prop->key()->AsLiteral()->AsPropertyName();
9761 PropertyAccessInfo info(this, LOAD, maps->first(), name);
9762 if (!info.CanAccessAsMonomorphic(maps)) {
9763 HandlePolymorphicCallNamed(expr, receiver, maps, name);
9764 return;
9765 }
9766 }
9767 HValue* key = NULL__null;
9768 if (!prop->key()->IsPropertyName()) {
9769 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->key()));
9770 key = Pop();
9771 }
9772
9773 CHECK_ALIVE(PushLoad(prop, receiver, key));
9774 HValue* function = Pop();
9775
9776 if (function->IsConstant() &&
9777 HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate())->IsJSFunction()) {
9778 // Push the function under the receiver.
9779 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(0, function);
9780 Push(receiver);
9781
9782 Handle<JSFunction> known_function = Handle<JSFunction>::cast(
9783 HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate()));
9784 expr->set_target(known_function);
9785
9786 if (TryIndirectCall(expr)) return;
9787 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitExpressions(expr->arguments()));
9788
9789 Handle<Map> map = maps->length() == 1 ? maps->first() : Handle<Map>();
9790 if (TryInlineBuiltinMethodCall(expr, known_function, map,
9791 expr->arguments()->length())) {
9792 if (FLAG_trace_inlining) {
9793 PrintF("Inlining builtin ");
9794 known_function->ShortPrint();
9795 PrintF("\n");
9796 }
9797 return;
9798 }
9799 if (TryInlineApiMethodCall(expr, receiver, maps)) return;
9800
9801 // Wrap the receiver if necessary.
9802 if (NeedsWrapping(maps->first(), known_function)) {
9803 // Since HWrapReceiver currently cannot actually wrap numbers and
9804 // strings, use the regular CallFunctionStub for method calls to wrap
9805 // the receiver.
9806 // TODO(verwaest): Support creation of value wrappers directly in
9807 // HWrapReceiver.
9808 call = New<HCallFunction>(function, argument_count,
9809 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined);
9810 } else if (TryInlineCall(expr)) {
9811 return;
9812 } else {
9813 call = BuildCallConstantFunction(known_function, argument_count);
9814 }
9815
9816 } else {
9817 ArgumentsAllowedFlag arguments_flag = ARGUMENTS_NOT_ALLOWED;
9818 if (CanBeFunctionApplyArguments(expr) && expr->is_uninitialized()) {
9819 // We have to use EAGER deoptimization here because Deoptimizer::SOFT
9820 // gets ignored by the always-opt flag, which leads to incorrect code.
9821 Add<HDeoptimize>(
9822 Deoptimizer::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCallWithArguments,
9823 Deoptimizer::EAGER);
9824 arguments_flag = ARGUMENTS_FAKED;
9825 }
9826
9827 // Push the function under the receiver.
9828 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(0, function);
9829 Push(receiver);
9830
9831 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitExpressions(expr->arguments(), arguments_flag));
9832 call = New<HCallFunction>(function, argument_count,
9833 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined);
9834 }
9835 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argument_count);
9836
9837 } else {
9838 VariableProxy* proxy = expr->expression()->AsVariableProxy();
9839 if (proxy != NULL__null && proxy->var()->is_possibly_eval(isolate())) {
9840 return Bailout(kPossibleDirectCallToEval);
9841 }
9842
9843 // The function is on the stack in the unoptimized code during
9844 // evaluation of the arguments.
9845 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->expression()));
9846 HValue* function = Top();
9847 if (function->IsConstant() &&
9848 HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate())->IsJSFunction()) {
9849 Handle<Object> constant = HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate());
9850 Handle<JSFunction> target = Handle<JSFunction>::cast(constant);
9851 expr->SetKnownGlobalTarget(target);
9852 }
9853
9854 // Placeholder for the receiver.
9855 Push(graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
9856 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitExpressions(expr->arguments()));
9857
9858 if (expr->IsMonomorphic() &&
9859 !IsClassConstructor(expr->target()->shared()->kind())) {
9860 Add<HCheckValue>(function, expr->target());
9861
9862 // Patch the global object on the stack by the expected receiver.
9863 HValue* receiver = ImplicitReceiverFor(function, expr->target());
9864 const int receiver_index = argument_count - 1;
9865 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(receiver_index, receiver);
9866
9867 if (TryInlineBuiltinFunctionCall(expr)) {
9868 if (FLAG_trace_inlining) {
9869 PrintF("Inlining builtin ");
9870 expr->target()->ShortPrint();
9871 PrintF("\n");
9872 }
9873 return;
9874 }
9875 if (TryInlineApiFunctionCall(expr, receiver)) return;
9876 if (TryHandleArrayCall(expr, function)) return;
9877 if (TryInlineCall(expr)) return;
9878
9879 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argument_count);
9880 call = BuildCallConstantFunction(expr->target(), argument_count);
9881 } else {
9882 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argument_count);
9883 HCallFunction* call_function = New<HCallFunction>(
9884 function, argument_count, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
9885 call = call_function;
9886 if (expr->is_uninitialized() &&
9887 expr->IsUsingCallFeedbackICSlot(isolate())) {
9888 // We've never seen this call before, so let's have Crankshaft learn
9889 // through the type vector.
9890 Handle<TypeFeedbackVector> vector =
9891 handle(current_feedback_vector(), isolate());
9892 FeedbackVectorSlot slot = expr->CallFeedbackICSlot();
9893 call_function->SetVectorAndSlot(vector, slot);
9894 }
9895 }
9896 }
9897
9898 Drop(1); // Drop the function.
9899 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(call, expr->id());
9900}
9901
9902
9903void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedCallArray(
9904 Expression* expression,
9905 int argument_count,
9906 Handle<AllocationSite> site) {
9907 DCHECK(!site.is_null())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!site.is_null())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9907, "Check failed: %s.", "!site.is_null()"
); } } while (0);
9908 DCHECK(argument_count >= 0 && argument_count <= 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(argument_count >= 0 &&
argument_count <= 1)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 9908, "Check failed: %s.", "argument_count >= 0 && argument_count <= 1"
); } } while (0);
9909 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
9910
9911 // We should at least have the constructor on the expression stack.
9912 HValue* constructor = environment()->ExpressionStackAt(argument_count);
9913
9914 // Register on the site for deoptimization if the transition feedback changes.
9915 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumeTransitionStable(site);
9916 ElementsKind kind = site->GetElementsKind();
9917 HInstruction* site_instruction = Add<HConstant>(site);
9918
9919 // In the single constant argument case, we may have to adjust elements kind
9920 // to avoid creating a packed non-empty array.
9921 if (argument_count == 1 && !IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
9922 HValue* argument = environment()->Top();
9923 if (argument->IsConstant()) {
9924 HConstant* constant_argument = HConstant::cast(argument);
9925 DCHECK(constant_argument->HasSmiValue())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(constant_argument->HasSmiValue
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9925, "Check failed: %s."
, "constant_argument->HasSmiValue()"); } } while (0);
9926 int constant_array_size = constant_argument->Integer32Value();
9927 if (constant_array_size != 0) {
9928 kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(kind);
9929 }
9930 }
9931 }
9932
9933 // Build the array.
9934 JSArrayBuilder array_builder(this,
9935 kind,
9936 site_instruction,
9937 constructor,
9938 DISABLE_ALLOCATION_SITES);
9939 HValue* new_object = argument_count == 0
9940 ? array_builder.AllocateEmptyArray()
9941 : BuildAllocateArrayFromLength(&array_builder, Top());
9942
9943 int args_to_drop = argument_count + (expression->IsCall() ? 2 : 1);
9944 Drop(args_to_drop);
9945 ast_context()->ReturnValue(new_object);
9946}
9947
9948
9949// Checks whether allocation using the given constructor can be inlined.
9950static bool IsAllocationInlineable(Handle<JSFunction> constructor) {
9951 return constructor->has_initial_map() &&
9952 !IsSubclassConstructor(constructor->shared()->kind()) &&
9953 constructor->initial_map()->instance_type() == JS_OBJECT_TYPE &&
9954 constructor->initial_map()->instance_size() <
9955 HAllocate::kMaxInlineSize;
9956}
9957
9958
9959bool HOptimizedGraphBuilder::IsCallArrayInlineable(
9960 int argument_count,
9961 Handle<AllocationSite> site) {
9962 Handle<JSFunction> caller = current_info()->closure();
9963 Handle<JSFunction> target = array_function();
9964 // We should have the function plus array arguments on the environment stack.
9965 DCHECK(environment()->length() >= (argument_count + 1))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(environment()->length() >=
(argument_count + 1))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 9965, "Check failed: %s.", "environment()->length() >= (argument_count + 1)"
); } } while (0);
9966 DCHECK(!site.is_null())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!site.is_null())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 9966, "Check failed: %s.", "!site.is_null()"
); } } while (0);
9967
9968 bool inline_ok = false;
9969 if (site->CanInlineCall()) {
9970 // We also want to avoid inlining in certain 1 argument scenarios.
9971 if (argument_count == 1) {
9972 HValue* argument = Top();
9973 if (argument->IsConstant()) {
9974 // Do not inline if the constant length argument is not a smi or
9975 // outside the valid range for unrolled loop initialization.
9976 HConstant* constant_argument = HConstant::cast(argument);
9977 if (constant_argument->HasSmiValue()) {
9978 int value = constant_argument->Integer32Value();
9979 inline_ok = value >= 0 && value <= kElementLoopUnrollThreshold;
9980 if (!inline_ok) {
9981 TraceInline(target, caller,
9982 "Constant length outside of valid inlining range.");
9983 }
9984 }
9985 } else {
9986 TraceInline(target, caller,
9987 "Dont inline [new] Array(n) where n isn't constant.");
9988 }
9989 } else if (argument_count == 0) {
9990 inline_ok = true;
9991 } else {
9992 TraceInline(target, caller, "Too many arguments to inline.");
9993 }
9994 } else {
9995 TraceInline(target, caller, "AllocationSite requested no inlining.");
9996 }
9997
9998 if (inline_ok) {
9999 TraceInline(target, caller, NULL__null);
10000 }
10001 return inline_ok;
10002}
10003
10004
10005void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitCallNew(CallNew* expr) {
10006 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10006, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
10007 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10007, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
10008 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10008,
"Check failed: %s.", "current_block()->HasPredecessor()")
; } } while (0);
10009 if (!top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) SetSourcePosition(expr->position());
10010 int argument_count = expr->arguments()->length() + 1; // Plus constructor.
10011 Factory* factory = isolate()->factory();
10012
10013 // The constructor function is on the stack in the unoptimized code
10014 // during evaluation of the arguments.
10015 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->expression()));
10016 HValue* function = Top();
10017 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitExpressions(expr->arguments()));
10018
10019 if (function->IsConstant() &&
10020 HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate())->IsJSFunction()) {
10021 Handle<Object> constant = HConstant::cast(function)->handle(isolate());
10022 expr->SetKnownGlobalTarget(Handle<JSFunction>::cast(constant));
10023 }
10024
10025 if (FLAG_inline_construct &&
10026 expr->IsMonomorphic() &&
10027 IsAllocationInlineable(expr->target())) {
10028 Handle<JSFunction> constructor = expr->target();
10029 DCHECK(do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(constructor->shared()->
construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins
::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub
() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi
))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10033, "Check failed: %s."
, "constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi)"
); } } while (0)
10030 constructor->shared()->construct_stub() ==do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(constructor->shared()->
construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins
::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub
() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi
))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10033, "Check failed: %s."
, "constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi)"
); } } while (0)
10031 isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubGeneric) ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(constructor->shared()->
construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins
::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub
() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi
))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10033, "Check failed: %s."
, "constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi)"
); } } while (0)
10032 constructor->shared()->construct_stub() ==do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(constructor->shared()->
construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins
::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub
() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi
))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10033, "Check failed: %s."
, "constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi)"
); } } while (0)
10033 isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(constructor->shared()->
construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins
::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub
() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi
))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10033, "Check failed: %s."
, "constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubGeneric) || constructor->shared()->construct_stub() == isolate()->builtins()->builtin(Builtins::kJSConstructStubApi)"
); } } while (0);
10034 HValue* check = Add<HCheckValue>(function, constructor);
10035
10036 // Force completion of inobject slack tracking before generating
10037 // allocation code to finalize instance size.
10038 constructor->CompleteInobjectSlackTrackingIfActive();
10039
10040 // Calculate instance size from initial map of constructor.
10041 DCHECK(constructor->has_initial_map())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(constructor->has_initial_map
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10041,
"Check failed: %s.", "constructor->has_initial_map()"); }
} while (0);
10042 Handle<Map> initial_map(constructor->initial_map());
10043 int instance_size = initial_map->instance_size();
10044
10045 // Allocate an instance of the implicit receiver object.
10046 HValue* size_in_bytes = Add<HConstant>(instance_size);
10047 HAllocationMode allocation_mode;
10048 HAllocate* receiver = BuildAllocate(
10049 size_in_bytes, HType::JSObject(), JS_OBJECT_TYPE, allocation_mode);
10050 receiver->set_known_initial_map(initial_map);
10051
10052 // Initialize map and fields of the newly allocated object.
10053 { NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
10054 DCHECK(initial_map->instance_type() == JS_OBJECT_TYPE)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(initial_map->instance_type
() == JS_OBJECT_TYPE)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 10054, "Check failed: %s.", "initial_map->instance_type() == JS_OBJECT_TYPE"
); } } while (0);
10055 Add<HStoreNamedField>(receiver,
10056 HObjectAccess::ForMapAndOffset(initial_map, JSObject::kMapOffset),
10057 Add<HConstant>(initial_map));
10058 HValue* empty_fixed_array = Add<HConstant>(factory->empty_fixed_array());
10059 Add<HStoreNamedField>(receiver,
10060 HObjectAccess::ForMapAndOffset(initial_map,
10061 JSObject::kPropertiesOffset),
10062 empty_fixed_array);
10063 Add<HStoreNamedField>(receiver,
10064 HObjectAccess::ForMapAndOffset(initial_map,
10065 JSObject::kElementsOffset),
10066 empty_fixed_array);
10067 BuildInitializeInobjectProperties(receiver, initial_map);
10068 }
10069
10070 // Replace the constructor function with a newly allocated receiver using
10071 // the index of the receiver from the top of the expression stack.
10072 const int receiver_index = argument_count - 1;
10073 DCHECK(environment()->ExpressionStackAt(receiver_index) == function)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(environment()->ExpressionStackAt
(receiver_index) == function)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 10073, "Check failed: %s.", "environment()->ExpressionStackAt(receiver_index) == function"
); } } while (0);
10074 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(receiver_index, receiver);
10075
10076 if (TryInlineConstruct(expr, receiver)) {
10077 // Inlining worked, add a dependency on the initial map to make sure that
10078 // this code is deoptimized whenever the initial map of the constructor
10079 // changes.
10080 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumeInitialMapCantChange(initial_map);
10081 return;
10082 }
10083
10084 // TODO(mstarzinger): For now we remove the previous HAllocate and all
10085 // corresponding instructions and instead add HPushArguments for the
10086 // arguments in case inlining failed. What we actually should do is for
10087 // inlining to try to build a subgraph without mutating the parent graph.
10088 HInstruction* instr = current_block()->last();
10089 do {
10090 HInstruction* prev_instr = instr->previous();
10091 instr->DeleteAndReplaceWith(NULL__null);
10092 instr = prev_instr;
10093 } while (instr != check);
10094 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(receiver_index, function);
10095 } else {
10096 // The constructor function is both an operand to the instruction and an
10097 // argument to the construct call.
10098 if (TryHandleArrayCallNew(expr, function)) return;
10099 }
10100
10101 HValue* arity = Add<HConstant>(argument_count - 1);
10102 HValue* op_vals[] = {context(), function, function, arity};
10103 Callable callable = CodeFactory::Construct(isolate());
10104 HConstant* stub = Add<HConstant>(callable.code());
10105 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argument_count);
10106 HInstruction* construct =
10107 New<HCallWithDescriptor>(stub, argument_count, callable.descriptor(),
10108 Vector<HValue*>(op_vals, arraysize(op_vals)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(op_vals)))));
10109 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(construct, expr->id());
10110}
10111
10112
10113void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildInitializeInobjectProperties(
10114 HValue* receiver, Handle<Map> initial_map) {
10115 if (initial_map->GetInObjectProperties() != 0) {
10116 HConstant* undefined = graph()->GetConstantUndefined();
10117 for (int i = 0; i < initial_map->GetInObjectProperties(); i++) {
10118 int property_offset = initial_map->GetInObjectPropertyOffset(i);
10119 Add<HStoreNamedField>(receiver, HObjectAccess::ForMapAndOffset(
10120 initial_map, property_offset),
10121 undefined);
10122 }
10123 }
10124}
10125
10126
10127HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildAllocateEmptyArrayBuffer(HValue* byte_length) {
10128 // We HForceRepresentation here to avoid allocations during an *-to-tagged
10129 // HChange that could cause GC while the array buffer object is not fully
10130 // initialized.
10131 HObjectAccess byte_length_access(HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferByteLength());
10132 byte_length = AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(
10133 byte_length, byte_length_access.representation());
10134 HAllocate* result =
10135 BuildAllocate(Add<HConstant>(JSArrayBuffer::kSizeWithInternalFields),
10136 HType::JSObject(), JS_ARRAY_BUFFER_TYPE, HAllocationMode());
10137
10138 HValue* native_context = BuildGetNativeContext();
10139 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10140 result, HObjectAccess::ForMap(),
10141 Add<HLoadNamedField>(
10142 native_context, nullptr,
10143 HObjectAccess::ForContextSlot(Context::ARRAY_BUFFER_MAP_INDEX)));
10144
10145 HConstant* empty_fixed_array =
10146 Add<HConstant>(isolate()->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
10147 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10148 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayOffset(JSArray::kPropertiesOffset),
10149 empty_fixed_array);
10150 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10151 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayOffset(JSArray::kElementsOffset),
10152 empty_fixed_array);
10153 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10154 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferBackingStore().WithRepresentation(
10155 Representation::Smi()),
10156 graph()->GetConstant0());
10157 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, byte_length_access, byte_length);
10158 Add<HStoreNamedField>(result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferBitFieldSlot(),
10159 graph()->GetConstant0());
10160 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10161 result, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferBitField(),
10162 Add<HConstant>((1 << JSArrayBuffer::IsExternal::kShift) |
10163 (1 << JSArrayBuffer::IsNeuterable::kShift)));
10164
10165 for (int field = 0; field < v8::ArrayBuffer::kInternalFieldCount; ++field) {
10166 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10167 result,
10168 HObjectAccess::ForObservableJSObjectOffset(
10169 JSArrayBuffer::kSize + field * kPointerSize, Representation::Smi()),
10170 graph()->GetConstant0());
10171 }
10172
10173 return result;
10174}
10175
10176
10177template <class ViewClass>
10178void HGraphBuilder::BuildArrayBufferViewInitialization(
10179 HValue* obj,
10180 HValue* buffer,
10181 HValue* byte_offset,
10182 HValue* byte_length) {
10183
10184 for (int offset = ViewClass::kSize;
10185 offset < ViewClass::kSizeWithInternalFields;
10186 offset += kPointerSize) {
10187 Add<HStoreNamedField>(obj,
10188 HObjectAccess::ForObservableJSObjectOffset(offset),
10189 graph()->GetConstant0());
10190 }
10191
10192 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10193 obj,
10194 HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(),
10195 byte_offset);
10196 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10197 obj,
10198 HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength(),
10199 byte_length);
10200 Add<HStoreNamedField>(obj, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(),
10201 buffer);
10202}
10203
10204
10205HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildAllocateExternalElements(
10206 ExternalArrayType array_type,
10207 bool is_zero_byte_offset,
10208 HValue* buffer, HValue* byte_offset, HValue* length) {
10209 Handle<Map> external_array_map(
10210 isolate()->heap()->MapForFixedTypedArray(array_type));
10211
10212 // The HForceRepresentation is to prevent possible deopt on int-smi
10213 // conversion after allocation but before the new object fields are set.
10214 length = AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(length, Representation::Smi());
10215 HValue* elements = Add<HAllocate>(
10216 Add<HConstant>(FixedTypedArrayBase::kHeaderSize), HType::HeapObject(),
10217 NOT_TENURED, external_array_map->instance_type());
10218
10219 AddStoreMapConstant(elements, external_array_map);
10220 Add<HStoreNamedField>(elements,
10221 HObjectAccess::ForFixedArrayLength(), length);
10222
10223 HValue* backing_store = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
10224 buffer, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayBufferBackingStore());
10225
10226 HValue* typed_array_start;
10227 if (is_zero_byte_offset) {
10228 typed_array_start = backing_store;
10229 } else {
10230 HInstruction* external_pointer =
10231 AddUncasted<HAdd>(backing_store, byte_offset);
10232 // Arguments are checked prior to call to TypedArrayInitialize,
10233 // including byte_offset.
10234 external_pointer->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
10235 typed_array_start = external_pointer;
10236 }
10237
10238 Add<HStoreNamedField>(elements,
10239 HObjectAccess::ForFixedTypedArrayBaseBasePointer(),
10240 graph()->GetConstant0());
10241 Add<HStoreNamedField>(elements,
10242 HObjectAccess::ForFixedTypedArrayBaseExternalPointer(),
10243 typed_array_start);
10244
10245 return elements;
10246}
10247
10248
10249HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildAllocateFixedTypedArray(
10250 ExternalArrayType array_type, size_t element_size,
10251 ElementsKind fixed_elements_kind, HValue* byte_length, HValue* length,
10252 bool initialize) {
10253 STATIC_ASSERT(static_assert((FixedTypedArrayBase::kHeaderSize & kObjectAlignmentMask
) == 0, "(FixedTypedArrayBase::kHeaderSize & kObjectAlignmentMask) == 0"
)
10254 (FixedTypedArrayBase::kHeaderSize & kObjectAlignmentMask) == 0)static_assert((FixedTypedArrayBase::kHeaderSize & kObjectAlignmentMask
) == 0, "(FixedTypedArrayBase::kHeaderSize & kObjectAlignmentMask) == 0"
);
10255 HValue* total_size;
10256
10257 // if fixed array's elements are not aligned to object's alignment,
10258 // we need to align the whole array to object alignment.
10259 if (element_size % kObjectAlignment != 0) {
10260 total_size = BuildObjectSizeAlignment(
10261 byte_length, FixedTypedArrayBase::kHeaderSize);
10262 } else {
10263 total_size = AddUncasted<HAdd>(byte_length,
10264 Add<HConstant>(FixedTypedArrayBase::kHeaderSize));
10265 total_size->ClearFlag(HValue::kCanOverflow);
10266 }
10267
10268 // The HForceRepresentation is to prevent possible deopt on int-smi
10269 // conversion after allocation but before the new object fields are set.
10270 length = AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(length, Representation::Smi());
10271 Handle<Map> fixed_typed_array_map(
10272 isolate()->heap()->MapForFixedTypedArray(array_type));
10273 HAllocate* elements =
10274 Add<HAllocate>(total_size, HType::HeapObject(), NOT_TENURED,
10275 fixed_typed_array_map->instance_type());
10276
10277#ifndef V8_HOST_ARCH_64_BIT1
10278 if (array_type == kExternalFloat64Array) {
10279 elements->MakeDoubleAligned();
10280 }
10281#endif
10282
10283 AddStoreMapConstant(elements, fixed_typed_array_map);
10284
10285 Add<HStoreNamedField>(elements,
10286 HObjectAccess::ForFixedArrayLength(),
10287 length);
10288 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10289 elements, HObjectAccess::ForFixedTypedArrayBaseBasePointer(), elements);
10290
10291 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10292 elements, HObjectAccess::ForFixedTypedArrayBaseExternalPointer(),
10293 Add<HConstant>(ExternalReference::fixed_typed_array_base_data_offset()));
10294
10295 HValue* filler = Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(0));
10296
10297 if (initialize) {
10298 LoopBuilder builder(this, context(), LoopBuilder::kPostIncrement);
10299
10300 HValue* backing_store = AddUncasted<HAdd>(
10301 Add<HConstant>(ExternalReference::fixed_typed_array_base_data_offset()),
10302 elements, AddOfExternalAndTagged);
10303
10304 HValue* key = builder.BeginBody(
10305 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(0)),
10306 length, Token::LT);
10307 Add<HStoreKeyed>(backing_store, key, filler, elements, fixed_elements_kind);
10308
10309 builder.EndBody();
10310 }
10311 return elements;
10312}
10313
10314
10315void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::GenerateTypedArrayInitialize(
10316 CallRuntime* expr) {
10317 ZoneList<Expression*>* arguments = expr->arguments();
10318
10319 static const int kObjectArg = 0;
10320 static const int kArrayIdArg = 1;
10321 static const int kBufferArg = 2;
10322 static const int kByteOffsetArg = 3;
10323 static const int kByteLengthArg = 4;
10324 static const int kInitializeArg = 5;
10325 static const int kArgsLength = 6;
10326 DCHECK(arguments->length() == kArgsLength)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(arguments->length() == kArgsLength
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10326, "Check failed: %s."
, "arguments->length() == kArgsLength"); } } while (0);
10327
10328
10329 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(arguments->at(kObjectArg)));
10330 HValue* obj = Pop();
10331
10332 if (!arguments->at(kArrayIdArg)->IsLiteral()) {
10333 // This should never happen in real use, but can happen when fuzzing.
10334 // Just bail out.
10335 Bailout(kNeedSmiLiteral);
10336 return;
10337 }
10338 Handle<Object> value =
10339 static_cast<Literal*>(arguments->at(kArrayIdArg))->value();
10340 if (!value->IsSmi()) {
10341 // This should never happen in real use, but can happen when fuzzing.
10342 // Just bail out.
10343 Bailout(kNeedSmiLiteral);
10344 return;
10345 }
10346 int array_id = Smi::cast(*value)->value();
10347
10348 HValue* buffer;
10349 if (!arguments->at(kBufferArg)->IsNullLiteral()) {
10350 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(arguments->at(kBufferArg)));
10351 buffer = Pop();
10352 } else {
10353 buffer = NULL__null;
10354 }
10355
10356 HValue* byte_offset;
10357 bool is_zero_byte_offset;
10358
10359 if (arguments->at(kByteOffsetArg)->IsLiteral()
10360 && Smi::FromInt(0) ==
10361 *static_cast<Literal*>(arguments->at(kByteOffsetArg))->value()) {
10362 byte_offset = Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(0));
10363 is_zero_byte_offset = true;
10364 } else {
10365 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(arguments->at(kByteOffsetArg)));
10366 byte_offset = Pop();
10367 is_zero_byte_offset = false;
10368 DCHECK(buffer != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(buffer != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10368, "Check failed: %s.",
"buffer != __null"); } } while (0);
10369 }
10370
10371 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(arguments->at(kByteLengthArg)));
10372 HValue* byte_length = Pop();
10373
10374 CHECK(arguments->at(kInitializeArg)->IsLiteral())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(arguments->at(kInitializeArg
)->IsLiteral())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 10374, "Check failed: %s.", "arguments->at(kInitializeArg)->IsLiteral()"
); } } while (0);
10375 bool initialize = static_cast<Literal*>(arguments->at(kInitializeArg))
10376 ->value()
10377 ->BooleanValue();
10378
10379 NoObservableSideEffectsScope scope(this);
10380 IfBuilder byte_offset_smi(this);
10381
10382 if (!is_zero_byte_offset) {
10383 byte_offset_smi.If<HIsSmiAndBranch>(byte_offset);
10384 byte_offset_smi.Then();
10385 }
10386
10387 ExternalArrayType array_type =
10388 kExternalInt8Array; // Bogus initialization.
10389 size_t element_size = 1; // Bogus initialization.
10390 ElementsKind fixed_elements_kind = // Bogus initialization.
10391 INT8_ELEMENTS;
10392 Runtime::ArrayIdToTypeAndSize(array_id,
10393 &array_type,
10394 &fixed_elements_kind,
10395 &element_size);
10396
10397
10398 { // byte_offset is Smi.
10399 HValue* allocated_buffer = buffer;
10400 if (buffer == NULL__null) {
10401 allocated_buffer = BuildAllocateEmptyArrayBuffer(byte_length);
10402 }
10403 BuildArrayBufferViewInitialization<JSTypedArray>(obj, allocated_buffer,
10404 byte_offset, byte_length);
10405
10406
10407 HInstruction* length = AddUncasted<HDiv>(byte_length,
10408 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int32_t>(element_size)));
10409
10410 Add<HStoreNamedField>(obj,
10411 HObjectAccess::ForJSTypedArrayLength(),
10412 length);
10413
10414 HValue* elements;
10415 if (buffer != NULL__null) {
10416 elements = BuildAllocateExternalElements(
10417 array_type, is_zero_byte_offset, buffer, byte_offset, length);
10418 } else {
10419 DCHECK(is_zero_byte_offset)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(is_zero_byte_offset)), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10419, "Check failed: %s."
, "is_zero_byte_offset"); } } while (0);
10420 elements = BuildAllocateFixedTypedArray(array_type, element_size,
10421 fixed_elements_kind, byte_length,
10422 length, initialize);
10423 }
10424 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
10425 obj, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(), elements);
10426 }
10427
10428 if (!is_zero_byte_offset) {
10429 byte_offset_smi.Else();
10430 { // byte_offset is not Smi.
10431 Push(obj);
10432 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(arguments->at(kArrayIdArg)));
10433 Push(buffer);
10434 Push(byte_offset);
10435 Push(byte_length);
10436 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(arguments->at(kInitializeArg)));
10437 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(kArgsLength);
10438 Add<HCallRuntime>(expr->function(), kArgsLength);
10439 }
10440 }
10441 byte_offset_smi.End();
10442}

10510
10511void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitCallRuntime(CallRuntime* expr) {
10512 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10512, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
10513 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10513, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
10514 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10514,
"Check failed: %s.", "current_block()->HasPredecessor()")
; } } while (0);
10515 if (expr->is_jsruntime()) {
10516 return Bailout(kCallToAJavaScriptRuntimeFunction);
10517 }
10518
10519 const Runtime::Function* function = expr->function();
10520 DCHECK(function != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(function != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10520, "Check failed: %s.",
"function != __null"); } } while (0);
10521 switch (function->function_id) {
10522#define CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(Name) \
10523 case Runtime::kInline##Name: \
10524 return Generate##Name(expr);
10525
10526 FOR_EACH_HYDROGEN_INTRINSIC(CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR)CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(IsSmi) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(IsArray
) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(IsTypedArray) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(IsRegExp) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(IsJSProxy) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(Call) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(ValueOf) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(StringCharFromCode) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(StringCharAt) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(OneByteSeqStringSetChar) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(TwoByteSeqStringSetChar
) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(ToInteger) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(ToName) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(ToObject) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(ToString) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(ToLength) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(ToNumber) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(IsJSReceiver) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(MathPow) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(HasCachedArrayIndex) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(GetCachedArrayIndex) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(DebugBreakInOptimizedCode
) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(StringCharCodeAt) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(SubString) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(RegExpExec) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(RegExpConstructResult) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(RegExpFlags)
CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(RegExpSource) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(NumberToString) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(DebugIsActive) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(TypedArrayInitialize) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(MaxSmi) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(TypedArrayMaxSizeInHeap) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(ArrayBufferViewGetByteLength
) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(ArrayBufferViewGetByteOffset) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(TypedArrayGetLength) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(ArrayBufferGetByteLength
) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(ConstructDouble) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(DoubleHi) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(DoubleLo) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(MathClz32) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(MathFloor) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(MathSqrt) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(MathLogRT) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(MapClear) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(MapInitialize) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(SetClear) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(SetInitialize) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(FixedArrayGet) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(FixedArraySet) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
(JSCollectionGetTable) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(StringGetRawHashField
) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(TheHole) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(
CreateIterResultObject) CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR(HasFastPackedElements
)
10527#undef CALL_INTRINSIC_GENERATOR
10528 default: {
10529 int argument_count = expr->arguments()->length();
10530 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitExpressions(expr->arguments()));
10531 PushArgumentsFromEnvironment(argument_count);
10532 HCallRuntime* call = New<HCallRuntime>(function, argument_count);
10533 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(call, expr->id());
10534 }
10535 }
10536}

10538
10539void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitUnaryOperation(UnaryOperation* expr) {
10540 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10540, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
10541 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10541, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
10542 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10542,
"Check failed: %s.", "current_block()->HasPredecessor()")
; } } while (0);
10543 switch (expr->op()) {
10544 case Token::DELETE: return VisitDelete(expr);
10545 case Token::VOID: return VisitVoid(expr);
10546 case Token::TYPEOF: return VisitTypeof(expr);
10547 case Token::NOT: return VisitNot(expr);
10548 default: UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10548, "unreachable code"
);
10549 }
10550}
10551
10552
10553void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitDelete(UnaryOperation* expr) {
10554 Property* prop = expr->expression()->AsProperty();
10555 VariableProxy* proxy = expr->expression()->AsVariableProxy();
10556 if (prop != NULL__null) {
10557 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->obj()));
10558 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->key()));
10559 HValue* key = Pop();
10560 HValue* obj = Pop();
10561 Add<HPushArguments>(obj, key);
10562 HInstruction* instr = New<HCallRuntime>(
10563 Runtime::FunctionForId(is_strict(function_language_mode())
10564 ? Runtime::kDeleteProperty_Strict
10565 : Runtime::kDeleteProperty_Sloppy),
10566 2);
10567 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());
10568 } else if (proxy != NULL__null) {
10569 Variable* var = proxy->var();
10570 if (var->IsUnallocatedOrGlobalSlot()) {
10571 Bailout(kDeleteWithGlobalVariable);
10572 } else if (var->IsStackAllocated() || var->IsContextSlot()) {
10573 // Result of deleting non-global variables is false. 'this' is not really
10574 // a variable, though we implement it as one. The subexpression does not
10575 // have side effects.
10576 HValue* value = var->HasThisName(isolate()) ? graph()->GetConstantTrue()
10577 : graph()->GetConstantFalse();
10578 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(value);
10579 } else {
10580 Bailout(kDeleteWithNonGlobalVariable);
10581 }
10582 } else {
10583 // Result of deleting non-property, non-variable reference is true.
10584 // Evaluate the subexpression for side effects.
10585 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForEffect(expr->expression()));
10586 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(graph()->GetConstantTrue());
10587 }
10588}
10589
10590
10591void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitVoid(UnaryOperation* expr) {
10592 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForEffect(expr->expression()));
10593 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
10594}
