10596
10597void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitTypeof(UnaryOperation* expr) {
10598 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForTypeOf(expr->expression()));
10599 HValue* value = Pop();
10600 HInstruction* instr = New<HTypeof>(value);
10601 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());
10602}
10603
10604
10605void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitNot(UnaryOperation* expr) {
10606 if (ast_context()->IsTest()) {
10607 TestContext* context = TestContext::cast(ast_context());
10608 VisitForControl(expr->expression(),
10609 context->if_false(),
10610 context->if_true());
10611 return;
10612 }
10613
10614 if (ast_context()->IsEffect()) {
10615 VisitForEffect(expr->expression());
10616 return;
10617 }
10618
10619 DCHECK(ast_context()->IsValue())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ast_context()->IsValue()))
, 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10619, "Check failed: %s."
, "ast_context()->IsValue()"); } } while (0);
10620 HBasicBlock* materialize_false = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
10621 HBasicBlock* materialize_true = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
10622 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(expr->expression(),
10623 materialize_false,
10624 materialize_true));
10625
10626 if (materialize_false->HasPredecessor()) {
10627 materialize_false->SetJoinId(expr->MaterializeFalseId());
10628 set_current_block(materialize_false);
10629 Push(graph()->GetConstantFalse());
10630 } else {
10631 materialize_false = NULL__null;
10632 }
10633
10634 if (materialize_true->HasPredecessor()) {
10635 materialize_true->SetJoinId(expr->MaterializeTrueId());
10636 set_current_block(materialize_true);
10637 Push(graph()->GetConstantTrue());
10638 } else {
10639 materialize_true = NULL__null;
10640 }
10641
10642 HBasicBlock* join =
10643 CreateJoin(materialize_false, materialize_true, expr->id());
10644 set_current_block(join);
10645 if (join != NULL__null) return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
10646}
10647
10648
10649static Representation RepresentationFor(Type* type) {
10650 DisallowHeapAllocation no_allocation;
10651 if (type->Is(Type::None())) return Representation::None();
10652 if (type->Is(Type::SignedSmall())) return Representation::Smi();
10653 if (type->Is(Type::Signed32())) return Representation::Integer32();
10654 if (type->Is(Type::Number())) return Representation::Double();
10655 return Representation::Tagged();
10656}
10657
10658
10659HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildIncrement(
10660 bool returns_original_input,
10661 CountOperation* expr) {
10662 // The input to the count operation is on top of the expression stack.
10663 Representation rep = RepresentationFor(expr->type());
10664 if (rep.IsNone() || rep.IsTagged()) {
10665 rep = Representation::Smi();
10666 }
10667
10668 if (returns_original_input && !is_strong(function_language_mode())) {
10669 // We need an explicit HValue representing ToNumber(input). The
10670 // actual HChange instruction we need is (sometimes) added in a later
10671 // phase, so it is not available now to be used as an input to HAdd and
10672 // as the return value.
10673 HInstruction* number_input = AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(Pop(), rep);
10674 if (!rep.IsDouble()) {
10675 number_input->SetFlag(HInstruction::kFlexibleRepresentation);
10676 number_input->SetFlag(HInstruction::kCannotBeTagged);
10677 }
10678 Push(number_input);
10679 }
10680
10681 // The addition has no side effects, so we do not need
10682 // to simulate the expression stack after this instruction.
10683 // Any later failures deopt to the load of the input or earlier.
10684 HConstant* delta = (expr->op() == Token::INC)
10685 ? graph()->GetConstant1()
10686 : graph()->GetConstantMinus1();
10687 HInstruction* instr = AddUncasted<HAdd>(Top(), delta);
10688 if (instr->IsAdd()) {
10689 HAdd* add = HAdd::cast(instr);
10690 add->set_observed_input_representation(1, rep);
10691 add->set_observed_input_representation(2, Representation::Smi());
10692 }
10693 if (!is_strong(function_language_mode())) {
10694 instr->ClearAllSideEffects();
10695 } else {
10696 Add<HSimulate>(expr->ToNumberId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
10697 }
10698 instr->SetFlag(HInstruction::kCannotBeTagged);
10699 return instr;
10700}
10701
10702
10703void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildStoreForEffect(
10704 Expression* expr, Property* prop, FeedbackVectorSlot slot, BailoutId ast_id,
10705 BailoutId return_id, HValue* object, HValue* key, HValue* value) {
10706 EffectContext for_effect(this);
10707 Push(object);
10708 if (key != NULL__null) Push(key);
1
Taking false branch
→
10709 Push(value);
10710 BuildStore(expr, prop, slot, ast_id, return_id);
2
←
Calling 'HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildStore'
→
10711}
10712
10713
10714void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitCountOperation(CountOperation* expr) {
10715 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10715, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
10716 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10716, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
10717 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10717,
"Check failed: %s.", "current_block()->HasPredecessor()")
; } } while (0);
10718 if (!top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) SetSourcePosition(expr->position());
10719 Expression* target = expr->expression();
10720 VariableProxy* proxy = target->AsVariableProxy();
10721 Property* prop = target->AsProperty();
10722 if (proxy == NULL__null && prop == NULL__null) {
10723 return Bailout(kInvalidLhsInCountOperation);
10724 }
10725
10726 // Match the full code generator stack by simulating an extra stack
10727 // element for postfix operations in a non-effect context. The return
10728 // value is ToNumber(input).
10729 bool returns_original_input =
10730 expr->is_postfix() && !ast_context()->IsEffect();
10731 HValue* input = NULL__null; // ToNumber(original_input).
10732 HValue* after = NULL__null; // The result after incrementing or decrementing.
10733
10734 if (proxy != NULL__null) {
10735 Variable* var = proxy->var();
10736 if (var->mode() == CONST_LEGACY) {
10737 return Bailout(kUnsupportedCountOperationWithConst);
10738 }
10739 if (var->mode() == CONST) {
10740 return Bailout(kNonInitializerAssignmentToConst);
10741 }
10742 // Argument of the count operation is a variable, not a property.
10743 DCHECK(prop == NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(prop == __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10743, "Check failed: %s.",
"prop == __null"); } } while (0);
10744 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(target));
10745
10746 after = BuildIncrement(returns_original_input, expr);
10747 input = returns_original_input ? Top() : Pop();
10748 Push(after);
10749
10750 switch (var->location()) {
10751 case VariableLocation::GLOBAL:
10752 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
10753 HandleGlobalVariableAssignment(var, after, expr->CountSlot(),
10754 expr->AssignmentId());
10755 break;
10756
10757 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
10758 case VariableLocation::LOCAL:
10759 BindIfLive(var, after);
10760 break;
10761
10762 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
10763 // Bail out if we try to mutate a parameter value in a function
10764 // using the arguments object. We do not (yet) correctly handle the
10765 // arguments property of the function.
10766 if (current_info()->scope()->arguments() != NULL__null) {
10767 // Parameters will rewrite to context slots. We have no direct
10768 // way to detect that the variable is a parameter so we use a
10769 // linear search of the parameter list.
10770 int count = current_info()->scope()->num_parameters();
10771 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
10772 if (var == current_info()->scope()->parameter(i)) {
10773 return Bailout(kAssignmentToParameterInArgumentsObject);
10774 }
10775 }
10776 }
10777
10778 HValue* context = BuildContextChainWalk(var);
10779 HStoreContextSlot::Mode mode = IsLexicalVariableMode(var->mode())
10780 ? HStoreContextSlot::kCheckDeoptimize : HStoreContextSlot::kNoCheck;
10781 HStoreContextSlot* instr = Add<HStoreContextSlot>(context, var->index(),
10782 mode, after);
10783 if (instr->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
10784 Add<HSimulate>(expr->AssignmentId(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
10785 }
10786 break;
10787 }
10788
10789 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP:
10790 return Bailout(kLookupVariableInCountOperation);
10791 }
10792
10793 Drop(returns_original_input ? 2 : 1);
10794 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(expr->is_postfix() ? input : after);
10795 }
10796
10797 // Argument of the count operation is a property.
10798 DCHECK(prop != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(prop != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10798, "Check failed: %s.",
"prop != __null"); } } while (0);
10799 if (returns_original_input) Push(graph()->GetConstantUndefined());
10800
10801 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->obj()));
10802 HValue* object = Top();
10803
10804 HValue* key = NULL__null;
10805 if (!prop->key()->IsPropertyName() || prop->IsStringAccess()) {
10806 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(prop->key()));
10807 key = Top();
10808 }
10809
10810 CHECK_ALIVE(PushLoad(prop, object, key));
10811
10812 after = BuildIncrement(returns_original_input, expr);
10813
10814 if (returns_original_input) {
10815 input = Pop();
10816 // Drop object and key to push it again in the effect context below.
10817 Drop(key == NULL__null ? 1 : 2);
10818 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(0, input);
10819 CHECK_ALIVE(BuildStoreForEffect(expr, prop, expr->CountSlot(), expr->id(),
10820 expr->AssignmentId(), object, key, after));
10821 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
10822 }
10823
10824 environment()->SetExpressionStackAt(0, after);
10825 return BuildStore(expr, prop, expr->CountSlot(), expr->id(),
10826 expr->AssignmentId());
10827}
10828
10829
10830HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildStringCharCodeAt(
10831 HValue* string,
10832 HValue* index) {
10833 if (string->IsConstant() && index->IsConstant()) {
10834 HConstant* c_string = HConstant::cast(string);
10835 HConstant* c_index = HConstant::cast(index);
10836 if (c_string->HasStringValue() && c_index->HasNumberValue()) {
10837 int32_t i = c_index->NumberValueAsInteger32();
10838 Handle<String> s = c_string->StringValue();
10839 if (i < 0 || i >= s->length()) {
10840 return New<HConstant>(std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN());
10841 }
10842 return New<HConstant>(s->Get(i));
10843 }
10844 }
10845 string = BuildCheckString(string);
10846 index = Add<HBoundsCheck>(index, AddLoadStringLength(string));
10847 return New<HStringCharCodeAt>(string, index);
10848}
10849
10850
10851// Checks if the given shift amounts have following forms:
10852// (N1) and (N2) with N1 + N2 = 32; (sa) and (32 - sa).
10853static bool ShiftAmountsAllowReplaceByRotate(HValue* sa,
10854 HValue* const32_minus_sa) {
10855 if (sa->IsConstant() && const32_minus_sa->IsConstant()) {
10856 const HConstant* c1 = HConstant::cast(sa);
10857 const HConstant* c2 = HConstant::cast(const32_minus_sa);
10858 return c1->HasInteger32Value() && c2->HasInteger32Value() &&
10859 (c1->Integer32Value() + c2->Integer32Value() == 32);
10860 }
10861 if (!const32_minus_sa->IsSub()) return false;
10862 HSub* sub = HSub::cast(const32_minus_sa);
10863 return sub->left()->EqualsInteger32Constant(32) && sub->right() == sa;
10864}
10865
10866
10867// Checks if the left and the right are shift instructions with the oposite
10868// directions that can be replaced by one rotate right instruction or not.
10869// Returns the operand and the shift amount for the rotate instruction in the
10870// former case.
10871bool HGraphBuilder::MatchRotateRight(HValue* left,
10872 HValue* right,
10873 HValue** operand,
10874 HValue** shift_amount) {
10875 HShl* shl;
10876 HShr* shr;
10877 if (left->IsShl() && right->IsShr()) {
10878 shl = HShl::cast(left);
10879 shr = HShr::cast(right);
10880 } else if (left->IsShr() && right->IsShl()) {
10881 shl = HShl::cast(right);
10882 shr = HShr::cast(left);
10883 } else {
10884 return false;
10885 }
10886 if (shl->left() != shr->left()) return false;
10887
10888 if (!ShiftAmountsAllowReplaceByRotate(shl->right(), shr->right()) &&
10889 !ShiftAmountsAllowReplaceByRotate(shr->right(), shl->right())) {
10890 return false;
10891 }
10892 *operand = shr->left();
10893 *shift_amount = shr->right();
10894 return true;
10895}
10896
10897
10898bool CanBeZero(HValue* right) {
10899 if (right->IsConstant()) {
10900 HConstant* right_const = HConstant::cast(right);
10901 if (right_const->HasInteger32Value() &&
10902 (right_const->Integer32Value() & 0x1f) != 0) {
10903 return false;
10904 }
10905 }
10906 return true;
10907}
10908
10909
10910HValue* HGraphBuilder::EnforceNumberType(HValue* number,
10911 Type* expected) {
10912 if (expected->Is(Type::SignedSmall())) {
10913 return AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(number, Representation::Smi());
10914 }
10915 if (expected->Is(Type::Signed32())) {
10916 return AddUncasted<HForceRepresentation>(number,
10917 Representation::Integer32());
10918 }
10919 return number;
10920}
10921
10922
10923HValue* HGraphBuilder::TruncateToNumber(HValue* value, Type** expected) {
10924 if (value->IsConstant()) {
10925 HConstant* constant = HConstant::cast(value);
10926 Maybe<HConstant*> number =
10927 constant->CopyToTruncatedNumber(isolate(), zone());
10928 if (number.IsJust()) {
10929 *expected = Type::Number();
10930 return AddInstruction(number.FromJust());
10931 }
10932 }
10933
10934 // We put temporary values on the stack, which don't correspond to anything
10935 // in baseline code. Since nothing is observable we avoid recording those
10936 // pushes with a NoObservableSideEffectsScope.
10937 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
10938
10939 Type* expected_type = *expected;
10940
10941 // Separate the number type from the rest.
10942 Type* expected_obj =
10943 Type::Intersect(expected_type, Type::NonNumber(), zone());
10944 Type* expected_number =
10945 Type::Intersect(expected_type, Type::Number(), zone());
10946
10947 // We expect to get a number.
10948 // (We need to check first, since Type::None->Is(Type::Any()) == true.
10949 if (expected_obj->Is(Type::None())) {
10950 DCHECK(!expected_number->Is(Type::None()))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!expected_number->Is(Type::
None()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 10950
, "Check failed: %s.", "!expected_number->Is(Type::None())"
); } } while (0);
10951 return value;
10952 }
10953
10954 if (expected_obj->Is(Type::Undefined())) {
10955 // This is already done by HChange.
10956 *expected = Type::Union(expected_number, Type::Number(), zone());
10957 return value;
10958 }
10959
10960 return value;
10961}
10962
10963
10964HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildBinaryOperation(
10965 BinaryOperation* expr,
10966 HValue* left,
10967 HValue* right,
10968 PushBeforeSimulateBehavior push_sim_result) {
10969 Type* left_type = expr->left()->bounds().lower;
10970 Type* right_type = expr->right()->bounds().lower;
10971 Type* result_type = expr->bounds().lower;
10972 Maybe<int> fixed_right_arg = expr->fixed_right_arg();
10973 Handle<AllocationSite> allocation_site = expr->allocation_site();
10974
10975 HAllocationMode allocation_mode;
10976 if (FLAG_allocation_site_pretenuring && !allocation_site.is_null()) {
10977 allocation_mode = HAllocationMode(allocation_site);
10978 }
10979 HValue* result = HGraphBuilder::BuildBinaryOperation(
10980 expr->op(), left, right, left_type, right_type, result_type,
10981 fixed_right_arg, allocation_mode, expr->id());
10982 // Add a simulate after instructions with observable side effects, and
10983 // after phis, which are the result of BuildBinaryOperation when we
10984 // inlined some complex subgraph.
10985 if (result->HasObservableSideEffects() || result->IsPhi()) {
10986 if (push_sim_result == PUSH_BEFORE_SIMULATE) {
10987 Push(result);
10988 Add<HSimulate>(expr->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
10989 Drop(1);
10990 } else {
10991 Add<HSimulate>(expr->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
10992 }
10993 }
10994 return result;
10995}
10996
10997HValue* HGraphBuilder::BuildBinaryOperation(Token::Value op, HValue* left,
10998 HValue* right, Type* left_type,
10999 Type* right_type, Type* result_type,
11000 Maybe<int> fixed_right_arg,
11001 HAllocationMode allocation_mode,
11002 BailoutId opt_id) {
11003 bool maybe_string_add = false;
11004 if (op == Token::ADD) {
11005 // If we are adding constant string with something for which we don't have
11006 // a feedback yet, assume that it's also going to be a string and don't
11007 // generate deopt instructions.
11008 if (!left_type->IsInhabited() && right->IsConstant() &&
11009 HConstant::cast(right)->HasStringValue()) {
11010 left_type = Type::String();
11011 }
11012
11013 if (!right_type->IsInhabited() && left->IsConstant() &&
11014 HConstant::cast(left)->HasStringValue()) {
11015 right_type = Type::String();
11016 }
11017
11018 maybe_string_add = (left_type->Maybe(Type::String()) ||
11019 left_type->Maybe(Type::Receiver()) ||
11020 right_type->Maybe(Type::String()) ||
11021 right_type->Maybe(Type::Receiver()));
11022 }
11023
11024 Representation left_rep = RepresentationFor(left_type);
11025 Representation right_rep = RepresentationFor(right_type);
11026
11027 if (!left_type->IsInhabited()) {
11028 Add<HDeoptimize>(
11029 Deoptimizer::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForLHSOfBinaryOperation,
11030 Deoptimizer::SOFT);
11031 left_type = Type::Any();
11032 left_rep = RepresentationFor(left_type);
11033 maybe_string_add = op == Token::ADD;
11034 }
11035
11036 if (!right_type->IsInhabited()) {
11037 Add<HDeoptimize>(
11038 Deoptimizer::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForRHSOfBinaryOperation,
11039 Deoptimizer::SOFT);
11040 right_type = Type::Any();
11041 right_rep = RepresentationFor(right_type);
11042 maybe_string_add = op == Token::ADD;
11043 }
11044
11045 if (!maybe_string_add) {
11046 left = TruncateToNumber(left, &left_type);
11047 right = TruncateToNumber(right, &right_type);
11048 }
11049
11050 // Special case for string addition here.
11051 if (op == Token::ADD &&
11052 (left_type->Is(Type::String()) || right_type->Is(Type::String()))) {
11053 // Validate type feedback for left argument.
11054 if (left_type->Is(Type::String())) {
11055 left = BuildCheckString(left);
11056 }
11057
11058 // Validate type feedback for right argument.
11059 if (right_type->Is(Type::String())) {
11060 right = BuildCheckString(right);
11061 }
11062
11063 // Convert left argument as necessary.
11064 if (left_type->Is(Type::Number())) {
11065 DCHECK(right_type->Is(Type::String()))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(right_type->Is(Type::String
()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11065
, "Check failed: %s.", "right_type->Is(Type::String())"); }
} while (0);
11066 left = BuildNumberToString(left, left_type);
11067 } else if (!left_type->Is(Type::String())) {
11068 DCHECK(right_type->Is(Type::String()))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(right_type->Is(Type::String
()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11068
, "Check failed: %s.", "right_type->Is(Type::String())"); }
} while (0);
11069 return AddUncasted<HStringAdd>(
11070 left, right, allocation_mode.GetPretenureMode(),
11071 STRING_ADD_CONVERT_LEFT, allocation_mode.feedback_site());
11072 }
11073
11074 // Convert right argument as necessary.
11075 if (right_type->Is(Type::Number())) {
11076 DCHECK(left_type->Is(Type::String()))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(left_type->Is(Type::String
()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11076
, "Check failed: %s.", "left_type->Is(Type::String())"); }
} while (0);
11077 right = BuildNumberToString(right, right_type);
11078 } else if (!right_type->Is(Type::String())) {
11079 DCHECK(left_type->Is(Type::String()))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(left_type->Is(Type::String
()))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11079
, "Check failed: %s.", "left_type->Is(Type::String())"); }
} while (0);
11080 return AddUncasted<HStringAdd>(
11081 left, right, allocation_mode.GetPretenureMode(),
11082 STRING_ADD_CONVERT_RIGHT, allocation_mode.feedback_site());
11083 }
11084
11085 // Fast paths for empty constant strings.
11086 Handle<String> left_string =
11087 left->IsConstant() && HConstant::cast(left)->HasStringValue()
11088 ? HConstant::cast(left)->StringValue()
11089 : Handle<String>();
11090 Handle<String> right_string =
11091 right->IsConstant() && HConstant::cast(right)->HasStringValue()
11092 ? HConstant::cast(right)->StringValue()
11093 : Handle<String>();
11094 if (!left_string.is_null() && left_string->length() == 0) return right;
11095 if (!right_string.is_null() && right_string->length() == 0) return left;
11096 if (!left_string.is_null() && !right_string.is_null()) {
11097 return AddUncasted<HStringAdd>(
11098 left, right, allocation_mode.GetPretenureMode(),
11099 STRING_ADD_CHECK_NONE, allocation_mode.feedback_site());
11100 }
11101
11102 // Register the dependent code with the allocation site.
11103 if (!allocation_mode.feedback_site().is_null()) {
11104 DCHECK(!graph()->info()->IsStub())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!graph()->info()->IsStub
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11104,
"Check failed: %s.", "!graph()->info()->IsStub()"); } }
while (0);
11105 Handle<AllocationSite> site(allocation_mode.feedback_site());
11106 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumeTenuringDecision(site);
11107 }
11108
11109 // Inline the string addition into the stub when creating allocation
11110 // mementos to gather allocation site feedback, or if we can statically
11111 // infer that we're going to create a cons string.
11112 if ((graph()->info()->IsStub() &&
11113 allocation_mode.CreateAllocationMementos()) ||
11114 (left->IsConstant() &&
11115 HConstant::cast(left)->HasStringValue() &&
11116 HConstant::cast(left)->StringValue()->length() + 1 >=
11117 ConsString::kMinLength) ||
11118 (right->IsConstant() &&
11119 HConstant::cast(right)->HasStringValue() &&
11120 HConstant::cast(right)->StringValue()->length() + 1 >=
11121 ConsString::kMinLength)) {
11122 return BuildStringAdd(left, right, allocation_mode);
11123 }
11124
11125 // Fallback to using the string add stub.
11126 return AddUncasted<HStringAdd>(
11127 left, right, allocation_mode.GetPretenureMode(), STRING_ADD_CHECK_NONE,
11128 allocation_mode.feedback_site());
11129 }
11130
11131 // Special case for +x here.
11132 if (op == Token::MUL) {
11133 if (left->EqualsInteger32Constant(1)) {
11134 return BuildToNumber(right);
11135 }
11136 if (right->EqualsInteger32Constant(1)) {
11137 return BuildToNumber(left);
11138 }
11139 }
11140
11141 if (graph()->info()->IsStub()) {
11142 left = EnforceNumberType(left, left_type);
11143 right = EnforceNumberType(right, right_type);
11144 }
11145
11146 Representation result_rep = RepresentationFor(result_type);
11147
11148 bool is_non_primitive = (left_rep.IsTagged() && !left_rep.IsSmi()) ||
11149 (right_rep.IsTagged() && !right_rep.IsSmi());
11150
11151 HInstruction* instr = NULL__null;
11152 // Only the stub is allowed to call into the runtime, since otherwise we would
11153 // inline several instructions (including the two pushes) for every tagged
11154 // operation in optimized code, which is more expensive, than a stub call.
11155 if (graph()->info()->IsStub() && is_non_primitive) {
11156 Runtime::FunctionId function_id;
11157 switch (op) {
11158 default:
11159 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11159, "unreachable code"
);
11160 case Token::ADD:
11161 function_id = Runtime::kAdd;
11162 break;
11163 case Token::SUB:
11164 function_id = Runtime::kSubtract;
11165 break;
11166 case Token::MUL:
11167 function_id = Runtime::kMultiply;
11168 break;
11169 case Token::DIV:
11170 function_id = Runtime::kDivide;
11171 break;
11172 case Token::MOD:
11173 function_id = Runtime::kModulus;
11174 break;
11175 case Token::BIT_OR:
11176 function_id = Runtime::kBitwiseOr;
11177 break;
11178 case Token::BIT_AND:
11179 function_id = Runtime::kBitwiseAnd;
11180 break;
11181 case Token::BIT_XOR:
11182 function_id = Runtime::kBitwiseXor;
11183 break;
11184 case Token::SAR:
11185 function_id = Runtime::kShiftRight;
11186 break;
11187 case Token::SHR:
11188 function_id = Runtime::kShiftRightLogical;
11189 break;
11190 case Token::SHL:
11191 function_id = Runtime::kShiftLeft;
11192 break;
11193 }
11194 Add<HPushArguments>(left, right);
11195 instr = AddUncasted<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(function_id), 2);
11196 } else {
11197 switch (op) {
11198 case Token::ADD:
11199 instr = AddUncasted<HAdd>(left, right);
11200 break;
11201 case Token::SUB:
11202 instr = AddUncasted<HSub>(left, right);
11203 break;
11204 case Token::MUL:
11205 instr = AddUncasted<HMul>(left, right);
11206 break;
11207 case Token::MOD: {
11208 if (fixed_right_arg.IsJust() &&
11209 !right->EqualsInteger32Constant(fixed_right_arg.FromJust())) {
11210 HConstant* fixed_right =
11211 Add<HConstant>(static_cast<int>(fixed_right_arg.FromJust()));
11212 IfBuilder if_same(this);
11213 if_same.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(right, fixed_right, Token::EQ);
11214 if_same.Then();
11215 if_same.ElseDeopt(Deoptimizer::kUnexpectedRHSOfBinaryOperation);
11216 right = fixed_right;
11217 }
11218 instr = AddUncasted<HMod>(left, right);
11219 break;
11220 }
11221 case Token::DIV:
11222 instr = AddUncasted<HDiv>(left, right);
11223 break;
11224 case Token::BIT_XOR:
11225 case Token::BIT_AND:
11226 instr = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(op, left, right);
11227 break;
11228 case Token::BIT_OR: {
11229 HValue *operand, *shift_amount;
11230 if (left_type->Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
11231 right_type->Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
11232 MatchRotateRight(left, right, &operand, &shift_amount)) {
11233 instr = AddUncasted<HRor>(operand, shift_amount);
11234 } else {
11235 instr = AddUncasted<HBitwise>(op, left, right);
11236 }
11237 break;
11238 }
11239 case Token::SAR:
11240 instr = AddUncasted<HSar>(left, right);
11241 break;
11242 case Token::SHR:
11243 instr = AddUncasted<HShr>(left, right);
11244 if (instr->IsShr() && CanBeZero(right)) {
11245 graph()->RecordUint32Instruction(instr);
11246 }
11247 break;
11248 case Token::SHL:
11249 instr = AddUncasted<HShl>(left, right);
11250 break;
11251 default:
11252 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11252, "unreachable code"
);
11253 }
11254 }
11255
11256 if (instr->IsBinaryOperation()) {
11257 HBinaryOperation* binop = HBinaryOperation::cast(instr);
11258 binop->set_observed_input_representation(1, left_rep);
11259 binop->set_observed_input_representation(2, right_rep);
11260 binop->initialize_output_representation(result_rep);
11261 if (graph()->info()->IsStub()) {
11262 // Stub should not call into stub.
11263 instr->SetFlag(HValue::kCannotBeTagged);
11264 // And should truncate on HForceRepresentation already.
11265 if (left->IsForceRepresentation()) {
11266 left->CopyFlag(HValue::kTruncatingToSmi, instr);
11267 left->CopyFlag(HValue::kTruncatingToInt32, instr);
11268 }
11269 if (right->IsForceRepresentation()) {
11270 right->CopyFlag(HValue::kTruncatingToSmi, instr);
11271 right->CopyFlag(HValue::kTruncatingToInt32, instr);
11272 }
11273 }
11274 }
11275 return instr;
11276}
11277
11278
11279// Check for the form (%_ClassOf(foo) === 'BarClass').
11280static bool IsClassOfTest(CompareOperation* expr) {
11281 if (expr->op() != Token::EQ_STRICT) return false;
11282 CallRuntime* call = expr->left()->AsCallRuntime();
11283 if (call == NULL__null) return false;
11284 Literal* literal = expr->right()->AsLiteral();
11285 if (literal == NULL__null) return false;
11286 if (!literal->value()->IsString()) return false;
11287 if (!call->is_jsruntime() &&
11288 call->function()->function_id != Runtime::kInlineClassOf) {
11289 return false;
11290 }
11291 DCHECK(call->arguments()->length() == 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(call->arguments()->length
() == 1)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11291
, "Check failed: %s.", "call->arguments()->length() == 1"
); } } while (0);
11292 return true;
11293}
11294
11295
11296void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitBinaryOperation(BinaryOperation* expr) {
11297 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11297, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
11298 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11298, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
11299 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11299,
"Check failed: %s.", "current_block()->HasPredecessor()")
; } } while (0);
11300 switch (expr->op()) {
11301 case Token::COMMA:
11302 return VisitComma(expr);
11303 case Token::OR:
11304 case Token::AND:
11305 return VisitLogicalExpression(expr);
11306 default:
11307 return VisitArithmeticExpression(expr);
11308 }
11309}
11310
11311
11312void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitComma(BinaryOperation* expr) {
11313 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForEffect(expr->left()));
11314 // Visit the right subexpression in the same AST context as the entire
11315 // expression.
11316 Visit(expr->right());
11317}
11318
11319
11320void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitLogicalExpression(BinaryOperation* expr) {
11321 bool is_logical_and = expr->op() == Token::AND;
11322 if (ast_context()->IsTest()) {
11323 TestContext* context = TestContext::cast(ast_context());
11324 // Translate left subexpression.
11325 HBasicBlock* eval_right = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
11326 if (is_logical_and) {
11327 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(expr->left(),
11328 eval_right,
11329 context->if_false()));
11330 } else {
11331 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(expr->left(),
11332 context->if_true(),
11333 eval_right));
11334 }
11335
11336 // Translate right subexpression by visiting it in the same AST
11337 // context as the entire expression.
11338 if (eval_right->HasPredecessor()) {
11339 eval_right->SetJoinId(expr->RightId());
11340 set_current_block(eval_right);
11341 Visit(expr->right());
11342 }
11343
11344 } else if (ast_context()->IsValue()) {
11345 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->left()));
11346 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11346, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
11347 HValue* left_value = Top();
11348
11349 // Short-circuit left values that always evaluate to the same boolean value.
11350 if (expr->left()->ToBooleanIsTrue() || expr->left()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
11351 // l (evals true) && r -> r
11352 // l (evals true) || r -> l
11353 // l (evals false) && r -> l
11354 // l (evals false) || r -> r
11355 if (is_logical_and == expr->left()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
11356 Drop(1);
11357 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->right()));
11358 }
11359 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
11360 }
11361
11362 // We need an extra block to maintain edge-split form.
11363 HBasicBlock* empty_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
11364 HBasicBlock* eval_right = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
11365 ToBooleanStub::Types expected(expr->left()->to_boolean_types());
11366 HBranch* test = is_logical_and
11367 ? New<HBranch>(left_value, expected, eval_right, empty_block)
11368 : New<HBranch>(left_value, expected, empty_block, eval_right);
11369 FinishCurrentBlock(test);
11370
11371 set_current_block(eval_right);
11372 Drop(1); // Value of the left subexpression.
11373 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForValue(expr->right()));
11374
11375 HBasicBlock* join_block =
11376 CreateJoin(empty_block, current_block(), expr->id());
11377 set_current_block(join_block);
11378 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
11379
11380 } else {
11381 DCHECK(ast_context()->IsEffect())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ast_context()->IsEffect())
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11381, "Check failed: %s."
, "ast_context()->IsEffect()"); } } while (0);
11382 // In an effect context, we don't need the value of the left subexpression,
11383 // only its control flow and side effects. We need an extra block to
11384 // maintain edge-split form.
11385 HBasicBlock* empty_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
11386 HBasicBlock* right_block = graph()->CreateBasicBlock();
11387 if (is_logical_and) {
11388 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(expr->left(), right_block, empty_block));
11389 } else {
11390 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForControl(expr->left(), empty_block, right_block));
11391 }
11392
11393 // TODO(kmillikin): Find a way to fix this. It's ugly that there are
11394 // actually two empty blocks (one here and one inserted by
11395 // TestContext::BuildBranch, and that they both have an HSimulate though the
11396 // second one is not a merge node, and that we really have no good AST ID to
11397 // put on that first HSimulate.
11398
11399 if (empty_block->HasPredecessor()) {
11400 empty_block->SetJoinId(expr->id());
11401 } else {
11402 empty_block = NULL__null;
11403 }
11404
11405 if (right_block->HasPredecessor()) {
11406 right_block->SetJoinId(expr->RightId());
11407 set_current_block(right_block);
11408 CHECK_BAILOUT(VisitForEffect(expr->right()));
11409 right_block = current_block();
11410 } else {
11411 right_block = NULL__null;
11412 }
11413
11414 HBasicBlock* join_block =
11415 CreateJoin(empty_block, right_block, expr->id());
11416 set_current_block(join_block);
11417 // We did not materialize any value in the predecessor environments,
11418 // so there is no need to handle it here.
11419 }
11420}
11421
11422
11423void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitArithmeticExpression(BinaryOperation* expr) {
11424 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->left()));
11425 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->right()));
11426 SetSourcePosition(expr->position());
11427 HValue* right = Pop();
11428 HValue* left = Pop();
11429 HValue* result =
11430 BuildBinaryOperation(expr, left, right,
11431 ast_context()->IsEffect() ? NO_PUSH_BEFORE_SIMULATE
11432 : PUSH_BEFORE_SIMULATE);
11433 if (top_info()->is_tracking_positions() && result->IsBinaryOperation()) {
11434 HBinaryOperation::cast(result)->SetOperandPositions(
11435 zone(),
11436 ScriptPositionToSourcePosition(expr->left()->position()),
11437 ScriptPositionToSourcePosition(expr->right()->position()));
11438 }
11439 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(result);
11440}
11441
11442
11443void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandleLiteralCompareTypeof(CompareOperation* expr,
11444 Expression* sub_expr,
11445 Handle<String> check) {
11446 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForTypeOf(sub_expr));
11447 SetSourcePosition(expr->position());
11448 HValue* value = Pop();
11449 HTypeofIsAndBranch* instr = New<HTypeofIsAndBranch>(value, check);
11450 return ast_context()->ReturnControl(instr, expr->id());
11451}
11452
11453
11454static bool IsLiteralCompareBool(Isolate* isolate,
11455 HValue* left,
11456 Token::Value op,
11457 HValue* right) {
11458 return op == Token::EQ_STRICT &&
11459 ((left->IsConstant() &&
11460 HConstant::cast(left)->handle(isolate)->IsBoolean()) ||
11461 (right->IsConstant() &&
11462 HConstant::cast(right)->handle(isolate)->IsBoolean()));
11463}
11464
11465
11466void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitCompareOperation(CompareOperation* expr) {
11467 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11467, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
11468 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11468, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
11469 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11469,
"Check failed: %s.", "current_block()->HasPredecessor()")
; } } while (0);
11470
11471 if (!top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) SetSourcePosition(expr->position());
11472
11473 // Check for a few fast cases. The AST visiting behavior must be in sync
11474 // with the full codegen: We don't push both left and right values onto
11475 // the expression stack when one side is a special-case literal.
11476 Expression* sub_expr = NULL__null;
11477 Handle<String> check;
11478 if (expr->IsLiteralCompareTypeof(&sub_expr, &check)) {
11479 return HandleLiteralCompareTypeof(expr, sub_expr, check);
11480 }
11481 if (expr->IsLiteralCompareUndefined(&sub_expr, isolate())) {
11482 return HandleLiteralCompareNil(expr, sub_expr, kUndefinedValue);
11483 }
11484 if (expr->IsLiteralCompareNull(&sub_expr)) {
11485 return HandleLiteralCompareNil(expr, sub_expr, kNullValue);
11486 }
11487
11488 if (IsClassOfTest(expr)) {
11489 CallRuntime* call = expr->left()->AsCallRuntime();
11490 DCHECK(call->arguments()->length() == 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(call->arguments()->length
() == 1)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11490
, "Check failed: %s.", "call->arguments()->length() == 1"
); } } while (0);
11491 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(call->arguments()->at(0)));
11492 HValue* value = Pop();
11493 Literal* literal = expr->right()->AsLiteral();
11494 Handle<String> rhs = Handle<String>::cast(literal->value());
11495 HClassOfTestAndBranch* instr = New<HClassOfTestAndBranch>(value, rhs);
11496 return ast_context()->ReturnControl(instr, expr->id());
11497 }
11498
11499 Type* left_type = expr->left()->bounds().lower;
11500 Type* right_type = expr->right()->bounds().lower;
11501 Type* combined_type = expr->combined_type();
11502
11503 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->left()));
11504 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(expr->right()));
11505
11506 HValue* right = Pop();
11507 HValue* left = Pop();
11508 Token::Value op = expr->op();
11509
11510 if (IsLiteralCompareBool(isolate(), left, op, right)) {
11511 HCompareObjectEqAndBranch* result =
11512 New<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(left, right);
11513 return ast_context()->ReturnControl(result, expr->id());
11514 }
11515
11516 if (op == Token::INSTANCEOF) {
11517 // Check to see if the rhs of the instanceof is a known function.
11518 if (right->IsConstant() &&
11519 HConstant::cast(right)->handle(isolate())->IsJSFunction()) {
11520 Handle<JSFunction> constructor =
11521 Handle<JSFunction>::cast(HConstant::cast(right)->handle(isolate()));
11522 if (constructor->IsConstructor() &&
11523 !constructor->map()->has_non_instance_prototype()) {
11524 JSFunction::EnsureHasInitialMap(constructor);
11525 DCHECK(constructor->has_initial_map())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(constructor->has_initial_map
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11525,
"Check failed: %s.", "constructor->has_initial_map()"); }
} while (0);
11526 Handle<Map> initial_map(constructor->initial_map(), isolate());
11527 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumeInitialMapCantChange(initial_map);
11528 HInstruction* prototype =
11529 Add<HConstant>(handle(initial_map->prototype(), isolate()));
11530 HHasInPrototypeChainAndBranch* result =
11531 New<HHasInPrototypeChainAndBranch>(left, prototype);
11532 return ast_context()->ReturnControl(result, expr->id());
11533 }
11534 }
11535
11536 HInstanceOf* result = New<HInstanceOf>(left, right);
11537 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
11538
11539 } else if (op == Token::IN) {
11540 Add<HPushArguments>(left, right);
11541 HInstruction* result =
11542 New<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kHasProperty), 2);
11543 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, expr->id());
11544 }
11545
11546 PushBeforeSimulateBehavior push_behavior =
11547 ast_context()->IsEffect() ? NO_PUSH_BEFORE_SIMULATE
11548 : PUSH_BEFORE_SIMULATE;
11549 HControlInstruction* compare = BuildCompareInstruction(
11550 op, left, right, left_type, right_type, combined_type,
11551 ScriptPositionToSourcePosition(expr->left()->position()),
11552 ScriptPositionToSourcePosition(expr->right()->position()),
11553 push_behavior, expr->id());
11554 if (compare == NULL__null) return; // Bailed out.
11555 return ast_context()->ReturnControl(compare, expr->id());
11556}
11557
11558
11559HControlInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildCompareInstruction(
11560 Token::Value op, HValue* left, HValue* right, Type* left_type,
11561 Type* right_type, Type* combined_type, SourcePosition left_position,
11562 SourcePosition right_position, PushBeforeSimulateBehavior push_sim_result,
11563 BailoutId bailout_id) {
11564 // Cases handled below depend on collected type feedback. They should
11565 // soft deoptimize when there is no type feedback.
11566 if (!combined_type->IsInhabited()) {
11567 Add<HDeoptimize>(
11568 Deoptimizer::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCombinedTypeOfBinaryOperation,
11569 Deoptimizer::SOFT);
11570 combined_type = left_type = right_type = Type::Any();
11571 }
11572
11573 Representation left_rep = RepresentationFor(left_type);
11574 Representation right_rep = RepresentationFor(right_type);
11575 Representation combined_rep = RepresentationFor(combined_type);
11576
11577 if (combined_type->Is(Type::Receiver())) {
11578 if (Token::IsEqualityOp(op)) {
11579 // HCompareObjectEqAndBranch can only deal with object, so
11580 // exclude numbers.
11581 if ((left->IsConstant() &&
11582 HConstant::cast(left)->HasNumberValue()) ||
11583 (right->IsConstant() &&
11584 HConstant::cast(right)->HasNumberValue())) {
11585 Add<HDeoptimize>(Deoptimizer::kTypeMismatchBetweenFeedbackAndConstant,
11586 Deoptimizer::SOFT);
11587 // The caller expects a branch instruction, so make it happy.
11588 return New<HBranch>(graph()->GetConstantTrue());
11589 }
11590 // Can we get away with map check and not instance type check?
11591 HValue* operand_to_check =
11592 left->block()->block_id() < right->block()->block_id() ? left : right;
11593 if (combined_type->IsClass()) {
11594 Handle<Map> map = combined_type->AsClass()->Map();
11595 AddCheckMap(operand_to_check, map);
11596 HCompareObjectEqAndBranch* result =
11597 New<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(left, right);
11598 if (top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) {
11599 result->set_operand_position(zone(), 0, left_position);
11600 result->set_operand_position(zone(), 1, right_position);
11601 }
11602 return result;
11603 } else {
11604 BuildCheckHeapObject(operand_to_check);
11605 Add<HCheckInstanceType>(operand_to_check,
11606 HCheckInstanceType::IS_JS_RECEIVER);
11607 HCompareObjectEqAndBranch* result =
11608 New<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(left, right);
11609 return result;
11610 }
11611 } else {
11612 if (combined_type->IsClass()) {
11613 // TODO(bmeurer): This is an optimized version of an x < y, x > y,
11614 // x <= y or x >= y, where both x and y are spec objects with the
11615 // same map. The CompareIC collects this map for us. So if we know
11616 // that there's no @@toPrimitive on the map (including the prototype
11617 // chain), and both valueOf and toString are the default initial
11618 // implementations (on the %ObjectPrototype%), then we can reduce
11619 // the comparison to map checks on x and y, because the comparison
11620 // will turn into a comparison of "[object CLASS]" to itself (the
11621 // default outcome of toString, since valueOf returns a spec object).
11622 // This is pretty much adhoc, so in TurboFan we could do a lot better
11623 // and inline the interesting parts of ToPrimitive (actually we could
11624 // even do that in Crankshaft but we don't want to waste too much
11625 // time on this now).
11626 DCHECK(Token::IsOrderedRelationalCompareOp(op))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(Token::IsOrderedRelationalCompareOp
(op))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11626
, "Check failed: %s.", "Token::IsOrderedRelationalCompareOp(op)"
); } } while (0);
11627 Handle<Map> map = combined_type->AsClass()->Map();
11628 PropertyAccessInfo value_of(this, LOAD, map,
11629 isolate()->factory()->valueOf_string());
11630 PropertyAccessInfo to_primitive(
11631 this, LOAD, map, isolate()->factory()->to_primitive_symbol());
11632 PropertyAccessInfo to_string(this, LOAD, map,
11633 isolate()->factory()->toString_string());
11634 PropertyAccessInfo to_string_tag(
11635 this, LOAD, map, isolate()->factory()->to_string_tag_symbol());
11636 if (to_primitive.CanAccessMonomorphic() && !to_primitive.IsFound() &&
11637 to_string_tag.CanAccessMonomorphic() &&
11638 (!to_string_tag.IsFound() || to_string_tag.IsData() ||
11639 to_string_tag.IsDataConstant()) &&
11640 value_of.CanAccessMonomorphic() && value_of.IsDataConstant() &&
11641 value_of.constant().is_identical_to(isolate()->object_value_of()) &&
11642 to_string.CanAccessMonomorphic() && to_string.IsDataConstant() &&
11643 to_string.constant().is_identical_to(
11644 isolate()->object_to_string())) {
11645 // We depend on the prototype chain to stay the same, because we
11646 // also need to deoptimize when someone installs @@toPrimitive
11647 // or @@toStringTag somewhere in the prototype chain.
11648 BuildCheckPrototypeMaps(handle(JSObject::cast(map->prototype())),
11649 Handle<JSObject>::null());
11650 AddCheckMap(left, map);
11651 AddCheckMap(right, map);
11652 // The caller expects a branch instruction, so make it happy.
11653 return New<HBranch>(
11654 graph()->GetConstantBool(op == Token::LTE || op == Token::GTE));
11655 }
11656 }
11657 Bailout(kUnsupportedNonPrimitiveCompare);
11658 return NULL__null;
11659 }
11660 } else if (combined_type->Is(Type::InternalizedString()) &&
11661 Token::IsEqualityOp(op)) {
11662 // If we have a constant argument, it should be consistent with the type
11663 // feedback (otherwise we fail assertions in HCompareObjectEqAndBranch).
11664 if ((left->IsConstant() &&
11665 !HConstant::cast(left)->HasInternalizedStringValue()) ||
11666 (right->IsConstant() &&
11667 !HConstant::cast(right)->HasInternalizedStringValue())) {
11668 Add<HDeoptimize>(Deoptimizer::kTypeMismatchBetweenFeedbackAndConstant,
11669 Deoptimizer::SOFT);
11670 // The caller expects a branch instruction, so make it happy.
11671 return New<HBranch>(graph()->GetConstantTrue());
11672 }
11673 BuildCheckHeapObject(left);
11674 Add<HCheckInstanceType>(left, HCheckInstanceType::IS_INTERNALIZED_STRING);
11675 BuildCheckHeapObject(right);
11676 Add<HCheckInstanceType>(right, HCheckInstanceType::IS_INTERNALIZED_STRING);
11677 HCompareObjectEqAndBranch* result =
11678 New<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(left, right);
11679 return result;
11680 } else if (combined_type->Is(Type::String())) {
11681 BuildCheckHeapObject(left);
11682 Add<HCheckInstanceType>(left, HCheckInstanceType::IS_STRING);
11683 BuildCheckHeapObject(right);
11684 Add<HCheckInstanceType>(right, HCheckInstanceType::IS_STRING);
11685 HStringCompareAndBranch* result =
11686 New<HStringCompareAndBranch>(left, right, op);
11687 return result;
11688 } else if (combined_type->Is(Type::Boolean())) {
11689 AddCheckMap(left, isolate()->factory()->boolean_map());
11690 AddCheckMap(right, isolate()->factory()->boolean_map());
11691 if (Token::IsEqualityOp(op)) {
11692 HCompareObjectEqAndBranch* result =
11693 New<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(left, right);
11694 return result;
11695 }
11696 left = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
11697 left, nullptr,
11698 HObjectAccess::ForOddballToNumber(Representation::Smi()));
11699 right = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
11700 right, nullptr,
11701 HObjectAccess::ForOddballToNumber(Representation::Smi()));
11702 HCompareNumericAndBranch* result =
11703 New<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(left, right, op);
11704 return result;
11705 } else {
11706 if (combined_rep.IsTagged() || combined_rep.IsNone()) {
11707 HCompareGeneric* result = Add<HCompareGeneric>(left, right, op);
11708 result->set_observed_input_representation(1, left_rep);
11709 result->set_observed_input_representation(2, right_rep);
11710 if (result->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
11711 if (push_sim_result == PUSH_BEFORE_SIMULATE) {
11712 Push(result);
11713 AddSimulate(bailout_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
11714 Drop(1);
11715 } else {
11716 AddSimulate(bailout_id, REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
11717 }
11718 }
11719 // TODO(jkummerow): Can we make this more efficient?
11720 HBranch* branch = New<HBranch>(result);
11721 return branch;
11722 } else {
11723 HCompareNumericAndBranch* result =
11724 New<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(left, right, op);
11725 result->set_observed_input_representation(left_rep, right_rep);
11726 if (top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) {
11727 result->SetOperandPositions(zone(), left_position, right_position);
11728 }
11729 return result;
11730 }
11731 }
11732}
11733
11734
11735void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::HandleLiteralCompareNil(CompareOperation* expr,
11736 Expression* sub_expr,
11737 NilValue nil) {
11738 DCHECK(!HasStackOverflow())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!HasStackOverflow())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11738, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);
11739 DCHECK(current_block() != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block() != __null)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11739, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);
11740 DCHECK(current_block()->HasPredecessor())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(current_block()->HasPredecessor
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11740,
"Check failed: %s.", "current_block()->HasPredecessor()")
; } } while (0);
11741 DCHECK(expr->op() == Token::EQ || expr->op() == Token::EQ_STRICT)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(expr->op() == Token::EQ ||
expr->op() == Token::EQ_STRICT)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 11741, "Check failed: %s.", "expr->op() == Token::EQ || expr->op() == Token::EQ_STRICT"
); } } while (0);
11742 if (!top_info()->is_tracking_positions()) SetSourcePosition(expr->position());
11743 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(sub_expr));
11744 HValue* value = Pop();
11745 if (expr->op() == Token::EQ_STRICT) {
11746 HConstant* nil_constant = nil == kNullValue
11747 ? graph()->GetConstantNull()
11748 : graph()->GetConstantUndefined();
11749 HCompareObjectEqAndBranch* instr =
11750 New<HCompareObjectEqAndBranch>(value, nil_constant);
11751 return ast_context()->ReturnControl(instr, expr->id());
11752 } else {
11753 DCHECK_EQ(Token::EQ, expr->op())do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (Token::
EQ), (expr->op()), "Token::EQ" " " "==" " " "expr->op()"
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11753, "Check failed: %s."
, _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0);
11754 Type* type = expr->combined_type()->Is(Type::None())
11755 ? Type::Any()
11756 : expr->combined_type();
11757 HIfContinuation continuation;
11758 BuildCompareNil(value, type, &continuation);
11759 return ast_context()->ReturnContinuation(&continuation, expr->id());
11760 }
11761}

11776
11777HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildThisFunction() {
11778 // If we share optimized code between different closures, the
11779 // this-function is not a constant, except inside an inlined body.
11780 if (function_state()->outer() != NULL__null) {
11781 return New<HConstant>(
11782 function_state()->compilation_info()->closure());
11783 } else {
11784 return New<HThisFunction>();
11785 }
11786}
11787
11788
11789HInstruction* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildFastLiteral(
11790 Handle<JSObject> boilerplate_object,
11791 AllocationSiteUsageContext* site_context) {
11792 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
11793 Handle<Map> initial_map(boilerplate_object->map());
11794 InstanceType instance_type = initial_map->instance_type();
11795 DCHECK(instance_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE || instance_type == JS_OBJECT_TYPE)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(instance_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE
|| instance_type == JS_OBJECT_TYPE)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 11795, "Check failed: %s.", "instance_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE || instance_type == JS_OBJECT_TYPE"
); } } while (0);
11796
11797 HType type = instance_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE
11798 ? HType::JSArray() : HType::JSObject();
11799 HValue* object_size_constant = Add<HConstant>(initial_map->instance_size());
11800
11801 PretenureFlag pretenure_flag = NOT_TENURED;
11802 Handle<AllocationSite> top_site(*site_context->top(), isolate());
11803 if (FLAG_allocation_site_pretenuring) {
11804 pretenure_flag = top_site->GetPretenureMode();
11805 }
11806
11807 Handle<AllocationSite> current_site(*site_context->current(), isolate());
11808 if (*top_site == *current_site) {
11809 // We install a dependency for pretenuring only on the outermost literal.
11810 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumeTenuringDecision(top_site);
11811 }
11812 top_info()->dependencies()->AssumeTransitionStable(current_site);
11813
11814 HInstruction* object = Add<HAllocate>(
11815 object_size_constant, type, pretenure_flag, instance_type, top_site);
11816
11817 // If allocation folding reaches Page::kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize the
11818 // elements array may not get folded into the object. Hence, we set the
11819 // elements pointer to empty fixed array and let store elimination remove
11820 // this store in the folding case.
11821 HConstant* empty_fixed_array = Add<HConstant>(
11822 isolate()->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
11823 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(),
11824 empty_fixed_array);
11825
11826 BuildEmitObjectHeader(boilerplate_object, object);
11827
11828 // Similarly to the elements pointer, there is no guarantee that all
11829 // property allocations can get folded, so pre-initialize all in-object
11830 // properties to a safe value.
11831 BuildInitializeInobjectProperties(object, initial_map);
11832
11833 Handle<FixedArrayBase> elements(boilerplate_object->elements());
11834 int elements_size = (elements->length() > 0 &&
11835 elements->map() != isolate()->heap()->fixed_cow_array_map()) ?
11836 elements->Size() : 0;
11837
11838 if (pretenure_flag == TENURED &&
11839 elements->map() == isolate()->heap()->fixed_cow_array_map() &&
11840 isolate()->heap()->InNewSpace(*elements)) {
11841 // If we would like to pretenure a fixed cow array, we must ensure that the
11842 // array is already in old space, otherwise we'll create too many old-to-
11843 // new-space pointers (overflowing the store buffer).
11844 elements = Handle<FixedArrayBase>(
11845 isolate()->factory()->CopyAndTenureFixedCOWArray(
11846 Handle<FixedArray>::cast(elements)));
11847 boilerplate_object->set_elements(*elements);
11848 }
11849
11850 HInstruction* object_elements = NULL__null;
11851 if (elements_size > 0) {
11852 HValue* object_elements_size = Add<HConstant>(elements_size);
11853 InstanceType instance_type = boilerplate_object->HasFastDoubleElements()
11854 ? FIXED_DOUBLE_ARRAY_TYPE : FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE;
11855 object_elements = Add<HAllocate>(object_elements_size, HType::HeapObject(),
11856 pretenure_flag, instance_type, top_site);
11857 BuildEmitElements(boilerplate_object, elements, object_elements,
11858 site_context);
11859 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(),
11860 object_elements);
11861 } else {
11862 Handle<Object> elements_field =
11863 Handle<Object>(boilerplate_object->elements(), isolate());
11864 HInstruction* object_elements_cow = Add<HConstant>(elements_field);
11865 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, HObjectAccess::ForElementsPointer(),
11866 object_elements_cow);
11867 }
11868
11869 // Copy in-object properties.
11870 if (initial_map->NumberOfFields() != 0 ||
11871 initial_map->unused_property_fields() > 0) {
11872 BuildEmitInObjectProperties(boilerplate_object, object, site_context,
11873 pretenure_flag);
11874 }
11875 return object;
11876}
11877
11878
11879void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildEmitObjectHeader(
11880 Handle<JSObject> boilerplate_object,
11881 HInstruction* object) {
11882 DCHECK(boilerplate_object->properties()->length() == 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(boilerplate_object->properties
()->length() == 0)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 11882, "Check failed: %s.", "boilerplate_object->properties()->length() == 0"
); } } while (0);
11883
11884 Handle<Map> boilerplate_object_map(boilerplate_object->map());
11885 AddStoreMapConstant(object, boilerplate_object_map);
11886
11887 Handle<Object> properties_field =
11888 Handle<Object>(boilerplate_object->properties(), isolate());
11889 DCHECK(*properties_field == isolate()->heap()->empty_fixed_array())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(*properties_field == isolate(
)->heap()->empty_fixed_array())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 11889, "Check failed: %s.", "*properties_field == isolate()->heap()->empty_fixed_array()"
); } } while (0);
11890 HInstruction* properties = Add<HConstant>(properties_field);
11891 HObjectAccess access = HObjectAccess::ForPropertiesPointer();
11892 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, access, properties);
11893
11894 if (boilerplate_object->IsJSArray()) {
11895 Handle<JSArray> boilerplate_array =
11896 Handle<JSArray>::cast(boilerplate_object);
11897 Handle<Object> length_field =
11898 Handle<Object>(boilerplate_array->length(), isolate());
11899 HInstruction* length = Add<HConstant>(length_field);
11900
11901 DCHECK(boilerplate_array->length()->IsSmi())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(boilerplate_array->length(
)->IsSmi())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 11901, "Check failed: %s.", "boilerplate_array->length()->IsSmi()"
); } } while (0);
11902 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, HObjectAccess::ForArrayLength(
11903 boilerplate_array->GetElementsKind()), length);
11904 }
11905}
11906
11907
11908void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildEmitInObjectProperties(
11909 Handle<JSObject> boilerplate_object,
11910 HInstruction* object,
11911 AllocationSiteUsageContext* site_context,
11912 PretenureFlag pretenure_flag) {
11913 Handle<Map> boilerplate_map(boilerplate_object->map());
11914 Handle<DescriptorArray> descriptors(boilerplate_map->instance_descriptors());
11915 int limit = boilerplate_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
11916
11917 int copied_fields = 0;
11918 for (int i = 0; i < limit; i++) {
11919 PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
11920 if (details.type() != DATA) continue;
11921 copied_fields++;
11922 FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(*boilerplate_map, i);
11923
11924
11925 int property_offset = field_index.offset();
11926 Handle<Name> name(descriptors->GetKey(i));
11927
11928 // The access for the store depends on the type of the boilerplate.
11929 HObjectAccess access = boilerplate_object->IsJSArray() ?
11930 HObjectAccess::ForJSArrayOffset(property_offset) :
11931 HObjectAccess::ForMapAndOffset(boilerplate_map, property_offset);
11932
11933 if (boilerplate_object->IsUnboxedDoubleField(field_index)) {
11934 CHECK(!boilerplate_object->IsJSArray())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!boilerplate_object->IsJSArray
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11934,
"Check failed: %s.", "!boilerplate_object->IsJSArray()");
} } while (0);
11935 double value = boilerplate_object->RawFastDoublePropertyAt(field_index);
11936 access = access.WithRepresentation(Representation::Double());
11937 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, access, Add<HConstant>(value));
11938 continue;
11939 }
11940 Handle<Object> value(boilerplate_object->RawFastPropertyAt(field_index),
11941 isolate());
11942
11943 if (value->IsJSObject()) {
11944 Handle<JSObject> value_object = Handle<JSObject>::cast(value);
11945 Handle<AllocationSite> current_site = site_context->EnterNewScope();
11946 HInstruction* result =
11947 BuildFastLiteral(value_object, site_context);
11948 site_context->ExitScope(current_site, value_object);
11949 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, access, result);
11950 } else {
11951 Representation representation = details.representation();
11952 HInstruction* value_instruction;
11953
11954 if (representation.IsDouble()) {
11955 // Allocate a HeapNumber box and store the value into it.
11956 HValue* heap_number_constant = Add<HConstant>(HeapNumber::kSize);
11957 HInstruction* double_box =
11958 Add<HAllocate>(heap_number_constant, HType::HeapObject(),
11959 pretenure_flag, MUTABLE_HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE);
11960 AddStoreMapConstant(double_box,
11961 isolate()->factory()->mutable_heap_number_map());
11962 // Unwrap the mutable heap number from the boilerplate.
11963 HValue* double_value =
11964 Add<HConstant>(Handle<HeapNumber>::cast(value)->value());
11965 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
11966 double_box, HObjectAccess::ForHeapNumberValue(), double_value);
11967 value_instruction = double_box;
11968 } else if (representation.IsSmi()) {
11969 value_instruction = value->IsUninitialized()
11970 ? graph()->GetConstant0()
11971 : Add<HConstant>(value);
11972 // Ensure that value is stored as smi.
11973 access = access.WithRepresentation(representation);
11974 } else {
11975 value_instruction = Add<HConstant>(value);
11976 }
11977
11978 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, access, value_instruction);
11979 }
11980 }
11981
11982 int inobject_properties = boilerplate_object->map()->GetInObjectProperties();
11983 HInstruction* value_instruction =
11984 Add<HConstant>(isolate()->factory()->one_pointer_filler_map());
11985 for (int i = copied_fields; i < inobject_properties; i++) {
11986 DCHECK(boilerplate_object->IsJSObject())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(boilerplate_object->IsJSObject
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 11986,
"Check failed: %s.", "boilerplate_object->IsJSObject()");
} } while (0);
11987 int property_offset = boilerplate_object->GetInObjectPropertyOffset(i);
11988 HObjectAccess access =
11989 HObjectAccess::ForMapAndOffset(boilerplate_map, property_offset);
11990 Add<HStoreNamedField>(object, access, value_instruction);
11991 }
11992}
11993
11994
11995void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildEmitElements(
11996 Handle<JSObject> boilerplate_object,
11997 Handle<FixedArrayBase> elements,
11998 HValue* object_elements,
11999 AllocationSiteUsageContext* site_context) {
12000 ElementsKind kind = boilerplate_object->map()->elements_kind();
12001 int elements_length = elements->length();
12002 HValue* object_elements_length = Add<HConstant>(elements_length);
12003 BuildInitializeElementsHeader(object_elements, kind, object_elements_length);
12004
12005 // Copy elements backing store content.
12006 if (elements->IsFixedDoubleArray()) {
12007 BuildEmitFixedDoubleArray(elements, kind, object_elements);
12008 } else if (elements->IsFixedArray()) {
12009 BuildEmitFixedArray(elements, kind, object_elements,
12010 site_context);
12011 } else {
12012 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12012, "unreachable code"
);
12013 }
12014}
12015
12016
12017void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildEmitFixedDoubleArray(
12018 Handle<FixedArrayBase> elements,
12019 ElementsKind kind,
12020 HValue* object_elements) {
12021 HInstruction* boilerplate_elements = Add<HConstant>(elements);
12022 int elements_length = elements->length();
12023 for (int i = 0; i < elements_length; i++) {
12024 HValue* key_constant = Add<HConstant>(i);
12025 HInstruction* value_instruction =
12026 Add<HLoadKeyed>(boilerplate_elements, key_constant, nullptr, nullptr,
12027 kind, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
12028 HInstruction* store = Add<HStoreKeyed>(object_elements, key_constant,
12029 value_instruction, nullptr, kind);
12030 store->SetFlag(HValue::kAllowUndefinedAsNaN);
12031 }
12032}
12033
12034
12035void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildEmitFixedArray(
12036 Handle<FixedArrayBase> elements,
12037 ElementsKind kind,
12038 HValue* object_elements,
12039 AllocationSiteUsageContext* site_context) {
12040 HInstruction* boilerplate_elements = Add<HConstant>(elements);
12041 int elements_length = elements->length();
12042 Handle<FixedArray> fast_elements = Handle<FixedArray>::cast(elements);
12043 for (int i = 0; i < elements_length; i++) {
12044 Handle<Object> value(fast_elements->get(i), isolate());
12045 HValue* key_constant = Add<HConstant>(i);
12046 if (value->IsJSObject()) {
12047 Handle<JSObject> value_object = Handle<JSObject>::cast(value);
12048 Handle<AllocationSite> current_site = site_context->EnterNewScope();
12049 HInstruction* result =
12050 BuildFastLiteral(value_object, site_context);
12051 site_context->ExitScope(current_site, value_object);
12052 Add<HStoreKeyed>(object_elements, key_constant, result, nullptr, kind);
12053 } else {
12054 ElementsKind copy_kind =
12055 kind == FAST_HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS ? FAST_HOLEY_ELEMENTS : kind;
12056 HInstruction* value_instruction =
12057 Add<HLoadKeyed>(boilerplate_elements, key_constant, nullptr, nullptr,
12058 copy_kind, ALLOW_RETURN_HOLE);
12059 Add<HStoreKeyed>(object_elements, key_constant, value_instruction,
12060 nullptr, copy_kind);
12061 }
12062 }
12063}

V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12067, "Check failed: %s."
, "!HasStackOverflow()"); } } while (0);

))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12068, "Check failed: %s."
, "current_block() != __null"); } } while (0);

())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12069,
"Check failed: %s.", "current_block()->HasPredecessor()")
; } } while (0);
12070 HInstruction* instr = BuildThisFunction();
12071 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(instr, expr->id());
12072}

12092void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitDeclarations(
12093 ZoneList<Declaration*>* declarations) {
12094 DCHECK(globals_.is_empty())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(globals_.is_empty())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12094, "Check failed: %s."
, "globals_.is_empty()"); } } while (0);
12095 AstVisitor::VisitDeclarations(declarations);
12096 if (!globals_.is_empty()) {
12097 Handle<FixedArray> array =
12098 isolate()->factory()->NewFixedArray(globals_.length(), TENURED);
12099 for (int i = 0; i < globals_.length(); ++i) array->set(i, *globals_.at(i));
12100 int flags =
12101 DeclareGlobalsEvalFlag::encode(current_info()->is_eval()) |
12102 DeclareGlobalsNativeFlag::encode(current_info()->is_native()) |
12103 DeclareGlobalsLanguageMode::encode(current_info()->language_mode());
12104 Add<HDeclareGlobals>(array, flags);
12105 globals_.Rewind(0);
12106 }
12107}

12109
12110void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitVariableDeclaration(
12111 VariableDeclaration* declaration) {
12112 VariableProxy* proxy = declaration->proxy();
12113 VariableMode mode = declaration->mode();
12114 Variable* variable = proxy->var();
12115 bool hole_init = mode == LET || mode == CONST || mode == CONST_LEGACY;
12116 switch (variable->location()) {
12117 case VariableLocation::GLOBAL:
12118 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
12119 globals_.Add(variable->name(), zone());
12120 globals_.Add(variable->binding_needs_init()
12121 ? isolate()->factory()->the_hole_value()
12122 : isolate()->factory()->undefined_value(), zone());
12123 return;
12124 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
12125 case VariableLocation::LOCAL:
12126 if (hole_init) {
12127 HValue* value = graph()->GetConstantHole();
12128 environment()->Bind(variable, value);
12129 }
12130 break;
12131 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT:
12132 if (hole_init) {
12133 HValue* value = graph()->GetConstantHole();
12134 HValue* context = environment()->context();
12135 HStoreContextSlot* store = Add<HStoreContextSlot>(
12136 context, variable->index(), HStoreContextSlot::kNoCheck, value);
12137 if (store->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
12138 Add<HSimulate>(proxy->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
12139 }
12140 }
12141 break;
12142 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP:
12143 return Bailout(kUnsupportedLookupSlotInDeclaration);
12144 }
12145}
12146
12147
12148void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::VisitFunctionDeclaration(
12149 FunctionDeclaration* declaration) {
12150 VariableProxy* proxy = declaration->proxy();
12151 Variable* variable = proxy->var();
12152 switch (variable->location()) {
12153 case VariableLocation::GLOBAL:
12154 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED: {
12155 globals_.Add(variable->name(), zone());
12156 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> function = Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(
12157 declaration->fun(), current_info()->script(), top_info());
12158 // Check for stack-overflow exception.
12159 if (function.is_null()) return SetStackOverflow();
12160 globals_.Add(function, zone());
12161 return;
12162 }
12163 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
12164 case VariableLocation::LOCAL: {
12165 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(declaration->fun()));
12166 HValue* value = Pop();
12167 BindIfLive(variable, value);
12168 break;
12169 }
12170 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
12171 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(declaration->fun()));
12172 HValue* value = Pop();
12173 HValue* context = environment()->context();
12174 HStoreContextSlot* store = Add<HStoreContextSlot>(
12175 context, variable->index(), HStoreContextSlot::kNoCheck, value);
12176 if (store->HasObservableSideEffects()) {
12177 Add<HSimulate>(proxy->id(), REMOVABLE_SIMULATE);
12178 }
12179 break;
12180 }
12181 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP:
12182 return Bailout(kUnsupportedLookupSlotInDeclaration);
12183 }
12184}

12268void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::GenerateToInteger(CallRuntime* call) {
12269 DCHECK_EQ(1, call->arguments()->length())do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (1), (call
->arguments()->length()), "1" " " "==" " " "call->arguments()->length()"
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12269, "Check failed: %s."
, _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0);
12270 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(call->arguments()->at(0)));
12271 HValue* input = Pop();
12272 if (input->type().IsSmi()) {
12273 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(input);
12274 } else {
12275 IfBuilder if_inputissmi(this);
12276 if_inputissmi.If<HIsSmiAndBranch>(input);
12277 if_inputissmi.Then();
12278 {
12279 // Return the input value.
12280 Push(input);
12281 Add<HSimulate>(call->id(), FIXED_SIMULATE);
12282 }
12283 if_inputissmi.Else();
12284 {
12285 Add<HPushArguments>(input);
12286 Push(Add<HCallRuntime>(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kToInteger), 1));
12287 Add<HSimulate>(call->id(), FIXED_SIMULATE);
12288 }
12289 if_inputissmi.End();
12290 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
12291 }
12292}

12295void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::GenerateToName(CallRuntime* call) {
12296 DCHECK_EQ(1, call->arguments()->length())do { if (std::string* _msg = ::v8::base::CheckEQImpl( (1), (call
->arguments()->length()), "1" " " "==" " " "call->arguments()->length()"
)) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12296, "Check failed: %s."
, _msg->c_str()); delete _msg; } } while (0);
12297 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(call->arguments()->at(0)));
12298 HValue* input = Pop();
12299 if (input->type().IsSmi()) {
12300 HValue* result = BuildNumberToString(input, Type::SignedSmall());
12301 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(result);
12302 } else if (input->type().IsTaggedNumber()) {
12303 HValue* result = BuildNumberToString(input, Type::Number());
12304 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(result);
12305 } else if (input->type().IsString()) {
12306 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(input);
12307 } else {
12308 Callable callable = CodeFactory::ToName(isolate());
12309 HValue* stub = Add<HConstant>(callable.code());
12310 HValue* values[] = {context(), input};
12311 HInstruction* result =
12312 New<HCallWithDescriptor>(stub, 0, callable.descriptor(),
12313 Vector<HValue*>(values, arraysize(values)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(values)))));
12314 return ast_context()->ReturnInstruction(result, call->id());
12315 }
12316}

12374
12375void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::GenerateIsJSProxy(CallRuntime* call) {
12376 DCHECK(call->arguments()->length() == 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(call->arguments()->length
() == 1)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12376
, "Check failed: %s.", "call->arguments()->length() == 1"
); } } while (0);
12377 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(call->arguments()->at(0)));
12378 HValue* value = Pop();
12379 HIfContinuation continuation;
12380 IfBuilder if_proxy(this);
12381
12382 HValue* smicheck = if_proxy.IfNot<HIsSmiAndBranch>(value);
12383 if_proxy.And();
12384 HValue* map = Add<HLoadNamedField>(value, smicheck, HObjectAccess::ForMap());
12385 HValue* instance_type =
12386 Add<HLoadNamedField>(map, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForMapInstanceType());
12387 if_proxy.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
12388 instance_type, Add<HConstant>(JS_PROXY_TYPE), Token::EQ);
12389
12390 if_proxy.CaptureContinuation(&continuation);
12391 return ast_context()->ReturnContinuation(&continuation, call->id());
12392}

12394
12395void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::GenerateHasFastPackedElements(CallRuntime* call) {
12396 DCHECK(call->arguments()->length() == 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(call->arguments()->length
() == 1)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12396
, "Check failed: %s.", "call->arguments()->length() == 1"
); } } while (0);
12397 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(call->arguments()->at(0)));
12398 HValue* object = Pop();
12399 HIfContinuation continuation(graph()->CreateBasicBlock(),
12400 graph()->CreateBasicBlock());
12401 IfBuilder if_not_smi(this);
12402 if_not_smi.IfNot<HIsSmiAndBranch>(object);
12403 if_not_smi.Then();
12404 {
12405 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
12406
12407 IfBuilder if_fast_packed(this);
12408 HValue* elements_kind = BuildGetElementsKind(object);
12409 if_fast_packed.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
12410 elements_kind, Add<HConstant>(FAST_SMI_ELEMENTS), Token::EQ);
12411 if_fast_packed.Or();
12412 if_fast_packed.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
12413 elements_kind, Add<HConstant>(FAST_ELEMENTS), Token::EQ);
12414 if_fast_packed.Or();
12415 if_fast_packed.If<HCompareNumericAndBranch>(
12416 elements_kind, Add<HConstant>(FAST_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS), Token::EQ);
12417 if_fast_packed.JoinContinuation(&continuation);
12418 }
12419 if_not_smi.JoinContinuation(&continuation);
12420 return ast_context()->ReturnContinuation(&continuation, call->id());
12421}
12422
12423
12424void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::GenerateValueOf(CallRuntime* call) {
12425 DCHECK(call->arguments()->length() == 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(call->arguments()->length
() == 1)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12425
, "Check failed: %s.", "call->arguments()->length() == 1"
); } } while (0);
12426 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(call->arguments()->at(0)));
12427 HValue* object = Pop();
12428
12429 IfBuilder if_objectisvalue(this);
12430 HValue* objectisvalue = if_objectisvalue.If<HHasInstanceTypeAndBranch>(
12431 object, JS_VALUE_TYPE);
12432 if_objectisvalue.Then();
12433 {
12434 // Return the actual value.
12435 Push(Add<HLoadNamedField>(
12436 object, objectisvalue,
12437 HObjectAccess::ForObservableJSObjectOffset(
12438 JSValue::kValueOffset)));
12439 Add<HSimulate>(call->id(), FIXED_SIMULATE);
12440 }
12441 if_objectisvalue.Else();
12442 {
12443 // If the object is not a value return the object.
12444 Push(object);
12445 Add<HSimulate>(call->id(), FIXED_SIMULATE);
12446 }
12447 if_objectisvalue.End();
12448 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(Pop());
12449}

12750
12751
12752template <typename CollectionType>
12753HValue* HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildAllocateOrderedHashTable() {
12754 static const int kCapacity = CollectionType::kMinCapacity;
12755 static const int kBucketCount = kCapacity / CollectionType::kLoadFactor;
12756 static const int kFixedArrayLength = CollectionType::kHashTableStartIndex +
12757 kBucketCount +
12758 (kCapacity * CollectionType::kEntrySize);
12759 static const int kSizeInBytes =
12760 FixedArray::kHeaderSize + (kFixedArrayLength * kPointerSize);
12761
12762 // Allocate the table and add the proper map.
12763 HValue* table =
12764 Add<HAllocate>(Add<HConstant>(kSizeInBytes), HType::HeapObject(),
12765 NOT_TENURED, FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE);
12766 AddStoreMapConstant(table, isolate()->factory()->ordered_hash_table_map());
12767
12768 // Initialize the FixedArray...
12769 HValue* length = Add<HConstant>(kFixedArrayLength);
12770 Add<HStoreNamedField>(table, HObjectAccess::ForFixedArrayLength(), length);
12771
12772 // ...and the OrderedHashTable fields.
12773 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
12774 table,
12775 HObjectAccess::ForOrderedHashTableNumberOfBuckets<CollectionType>(),
12776 Add<HConstant>(kBucketCount));
12777 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
12778 table,
12779 HObjectAccess::ForOrderedHashTableNumberOfElements<CollectionType>(),
12780 graph()->GetConstant0());
12781 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
12782 table, HObjectAccess::ForOrderedHashTableNumberOfDeletedElements<
12783 CollectionType>(),
12784 graph()->GetConstant0());
12785
12786 // Fill the buckets with kNotFound.
12787 HValue* not_found = Add<HConstant>(CollectionType::kNotFound);
12788 for (int i = 0; i < kBucketCount; ++i) {
12789 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
12790 table, HObjectAccess::ForOrderedHashTableBucket<CollectionType>(i),
12791 not_found);
12792 }
12793
12794 // Fill the data table with undefined.
12795 HValue* undefined = graph()->GetConstantUndefined();
12796 for (int i = 0; i < (kCapacity * CollectionType::kEntrySize); ++i) {
12797 Add<HStoreNamedField>(table,
12798 HObjectAccess::ForOrderedHashTableDataTableIndex<
12799 CollectionType, kBucketCount>(i),
12800 undefined);
12801 }
12802
12803 return table;
12804}

12807void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::GenerateSetInitialize(CallRuntime* call) {
12808 DCHECK(call->arguments()->length() == 1)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(call->arguments()->length
() == 1)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 12808
, "Check failed: %s.", "call->arguments()->length() == 1"
); } } while (0);
12809 CHECK_ALIVE(VisitForValue(call->arguments()->at(0)));
12810 HValue* receiver = Pop();
12811
12812 NoObservableSideEffectsScope no_effects(this);
12813 HValue* table = BuildAllocateOrderedHashTable<OrderedHashSet>();
12814 Add<HStoreNamedField>(receiver, HObjectAccess::ForJSCollectionTable(), table);
12815 return ast_context()->ReturnValue(receiver);
12816}

12830
12831template <typename CollectionType>
12832void HOptimizedGraphBuilder::BuildOrderedHashTableClear(HValue* receiver) {
12833 HValue* old_table = Add<HLoadNamedField>(
12834 receiver, nullptr, HObjectAccess::ForJSCollectionTable());
12835 HValue* new_table = BuildAllocateOrderedHashTable<CollectionType>();
12836 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
12837 old_table, HObjectAccess::ForOrderedHashTableNextTable<CollectionType>(),
12838 new_table);
12839 Add<HStoreNamedField>(
12840 old_table, HObjectAccess::ForOrderedHashTableNumberOfDeletedElements<
12841 CollectionType>(),
12842 Add<HConstant>(CollectionType::kClearedTableSentinel));
12843 Add<HStoreNamedField>(receiver, HObjectAccess::ForJSCollectionTable(),
12844 new_table);
12845}

12900HEnvironment::HEnvironment(HEnvironment* outer,
12901 Scope* scope,
12902 Handle<JSFunction> closure,
12903 Zone* zone)
12904 : closure_(closure),
12905 values_(0, zone),
12906 frame_type_(JS_FUNCTION),
12907 parameter_count_(0),
12908 specials_count_(1),
12909 local_count_(0),
12910 outer_(outer),
12911 entry_(NULL__null),
12912 pop_count_(0),
12913 push_count_(0),
12914 ast_id_(BailoutId::None()),
12915 zone_(zone) {
12916 Scope* declaration_scope = scope->DeclarationScope();
12917 Initialize(declaration_scope->num_parameters() + 1,
12918 declaration_scope->num_stack_slots(), 0);
12919}

12923 : values_(0, zone),
12924 frame_type_(STUB),

12926 specials_count_(1),
12927 local_count_(0),
12928 outer_(NULL__null),
12929 entry_(NULL__null),
12930 pop_count_(0),
12931 push_count_(0),

12938HEnvironment::HEnvironment(const HEnvironment* other, Zone* zone)
12939 : values_(0, zone),
12940 frame_type_(JS_FUNCTION),
12941 parameter_count_(0),
12942 specials_count_(0),
12943 local_count_(0),
12944 outer_(NULL__null),
12945 entry_(NULL__null),
12946 pop_count_(0),
12947 push_count_(0),

12956 FrameType frame_type,
12957 int arguments,
12958 Zone* zone)
12959 : closure_(closure),
