12973
12974void HEnvironment::Initialize(int parameter_count,
12975 int local_count,
12976 int stack_height) {
12977 parameter_count_ = parameter_count;
12978 local_count_ = local_count;
12979
12980 // Avoid reallocating the temporaries' backing store on the first Push.
12981 int total = parameter_count + specials_count_ + local_count + stack_height;
12982 values_.Initialize(total + 4, zone());
12983 for (int i = 0; i < total; ++i) values_.Add(NULL__null, zone());
12984}
12985
12986
12987void HEnvironment::Initialize(const HEnvironment* other) {
12988 closure_ = other->closure();
12989 values_.AddAll(other->values_, zone());
12990 assigned_variables_.Union(other->assigned_variables_, zone());
12991 frame_type_ = other->frame_type_;
12992 parameter_count_ = other->parameter_count_;
12993 local_count_ = other->local_count_;
12994 if (other->outer_ != NULL__null) outer_ = other->outer_->Copy(); // Deep copy.
12995 entry_ = other->entry_;
12996 pop_count_ = other->pop_count_;
12997 push_count_ = other->push_count_;
12998 specials_count_ = other->specials_count_;
12999 ast_id_ = other->ast_id_;
13000}
13001
13002
13003void HEnvironment::AddIncomingEdge(HBasicBlock* block, HEnvironment* other) {
13004 DCHECK(!block->IsLoopHeader())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!block->IsLoopHeader())), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 13004, "Check failed: %s."
, "!block->IsLoopHeader()"); } } while (0);
13005 DCHECK(values_.length() == other->values_.length())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(values_.length() == other->
values_.length())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 13005, "Check failed: %s.", "values_.length() == other->values_.length()"
); } } while (0);
13006
13007 int length = values_.length();
13008 for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
13009 HValue* value = values_[i];
13010 if (value != NULL__null && value->IsPhi() && value->block() == block) {
13011 // There is already a phi for the i'th value.
13012 HPhi* phi = HPhi::cast(value);
13013 // Assert index is correct and that we haven't missed an incoming edge.
13014 DCHECK(phi->merged_index() == i || !phi->HasMergedIndex())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(phi->merged_index() == i ||
!phi->HasMergedIndex())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 13014, "Check failed: %s.", "phi->merged_index() == i || !phi->HasMergedIndex()"
); } } while (0);
13015 DCHECK(phi->OperandCount() == block->predecessors()->length())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(phi->OperandCount() == block
->predecessors()->length())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 13015, "Check failed: %s.", "phi->OperandCount() == block->predecessors()->length()"
); } } while (0);
13016 phi->AddInput(other->values_[i]);
13017 } else if (values_[i] != other->values_[i]) {
13018 // There is a fresh value on the incoming edge, a phi is needed.
13019 DCHECK(values_[i] != NULL && other->values_[i] != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(values_[i] != __null &&
other->values_[i] != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc"
, 13019, "Check failed: %s.", "values_[i] != __null && other->values_[i] != __null"
); } } while (0);
13020 HPhi* phi = block->AddNewPhi(i);
13021 HValue* old_value = values_[i];
13022 for (int j = 0; j < block->predecessors()->length(); j++) {
13023 phi->AddInput(old_value);
13024 }
13025 phi->AddInput(other->values_[i]);
13026 this->values_[i] = phi;
13027 }
13028 }
13029}
13030
13031
13032void HEnvironment::Bind(int index, HValue* value) {
13033 DCHECK(value != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(value != __null)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 13033, "Check failed: %s.",
"value != __null"); } } while (0);
13034 assigned_variables_.Add(index, zone());
13035 values_[index] = value;
13036}

13038
13039bool HEnvironment::HasExpressionAt(int index) const {
13040 return index >= parameter_count_ + specials_count_ + local_count_;
13041}
13042
13043
13044bool HEnvironment::ExpressionStackIsEmpty() const {
13045 DCHECK(length() >= first_expression_index())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(length() >= first_expression_index
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 13045,
"Check failed: %s.", "length() >= first_expression_index()"
); } } while (0);
13046 return length() == first_expression_index();
13047}
13048
13049
13050void HEnvironment::SetExpressionStackAt(int index_from_top, HValue* value) {
13051 int count = index_from_top + 1;
13052 int index = values_.length() - count;
13053 DCHECK(HasExpressionAt(index))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(HasExpressionAt(index))), 0))
) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 13053, "Check failed: %s."
, "HasExpressionAt(index)"); } } while (0);
13054 // The push count must include at least the element in question or else
13055 // the new value will not be included in this environment's history.
13056 if (push_count_ < count) {
13057 // This is the same effect as popping then re-pushing 'count' elements.
13058 pop_count_ += (count - push_count_);
13059 push_count_ = count;
13060 }
13061 values_[index] = value;
13062}
13063
13064
13065HValue* HEnvironment::RemoveExpressionStackAt(int index_from_top) {
13066 int count = index_from_top + 1;
13067 int index = values_.length() - count;
13068 DCHECK(HasExpressionAt(index))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(HasExpressionAt(index))), 0))
) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 13068, "Check failed: %s."
, "HasExpressionAt(index)"); } } while (0);
13069 // Simulate popping 'count' elements and then
13070 // pushing 'count - 1' elements back.
13071 pop_count_ += Max(count - push_count_, 0);
13072 push_count_ = Max(push_count_ - count, 0) + (count - 1);
13073 return values_.Remove(index);
13074}
13075
13076
13077void HEnvironment::Drop(int count) {
13078 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
13079 Pop();
13080 }
13081}

13101
13102HEnvironment* HEnvironment::CopyAsLoopHeader(HBasicBlock* loop_header) const {
13103 HEnvironment* new_env = Copy();
13104 for (int i = 0; i < values_.length(); ++i) {
13105 HPhi* phi = loop_header->AddNewPhi(i);
13106 phi->AddInput(values_[i]);
13107 new_env->values_[i] = phi;
13108 }
13109 new_env->ClearHistory();
13110 return new_env;
13111}
13112
13113
13114HEnvironment* HEnvironment::CreateStubEnvironment(HEnvironment* outer,
13115 Handle<JSFunction> target,
13116 FrameType frame_type,
13117 int arguments) const {
13118 HEnvironment* new_env =
13119 new(zone()) HEnvironment(outer, target, frame_type,
13120 arguments + 1, zone());
13121 for (int i = 0; i <= arguments; ++i) { // Include receiver.
13122 new_env->Push(ExpressionStackAt(arguments - i));
13123 }
13124 new_env->ClearHistory();
13125 return new_env;
13126}
13127
13128
13129HEnvironment* HEnvironment::CopyForInlining(
13130 Handle<JSFunction> target,
13131 int arguments,
13132 FunctionLiteral* function,
13133 HConstant* undefined,
13134 InliningKind inlining_kind) const {
13135 DCHECK(frame_type() == JS_FUNCTION)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(frame_type() == JS_FUNCTION))
, 0))) { V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 13135, "Check failed: %s."
, "frame_type() == JS_FUNCTION"); } } while (0);
13136
13137 // Outer environment is a copy of this one without the arguments.
13138 int arity = function->scope()->num_parameters();
13139
13140 HEnvironment* outer = Copy();
13141 outer->Drop(arguments + 1); // Including receiver.
13142 outer->ClearHistory();
13143
13144 if (inlining_kind == CONSTRUCT_CALL_RETURN) {
13145 // Create artificial constructor stub environment. The receiver should
13146 // actually be the constructor function, but we pass the newly allocated
13147 // object instead, DoComputeConstructStubFrame() relies on that.
13148 outer = CreateStubEnvironment(outer, target, JS_CONSTRUCT, arguments);
13149 } else if (inlining_kind == GETTER_CALL_RETURN) {
13150 // We need an additional StackFrame::INTERNAL frame for restoring the
13151 // correct context.
13152 outer = CreateStubEnvironment(outer, target, JS_GETTER, arguments);
13153 } else if (inlining_kind == SETTER_CALL_RETURN) {
13154 // We need an additional StackFrame::INTERNAL frame for temporarily saving
13155 // the argument of the setter, see StoreStubCompiler::CompileStoreViaSetter.
13156 outer = CreateStubEnvironment(outer, target, JS_SETTER, arguments);
13157 }
13158
13159 if (arity != arguments) {
13160 // Create artificial arguments adaptation environment.
13161 outer = CreateStubEnvironment(outer, target, ARGUMENTS_ADAPTOR, arguments);
13162 }
13163
13164 HEnvironment* inner =
13165 new(zone()) HEnvironment(outer, function->scope(), target, zone());
13166 // Get the argument values from the original environment.
13167 for (int i = 0; i <= arity; ++i) { // Include receiver.
13168 HValue* push = (i <= arguments) ?
13169 ExpressionStackAt(arguments - i) : undefined;
13170 inner->SetValueAt(i, push);
13171 }
13172 inner->SetValueAt(arity + 1, context());
13173 for (int i = arity + 2; i < inner->length(); ++i) {
13174 inner->SetValueAt(i, undefined);
13175 }
13176
13177 inner->set_ast_id(BailoutId::FunctionEntry());
13178 return inner;
13179}
13180
13181
13182std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const HEnvironment& env) {
13183 for (int i = 0; i < env.length(); i++) {
13184 if (i == 0) os << "parameters\n";
13185 if (i == env.parameter_count()) os << "specials\n";
13186 if (i == env.parameter_count() + env.specials_count()) os << "locals\n";
13187 if (i == env.parameter_count() + env.specials_count() + env.local_count()) {
13188 os << "expressions\n";
13189 }
13190 HValue* val = env.values()->at(i);
13191 os << i << ": ";
13192 if (val != NULL__null) {
13193 os << val;
13194 } else {
13195 os << "NULL";
13196 }
13197 os << "\n";
13198 }
13199 return os << "\n";
13200}

13210 } else {

13216}

13233
13234
13235void HTracer::Trace(const char* name, HGraph* graph, LChunk* chunk) {
13236 Tag tag(this, "cfg");
13237 PrintStringProperty("name", name);
13238 const ZoneList<HBasicBlock*>* blocks = graph->blocks();
13239 for (int i = 0; i < blocks->length(); i++) {
13240 HBasicBlock* current = blocks->at(i);
13241 Tag block_tag(this, "block");
13242 PrintBlockProperty("name", current->block_id());
13243 PrintIntProperty("from_bci", -1);
13244 PrintIntProperty("to_bci", -1);
13245
13246 if (!current->predecessors()->is_empty()) {
13247 PrintIndent();
13248 trace_.Add("predecessors");
13249 for (int j = 0; j < current->predecessors()->length(); ++j) {
13250 trace_.Add(" \"B%d\"", current->predecessors()->at(j)->block_id());
13251 }
13252 trace_.Add("\n");
13253 } else {
13254 PrintEmptyProperty("predecessors");
13255 }
13256
13257 if (current->end()->SuccessorCount() == 0) {
13258 PrintEmptyProperty("successors");
13259 } else {
13260 PrintIndent();
13261 trace_.Add("successors");
13262 for (HSuccessorIterator it(current->end()); !it.Done(); it.Advance()) {
13263 trace_.Add(" \"B%d\"", it.Current()->block_id());
13264 }
13265 trace_.Add("\n");
13266 }
13267
13268 PrintEmptyProperty("xhandlers");
13269
13270 {
13271 PrintIndent();
13272 trace_.Add("flags");
13273 if (current->IsLoopSuccessorDominator()) {
13274 trace_.Add(" \"dom-loop-succ\"");
13275 }
13276 if (current->IsUnreachable()) {
13277 trace_.Add(" \"dead\"");
13278 }
13279 if (current->is_osr_entry()) {
13280 trace_.Add(" \"osr\"");
13281 }
13282 trace_.Add("\n");
13283 }
13284
13285 if (current->dominator() != NULL__null) {
13286 PrintBlockProperty("dominator", current->dominator()->block_id());
13287 }
13288
13289 PrintIntProperty("loop_depth", current->LoopNestingDepth());
13290
13291 if (chunk != NULL__null) {
13292 int first_index = current->first_instruction_index();
13293 int last_index = current->last_instruction_index();
13294 PrintIntProperty(
13295 "first_lir_id",
13296 LifetimePosition::FromInstructionIndex(first_index).Value());
13297 PrintIntProperty(
13298 "last_lir_id",
13299 LifetimePosition::FromInstructionIndex(last_index).Value());
13300 }
13301
13302 {
13303 Tag states_tag(this, "states");
13304 Tag locals_tag(this, "locals");
13305 int total = current->phis()->length();
13306 PrintIntProperty("size", current->phis()->length());
13307 PrintStringProperty("method", "None");
13308 for (int j = 0; j < total; ++j) {
13309 HPhi* phi = current->phis()->at(j);
13310 PrintIndent();
13311 std::ostringstream os;
13312 os << phi->merged_index() << " " << NameOf(phi) << " " << *phi << "\n";
13313 trace_.Add(os.str().c_str());
13314 }
13315 }
13316
13317 {
13318 Tag HIR_tag(this, "HIR");
13319 for (HInstructionIterator it(current); !it.Done(); it.Advance()) {
13320 HInstruction* instruction = it.Current();
13321 int uses = instruction->UseCount();
13322 PrintIndent();
13323 std::ostringstream os;
13324 os << "0 " << uses << " " << NameOf(instruction) << " " << *instruction;
13325 if (graph->info()->is_tracking_positions() &&
13326 instruction->has_position() && instruction->position().raw() != 0) {
13327 const SourcePosition pos = instruction->position();
13328 os << " pos:";
13329 if (pos.inlining_id() != 0) os << pos.inlining_id() << "_";
13330 os << pos.position();
13331 }
13332 os << " <|@\n";
13333 trace_.Add(os.str().c_str());
13334 }
13335 }
13336
13337
13338 if (chunk != NULL__null) {
13339 Tag LIR_tag(this, "LIR");
13340 int first_index = current->first_instruction_index();
13341 int last_index = current->last_instruction_index();
13342 if (first_index != -1 && last_index != -1) {
13343 const ZoneList<LInstruction*>* instructions = chunk->instructions();
13344 for (int i = first_index; i <= last_index; ++i) {
13345 LInstruction* linstr = instructions->at(i);
13346 if (linstr != NULL__null) {
13347 PrintIndent();
13348 trace_.Add("%d ",
13349 LifetimePosition::FromInstructionIndex(i).Value());
13350 linstr->PrintTo(&trace_);
13351 std::ostringstream os;
13352 os << " [hir:" << NameOf(linstr->hydrogen_value()) << "] <|@\n";
13353 trace_.Add(os.str().c_str());
13354 }
13355 }
13356 }
13357 }
13358 }
13359}
13360
13361
13362void HTracer::TraceLiveRanges(const char* name, LAllocator* allocator) {
13363 Tag tag(this, "intervals");
13364 PrintStringProperty("name", name);
13365
13366 const Vector<LiveRange*>* fixed_d = allocator->fixed_double_live_ranges();
13367 for (int i = 0; i < fixed_d->length(); ++i) {
13368 TraceLiveRange(fixed_d->at(i), "fixed", allocator->zone());
13369 }
13370
13371 const Vector<LiveRange*>* fixed = allocator->fixed_live_ranges();
13372 for (int i = 0; i < fixed->length(); ++i) {
13373 TraceLiveRange(fixed->at(i), "fixed", allocator->zone());
13374 }
13375
13376 const ZoneList<LiveRange*>* live_ranges = allocator->live_ranges();
13377 for (int i = 0; i < live_ranges->length(); ++i) {
13378 TraceLiveRange(live_ranges->at(i), "object", allocator->zone());
13379 }
13380}
13381
13382
13383void HTracer::TraceLiveRange(LiveRange* range, const char* type,
13384 Zone* zone) {
13385 if (range != NULL__null && !range->IsEmpty()) {
13386 PrintIndent();
13387 trace_.Add("%d %s", range->id(), type);
13388 if (range->HasRegisterAssigned()) {
13389 LOperand* op = range->CreateAssignedOperand(zone);
13390 int assigned_reg = op->index();
13391 if (op->IsDoubleRegister()) {
13392 trace_.Add(" \"%s\"",
13393 DoubleRegister::from_code(assigned_reg).ToString());
13394 } else {
13395 DCHECK(op->IsRegister())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(op->IsRegister())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 13395, "Check failed: %s."
, "op->IsRegister()"); } } while (0);
13396 trace_.Add(" \"%s\"", Register::from_code(assigned_reg).ToString());
13397 }
13398 } else if (range->IsSpilled()) {
13399 LOperand* op = range->TopLevel()->GetSpillOperand();
13400 if (op->IsDoubleStackSlot()) {
13401 trace_.Add(" \"double_stack:%d\"", op->index());
13402 } else {
13403 DCHECK(op->IsStackSlot())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(op->IsStackSlot())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("../src/crankshaft/hydrogen.cc", 13403, "Check failed: %s."
, "op->IsStackSlot()"); } } while (0);
13404 trace_.Add(" \"stack:%d\"", op->index());
13405 }
13406 }
13407 int parent_index = -1;
13408 if (range->IsChild()) {
13409 parent_index = range->parent()->id();
13410 } else {
13411 parent_index = range->id();
13412 }
13413 LOperand* op = range->FirstHint();
13414 int hint_index = -1;
13415 if (op != NULL__null && op->IsUnallocated()) {
13416 hint_index = LUnallocated::cast(op)->virtual_register();
13417 }
13418 trace_.Add(" %d %d", parent_index, hint_index);
13419 UseInterval* cur_interval = range->first_interval();
13420 while (cur_interval != NULL__null && range->Covers(cur_interval->start())) {
13421 trace_.Add(" [%d, %d[",
13422 cur_interval->start().Value(),
13423 cur_interval->end().Value());
13424 cur_interval = cur_interval->next();
13425 }
13426
13427 UsePosition* current_pos = range->first_pos();
13428 while (current_pos != NULL__null) {
13429 if (current_pos->RegisterIsBeneficial() || FLAG_trace_all_uses) {
13430 trace_.Add(" %d M", current_pos->pos().Value());
13431 }
13432 current_pos = current_pos->next();
13433 }
13434
13435 trace_.Add(" \"\"\n");
13436 }
13437}
13438
13439
13440void HTracer::FlushToFile() {
13441 AppendChars(filename_.start(), trace_.ToCString().get(), trace_.length(),
13442 false);
13443 trace_.Reset();
13444}

13446
13447void HStatistics::Initialize(CompilationInfo* info) {
13448 if (!info->has_shared_info()) return;
13449 source_size_ += info->shared_info()->SourceSize();
13450}
13451
13452
13453void HStatistics::Print() {
13454 PrintF(
13455 "\n"
13456 "----------------------------------------"
13457 "----------------------------------------\n"
13458 "--- Hydrogen timing results:\n"
13459 "----------------------------------------"
13460 "----------------------------------------\n");
13461 base::TimeDelta sum;
13462 for (int i = 0; i < times_.length(); ++i) {
13463 sum += times_[i];
13464 }
13465
13466 for (int i = 0; i < names_.length(); ++i) {
13467 PrintF("%33s", names_[i]);
13468 double ms = times_[i].InMillisecondsF();
13469 double percent = times_[i].PercentOf(sum);
13470 PrintF(" %8.3f ms / %4.1f %% ", ms, percent);
13471
13472 size_t size = sizes_[i];
13473 double size_percent = static_cast<double>(size) * 100 / total_size_;
13474 PrintF(" %9zu bytes / %4.1f %%\n", size, size_percent);
13475 }
13476
13477 PrintF(
13478 "----------------------------------------"
13479 "----------------------------------------\n");
13480 base::TimeDelta total = create_graph_ + optimize_graph_ + generate_code_;
13481 PrintF("%33s %8.3f ms / %4.1f %% \n", "Create graph",
13482 create_graph_.InMillisecondsF(), create_graph_.PercentOf(total));
13483 PrintF("%33s %8.3f ms / %4.1f %% \n", "Optimize graph",
13484 optimize_graph_.InMillisecondsF(), optimize_graph_.PercentOf(total));
13485 PrintF("%33s %8.3f ms / %4.1f %% \n", "Generate and install code",
13486 generate_code_.InMillisecondsF(), generate_code_.PercentOf(total));
13487 PrintF(
13488 "----------------------------------------"
13489 "----------------------------------------\n");
13490 PrintF("%33s %8.3f ms %9zu bytes\n", "Total",
13491 total.InMillisecondsF(), total_size_);
13492 PrintF("%33s (%.1f times slower than full code gen)\n", "",
13493 total.TimesOf(full_code_gen_));
13494
13495 double source_size_in_kb = static_cast<double>(source_size_) / 1024;
13496 double normalized_time = source_size_in_kb > 0
13497 ? total.InMillisecondsF() / source_size_in_kb
13498 : 0;
13499 double normalized_size_in_kb =
13500 source_size_in_kb > 0
13501 ? static_cast<double>(total_size_) / 1024 / source_size_in_kb
13502 : 0;
13503 PrintF("%33s %8.3f ms %7.3f kB allocated\n",
13504 "Average per kB source", normalized_time, normalized_size_in_kb);
13505}
13506
13507
13508void HStatistics::SaveTiming(const char* name, base::TimeDelta time,
13509 size_t size) {
13510 total_size_ += size;
13511 for (int i = 0; i < names_.length(); ++i) {
13512 if (strcmp(names_[i], name) == 0) {
13513 times_[i] += time;
13514 sizes_[i] += size;
13515 return;
13516 }
13517 }
13518 names_.Add(name);
13519 times_.Add(time);
13520 sizes_.Add(size);
13521}

13524HPhase::~HPhase() {
13525 if (ShouldProduceTraceOutput()) {
13526 isolate()->GetHTracer()->TraceHydrogen(name(), graph_);
13527 }
13528
13529#ifdef DEBUG1
13530 graph_->Verify(false); // No full verify.
13531#endif
13532}
